INSERT INTO `meals` VALUES (5,'rrpogy','Nutty Chicken Satay Strips with Sweet Potato and Corn Salad','Chicken strips cooked in a nutty satay sauce with a side of salad - but this is no ordinary salad.\nRed onion, seasoned sweet potato chunks and corn are roasted with a drizzle of olive oil, cherry\ntomatoes add colour and the whole thing is taken to a new level with our very special homemade\nLemon & Mint dressing.','Nuts',10,50,'<div>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees C.&nbsp;<br />Place the cubed sweet potato and sliced onion in a baking dish. Drizzle with oil and add a pinch of salt. Bake for 30 &ndash; 40 minutes until soft. 10 minutes from the end, add the corn to the dish.</div>\n<div>While the sweet potato is cooking, get the chicken ready: Add the satay sauce to a bowl. You may need to stir in a little hot water to thin it out.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Add the chicken strips to the sauce and stir to coat.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Line a baking tray with baking paper. Lay the chicken strips out, spaced apart.</div>\n<div>Once the sweet potato is cooked through, remove from the oven to cool and place the chicken in the oven. Cook the chicken for 10 &ndash; 12 minutes.</div>\n<div>While the chicken is cooking, place the sweet potato, corn and onion in a large salad bowl. Halve the cherry tomatoes and add them. Add dressing and stir to combine.<br />Serve the chicken with a side of the sweet potato and corn salad.&nbsp;<br /><br /></div>',495,38,21,41,1,'2020-06-23 13:07:22','2022-11-01 11:44:12','<p>Lemon Mint Dressing</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>1/2 cup extra-virgin olive oil&nbsp;</p>\n<p>1/2 cup lemon juice</p>\n<p>1/4 cup packed fresh mint leaves&nbsp;</p>\n<p>3 tablespoons honey</p>\n<p>1 tablespoon Dijon mustard&nbsp;</p>\n<p>2 cloves garlic, roughly chopped&nbsp;</p>\n<p>1/4 teaspoon fine sea salt&nbsp;</p>\n<p>10 twists of freshly ground black pepper</p>\n<p>Mix very well together and more salt or pepper if you desire. This dressing keeps for a week in the fridge.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(6,'oxabyd','Pita Burgers with Tangy Coleslaw','A new take on burgers, and so yummy you’ll never want to go back to the same-old! Mince made with red wine and our own special Marinara Sauce is stuffed into pitas and then baked to crispy perfection. Served with coleslaw and homemade tangy dressing.','Gluten and Lactose',10,40,'<div>Heat your oven to 200 Celsius.<br />In a large pot, heat some oil and fry the onion until soft, about 3 minutes.</div>\n<div>Add the mince and break apart with a wooden spoon stir-frying until it is brown. Add salt and black pepper.</div>\n<div>Add the marinara sauce and the red wine. Turn the heat down and let it simmer for 15 minutes. If it still looks like there is a lot of liquid, let it simmer a bit longer &ndash; you don&rsquo;t want your mince to be too &ldquo;wet&rdquo; when it goes into the pitas.<br />Taste mince to check seasoning.</div>\n<div>TOP TIP: If you pop your pita breads into the microwave for a few seconds to warm them they will be easier to prise open.</div>\n<div>Use a sharp knife to cut the pitas into half moons.<br />Gently holding open a half pita (it is easier to get someone to help you here), use a dessert spoon to put 2 &ndash; 3 spoonfuls in each pita. Don&rsquo;t overstuff the pitas as you don&rsquo;t want them to split &ndash; rather keep some mince aside for another meal!</div>\n<div>On a baking tray, lay down your baking paper. Spread a little oil on the baking paper and lay your pitas down flat. Use a little more oil to brush the pitas on the top &ndash; don&rsquo;t skip this step, this is the key to the pitas crisping up nicely!</div>\n<div>Place in the oven and let them brown and crisp for about 10 minutes on each side. You can check on them now and then and tap with your nail to see that they are crispy! Some ovens are quicker than others so don\'t overcook!</div>\n<div>While the pitas are cooking, place your cabbage, carrots and raisins in a large salad bowl. Use your (clean) hands to mix together. Spoon your tangy dressing over and use a large spoon to stir in.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Serve your pitas hot from the oven with a side of tangy coleslaw!&nbsp;<br /><br /></div>',767,65,51,29,1,'2020-06-23 13:28:28','2022-08-26 12:04:34','<p>Marinara Sauce</p>\n<p>1 onion, chopped<br />2 tsp crushed garlic<br />1 tin chopped tomatoes<br />1 Tbsp tomato paste<br />1 tsp sugar<br />1 tsp dried basil<br />1 tsp dried oregano<br />salt and pepper to taste</p>\n<p>Fry the onion for 3 minutes. Add the garlic and fry for 1 minute more.<br />Add the tomatoes and the tomato paste, the sugar, the basil, and the oregano.<br />Bring to a simmer for 20 minutes or until the consistency and taste is good.<br />Add salt and pepper if need be.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Tangy Mayo Dressing</p>\n<p><br />1/2 cup cream or sour cream<br />1/2 cup mayo<br />1/4 cup white spirit vinegar<br />1 TBS sugar<br />1/2 tsp salt</p>\n<p><br />Mix all together well.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(7,'horgjm','Pork chops & Sweet Potato Chunks with a Tangy Garlic Sauce','The secret is in the sauce! It is garlicky, lemony and creamy all at the same time - a burst of flavour. Pair that with sweet potato chunks and green beans and cherry tomatoes roasted with a splash of balsamic and serve alongside a perfectly-fried pork chop. Delicious!','Lactose',20,40,'<div>Pre heat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.</div>\n<div>Place the sweet potato rounds on a lightly greased/lined baking sheet. Drizzle with some oil and sprinkle with the Cajun spice.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Place the foil-wrapped garlic head in the centre of the sweet potatoes. Bake the sweet potatoes and garlic for 30 &ndash; 40 minutes, until the sweet potato is cooked though.</div>\n<div>While the sweet potato is cooking, chop the cherry tomatoes in half and place them with the beans in an oven proof dish. Drizzle with a little oil, balsamic vinegar, salt and pepper. Toss together. Bake alongside or just above the sweet potato for 20 minutes.</div>\n<div>Heat a pan on the stove with some oil. Once the pan is hot, sear&nbsp; the pork chops on each side for a minute and then cook for 8 &ndash; 10 minutes, turning the chops regularly.<br />Add the yoghurt to a bowl. Cut the lemon in half and squeeze each half into the yoghurt. Add some salt and pepper.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Remove the garlic from the foil and let it cool for a few minutes. Then squeeze out the garlic from inside each clove into the yoghurt mixture &ndash; the garlic should be cooked to a soft paste by now. Stir into the yoghurt well. Set aside.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>When everything is done, on each plate, serve a chop or two, a few pieces of sweet potato, topped with 1 &ndash; 2 spoons of yoghurt and garlic sauce and a serving of baked green beans and tomato.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',550,26,32,33,1,'2020-06-24 08:43:34','2022-10-25 10:03:52',NULL),(8,'exwstj','Bean & Mushroom Stroganoff','This vegetarian stroganoff is so good that meat-eaters will not even miss the meat. The mushroom base is given a bit of a kick with paprika, garlic, soy sauce and red wine and the red kidney beans\nmake this dish very satisfying. With its short preparation and cooking time, this recipe will always be a weekday winner.','Gluten, lactose',5,25,'<div>Place the rice in a pot of salted water and bring to the boil. Time 20 minutes from boiling and it should be ready. Drain and keep warm.<br />Heat some oil in a large pot and fry the onions until soft, about 3 minutes. Add mushrooms and stir fry for one minute.<br />Add water, 32 ml per person you are cooking for, i.e 128 ml for 4 people. Simmer until mushrooms are soft. When most of the liquid is gone sprinkle the flour into the pot and combine with mushrooms and onions. Cook for a few minutes, stirring all the time.<br />Add paprika, salt to taste and garlic powder and mix in thoroughly. Stir the milk in slowly to make a thick smooth sauce.<br />Stir in the red wine, soya sauce and tomato sauce. Add the beans. Allow the stroganoff to heat through with the beans in and stir in the parsley.<br />Serve on rice. Feel free to leave the rice out of you are counting carbs.<br />Halve the cherry tomatoes and toss them with the baby spinach and dressing to serve on the side.</div>',247,64,8,12,1,'2020-06-24 10:13:47','2022-04-11 10:54:09',NULL),(9,'dslnct','Chicken, leek and butterbean bake','Chicken, leek, garlic cloves and butterbeans done in white wine and chicken stock with a pinch of\nherbs - what’s not to like? And because your health is always foremost on our minds, there’s some\nfresh spinach nestling in there too.','None',5,40,'<p>Make your stock by dissolving the chicken stock powder in the specified amount of boiling water</p>\n<p>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.</p>\n<p>Season the chicken with salt and pepper.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a big pot and brown the chicken on both sides. Add the leeks and fry for a few minutes. Pour in the white wine and let it bubble while you scrape the bits off the bottom of the pot and then add the stock.</p>\n<p>Pour this mixture into an oven dish, adding the dried thyme.</p>\n<div>Place the garlic in the pan and the spinach and butter beans in between the chicken pieces.</div>\n<div>Season with salt and pepper and bake for 40 minutes.</div>\n<div>Smoosh the garlic into the sauce and serve in bowls.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',559,40,21,43,1,'2020-06-24 10:25:52','2022-05-13 15:28:31',NULL),(10,'spnape','Lasagna','A firm favourite with everyone, Italian or not. Here we make life easy for you by supplying our ready made cheese sauce, marinara for the mince and precooked lasagne sheets. Just make the\nmince, assemble, bake and enjoy!','Gluten, lactose',20,45,'<div>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.<br>Heat some oil and fry the mince, breaking up nicely with a wooden spoon so that there are no clumps. Season with salt &amp; pepper and fry until brown.<br>Add the wine and cook for a few minutes, stirring occasionally.<br>Add the marinara sauce and simmer for 20 minutes.<br>Taste to see if additional seasoning is necessary.<br>Gently heat the cheese sauce, only until you can pour or spread it - do not boil.<br>Put a thin layer of meat sauce on the bottom of the dish.<br>Then a layer of pasta sheets. Then a layer of cheese sauce. Repeat these three layers until your sauces run out, finishing either with cheese sauce or meat sauce. Sprinkle the top with the grated cheddar cheese.<br>Cover with foil and bake for a total of 45 minutes. Take the foil off for the last 15 minutes to brown the cheese.<br><br></div><div>&nbsp;<br><br></div>',782,24,63,46,1,'2020-06-24 10:44:19','2022-11-30 10:45:16',NULL),(11,'xiysdk','Coconut Chicken Curry (Mild)','A mild, fragrant curry with a taste of Thai - this dish will fill your kitchen with an exotic spicy aroma\n- and it tastes as good as it smells! You won’t believe how easy it is to put together.','None',5,25,'<div>Place rice and a little salt into a pot and cover with water. Bring to the boil and time 20 minutes from boiling point. Keep an eye on it that it doesn\'t boil dry.<br>Drain and keep warm.<br>While the rice is cooking, heat some oil in a pot and fry the chicken cubes for 5 minutes until golden brown.<br>Remove the chicken from the pot. Add some more oil and fry the onion until lightly browned.<br>Add the garlic, turmeric and curry paste and stir for a minute.<br>Add back the chicken, mushrooms, red pepper, bay leaves and coconut cream. Add just enough water to thin it a little.&nbsp;<br>Simmer on a low heat for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve on top of some rice.&nbsp;</div>',631,41,31,43,1,'2020-06-29 07:52:10','2021-02-02 09:08:01',NULL),(12,'ixzwqn','Courgette and Chicken Pasta','Cream cheese and our own special marinara sauce make this pasta bake delectably more-ish!\nIt is also packed with veggie goodness so you know you are taking care of your health while you\nindulge yourself.  NOTE: SALAD NOT INCLUDED IN KIT.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,35,'<div>Heat the oven to 200 Celsius.<br />Grate the courgettes (baby marrow) and set aside in a bowl.&nbsp;<br />In a pot, heat some oil and brown the chicken turning and stirring for 5 minutes. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from the pot and set aside.<br />In the same pot, saut&eacute; onion for 5 minutes. Add the garlic and stir. Add the courgettes and cook for a few minutes while stirring.<br />Stir in 2/3 of the cream cheese and 2/3 of the grated cheddar. Combine well. Season with salt and pepper to taste.<br />In an oven dish, layer half the courgette mix, half the chicken pieces, 3 lasagne sheets and half the marinara sauce. Repeat this.<br />Blob the rest of the cream cheese on top, and sprinkle with the rest of the cheddar.<br />Bake in the oven for 10 &ndash; 15 minutes. While still hot, use the back of a spoon to spread the cream cheese over the top. Cool for 5 minutes and then serve.</div>',667,39,44,51,1,'2020-06-29 08:16:21','2022-02-03 15:11:33',NULL),(14,'rjffbp','Pork Sausages With a Creamy Red Wine Gravy, Served With Mashed Sweet Potato And Broccoli','Bangers and Mash is an old family favourite, but this version of it will knock their socks off with its\nrich and flavoursome red wine gravy. Sweet Potatoes are not only tasty but they are low on the\nGlycemic Index, meaning they do not spike your sugar levels as much as regular potatoes, turning\ncomfort food into healthy food!','Lactose',5,40,'<div>Cook the sausages and the sweet potato at the same time. While the gravy is simmering you can cook the broccoli.<br />Heat some oil or butter in a frying pan and cook the sausages over a medium heat for 20 to 25 minutes.<br />Boil the sweet potato chunks in salted water until soft &ndash; 20 to 30 minutes. Drain and mash with salt, pepper and butter. Keep the mashed potato warm.<br />Make your stock by adding the stock powder to the specified amount of boiling water.<br />When the sausages are done, use the same pan with the juices from the meat to make your gravy. Heat the juices and pour in the red wine. Stir with a wooden spoon, scraping the bits off the bottom of the pan to incorporate them into the gravy. Leave to simmer for 5 minutes. Then stir in the stock. Again leave to simmer for 5 minutes. Stir in the cream and simmer for 5 minutes more, stirring occasionally. The gravy will darken slightly and thicken up.<br />While the gravy is simmering, bring a pot of lightly salted water to the boil. Add the broccoli and boil for 4 minutes. Drain and keep warm.<br />Serve each person with 1 or 2 pork sausages, mash and broccoli. Spoon a generous portion of gravy over the top.</div>',648,60,30,25,1,'2020-06-29 10:49:18','2022-07-16 11:04:04',NULL),(15,'uayfwc','Easy-Peasy Pizzas (vegetarian)','The easiest pizza base we have ever found, topped with a scrumptious combination of crumbled feta, mint,\nmushrooms, garlic and grated cheddar over our own homemade pizza sauce.','Gluten and Lactose',5,50,'<div>Heat your oven to 200 degrees C. Grease 2 baking sheets. If you are cooking for one or two then one sheet is plenty.<br />In a bowl, add the flour and the yoghurt. Use a spoon to mix together &ndash; a dough will start to form.<br />Sprinkle some of your extra flour on a clean surface. Plop the dough out onto the surface and<br />knead a bit with your hands. You don&rsquo;t have to start flattening it out yet.<br />Split the dough into two even balls (or one ball if one or two people) and place&nbsp; on the baking sheets. Have a bowl of cold water ready nearby. Use your hands to start flattening the dough on your baking sheets. The dough will be very sticky &ndash; don&rsquo;t panic! Keep wetting your hands to help with the process of flattening the dough out. The dough does not have to cover your whole baking sheet but make sure it is not too thick in places.<br />Place in the oven and bake for 20 &ndash; 25 minutes &ndash; check on it a few times to make sure the edges are not burning. It does not have to be 100 % cooked now &ndash; it will cook again once your toppings are on.<br />While the dough is cooking, heat the oil in a frying pan. Add the mushrooms, salt and pepper to taste and soften. Remove from heat.<br />Spread the garlic onto the semi-cooked dough.<br />Spread the pizza sauce onto the dough.<br />Add the mushrooms and the mint. Sprinkle with the feta and cheddar cheese.<br />Put back into the oven and cook for 5 &ndash; 10 minutes or until the cheese is nicely melted.</div>',614,76,26,26,1,'2020-07-01 12:49:25','2022-07-09 09:43:22','<p>Pizza Tomato Sauce</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 onion, chopped</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp crushed garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tin chopped tomatoes</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 Tbsp tomato paste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tsp sugar</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tsp dried basil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tsp dried oregano</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">salt and pepper to taste</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fry the onion for 3 minutes. Add the garlic and fry for 1 minute more.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add the tomatoes and the tomato paste. the sugar, the basil, and the oregano.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bring to a simmer for 20 minutes or until the consistency and taste is good.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add salt and pepper if need be.</span></p>'),(16,'wtzqjg','Easy-Peasy Pizzas','The easiest pizza base we have ever found, topped with a scrumptious combination of our own homemade pizza sauce, bits of bacon, green pepper, mushrooms, garlic and cheese.','Gluten and Lactose',5,50,'<div>Heat your oven to 200 Celsius. Grease two baking sheets. If you are cooking for 1 or 2 people then one sheet should be enough.<br />In a bowl, add the flour and the yoghurt. Use a spoon to mix together &ndash; a dough will start to form.<br />Sprinkle the extra flour on to a clean surface. Plop the dough onto the surface and knead a bit with your hands. You do not have to start flattening it yet.<br />Split the dough into two even balls and place one on each of the baking sheets.<br />Have a bowl of cold water ready nearby. Use your hands to start flattening the dough on your baking sheets. The dough will be very sticky &ndash; don&rsquo;t panic! Keep wetting your hands to help with the process of flattening the dough. It does not have to cover the baking sheets but make sure it is not too thick in places.<br />Place in the oven and bake for 20 &ndash; 25 minutes &ndash; check on it a few times to make sure the edges are not burning. It does not have to be 100 % cooked now &ndash; it will cook again once your toppings are on.<br />While the dough is cooking, heat some oil in a pan and cook the bacon bits. Add the green pepper and the mushrooms after 5 minutes.<br />When the mushrooms and green peppers are soft remove from the heat.<br />When the base(s) come out of the oven spread it (them) with the garlic.<br />Spread the pizza sauce on top of the garlic. Then spread the bacon bits, mushroom and green pepper.<br />Sprinkle the pizzas with a mixture of the grated cheddar and mozzarella.<br />Put them back in the oven and cook for 5 &ndash; 10 minutes or until the cheese is nicely melted.</div>',791,76,39,38,1,'2020-07-01 12:55:01','2023-03-27 16:32:50',NULL),(17,'vnuwig','Roast Vegetables, Feta and Barley Salad','This vegetarian dish ticks so many boxes - satisfying, colourful, healthy, easy to make and\ndelicious to eat. It is scrumptious hot or cold so any leftovers can be popped into a lunchbox for the\nnext day.','Gluten',5,45,'<div>Heat the oven to 180 Celsius.<br>Place the barley in a pot. Add the vegetable stock powder mixed with the specified amount of boiling water.<br>Bring to a boil and then lower the heat. Simmer, covered with a lid, for 40 – 50 minutes, checking regularly to see if the liquid has been absorbed. Once there is no liquid left the barley should be done. If it is a bit hard, add a little more water and simmer further.<br>While the barley is cooking, place the veggies in a roasting pan. Sprinkle with oil and season with salt and pepper. Bake in the oven until cooked through, about 40 minutes.<br>Place the cooked barley in a large serving bowl. Add the roasted veggies and mix together.<br>Add the cubed feta and stir in gently. Serve immediately or place in the fridge to serve cold later.</div>',461,56,20,15,1,'2020-07-01 13:00:21','2020-12-27 13:07:49',NULL),(19,'cuynxk','Bolognese Mince with Spaghetti and Cheese','The Bolognese mince with this old family favourite is no ordinary mince. It has exceptional depth of\nflavour thanks to mushrooms, red wine and our very special homemade Marinara sauce. And the spaghetti is handmade locally -what a win!','Gluten',5,45,'<div>In a pot, heat the oil. Add the onion and soften. Add the mushrooms and soften.</div><div>Add the mince, and break apart with a wooden spoon and allow it to brown.<br>Season to taste with salt and black pepper.</div><div>Add the red wine and marinara sauce. Turn the heat down and allow it to simmer for about 15 minutes.</div><div>While your mince is simmering, use another pot to boil salted water for the spaghetti. Once the water is rapidly boiling, add the spaghetti. Stir immediately to prevent it from sticking together. Boil for 2 minutes or until al dente. Drain.</div><div>Serve a portion of spaghetti into each bowl, serve the mince over the spaghetti and sprinkle grated cheese over each helping.</div>',790,55,58,34,1,'2020-07-01 13:16:37','2022-11-02 11:19:35','<p><strong>Marinara sauce</strong></p>\n<p><br />1 onion, finely chopped<br />1 tsp crushed garlic<br />a little oil<br />2 tbsp tomato paste (1 sachet)<br />2 tbsp balsamic vinegar&nbsp;<br />1 tin crushed tomato<br />1 tsp dried basil<br />1 tsp dried oregano&nbsp;<br />&frac12; tsp salt<br />Pepper, to taste</p>\n<p>Fry the onions in the oil until soft.<br />Add tomato paste, garlic, vinegar, crushed tomato and bring to a boil.<br />Add the herbs, salt and pepper.<br />Let it simmer on low for 20 minutes plus.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(20,'aqyvjl','Beef Tacos with Salsa, Peri-Mayo Sauce and Cheddar','A richly flavoured Bolognese style mince, a fresh salsa, grated cheddar cheese and our own brand of peri-\nperi mayonnaise – put it together, pop it on the table with the heated taco shells and let the fun begin.','Traces of Lactose',5,40,'<div>Pre-heat your oven to 180 degrees Celsius.<br />In a pot, heat some oil. Add the onion and soften. Add the mushrooms and soften.<br />Add the mince, and break apart with a wooden spoon and allow it to brown.<br />Season with salt and black pepper.<br />Add the red wine and marinara sauce. Turn the heat down and allow it to simmer for about 15 minutes or until the mince is not too liquid.<br />While the mince is cooking make your salsa. Chop the fresh coriander. Mix the tomatoes, green pepper, spring onion and chopped coriander together. Cut the lime in half and squeeze some lime juice over the top. Mix in and season to taste.<br />When your mince is close to being ready, place your taco shells on a baking tray and place in the oven for 3 minutes to crisp up.<br />Place the mince, the salsa, the peri-mayo, the tacos and the cheese on the table. Allow each person to fill their taco with the mince, some salsa, some sauce and finally the cheese. Dig in and enjoy!</div>',1156,49,90,32,1,'2020-07-14 10:11:38','2022-10-18 10:11:04',NULL),(21,'ulsmuu','Bean tacos with salsa, peri-mayo sauce and cheddar','Richly flavoured beans and mushrooms, a fresh salsa, grated cheddar cheese and our own brand of peri-\nperi mayonnaise – put it together, pop it on the table with the heated taco shells and let the fun begin.','Traces of Lactose',5,25,'<div>Pre-heat your oven to 180 degrees Celsius.<br />In a pot, heat some oil. Add the onion and soften. Add the cumin and paprika and mix well with the onion.&nbsp;<br />Add the mushrooms and soften. If your pot is a bit dry add a splash more oil.<br />Add the tomato paste and balsamic vinegar, stir in well.<br />Add the red kidney beans and bring to a simmer.<br />Turn the heat down and allow it to simmer for 5 to 10 minutes or until there is not too much liquid. Pop the bean mixture into a serving bowl.<br />Put your taco shells on a baking tray and place in the oven for 3 minutes to crisp up.</div>\n<div>Put the ready-made salsa in a serving bowl and place the beans, the salsa, the peri-mayo, the tacos and the cheese on the table. Allow each person to fill their taco with the beans, some salsa, some sauce and finally the grated cheese. Dig in and enjoy!</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-07-14 13:35:50','2021-05-25 13:03:54',NULL),(22,'yepgod','Chicken and Chorizo Ragu with Oven Roasted Green Beans','Spicy sausage and cubes of chicken simmered slowly in a tomato sauce with paprika and sun dried\ntomatoes. Serve with green beans baked with olive oil and Italian seasoning for a hearty, healthy meal.','None',5,50,'<div>Turn the oven on to 180 degrees C.&nbsp;<br />Place chopped beans into an oven dish, sprinkle with the Italian seasoning and some oil. Toss to coat the beans nicely. When the oven is ready these can go in to cook for 30 minutes.<br />In a large pot on a medium heat fry the Chorizo in a little oil for 5 minutes.&nbsp;<br />Add the onion and fry for a further 5 minutes. Put in the garlic, fry for another 1<br />minute and then add the paprika, a little salt to taste and sun dried tomatoes.<br />Add the chicken and fry until well coated with the spices and browned.<br />Make your stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified.<br />Pour the chopped tomatoes into the pot followed by the stock and simmer for 40 minutes.<br />Stir in the lemon juice. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.<br />Serve with the oven roasted beans.</div>',454,18,21,12,1,'2020-07-21 09:50:42','2022-04-11 11:00:19',NULL),(24,'wbpwer','Halloumi and Lentil Fattoush','A fattoush is a Middle Eastern salad which usually contains crispy bits of fried pita bread, tomatoes,\nseasonal greens and herbs and a light lemony dressing. Here we give the fattoush a bit of a twist by tossing\nit with black lentils and serving it with pan-fried Halloumi.','None',5,35,'<div>Add the vegetable stock powder to the specified amount of boiling water and place in pot. Bring to a simmer, add lentils, cover and cook on low for 20 to 30 minutes. If the lentils are left to simmer too vigorously they will become mushy.<br />While the lentils are cooking, heat the grill. Toss the pita pieces in some oil and spread on a baking sheet. Grill for 3 to 4 minutes, turning halfway. They should be golden and crisp. Set aside to cool.<br />Heat a non-stick pan over a high heat and cook the halloumi in a little bit of oil for 1 to 2 minutes each side. It should be brown and crispy on the outside.</div>\n<div>Chop each tomato into 8 wedges, scooping out seeds where you can.</div>\n<div>Chop the mint leaves and the fresh dill.<br />Once the lentils have cooled, toss them with the tomatoes, cucumber, spring onion and most of the dill and mint. Stir through the olive oil, lemon juice &amp; garlic dressing. Tip onto a serving plate and top with the remaining dill and mint, the bits of pita and the halloumi.</div>',556,36,28,22,1,'2020-07-22 13:47:33','2022-09-12 13:46:29',NULL),(25,'kkwiir','Vegetable Ragu with Parmesan on Pita','A rich, tomato sauce packed with nutritious and delicious vegetables, paired with the sharp flavour of parmesan, served on a warm pita bread. Mouthwatering.','Gluten & Lactose',10,25,'<div>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees C.<br />Put the onion, carrot and celery into a medium sized pot with a bit of water - if you are cooking for one or two it will be 2 tablespoons, if you are cooking for four it will be 4 tablespoons.<br />Cook on a medium heat stirring often until the veggies soften and the liquid is gone.<br />Add the tomato paste, balsamic vinegar and garlic, turn the heat up high and cook for one minute. Add 1/4 teaspoon of sugar per person you are cooking for.<br />Add the chopped tomatoes, the mushrooms, the red pepper, the lentils, the basil and the oreganum. Bring to the boil.<br />Turn your heat down to medium and simmer without the lid on for 20 minutes. Then remove from the heat and let it stand for 5 minutes. Check for seasoning and add salt &amp; black pepper to taste.<br />While the ragu is standing pop the pitas onto a baking tray in the oven for 5 minutes just to heat them up.<br />Serve the ragu on the warm pita bread and sprinkle with parmesan.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-07-22 14:04:04','2023-01-02 13:04:12',NULL),(26,'kcjtdf','Baked Tomato, Spinach and Mozzarella Gnocchi','Gnocchi always makes for satisfying comfort food, but here we add plenty of tomato, spinach, garlic & cheese for a healthy dose of nutrients and fabulous flavour. It’s not just the vegetarians that rave about this dish – even your most ardent meat-lover will be impressed.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,25,'<div>Preheat the oven to 220C.<br />Bring a large saucepan of salted water to the boil and cook the gnocchi for 2 &ndash; 3 minutes, or until they float to the surface. Drain and tip into an oven-proof baking dish. Mix in a bit of oil to keep it moist.<br />Heat a bit more oil in the now empty saucepan and gently fry the garlic and chilli flakes for 1 minute. You can reduce the amount of chilli flakes if you don\'t want the heat.<br />Add the tomato passata and spinach and heat through, seasoning to taste with salt and pepper.<br />Add the tomato passata and spinach mix to the baking dish with the gnocchi in, and mix it all together.&nbsp;<br />Scatter with the grated mozzarella and bake for 15 minutes until the cheese is melted and bubbling.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-07-30 10:18:22','2023-04-01 14:50:53','<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Passata</span></h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ingredients:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 large onion</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp ground black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS tomato paste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Method:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(28,'yqbuyh','Spicy pork and rice','Stir-Fry falls in love and marries Risotto – surely a match made in heaven! This one-pot meal is easy, fairly quick to the table and packs a healthy punch with its red pepper, green beans and aromatic spices.','None',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>Heat some oil in a large pot. Fry the onion wedges over a medium-high heat for 3 minutes until they&rsquo;re softened and lightly browned, stirring regularly.</li>\n<li>Make the chicken stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of water specified on the package. Set aside for now.</li>\n<li>Season the pork with salt and black pepper, then add it to the pan and stir-fry with the onion for 2 minutes until lightly browned.</li>\n<li>Add the chorizo, garlic, pepper and beans and stir-fry together for 2 minutes more.</li>\n<li>Sprinkle with the spice mix and stir in the rice letting it fry with the other ingredinets for 2 minutes.</li>\n<li>Pour in the stock and bring to the boil.</li>\n<li>Reduce the heat until there is a vigorous simmer and cook for 30 minutes, stirring regularly, until the liquid has been absorbed and the rice and pork are both tender.</li>\n</ol>',627,39,38,28,1,'2020-08-03 09:33:38','2022-06-16 15:48:43',NULL),(29,'xubmuh','Summer Chicken Stew','Summery in its green and white theme, and light enough to cook and eat on a summer’s evening, our Summer Chicken Stew with \nbaby potatoes, leeks, peas and beans will please the whole family.','None',5,45,'<div>Make your chicken stock by mixing the powder with the amount of boiling water specified on the package.<br />Heat some oil in a large pot over a medium heat. Add the leeks, garlic and thyme, cover and cook gently for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Season the chicken and add to the pot, along with the potatoes.<br />Turn up the heat, pour in the stock and bring to a simmer. Reduce the heat and allow to gently bubble with the lid on for 25 minutes. Add the green beans and peas, bring back to a simmer and cook for a further 10 minutes.<br />Season to taste.</div>\n<div>Serve in bowls or lipped plates. Cut the lemon into wedges and squeeze over each serving.</div>',772,36,58,38,1,'2020-08-05 13:14:26','2021-11-02 14:28:42',NULL),(30,'lhlcry','Cauliflower, Leek and Potato Gratin','Potatoes, cream and cheese – you can’t go wrong! Add some leeks and cauliflower and you have a deliciously satisfying vegetarian dish that even the most hardened meat-lover will enjoy.','Lactose',5,50,'<div>Turn the oven on to 200 degrees C.<br />Put a pot of salted water on to boil.<br />Slice the potatoes thickly, leave the skins on.<br />Put the potatoes into the boiling water first and after 10 minutes add the cauliflower for a further 10 minutes.<br />While the potatoes and cauliflower are boiling fry the leeks and the garlic in a little oil for a few minutes.<br />Take an oven dish and place a layer of potato and cauliflower. Sprinkle with some of the fried leeks and garlic. Season with salt and black pepper. Drizzle some of the cream over the top and a small handful of the cheese. Continue layering like this, finishing with grated cheese on top.<br />Bake for 30 minutes uncovered or until it is golden and bubbling. Test to see if the potato is soft. If not, leave in a little longer.</div>\n<div>Halve the cherry tomatoes and toss with the dressing and the greens to serve alongside the Gratin.</div>',677,90,30,18,1,'2020-08-05 13:26:31','2022-07-16 11:22:41','<p>Italian Dressing</p>\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Ingredients</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Makes approx 250 ml</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>1/2 cup extra-virgin olive oil</p>\n<p>1/4 cup white wine vinegar OR red wine vinegar OR a combo of the two</p>\n<p>2 tablespoons water</p>\n<p>1 to 2 teaspoons honey</p>\n<p>1 teaspoon freshly squeezed lemon juice</p>\n<p>3 tablespoons freshly grated Parmesan</p>\n<p>3/4 teaspoon garlic salt</p>\n<p>3/4 teaspoon dried parsley</p>\n<p>3/4 teaspoon dried basil</p>\n<p>1/8 teaspoon dried oregano</p>\n<p>Pinch of red pepper flakes</p>\n<p>Freshly ground black pepper to taste</p>\n<p>Instructions</p>\n<p>1. Measure all ingredients into a jar with a tight-fitting lid. Shake vigorously until well-blended and emulsified. Taste and adjust seasonings, adding more salt and pepper if necessary. (Alternatively, you may whisk ingredients together in a bowl, process ingredients in a mini food processor, or blend them in a blender.) Store leftovers in a sealed container in the refrigerator; allow to come to room temperature and shake well before using.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>'),(31,'sphmrt','Chicken Korma','A Korma is a South Asian dish where meat or chicken is simmered in a well seasoned sauce thickened with yoghurt, cream and sometimes coconut. Our Chicken Korma incorporates baby marrows, yellow pepper and chickpeas for a healthy twist and we use yoghurt, coconut cream and coconut in the sauce.','Lactose',5,45,'<div>Place the rice and some salted water in a pot and bring to the boil. Boil with the lid off for 20 minutes, watching that the pot does not boil dry. Drain and keep warm.</div>\n<div>Chop the fresh coriander and set aside.<br />Put a large pan on high heat and add enough oil to just coat the bottom of the pan. Add the chicken (in batches if necessary, so that you don\'t overcrowd the pan), season with salt and pepper, and cook until nicely browned on all sides, remove from the pan and reserve.&nbsp;<br />Add the butter to the pan and heat. Add the onion and fry for 5 minutes and then the ginger and garlic and fry for 2 minutes more. Add the Korma powder and fry for another 1 minute.<br />Add the yellow pepper, baby marrow and half of the coriander to the pan and cook until golden in colour, about 8-10 minutes.<br />Add the coconut cream, half the yoghurt, chickpeas, shredded coconut and chicken to the pot. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer vigorously, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes. Check for seasoning before serving, adding more salt and pepper if needed.<br />Serve with rice and top with a dollop of yogurt and a sprinkling of fresh coriander leaves.&nbsp;<br /><br /></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-08-05 13:47:39','2022-01-24 16:00:05',NULL),(32,'oxntvc','Stuffed Sweet Potatoes','Oven roasted sweet potatoes stuffed with a richly flavoured beef mince and topped with sour cream,\nrocket and an optional dash of mild peri peri sauce. This dish looks very impressive when served and its good looks are only\nsurpassed by its tastiness.','Lactose',5,55,'<div>Preheat oven to 200C/180C fan forced. Place sweet potatoes on an oven rack in the oven. Roast for 45 minutes or until tender. A knife or skewer should poke through the potato easily.<br />Meanwhile, heat some oil in a large frying pan over high heat. Add the garlic and onion. Reduce heat to low and cook for 5 minutes.<br />Stir in the spice mix and cook for 1 minute.<br />Increase heat. Add the mince to the pan. Cook, breaking up the mince with a wooden spoon, for 5 minutes or until browned.<br />Add the marjoram &amp; bay leaf, the tomato puree and an amount of water equal to the amount of puree.<br />Bring to the boil. Season well. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 30 minutes.<br />Slice the potatoes almost in half (don&rsquo;t cut all the way through). Divide the mince mixture among the potatoes.<br />Drizzle with a little sour cream and peri-peri sauce if using and top with rocket/baby spinach.</div>',688,50,44,24,1,'2020-08-05 14:27:12','2022-01-24 15:48:17',NULL),(33,'zhlcg','Aubergine and Sweet Potato Bake with Pork Sausages','Our Aubergine and Sweet Potato Bake is so good looking! Plenty of tomato, red peppers, basil, parsley and Kalamata olives give this dish it’s amazing colour and rich flavours. We pair it with pork sausages for a well rounded meal.','None',10,50,'<div>Heat the oven to 190 degrees C.&nbsp;<br />Boil the sweet potato slices in salted water for 10- 15 mins, then drain, tip into a bowl (don&rsquo;t worry if they break up a little). Add a dash of milk and half the cheese. Mix together.</div>\n<div>Roughly chop the fresh basil leaves and set aside.<br />While the sweet potato is cooking, heat some oil in a large frying pan and cook the onion until softened. Spoon in the balsamic vinegar and stock powder, then stir in the tomatoes, aubergine, peppers, basil and garlic.</div>\n<div>Add a half teaspoon of sugar for each person you are cooking for i.e. 2 teaspoons for 4 people.<br />Cover and cook for 20 mins, stirring frequently and adding a little water if necessary, until the aubergine is tender when tested with a knife.</div>\n<div>Chop the parsley.<br />Remove the pan from the heat and stir in the olives and parsley. Tip into a baking dish. Cover with the sweet potatoes, season with salt and pepper and sprinkle with the remaining cheese. Place in the oven and cook until golden, about 15 &ndash; 20 minutes.<br />While that is cooking, pan fry the pork sausages in a splash of oil on a medium high heat, turning them now and then, for 20 minutes.&nbsp; Serve the sausages with a side of the aubergine bake.</div>',740,39,47,44,1,'2020-08-10 07:27:52','2022-08-03 08:39:25',NULL),(34,'bkdoge','Chicken Savoy with Mashed Butternut','This Italian-American dish was invented by the chef known as “Stretch” at the Belmont Tavern in Belleville\nNew Jersey way back in the late 60’s. Fifty years later you can still order it if you happen to be at the\nBelmont, but why not try it at home. Think rich flavours, succulent meat and an ultra-crispy cheese and\nherb encrusted skin - an absolute delight, and pretty easy to make too. We serve our Chicken Savoy on a\nbed of mashed butternut.','Traces of Lactose',10,50,'<div>Heat oven to 230 degrees Celsius.<br>Place chicken thighs into oven dish.<br>Make up your stock by adding the powder to the specified amount of boiling water.<br>Drizzle the chicken with oil and then pour the chicken stock over the chicken.<br>Dot your pieces of garlic clove in between the chicken pieces.<br>Sprinkle the oregano over the chicken pieces and lightly season with salt and black pepper.<br>Top with the Parmesan cheese.<br>Bake the chicken for 45 minutes. If the chicken is still pink inside, leave for a few more minutes.<br>While the chicken is cooking, steam or boil the cubed butternut until soft - about 15 minutes. Mash it with the butter and salt to taste.<br>Take the cooked chicken from the oven and smoosh the soft garlic pieces into the juices.<br>Drizzle the balsamic vinegar over the chicken pieces and let it stand for 5 minutes.<br>Serve the chicken on a bed of butternut with the juices from the oven dish spooned over the top.</div>',659,17,42,36,1,'2020-08-10 07:41:03','2021-04-14 09:24:10',NULL),(35,'wjgkgu','Smokey Bacon and Tomato Pasta','Our homemade tomato passata lends a rich Mediterranean flavor to this delightfully easy to make pasta\nand the addition of bacon and mushrooms will give you a firm family favourite.','Gluten',5,25,'<div>Tip the pasta into a pot of boiling, salted water, stir once, then cook for 10-12 minutes until al dente. (Cooked but not soggy!)<br />Meanwhile, heat some oil in another pot and fry the bacon for a couple of minutes until crispy.&nbsp;<br />Add the onion and cook for another minute or two until softened, stirring occasionally.&nbsp;<br />Add the mushrooms with paprika and chilli and cook for 1 minute, stirring.<br />Stir in the passata and cook for 2 minutes until heated through. Add a pinch of sugar and season to taste.</div>\n<div>Chop the basil.<br />When the pasta is cooked, drain well and then return to the pot. Pour the tomato mixture into the pasta and add most of the basil, then fold everything together until well combined.<br />Serve in bowls with the remaining basil sprinkled over the top.</div>',688,81,32,23,1,'2020-08-10 07:54:23','2023-05-22 06:49:43','<p><strong>Passata</strong></p>\n<p><br /><strong>Ingredients:</strong><br />4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped<br />1 large onion<br />2 TBSP olive oil<br />4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic<br />8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)<br />1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste<br />2 tsp ground black pepper<br />2 TBSP tomato paste<br />Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</p>\n<p><br /><strong>Method:</strong><br />Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.<br />Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.<br />Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.<br />Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.<br />Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</p>'),(36,'vlgxxr','Beef Moussaka with Parmesan Topping','This classic dish with its meaty base, roasted aubergines and a rich parmesan sauce is easy to put together with our premade bechamel sauce and easy-to-follow instructions. Pair with a good red wine if you so desire and be transported to Greece!  NOTE: Salad is not included in the kit.','Lactose.',NULL,60,'<div>Preheat oven to 200 degrees C.<br />Dissolve the stock powder in the specified amount of boiling water.<br />Heat some oil in a medium sized pot and fry the onions and garlic gently for 2 minutes.<br />Add the mince and break up nicely with a wooden spoon so you do not get clumps of mince. Fry until browned.<br />Add the cinnamon and cook for 30 seconds.<br />Add the stock, the wine, the parsley and the tomatoes and cook for 30 minutes.<br />Leave the lid off and simmer vigorously so that the sauce is reduced and the mixture not too runny.<br />While the mince is cooking brush both sides of the aubergine pieces with oil, season well with salt and pepper, place on a baking tray and roast in the oven for about 20 minutes, turning once.<br />Leave the oven on the same heat.<br />Also while the mince is cooking, heat the white sauce gently (do not boil) and stir in the parmesan.</div>\n<div>Chop the mint leaves.<br />When the mince is ready season it with salt and pepper and stir in the mint.<br />In a suitable sized baking dish, layer the aubergines and the mince and top with the white sauce and parmesan.<br />Bake for 20 minutes or until golden and bubbling.<br /><br /></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',974,46,71,39,1,'2020-09-07 12:30:15','2022-12-09 09:22:52',NULL),(37,'hsvyml','Chicken a la King','A family classic – tasty, satisfying and nutritious. What more could you want? The peas add a friendly pop of green to this nourishing dish.\nNote: The salad in the picture is not included.','Gluten and Lactose',5,30,'<div>Place the rice in a pot and cover well with water. Add salt. Place on stove and bring to a boil.<br />Once boiling take the lid off and boil for 20 minutes. Keep an eye on the water level. When the rice is done drain it and keep it warm.<br />Heat some oil in a pot on a medium high heat and fry the onion until just golden.<br />Add the chicken strips, the garlic and the mushrooms and fry for about 10 minutes stirring frequently.<br />Add the flour and stir into the mixture. Cook for a few minutes whilst stirring so the flour doesn&rsquo;t catch on the bottom of the pot.<br />Slowly, bit by bit, add the milk and keep stirring until the sauce thickens. This should be done at a low to medium heat.<br />Add the stock powder and then allow the mixture to simmer for 5 minutes. If it appears to be too thick, add a little extra milk.<br />Add the peas and allow to simmer for 2 minutes.</div>\n<div>Chop the fresh parsley.<br />Season to taste with salt and pepper. Just before serving stir through the parsley.<br />Serve on cooked rice. If you are trying to cut down on carbs leave the rice out or only use a very small portion.</div>',603,67,22,49,1,'2020-09-07 12:51:49','2022-09-12 13:53:09',NULL),(38,'xslejx','Pork Chops Baked with Apple and Fennel, served with Sweet Potato','Pork, apple and fennel are a classic combination. Here they are baked together in apple cider vinegar, olive oil, Dijon mustard and a touch of garlic and served on a bed of mashed sweet potato to soak up the juices.','None',10,35,'<div>Preheat oven to 200 degrees Celsius.<br />Slice the apples and quarter the lemon and place with the sliced onion and fennel in a suitable size oven dish.<br />Season the chops and fry in a little oil 1 to 2 minutes each side just to seal them.<br />Place the browned chops on top of the apple, lemon, onion and fennel and pour the Apple Cider &amp; Dijon Mustard Mix over the top.<br />Bake for 35 minutes.<br />While the pork is baking boil the sweet potato cubes for 20 minutes or until soft. Mash them with a little milk or butter, salt and pepper.<br />Serve the pork on a bed of sweet potato and spoon some sauce over the top. Pick out the lemon quarters and squeeze one over each serving.</div>',511,42,24,34,1,'2020-09-07 13:02:12','2021-09-28 15:22:08',NULL),(40,'gdukqe','One Pot Honey Mustard Beef','A one pot meal is a winner for he (she?) who washes up but a tastier one will be hard to find. Fried beef strips, shredded cabbage, cauliflower florets, red pepper and sweet potato are all simmered in a wonderful homemade honey mustard sauce which comes ready made in your kit.','None',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>In a large pot or skillet with a lid, heat some oil. Add the beef strips, salt and pepper to taste and brown for a few minutes, no lid. Remove from the pot.</li>\n<li>Add a little more oil if need be and add the pepper, cabbage and cauliflower. Keep stirring and allow to cook and soften, also without the lid.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add the beef strips back, along with the honey mustard sauce. Sprinkle the corn flour over the mixture and stir to combine.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Place the sweet potato cubes on top and cover with the lid to allow the steam to cook the potato. Allow to simmer on a low heat until the sweet potato is cooked through - about 20 - 25 minutes.</li>\n<li>Stir the sweet potato into the beef and veg and serve in bowls.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-07 13:40:51','2022-02-24 10:24:27',NULL),(41,'ybhika','Chicken Satay Skewers with Peanut Dipping Sauce and a Cabbage Salad','Wow! Even if we say so ourselves, the peanut dipping sauce is to die for. You won’t wash the pot without licking it first! The chicken is marinated before being threaded onto the skewers and is incredibly moist and flavoursome. Add to this a cabbage salad with a honey and mustard dressing and you have a winner.','Peanuts',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Place the chicken cubes in a bowl and mix with the marinade. Let it sit for 20 minutes.</li>\n<li>Mix the cabbage and carrot together in a large bowl. Pour the dressing over the cabbage and carrot. Combine well and allow it to sit at room temperature.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add all the dipping sauce ingredients into a small pot and cook for 5 minutes. If it thickens too much add a splash of water. Set aside to cool.</li>\n<li>Thread the chicken cubes onto skewers. Heat your grill and grill the skewers on a baking tray for 15 minutes or until the chicken looks done, turning halfway.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Serve the chicken skewers with a small bowl of the dipping sauce on the side and a serving of the cabbage salad.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-07 14:13:22','2021-06-21 11:05:44',NULL),(42,'xhlqvh','Spicy Pork Soup with Egg Noodles','An Asian-inspired soup featuring pork mince, garlic and ginger, cumin and chilli, finely shredded spinach and spring onions.  And it wouldn’t be Asian without a splash of soy and fish sauces and a good portion of egg noodles to round out the meal.','Gluten',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Mix the pork, garlic, ginger, chili flakes, and cumin in a medium bowl.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add the pork mixture; season with salt and pepper and cook, stirring and breaking up with a spoon, until browned and cooked through, 8&ndash;10 minutes.</li>\n<li>Make your chicken stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Add the chicken stock to the pork and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until flavours meld, 8&ndash;10 minutes. Add the spinach, spring onions, soy sauce and fish sauce and cook, stirring occasionally, until spinach is tender, 5&ndash;8 minutes.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Season with salt and black pepper if necessary.</li>\n<li>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Add the noodles and boil for 3 minutes. Drain and rinse under cold water. Divide the noodles into 4 bowls and ladle the piping hot soup over the top.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-07 14:51:36','2021-10-26 11:23:02',NULL),(43,'kuaita','Creamy Spinach Polenta with Pan Fried Halloumi','Unless you happen to be from Italy, polenta is probably something that doesn’t find itself on your table often. It is made from coarsely ground yellow mealies and precooked before it is packaged giving us an easy-to-cook source of healthy carbs, fibre and minerals.   Cook it with spinach for a double dose of good health, adding parmesan and cream for that extra yumminess. Pair it with pan fried halloumi for a satisfying and healthy meal.','Lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Heat a little butter or oil in a pan on a high heat. If you have butter it does give the halloumi a wonderful flavour. Fry the halloumi pieces for 2 to 3 minutes flipping over now and then. It needs to turn a golden brown but this happens quickly so watch it carefully.&nbsp; Once done, put the halloumi aside and keep warm.</li>\n<li>Mix the stock powder with the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Bring the stock and milk to the boil in a pot and add a pinch of salt. Turn the heat down to medium and pour the polenta into the pot slowly while whisking the mixture. Cook, stirring constantly until the polenta has thickened nicely. Turn down to very low and stir in the cream, parmesan and the spinach. Season with salt and pepper to taste and take off the heat as soon as the spinach is wilted and the cheese is melted.</li>\n<li>Serve the spinach polenta with a few pieces of halloumi on top or alongside.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-07 15:09:36','2022-06-30 12:25:58',NULL),(44,'gouwey','Chickpea Burritos','Tex-Mex is a popular category of take-away or fast food. Rather make your own though and avoid the seed oils, fillers and preservatives that come with mass production. We don’t see why only the meat-eaters should enjoy a good burrito. Here is a chickpea burrito dish that is high on flavour, better for your health and easy to prepare. Enjoy!','Gluten & Lactose',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Heat some oil in a pot and cook the onions for 5 minutes. Add the carrot and cook for a further 3 minutes. Add a tiny bit of water if you find they are sticking but stir frequently.</li>\n<li>Add the chilli powder and stir fry for one minute.</li>\n<li>Add the tomatoes and chickpeas and bring to the boil. When boiling turn the heat down and simmer for 10 minutes, letting the mixture thicken. Give it a stir frequently to check it&rsquo;s not catching on the bottom of the pot.</li>\n<li>Heat your grill.</li>\n<li>Spread a couple of spoonfuls of the tomato and chickpea mix over the bottom of an oven dish that will fit 6 burritos.</li>\n<li>Heat the tortillas for a few seconds in the microwave - they are easier to work with when warm.</li>\n<li>Lay each tortilla on a board and put some tomato/chickpea mix down the centre. Tuck the ends in and roll in to a burrito shape - don&rsquo;t worry about being exact - the taste will still be awesome.</li>\n<li>Lay the burrito on top of the layer of sauce in the oven dish and repeat the process with the remaining five tortillas.</li>\n<li>Spoon the remainder of the tomato/chickpea mix on top of the burritos.</li>\n<li>Mix the grated cheese and yoghurt together with some salt and pepper and spoon over the top of your burrito dish.</li>\n<li>Place under the grill until the top is golden and bubbly.</li>\n<li>Serve with some leafy greens on the side.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-07 15:22:13','2021-06-07 15:35:58',NULL),(45,'nbhluu','Mexican Bean Soup with Toasted Feta Wraps','After a hard day\'s work it\'s very satisfying to whip up a quick Mexican Bean Soup, with two different types of bean and our home made tomato passata. Pair the soup with pan-fried toasties made from wraps, garlic and crumbled feta - rich and delicious!','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Make your stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Set aside</li>\n<li>Chop the fresh coriander and set aside.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a large pot and cook the onion over a medium heat for 5 minutes to soften. Stir in the chilli powder, passata, stock and all the beans. Bring to the boil, then gently simmer for 10 minutes. Season to taste. Remove from heat and allow to cool slightly.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Meanwhile, in a bowl crumble the feta and mix with the garlic. Lay each wrap down on a flat surface and sprinkle half of each wrap with some of the feta and garlic mix. Then fold over the empty half of the wrap, so the wrap is now a half moon shape.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Heat a little oil in a pan and cook each wrap on each side for a few minutes until nicely browned. Remove from the pan and use a sharp knife to cut into halves or thirds.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Divide the soup between bowls, scatter with coriander and serve with the wrap wedges.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-07 15:33:19','2022-10-24 10:39:19','<p>Passata</p>\n<p>Ingredients:</p>\n<p>4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped<br />1 large onion<br />2 TBS olive oil<br />4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic<br />8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)<br />1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste<br />2 tsp ground black pepper<br />2 TBS tomato paste<br />Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</p>\n<p>Method:</p>\n<p>Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.<br />Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.<br />Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.<br />Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.<br />Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</p>'),(46,'kmhnda','Tuscan Chicken','A simple to make chicken dish, with lovely colour from the cherry tomatoes and the spinach, and pulled together by a delicious sauce with butter, garlic, mustard, cream and Parmesan. Close your eyes and you’re in Tuscany! \nServed on a bed of mashed pumpkin.','Traces of lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Bring a large pot of water to the boil and add the pumpkin. Boil for 15 - 20 minutes or until soft enough to mash. Use a potato masher to mash, and season well with salt and pepper.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>In a large pot or skillet heat some oil over a medium-high heat. Add the chicken and season with salt, pepper, and oregano. Cook until golden and no longer pink, 8 minutes per side. Remove from pot and set aside.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>In the same pot over medium heat, melt the butter. Stir in the garlic and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute. Add the cherry tomatoes and season with salt and pepper. Cook until tomatoes are beginning to burst then add the spinach and cook until it is beginning to wilt.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Stir in the cream, mustard and parmesan and bring mixture to a simmer. Reduce heat to low and simmer until the sauce is slightly reduced, about 3 minutes. Return the chicken to the pot and cook until heated through, about 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Serve the chicken alongside the mashed pumpkin.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-08 07:10:47','2021-06-02 11:12:27',NULL),(47,'bveqhl','Bacon & Mushroom Risotto served with Green Beans','The signature characteristic of a risotto is its creaminess so it is important that the right type of rice is used and the method followed carefully. But don’t you worry about that - we will source the right type of short-grained rice and give you an easy to follow recipe card. This risotto is flavoured with bacon, mushroom and grated Parmesan. And we haven’t forgotten your greens!','Traces of lactose',5,35,'<ol><li>Heat some oil in a pot and cook the onion and bacon for 5 mins to soften. Add the mushrooms and cook for a further 5 mins until they start to release their juices. Stir in the rice and cook until all the juices have been absorbed.</li><li>Make your stock by adding the powder to the specified amount of boiling water.</li><li>Add the stock, a ladleful at a time, stirring well and waiting for most of the stock to be absorbed before adding the next ladleful – it will take about 20 minutes for all the stock to be added. Once the rice is cooked, remove from the heat, stir through the cream and season with salt and pepper.</li><li>While you are adding stock and waiting for the rice to be cooked, boil or steam your green beans for 5 to 10 minutes, depending on how crunchy you like them. Drain and keep warm.<br>Serve the risotto scattered with the parmesan with a side of green beans.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-08 07:37:54','2020-12-27 13:10:05',NULL),(48,'rgdonn','Beef Taco Pie','All the taco flavour without the fuss. Mexican flavoured beef mince, tortillas, tomato and cheddar cheese are layered into a casserole, baked until the tortillas are golden, and served in wedges or squares garnished with fresh coriander.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat the oven to 200 degrees C.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a medium sized pot over a medium-high heat and fry the onion and green pepper for two minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the beef mince, breaking up with a wooden spoon to avoid clumps, and fry until brown all over.</li>\n<li>Add chilli flakes and cinnamon and fry for 1 minute and then stir in 1/3 of the chopped tomato. Bring back to the boil and then turn the heat to medium. Cook uncovered for 3 minutes. Add salt to taste. Take off the stove.</li>\n<li>Grease a 22cm diameter round oven dish. If you do not have a round pie dish use a square or rectangular one - you will just cut your tortillas accordingly.</li>\n<li>Spread 1/3 of the tomatoes over the bottom of the oven dish and top with whole tortillas or tortilla strips overlapping where necessary.</li>\n<li>Place mince in the oven dish and then layer tortilla strips and cheddar cheese on top. Pour remaining tomato on top of that and leftover cheese if there is any.</li>\n<li>Bake uncovered for 20 to 25 minutes. The tortillas should be golden/light brown. Take out of the oven and let the dish stand for 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Chop the fresh coriander.</li>\n<li>Serve in wedges or squares with fresh coriander on top.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-08 08:10:34','2022-09-26 15:29:58',NULL),(49,'fathtt','Vegetarian Bean Pot with Whole Wheat Pita Breads','This is actually a vegetarian cassoulet - a white-bean stew of French origin. We have left out the traditional meat but added wholewheat pita on the side (we like a fusion of nationalities, it adds interest!) None of the original flavour is lost as we have leeks, carrots, celery, fennel seeds, thyme, garlic and a touch of tomato along with those beans.','Gluten & traces of lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Heat some oil in a pot and add the leeks, carrots and celery. Stir and add a splash of water and a pinch of salt.</li>\n<li>Put the lid on and cook for 10 minutes over a medium heat, stirring now and again to make sure it&rsquo;s not catching.</li>\n<li>Add the garlic, tomato paste, fennel seeds and dried thyme. Stir in well and cook for 1 minute.</li>\n<li>Make your stock by adding the powder to the specified amount of boiling water.</li>\n<li>Add the vegetable stock and beans to the pot and cook, with the lid on, over a medium to low heat for 15 minutes. Stir frequently and if the stew is becoming too dry add a splash or two of hot water.</li>\n<li>Add salt and black pepper to taste.</li>\n<li>Chop the parsley.</li>\n<li>Serve in bowls, sprinkling each with grated cheese and chopped parsley, along with the pita breads.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-08 08:25:11','2022-07-16 11:51:33',NULL),(50,'kvpbju','Mushroom & Sun Dried Tomato Risotto served with Green Beans','The signature characteristic of a risotto is its creaminess so it is important that the right type of rice is used and the method followed carefully. But don’t you worry about that - we will source the right type of short-grained rice and give you an easy to follow recipe card. This risotto is flavoured with mushrooms, sun dried tomatoes  and grated Parmesan. And we haven’t forgotten your greens!','Traces of lactose',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Heat a little oil in a deep frying pan or pot and cook the onion for 5 mins to soften. Add the mushrooms and cook for a further 5 mins until they start to release their juices. Stir in the rice and sun dried tomatoes and cook until all the juices have been absorbed.</li>\n<li>Dissolve the stock in the amount of water stipulated.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add the stock, a ladleful at a time, stirring well and waiting for most of the stock to be absorbed before adding the next ladleful &ndash; it will take about 20 mins for all the stock to be added. Once the rice is cooked, remove from the heat, stir through the cream, season with salt and pepper and serve with the grated Parmesan and a side of green beans.<br />While you are adding stock and waiting for the rice to be cooked, boil or steam your green beans for 5 to 10 minutes, depending on how crunchy you like them. Drain and keep warm.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-08 08:39:59','2022-07-17 09:47:12',NULL),(51,'vipolk','Cauliflower & Chickpea Curry','Chickpeas and curry are the perfect match. Add a whole lot of veggies, like onion, tomato. cauliflower and peas, not to mention the garlic, ginger and spices, and you not only have fabulous flavour but you are looking after your health in the nicest possible way.','None',5,30,'<ol>\n<li>Place the rice in a pot and cover well with water. Add salt. Place on the stove and bring to a boil. Once boiling take the lid off and boil for 20 minutes. Keep an eye on the water level, it should always be covered with some water. Do not let it burn dry. When the rice is done drain it and keep it warm.</li>\n<li>Dissolve the stock powder in the amount of boiling water stipulated on the package.</li>\n<li>Heat oil in a large deep skillet or pot over medium high heat. Add garlic and ginger, cook for 1 minute. Add onion and cook for 6 - 8 minutes or until golden.</li>\n<li>Add the spice mix.&nbsp; Cook for 1 minute.</li>\n<li>Add vegetable stock and tomato. Stir to combine, bring to simmer and cook for 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add cauliflower and chickpeas. Cook for 15 minutes or until the cauliflower is soft and sauce has thickened. If sauce is thickening too quickly, put the lid on. Adjust salt to taste, and add sugar - 1/4 teaspoon per person you are cooking for, i.e. 1 teaspoon for 4 people.</li>\n<li>Add peas and garam masala. Cook for 2 minutes, then remove from the stove.</li>\n<li>Chop the fresh coriander and stir most of it through the curry.</li>\n<li>Serve the curry with rice, the reserved fresh coriander and a swirl of yoghurt.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-08 08:50:23','2021-10-25 12:58:19',NULL),(54,'hurriz','Mushroom A La King','Mushroom A La King is just as tasty as its chicken counterpart. Serve with rice for a vegetarian version of your classic family favourite.','Lactose and Gluten',5,35,'<div>Place the rice in a pot and cover well with water. Add salt. Place on stove and bring to a boil. Once boiling take the lid off and boil for 20 minutes. Keep an eye on the water level. When the rice is done drain it and keep it warm<br />While the rice is cooking, make the mushroom mixture.<br />Heat some oil over medium to high heat in a skillet or pot.<br />Fry the onion for two minutes.<br />Add the garlic and the mushrooms and fry for 5 minutes.<br />Stir in the flour and keep stirring for one minute while the flour blends. Then allow the flour to cook for a minute or two.</div>\n<div>Heat the milk for 1 to 2 minutes in the microwave while the flour cooks - the milk should be warm to hot but not boiling.<br />Add the milk to the pot and stir well with a wooden spoon - the sauce should start thickening. Keep stirring until the sauce has thickened.<br />Stir in the vegetable stock powder.<br />Stir in the peas and cook for one minute.<br />Add salt and black pepper to taste.<br />Serve the mushroom mixture on a bed of rice.</div>',388,55,12,15,1,'2020-09-08 10:48:34','2023-01-23 09:18:11',NULL),(55,'vtbqif','Lamb Chops with Vegetables Roasted In a Creamy Passata Sauce','Roasted veggies with a difference. Instead of the usual olive oil, salt & pepper, we roast them in a creamy sauce. The perfect companion to pan-fried lamb chops.','Lactose',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 180 Celsius. Place all the veggies in a large roasting dish. Pour the Creamy Passata Sauce over the top. Place in the oven and cook for 40-45 minutes or until all the veg is soft.</li>\n<li>When the veg is almost ready, pan-fry the lamb chops: Cook for 3 &ndash; 5 minutes each side, or longer if you prefer them well-done. Serve lamb chops with a side of the roasted vegetables.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-14 07:17:20','2021-06-21 15:41:01',NULL),(56,'aoyhpt','Creamy Chicken Stew','Comforting chicken stew at its finest - with leeks, mushrooms, chunks of sweet potato and a big dollop of cream and Dijon mustard. A perfect family meal.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Heat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.</li>\n<li>In a large pot heat some oil on a medium high heat and add leeks and mushrooms. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.</li>\n<li>Add the chicken thighs and brown for a few minutes on each side.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Make your stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Pour the stock over the chicken and add the cubed sweet potatoes. Cover and simmer on low for 30 minutes.</li>\n<li>Turn heat off and stir through the mustard and cream. Season well with salt and pepper. Pour all of it into an ovenproof dish. Chop up the parsley. Sprinkle with the breadcrumbs and parsley.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Bake in the oven for 15 minutes.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Serve in bowls.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-14 07:28:25','2022-04-11 10:30:38',NULL),(57,'ertrwj','Baked Aubergine & Cheese Casserole','An unusual casserole that combines aubergine, spices, onion, garlic, red pepper, eggs and cheese making a nutritious and tasty meal. A good way of disguising veggies for those picky eaters! Note: Salad for photographic purposes only, not included in the kit.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius and grease an oven dish.</li>\n<li>Put the cubed aubergine in a colander and sprinkle generously with salt. Leave for 5 to 10 minutes while you carry on with the next steps.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil over a medium heat and fry the onion until just soft. Add the garlic, celery seeds and Cajun spice and fry while stirring for 1 minute. Add the red pepper and continue stirring until it is tender. Take off the heat.</li>\n<li>Beat the eggs in a big bowl, add half the breadcrumbs,&nbsp; and two thirds of the grated cheese. The balance of the breadcrumbs and cheese is for the topping.</li>\n<li>Put the spicy onion &amp; pepper mix and the drained aubergine into the bowl and stir into the other ingredients. Add 1/4 teaspoon of salt per person you are cooking for and a good shaking of black pepper. Stir well and place in the greased oven dish.</li>\n<li>Melt the butter and stir the rest of the breadcrumbs into the melted butter. Sprinkle the mix and the remaining grated cheese over the top of the casserole and bake uncovered for 30 minutes.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-14 07:53:16','2022-04-11 10:47:38',NULL),(58,'brjvfh','Pan-fried Halloumi with Vegetables Roasted In a Creamy Tomato & Garlic Sauce','Roasted veggies with a difference. Instead of the usual olive oil, salt & pepper, we roast them in a creamy tomato sauce. The perfect companion to pan-fried halloumi.','Lactose',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 180 degrees C.</li>\n<li>Place all the veggies in a large roasting dish.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Pour the creamy tomato and garlic sauce over the top.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Place in the oven and cook for about 40-45 minutes or until all the veg is soft.</li>\n<li>When the veg is almost ready, pan-fry the halloumi.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Cook for 1 &ndash; 2 minutes each side in a little oil in a hot pan. They brown up quickly so watch them carefully.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Serve with a side of the roasted vegetables.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-14 08:11:04','2022-07-09 18:24:35','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Passata</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ingredients:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 large onion</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp ground black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS tomato paste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Method:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(59,'rraneo','Moroccan Chickpea Soup with Cheesy Roti Rolls','Rotis are not just for curry! Here we roll them with a cheesy mixture and bake them until crisp to go with our very flavoursome Moroccan-style soup which contains not only chickpeas, onion and cumin, but celery, green beans and tomato as well. Delicious and nutritious.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 180 degrees C.</li>\n<li>Make your stock by dissolving the stock powder in the specified amount of boiling water.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a big pot and fry the onion and celery gently for 10 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the ground cumin and garlic and fry for 1 minute.</li>\n<li>Turn up the heat and add the stock, tomatoes and chickpeas.</li>\n<li>Season with a good grind of black pepper.</li>\n<li>Simmer without a lid for 6 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the beans and the juice of the lemon. If you are cooking for one or two people use half the lemon. Add some lemon zest (optional) and simmer for a further 4 minutes.</li>\n<li>Grease a baking tray.</li>\n<li>Chop the fresh parsley.</li>\n<li>Mix the grated cheddar with the paprika and some of the chopped parsley.</li>\n<li>Lay a roti on a board. Sprinkle some of the cheese mixture over the top and roll up, securing with two toothpicks. Lay on the baking tray and repeat with the remaining rotis.</li>\n<li>Pop the rotis in the oven for 15 minutes but keep an eye on them, don&rsquo;t let them burn. They should be crispy and the cheese melted. Take them out and remove the toothpicks - they should hold their shape.</li>\n<li>Serve a bowl of soup garnished with parsley along with a roti rollup or two.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-14 08:21:36','2022-05-12 18:15:42',NULL),(60,'dsnzwy','Caprese Chicken & Zucchini with Brown Rice','Our Caprese chicken dish yields very generous portions and is packed with green and red goodness - tomatoes, zucchini and fresh basil. Flavoured with garlic, oregano, balsamic vinegar and black pepper and topped with melty mozzarella, this meal uses brown rice to mop up the delicious sauce.','Traces of Lactose',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>Cook brown rice &ndash; cover with water and boil on low for 40-45 minutes. Top up the water if necessary.</li>\n<li>Roughly chop the basil leaves and set aside.</li>\n<li>While the rice is cooking, heat some oil in a large pot on medium heat.</li>\n<li>Add the onion and soften for a few minutes. Add the chicken with salt and pepper to taste. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring now and again.</li>\n<li>Remove the chicken and onion for now. Add some more oil and the garlic and saut&eacute; for 30 seconds, stirring frequently.</li>\n<li>Add tomatoes, tomato paste, balsamic vinegar, oreganum, salt to taste and most of the basil. Cook this for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.</li>\n<li>Add baby marrow and the chicken &amp; onion mix, stir everything together, cover and cook on low-medium for 12 minutes.</li>\n<li>Place mozzarella on top, reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 5 minutes, to melt the mozzaella.</li>\n<li>Sprinkle the rest of the&nbsp; basil and ground black pepper on top. Serve hot with the brown rice.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-14 08:48:41','2022-07-09 07:20:53',NULL),(61,'fwlfrd','Honey & Mustard Pork Fillet with Roasted Veg','A honey and mustard sauce and pork fillet medallions are definitely a match made in heaven. Add butternut, mushrooms and baby marrow, drizzled in oil, sprinkled with Italian herbs and roasted to perfection and you have a healthy, delicious meal.','Gluten',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Place the butternut, marrow and mushrooms in a baking dish. Sprinkle with oil and the Italian herbs and bake until the butternut is cooked through, about 40-45 minutes. Once the veg is halfway through, start with the pork.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Season the pork with salt and pepper, then lightly coat in the seasoned flour (the easiest way to do this is to put the flour and seasoning in a zip loc bag, add the pork and shake well). Heat the oil in a large frying pan, preferably non-stick, then add the pork and quickly fry until it is browned all over. Cook the pork for about 5 minutes, then remove to a plate and cover with foil while you make the sauce.</li>\n<li>Make your stock by adding the powder to the specified amount of boiling water.</li>\n<li>Add the onion to the pan (with a touch more oil if needed), then quickly fry until lightly coloured, add the stock, then bring to the boil. Boil hard for a couple of minutes to reduce the stock a little, stir in the honey, mustard and lemon juice, then bring back to the boil, stirring well.</li>\n<li>Return the pork to the pan and gently simmer for a further 3-4 minutes until it is cooked through.</li>\n<li>Serve the pork and sauce alongside the roasted veggies.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-15 06:13:06','2022-06-30 12:40:36',NULL),(63,'gtnhht','Cheesy Cauliflower and Bean Casserole','No less than three different cheeses go into the sauce of this casserole. Very simple to put together - toss the cauliflower, green beans and butter beans in the sauce, top with a buttery breadcrumb crust and bake. You will have a delicious vegetarian meal on the table in no time.','Gluten & Lactose',5,25,'<ol><li>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.</li><li>Boil or steam the green beans and cauliflower for 8 minutes. Drain and set aside.</li><li>In a bowl mix the milk, cream cheese, cheddar and Parmesan until it is thoroughly mixed. Season to taste.</li><li>Melt the butter in another small bowl and mix the breadcrumbs into the melted butter.</li><li>Transfer the cauliflower, green beans and butter beans to the milk &amp; cheese mixture and toss all together.</li><li>Place in an ovenproof dish.</li><li>Top with the breadcrumb and butter mixture.</li><li>Bake for 20 minutes.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-15 06:46:13','2020-12-22 06:04:26',NULL),(64,'evdmti','Sweet Potatoes Stuffed With a Lentil, Rocket & Tomato Filling','Sweet potatoes are a healthy starch. They are extremely rich in Vitamin A and fibre, but also contain many other vitamins and minerals. Add a delicious filling of lentils, rocket, parsley and tomato and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and you have a deliciously healthy and satisfying meal.','None',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 200 degrees Celsius.</li>\n<li>Pop the foil wrapped sweet potatoes into the oven - put them straight in, don&rsquo;t wait for the oven to heat.</li>\n<li>Cook your lentils, using the amount of water of boiling water written on the label of your lentils. Pop the boiling water and the lentils in a pot and put on a medium high heat. They should have absorbed all the water in about 15 minutes. Take them off the heat.</li>\n<li>Heat the oil in a pot and fry the onion for a few minutes before adding the garlic and frying for another minute.</li>\n<li>Add the tomatoes, balsamic vinegar, salt, sugar and black pepper and cook for 5 minutes. For the salt and the sugar add half a teaspoon of each for each person you are cooking for, ie for 2 people you will use 1 teaspoon of salt and one of sugar.</li>\n<li>Add the lentils and yoghurt and cook for another 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Chop the parsley and roughly break up the rocket.</li>\n<li>Stir the parsley and the rocket into the pot. When the rocket has wilted into the sauce, take off the heat.</li>\n<li>Take the sweet potatoes from the oven and unwrap them. Cut them half way through lengthwise, squeezing them open.</li>\n<li>Stuff some of the lentil mixture into each potato and sprinkle with the grated cheese.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-15 13:06:34','2023-05-15 11:54:00',NULL),(65,'ufykrb','Vegetarian Bolognese with Fresh Homemade Spaghetti','An old classic that never disappoints but what really excites us is the fresh homemade spaghetti. Wherever we can we like to use ingredients that are local and freshly sourced and this pasta ticks all the boxes. Our vegetarian Bolognese sauce uses soya mince in place of beef.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,30,'<ol>\n<li>Soak the soya mince in boiling water for 10 minutes and then drain.</li>\n<li>In a pot, heat some oil on a medium high heat. Add the onion and soften for 2 minutes. Add the garlic and mushrooms and cook for a further 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the wine and stir well scraping the bits off the bottom of the pot. Then add the soya and all other ingredients except the spaghetti and cheese.&nbsp; Turn the heat down and allow it to simmer for 20 minutes, stirring every now and again. Taste for seasoning and add salt and black pepper.</li>\n<li>While the soya mince is simmering, bring a pot of water to the boil. Add salt to the water and a splash of oil. Once the water is rapidly boiling, add the spaghetti. Stir immediately to prevent it from sticking together. As it is freshly made it will only take 6 minutes to cook. Drain well.</li>\n<li>Serve a portion of spaghetti into each bowl, serve the soya mince over the spaghetti and sprinkle a bit of grated cheese over each helping.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-15 13:19:05','2022-07-09 18:36:29',NULL),(67,'zqsnur','Beef Strips in a Creamy Passata Sauce','Our home made tomato passata never fails to deliver. Here you will use it to make a fabulously creamy sauce which dresses up stir-fried beef strips, onion, green pepper and zucchini. Serve on roast pumpkin and sweet potato for a healthy and well rounded family meal.','Traces of lactose',5,45,'<div>Turn on the oven to 200 degrees C. Place pumpkin and sweet potato in an oven dish. Season with salt and black pepper and drizzle with oil. Toss together and bake uncovered for 40 minutes. You do not need to wait for the oven to reach the right temperature. The chunks of veg should be soft after 40 minutes. If not, leave a little longer.<br />Heat some oil in a pot and fry the onion, garlic, green pepper and baby marrow for 2 minutes.<br />Add the beef strips and season with salt and black pepper. Stir fry for 8 minutes.</div>\n<div>Mix together the cream, yoghurt and tomato passata and add the mixture to the beef in the pan.<br />Simmer, stirring frequently, for 10 minutes.<br />Serve on the roast pumpkin and sweet potato<br /><br /></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-23 07:22:09','2023-05-16 13:33:24','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Passata</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ingredients:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 large onion</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp ground black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS tomato paste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Method:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(68,'wmgtmn','Butter Chicken & Chickpea Bake','Make your own butter chicken sauce for an oven bake of onion, chicken, chickpeas, cauliflower, green peas and cashew nuts. Serve garnished with coriander and a helping of freshly made Tzatziki - delicious!','Lactose',5,55,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat oven to 200 Celsius.</li>\n<li>Make the butter chicken sauce by mixing the curry paste, tomato paste, the yoghurt, cornstarch and a pinch of sugar (1/4 teaspoon for each person you are cooking for) together in a bowl. Then stir in the onion, cauliflower and chickpeas.</li>\n<li>Place this sauce mixture into an oven dish and top with the chicken pieces. Season with salt and pepper and drizzle with a little oil. Sprinkle the chilli flakes over the top.</li>\n<li>Bake for 40 minutes. Top with peas and cashews. Bake for a further 10 minutes or until chicken is cooked through and peas are bright green and tender.</li>\n<li>Chop the coriander and sprinkle over the top of the bake.</li>\n<li>Serve the Tzatziki alongside the bake.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-23 07:53:14','2022-10-18 09:12:41',NULL),(69,'mzgcoy','Garlic & Herb Pork Medallions with Ratatouille','Pork medallions coated with garlic, thyme and black pepper are the perfect companion for a good ratatouille. This dish is choc-full of flavour and veggies, packing a big punch of antioxidants, vitamins, minerals and fibre. A tasty way to good health!','None',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>&nbsp;Heat some oil in a large non-stick pan and fry the onion for 5 minutes or until softened.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Stir in the green pepper, aubergine, baby marrow and half of the garlic, and cook, stirring, for a few minutes. Tip in the tomatoes, then stir in the veg stock powder, the fresh thyme and dried basil. Add 1/4 teaspoon of sugar per person you are cooking for. Stir together well.</li>\n<li>Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until tender. Chop the basil leaves and stir them through the ratatouille.</li>\n<li>Meanwhile, rub the pork with the rest of the garlic, dried thyme, black pepper and salt, patting it so it sticks all over. Heat some more oil in a non-stick frying pan and cook the pork on a medium high heat for about 3 minutes each side. Remove from the heat, cover and rest for 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Serve a few pork medallions with the ratatouille.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-23 08:06:34','2022-08-03 08:42:59',NULL),(70,'yhxxjn','Halloumi & Cabbage Satay Wraps','Pan-fried halloumi pieces are coated in a divine sweet and spicy peanut sauce which is perfectly complemented by shredded cabbage and carrot in natural yoghurt. Wrap it all together to make a fabulous taste bomb.','Nuts, Lactose',5,25,'<div>If you do not have a microwave then preheat your oven to 180 degrees C. Wrap your wraps in tin foil and heat them in the oven for about 10 minutes. Make sure they are well wrapped - they must not dry out or they will be impossible to roll. If you have a microwave then 10 seconds in the microwave on high (not wrapped) just before you use them will make them easy to roll.<br />Mix the carrot, cabbage and yoghurt together with a little salt and pepper.</div>\n<ol>\n<li>Heat your oil or butter on a fairly high heat and fry the halloumi pieces - they only need a few minutes per side to be nicely browned. Turn heat down to medium and remove the halloumi from the pan.</li>\n<li>Put the peanut sauce into the pan and stir while it heats. Add the halloumi bits to the heated sauce and coat them well. Turn the heat right down - just enough to keep the pan warm, not to cook further.</li>\n<li>Heat the wraps as per instructions above.&nbsp; Place each on a plate. Place some of the cabbage mix down the centre topped by halloumi bits in satay sauce.</li>\n<li>Wrap it up and enjoy!<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-23 10:42:07','2021-06-28 13:42:53',NULL),(71,'nesptc','Butter Paneer & Chickpea Bake','Cubes of paneer baked in a mildly spicy but delicious yoghurt-based curry sauce with cauliflower and chickpeas. Topped with green peas & cashews and served with fresh coriander.','Lactose',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.</li>\n<li>Decant the curry sauce into a bowl. Then stir in the onion, cauliflower and chickpeas.</li>\n<li>Place this mixture into an oven dish and place the paneer cubes in it. Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle the chilli flakes over the top.</li>\n<li>Bake for 30 minutes. Top with peas and cashews. Bake for a further 10 minutes or until peas are bright green and tender.</li>\n<li>Chop the fresh coriander and use it to garnish each serving.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-23 10:48:07','2022-02-09 14:45:15',NULL),(72,'hiqgcd','Coconut & Cashew Tofu Curry','Coconut, cashews and curry, cooked together, are guaranteed to make your tastebuds sing. Our vegetarian curry is quick and easy to put together with cauliflower, carrots, green pepper and tofu making it a substantial meal that can stand alone. Simply serve in a bowl garnished with fresh coriander and extra cashews - it’s all in your kit!','Nuts',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>Make your stock by mixing the powder with the specified amount of boiling water.</li>\n<li>Add oil to a large pot and place over medium high heat. Add in garlic, ginger, dried chilli flakes, sweet potato, cauliflower, green pepper, and carrots. Saut&eacute; for 10 minutes, stirring frequently, until carrots start to soften.</li>\n<li>Next stir in the spice mix and some salt to taste.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add in coconut milk, tomato sauce, vegetable stock and ground cashews. Stir until smooth.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Simmer on low heat for 30 minutes or until sweet potatoes and carrots are fork tender. When there is 10 minutes to go, gently add in tofu and stir.</li>\n<li>Chop the coriander.</li>\n<li>Serve immediately with coriander and whole cashews.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-23 10:57:54','2022-07-17 16:35:43',NULL),(73,'aogfdb','Cheeseburger Soup with Flatbread','You feel like a cheeseburger? You want it really warm and filling? And good for you? You’ve come to the right place. Enjoy your favourite flavours in a creamy, cheesy soup complete with beef mince, onion, pepper and mushroom, accompanied by a homemade flatbread. It’s easy to make - let us show you how.','Gluten and lactose',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Mix the yoghurt and flour marked for the flatbread together. Add a pinch of salt. Put some of the flour marked for working the dough on a clean surface and knead the dough until smooth. Use extra flour on your hands to stop them sticking. Pop the dough back into the bowl and leave for a few minutes while you make the soup.</li>\n<li>Mix the beef stock powder with the specified amount of boiling water. Then stir in the flour that is marked for the soup, combining well so there are no lumps.</li>\n<li>In a big pot heat some oil and fry the onion and pepper for 2 minutes. Add the mushrooms and the mince, breaking the mince apart with a wooden spoon so that it does not clump together. Season to taste with salt and black pepper and stir fry this mixture for 10 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the flour and stock mixture to the mince mixture in the pot and bring to the boil while stirring.</li>\n<li>Stir in the milk. Again, bring to the boil stirring frequently. Reduce the heat to low so that the soup stays hot.</li>\n<li>Make your flatbread: Divide the dough into balls. Flatten a ball to more or less the size of your pan, using the extra flour to stop it sticking. Pour a little oil into the pan and keep the pan fairly hot.</li>\n<li>Place a flatbread into the pan and brush the top of it with a little oil. One minute each side should be enough to cook it and it should have golden patches. It will puff up a bit. Pop each cooked flatbread onto an oven tray to keep warm. Repeat until you have 4 or 5 flatbreads.</li>\n<li>Now stir the grated cheese into your soup which should still be hot and stir in the spinach just before serving.&nbsp; Chop the tomato and season with salt and pepper.</li>\n<li>Serve the soup in bowls with a bit of chopped and seasoned tomato on top with flatbread on the side.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-23 11:28:08','2021-09-06 09:54:04',NULL),(76,'frtegy','Dijon Chicken Thighs with Creamy Spinach Polenta','Dijon mustard, white wine, cream and thyme make these chicken thighs something special. Add in mushrooms and green beans for more flavour and and a dash of colour and serve on polenta. Not any old polenta, though. Our creamy polenta is made with milk, chicken stock and cream cheese and has spinach stirred into it for those extra nutrients.','Gluten & Lactose',5,35,'<div>Make up two amounts of stock using the specified amount of boiling water on each package. The smaller amount is for the chicken and the larger amount is for the polenta.<br>Place the chicken thighs in a bowl and season with salt and black pepper. Sprinkle the flour over the chicken and use your hands to coat each piece of chicken with some flour. There will be flour left in the bottom of the bowl – don’t discard this.<br>Heat the oil over medium heat in a large pot and add the chicken, turning occasionally until browned, 6 to 8 minutes. Remove and set aside on a plate for now.<br>To the pot, add the mushrooms and green beans. Cook for about 5 minutes.&nbsp;<br>In the bowl with the leftover flour, add the smaller amount of chicken stock, white wine, cream, Dijon mustard, and dried thyme. Pour this sauce over the mushrooms and beans, scraping any browned bits. Add the chicken thighs back and cook, turning occasionally until cooked through, 10 to 12 minutes.<br>While the chicken thighs are cooking, put your milk and and the larger amount of stock in another large pot and bring to the boil. Once it is boiling, turn down the heat and, using a whisk to stir continuously, slowly add the polenta bit by bit. It will slowly start to thicken up. The process should take 5 – 8 minutes. Once it has thickened, turn the heat off and stir through the spinach and cream cheese with a wooden spoon.<br>Serve a chicken thigh or two with a side of creamy polenta.<br><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-09-24 08:22:45','2021-02-13 15:52:02',NULL),(77,'ufzsex','Spiced Carrot & Lentil Soup with Homemade Flatbread','This soup is simple to make yet so delicious. Spiced with cumin seeds, chilli flakes, turmeric and cayenne pepper, it has a nice little bite and the split red lentils add a lovely thick texture. Pair it with a home made flatbread and you have a very satisfying and nutritious meal.','Gluten and Lactose',5,30,'<div>Start by making the flatbread: mix together the flour marked \"for flatbread\", the yoghurt marked \"for flatbread\" and 1/4 tsp salt per person you are cooking for. Put some of the flour marked \"for flattening\" on a clean surface and knead the dough until smooth. Use extra flour on your hands to stop sticking. Pop the dough back into the bowl and leave for a few minutes while you do the soup.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Make your vegetable stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Set aside</div>\n<div>Heat a large saucepan and dry-fry the cumin seeds and chilli flakes for 1 minute, or until they start to jump around the pan and release their aromas.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />Add some oil, the grated carrots, split red lentils, vegetable stock and the coconut milk to the pan and bring to the boil.&nbsp;<br />Season with salt, pepper, turmeric and cayenne pepper and simmer for 15 minutes or until the lentils have swollen and softened.<br />Whizz the soup with a stick blender until smooth or you can leave it chunky, whichever you prefer - both are nice.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Keep your soup warm.</div>\n<div><br />Make your flatbread: Divide the dough into balls. Flatten a ball to more or less the size of your pan, using the extra flour to stop it sticking. Pour a little oil into the pan and keep the pan fairly hot.<br />Place a flatbread into the pan and brush the top of it with a little oil. One minute each side should be enough to cook it and it should have golden patches. It will puff up a bit. Pop each cooked flatbread onto an oven tray to keep warm. Repeat until you have 4 or 5 flatbreads.</div>\n<div><br />Season the soup to taste and finish with a dollop of plain yogurt. Serve with flatbreads.&nbsp;<br /><br /></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-07 06:27:41','2022-11-15 09:37:27',NULL),(80,'sdiobh','Tomato, Spinach & Paneer Pasta Bake','A rich & tasty tomato sauce with spinach, mushrooms and baby marrow is poured over penne pasta with chunks of paneer, a ricotta-type cheese, nestled into it. This is topped with a mixture of breadcrumbs and grated cheddar and baked until golden and crispy.','Gluten and lactose',5,45,'<div>Heat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.<br>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil and cook the pasta in the boiling water for 12 minutes. Drain and put into an oven dish.<br>Heat the oil in a pot and fry the onion for a few minutes, then add the garlic, baby marrows and mushrooms. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring now and again.<br>Add the tomatoes, tomato paste, Italian herbs and salt and pepper. Simmer for 5 minutes.<br>Add the spinach and yoghurt. Stir in well and simmer for a minute or two.<br>Add the grated parmesan and take off the heat.<br>Place the paneer cubes on top of the pasta, nestling it in. Then pour the tomato and spinach mixture over that. Cover with the breadcrumbs and grated cheddar.<br>Bake for 30 mins.<br><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-07 06:56:30','2021-02-23 10:57:42',NULL),(81,'cwxtts','Red Onion & Mushroom Tostadas','A tostada is a crispy, baked tortilla which is topped with mashed black beans - a yummy vehicle for any number of interesting toppings. Here we use red onion, lots of mushroom and a bit of green pepper sautéed with Italian herbs and paprika and finished off with grated mozzarella. Pop them back in the oven until melty and delicious!','Gluten and traces of lactose',5,25,'<div>Heat the oven to 200 Celsius. Line one or two baking sheets with baking paper and place the tortillas on the sheet. Rub some oil over each side of the tortilla and season with salt. Bake for 5 minutes, flip them over and bake for another 5 minutes. They should be crispy. Remove from the oven and allow to cool. Keep the oven on.<br>In a pan, heat the oil and add the red onion and green pepper. Fry for a few minutes until soft. Add the mushrooms and season with salt, pepper, paprika and Italian herbs.&nbsp;<br>Add the black beans to a microwave safe bowl and add a drop of oil. Heat for a minute and then use a fork to smoosh the beans.<br>Dollop some of the black beans onto each tortilla and spread. Add some of the red onion and mushroom mix and sprinkle with mozzarella.<br>Place the tortillas back in the oven for a few minutes until the cheese is nicely melted.&nbsp;<br><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-07 07:09:49','2021-02-26 11:27:58',NULL),(83,'bgrtkn','Cheesy Pork Pilaf with Mushrooms and Peas','A tasty rice pilaf with pork strips, garlic, red pepper, mushroom and peas. Finish it off with grated cheddar\nstirred into all that goodness and you have a satisfying family meal that is quick and easy to put together.','Traces of Lactose',5,35,'<div>Make up your stock by mixing the stock powder with the amount of boiling water specified on the stock package.<br>Heat oil in a large pot and fry the onion wedges for 3 minutes.<br>Season the pork with salt and pepper and add to the pot, frying with the onion for 2 or 3 minutes until browned.<br>Add garlic, red pepper and mushrooms and stir fry for 2 minutes more.<br>Stir in the rice and chicken stock and bring to the boil. Simmer vigorously for 20 minutes.&nbsp;<br>Add the frozen peas and continue simmering until the rice has absorbed the stock, stirring occasionally.<br>Once the liquid is absorbed, add the grated cheese, stir and serve.</div>',477,35,36,30,1,'2020-10-19 12:23:50','2021-03-20 15:19:43',NULL),(84,'lbubnb','Chicken Cauliflower Alfredo','A quick all-in-one dish bringing you chicken, bacon, cauliflower and spinach in a rich, creamy Alfredo sauce, complete with garlic and Parmesan. Salad not included in the kit.','Lactose',10,20,'<div>Fry the bacon bits in a little oil until crispy. Set aside.<br>In the same pan, fry the chicken cubes and garlic until the chicken is done, about 10 minutes. Turn the pieces often. Set aside when cooked.<br>Fry the spinach in the same pan but only until wilted, no longer than this. Set the spinach aside.<br>Add the cream and simmer for two minutes. Then add back the bacon, chicken, garlic and&nbsp;spinach and stir in the grated parmesan.<br>Allow to simmer while you boil or steam the cauliflower for 10 minutes. If boiling bring the water to the boil before you put the cauliflower in and then time it. Drain the cauliflower well and add to the chicken in the pot.<br>Stir well and serve.</div>',727,17,48,69,1,'2020-10-19 13:07:47','2022-07-17 09:20:35',NULL),(85,'btvqpg','Sweet Corn Fritters with Black Bean Salsa','Our sweet corn fritters are good enough to eat straight from the oven with a knob of butter so try not to\nsteal them before they get to the table. Add some fresh tomato and black bean salsa, a sprinkle of chopped\ncoriander and a dollop of our special peri-mayonnaise to make a tasty and well-rounded meal.','Gluten',10,20,'<div>Heat the oven to 200C/180C fan and line a large baking tray with baking paper.<br />Heat some oil in a pan and fry the onion and red pepper for 5 minutes until softened.&nbsp;<br />Beat the eggs in a small bowl. Place the seasoned flour into another bowl. Add the onions, red pepper and sweet corn to the flour. Add the beaten eggs, then mix together well. If you are cooking for 1 person, add the beaten egg slowly, and if the mixture seems to be getting too sloppy, discard half the egg.&nbsp;<br />Spoon&nbsp; 8, 4 or 2 mounds of the mixture onto the baking tray, depending on how many you are cooking for, well spaced apart, then flatten slightly with the back of the spoon. Bake for 20 minutes until set and golden.</div>\n<div>Place the tomato and bean mix into a serving bowl. Chop the fresh coriander and add it to the tomato and beans. Grate the lime to make lime zest. Add the zest and then squeeze the juice from the lime into the salsa. Mix together well.<br />Serve 1 &ndash; 2 fritters with a side of salsa and a dollop of peri-mayo for each person.</div>',363,52,16,12,1,'2020-10-19 13:50:37','2022-09-26 14:46:30','<p>How to Make Self Raising Flour</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>1 cup of flour (in this case brown)</p>\n<p>1,5 teaspoons baking powder</p>\n<p>0,25 teaspoons salt</p>\n<p>Mix together well.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(86,'fyunrk','Mexican Beef Mince with Polenta Topping','A perfect family meal - rich tomato, bean and mince sauce with hints of Mexican spice topped with polenta  strips and grated mozzarella. The polenta is easy to make and flavoured with parmesan, butter and rosemary. Served with green beans.','Traces of Lactose',10,35,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees centigrade.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Grease a baking tray for the polenta.</li>\n<li>Bring the amount of water specified on the polenta package to the boil. Then whisk in the polenta a little at a time. Keep stirring until the polenta thickens to a porridge consistency and add the butter, salt to taste, parmesan and the rosemary that is marked for the polenta. Take off the heat and pour into the greased tray. Set aside and let it cool.</li>\n<li>In a big pot, heat a bit of oil and fry the onion, garlic, half of the other rosemary and the thyme until the onion is soft, a few minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the mince and break up with a wooden spoon so it doesn&rsquo;t form clumps. Cook for 5 minutes to brown the meat nicely.</li>\n<li>Add the tomato &amp; onion mix, beans, tomato paste, and spice mix.&nbsp; Stir in and simmer for 10 minutes, uncovered.</li>\n<li>While the beef sauce is simmering steam or boil the green beans until just soft, 5 to 10 minutes, depending on your preference.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Then cut your cooled polenta into strips. You will overlap these strips over the mince to form the topping.</li>\n<li>Pour the mince into an oven dish and place your polenta strips on top. Sprinkle with the mozzarella cheese and the rest of the rosemary.</li>\n<li>Bake for 20 minutes - the top should be golden and the mince bubbling up between the polenta shapes. Serve with the green beans on the side.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 06:04:45','2022-09-05 10:49:16',NULL),(87,'kirbtv','Cheesy Chicken Stuffed Peppers','Roasted peppers bursting with cheesy, flavourful chicken and a touch of tomato and chilli. They seem too good to be healthy but they really are!','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Rub pepper halves with a little oil and place facing upwards (like a cup) on the baking tray. When the oven is hot enough roast peppers for 20 minutes.</li>\n<li>While the peppers are roasting, heat a little oil in a pan, season the chicken and stir fry until brown - 5 to 8 minutes. Set aside.</li>\n<li>In a large bowl mix most of the mozzarella and nearly all the parmesan. The remaining cheese is for sprinkling over the top of the peppers.</li>\n<li>Chop the parsely.</li>\n<li>To the cheese in the bowl add the garlic, passata, parsley, chilli flakes, breadcrumbs and the chicken. Mix together well.</li>\n<li>When the peppers are roasted, spoon this mixture into them and top with the remaining cheese.</li>\n<li>Put back into the oven for 20 minutes. Switch to grill for a few minutes to brown the cheese if necessary.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 06:23:32','2021-11-30 09:50:56',NULL),(88,'uxbcva','Pork Fillet Medallions in a Thyme & Sage Sauce','Pork fillet medallions are flash-fried and then added to the sauce to simmer, along with leeks, herbs, mushrooms and sweet potato cubes. After stirring in cream and parsley, broccoli florets are placed on top and allowed to steam until done. A very hearty and tasty meal, with lots of nutrition packed in.','Traces of Lactose',10,40,'<ol>\n<li>Heat some oil in a large pot. Sear the pork medallions on each side for a few minutes.&nbsp; Season with salt and pepper. Remove and set aside.</li>\n<li>Make your stock by adding the stock powder to the specified amount of boiling water.</li>\n<li>In the same pot you used for the pork, add a bit more oil and the leeks and cook for a few minutes and then add the mushrooms sage and thyme. Cook for 5 minutes. Add the cubed sweet potato along with the stock. Stir.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add the meat back into the pot, cover with the lid and simmer for 20 minutes.</li>\n<li>Chop the parsley.</li>\n<li>Stir the cream and the parsley through the pork dish. Put the lid back on for another 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Place the broccoli on top of the pork and put the lid back on, allowing it to steam for 10 minutes.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 06:38:11','2021-10-25 13:35:42',NULL),(89,'lemcjb','Mexican Bean and Tomato with Polenta Topping','A perfect family meal - rich tomato and bean mix with hints of Mexican spice topped with polenta  strips and grated mozzarella. The polenta is easy to make and flavoured with parmesan, butter and rosemary. Served with green beans.','Traces of Lactose',10,40,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees C.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Grease a baking tray for the polenta.</li>\n<li>Bring the water for the polenta to the boil. Check the polenta package to see how much water you should use. Then whisk in the polenta a little at a time. Keep stirring until the polenta thickens to a porridge consistency and add the butter, salt to taste, parmesan and rosemary. Take off the heat and pour into the greased tray. Set aside and let it cool.</li>\n<li>In a big pot, heat a bit of oil and fry the onion, garlic and rosemary until the onion is soft, a few minutes.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add the tomato, beans and spice mix, stir in and simmer for 10 minutes, uncovered. Taste for seasoning.</li>\n<li>While the beans are simmering steam or boil the green beans until just soft, 5 to 10 minutes, depending on your preference.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Then cut your cooled polenta into strips. You will overlap these strips over the bean mix to form the topping.</li>\n<li>Pour the tomato and beans into an oven dish and place your polenta strips on top. Sprinkle with the mozzarella cheese.</li>\n<li>Bake for 20 minutes - the top should be golden and the bean mix bubbling up between the polenta shapes. Serve with some green beans on the side.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 06:58:31','2022-11-21 10:28:39','<p><strong>Tex Mex Seaasoning</strong></p>\n<p>1 tbsp chili powder<br />2 tsp paprika powder<br />2 tsp ground cumin<br />1 tsp garlic powder<br />1 tsp onion powder<br />1&frasl;2 tsp chili flakes<br />1&frasl;2 tsp dried oregano<br />1&frasl;2 tsp ground black pepper<br />1 pinch ground cinnamon&nbsp; and 1 pinch ground cloves<br />1 tbsp sea salt (optional)</p>\n<p>Add all ingredients to a bowl and stir until thoroughly blended. Pour into a jar with a tight-fitting lid.<br />If you use whole seeds, grind in a grinder either in advance or when cooking.<br />Keep the spices in a dark, dry and cool/room temperature place. Small tin cans are great.<br />Make a big batch to last for 4&ndash;6 months; after this the spices will lose some flavor and color. They won\'t go bad, but will just be less powerful.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(90,'mhsjid','Cheesy Chickpea Stuffed Peppers','In our vegetarian version of stuffed peppers, chickpeas work their magic, blending beautifully with the two cheeses, passata, herbs and spices to give us an amazing burst of flavour. They also give us a good dose of Vitamin B6 and folate, along with iron, phosphorus, manganese, copper and magnesium. Peppers are full of vitamin C so please feel virtuous while you chomp on these beauties.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',10,40,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Rub pepper halves with a little oil and place facing upwards (like a cup) on the baking tray. When the oven is hot enough roast peppers for 20 minutes.</li>\n<li>In a large bowl mix most of the mozzarella and nearly all the parmesan. The remaining cheese is for sprinkling over the top of the peppers.</li>\n<li>Chop the parsley.</li>\n<li>To the bowl add the chickpeas, garlic, passata, parsley, chilli flakes and the breadcrumbs . Mix together well.</li>\n<li>When the peppers are roasted, spoon this mixture into them and top with the remaining cheese.</li>\n<li>Put back into the oven for 20 minutes. Switch to grill for a few minutes to brown the cheese if necessary.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 07:13:08','2022-07-17 16:42:50','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Passata</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ingredients:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 large onion</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp ground black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS tomato paste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Method:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(91,'gthyca','Aubergine Parmigiana','Traditionally, in Italy, the aubergine is coated in seasoned flour and deep fried before layering with a tomato sauce, parmesan and mozzarella. We bake our aubergine with a little oil and lemon juice which keeps the dish lighter. We then use ricotta and a little mozzarella for the layering with the grated Parmesan on top – lighter in calories without losing any flavor!','Traces of Lactose',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Heat oven to 200 degrees C.</li>\n<li>Mix the lemon juice with an equal amount of oil and brush a little extra oil onto a baking tin.</li>\n<li>Place the aubergine slices on the tin and brush with the lemon and oil mixture. Season with black pepper. Bake for 10 minutes. Turn the pieces over, brush with lemon and oil mixture season with more black pepper and bake for a further 10 minutes.</li>\n<li>While the aubergine is in the oven, heat some more oil in a pot. Add the onion and garlic and fry for 3 minutes. Add the chopped tomatoes, balsamic vinegar, the tomato paste, oregano, salt and pepper and stir well.</li>\n<li>Simmer for 10 minutes &ndash; the mixture should be thick and saucy.</li>\n<li>Roughly chop the fresh basil leaves.</li>\n<li>In an ovenproof dish place a thin layer of tomato sauce on the bottom.</li>\n<li>Then layer one third of the aubergine followed by one third of the remaining tomato sauce.</li>\n<li>Place half the ricotta in pieces or spoonfuls and half the mozzarella over that with half the basil leaves. Season well with pepper.</li>\n<li>Repeat the layers of aubergine, tomato sauce, pepper, basil leaves, ricotta and mozzarella.</li>\n<li>Put the final pieces of aubergine and the fresh tomato slices on top with the remaining tomato sauce poured over.</li>\n<li>Season with pepper and scatter the grated parmesan over the top.</li>\n<li>Bake for 20 minutes. The cheese should be golden and the juices bubbling through.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 07:21:28','2023-04-17 11:11:18','<p>One medium brinjal is about 250 grams</p>'),(92,'ltxyrg','Chicken Breasts Stuffed with Ricotta & Spinach served with Roasted Veg','This may sound complicated but it’s a breeze to put together. The colours of the veg with their lovely garlic & lemon twist are amazing - amazingly good health-wise too.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',10,40,'<ol><li>Heat oven to 200 degrees Celsius.</li><li>Put spinach into a colander and pour a kettle of boiling water over it to wilt it. Drain and cool slightly, then squeeze as much water out of it as possible.&nbsp;</li><li>Put ricotta in a bowl, and grate over a small amount of lemon zest (put lemon aside to use the juice later), salt &amp; pepper and the nutmeg. Stir in the spinach and mix well.</li><li>Cut a slit into each chicken breast and push open with your fingers to make a pocket. Fill with the ricotta and spinach mixture. Rub with a bit of oil and sprinkle the breadcrumbs on top. Arrange in an oven dish.</li><li>Put the chicken in the oven - it should take 40 minutes to cook.</li><li>In another oven dish arrange the veg and garlic cloves, sprinkle with some oil and toss with salt and pepper.</li><li>Put the veg in the oven - they should take about 30 minutes.</li><li>When the veg is done, remove the garlic cloves and mash them with a squeeze of juice from the lemon. Stir back into the veg.&nbsp;</li><li>Serve a portion of chicken with roasted veg on the side.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 07:41:33','2021-01-19 10:26:50',NULL),(93,'fvpzes','Swedish Meatballs with Cauli-Rice','Classic Swedish Meatballs - tender and juicy meatballs topped with a rich gravy made from beef stock and cream. Our original (in the pic) was served on zoodles but zoodles do not pack and keep well so we have replaced them with cauli-rice. It\'s just as good at soaking up that yummy sauce!','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Chop the parsely.</li>\n<li>In a large bowl mix together the mince, the spiced breadcrumbs, the parsley,&nbsp; and salt and pepper to taste.</li>\n<li>In a separate bowl, beat the egg. Add as much egg as you need to the mince mixture to make it wet enough to make into meatballs - if you are cooking for 4 you will use the whole egg, if cooking for fewer people, then you will use less. Combine well and shape into meatballs.</li>\n<li>Make your beef stock by adding the powder to the specified amount of boiling water.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a large skillet and fry the meatballs, turning fairly often to brown them nicely and cook them through, about 10 minutes. Transfer them to a plate and keep warm.</li>\n<li>In the same skillet, using the juices from the frying meatballs, melt the butter and stir in the flour. Let it cook while stirring for a minute.</li>\n<li>Add the beef stock and cream, stirring rapidly to blend the sauce nicely. Add the Worcestershire sauce and the mustard and simmer while stirring until the sauce thickens.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add the meatballs back to the sauce and allow to simmer for two minutes.</li>\n<li>While the meatballs are simmering in the sauce (or keeping warm) stir fry your cauli-rice in hot oil for 2 to 3 minutes. Do not overcook or it gets soggy.</li>\n<li>Serve the Swedish meatballs on top of the cauli-rice.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 07:54:41','2022-05-13 15:49:13','<p>Feel free to use zoodles as in our original pic as long as you make them or buy them and cook them on the same day.</p>\n<p>You could also use rice or mashed potato along with some green beans.</p>'),(94,'cgxnqj','Halloumi & Bean Stew','This is a very hearty vegetarian stew that will surely impress the meat eaters as well. We seem to use the word “hearty” a lot - it means “satisfying and wholesome” and we like to think most of our meal kits will deliver just that. This one combines onion, red pepper, garlic, tomato pesto, chopped tomatoes, mixed beans - kidney, black or butter beans - and couscous. Topping that is a generous amount of fried halloumi and chopped coriander.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Heat some oil in a pot over a medium heat. Add the onion and pepper, along with a pinch of salt and fry for 10 mins or until softened. Add the garlic, pesto and ground coriander, and cook for 1 min. Tip in the beans and tomatoes along with the specified amount of water, then bring to a simmer and cook uncovered for 8 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the couscous and cook for another few minutes while the stew thickens.</li>\n<li>Add a little oil to a frying pan over a medium to high heat. Fry the halloumi for 2 mins on each side or until golden brown. &nbsp;</li>\n<li>Chop the fresh coriander.</li>\n<li>Taste the beans for seasoning, then spoon into deep bowls. Top with the halloumi and the chopped coriander</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 08:11:12','2022-02-23 10:48:15',NULL),(95,'oolkvz','Butternut and Spinach Lasagne','This Butternut & Spinach Lasagne is not only a super-healthy meal - it is decadently different with chopped pecan nuts and loads of mozzarella. Even the most hardened carnivore will be impressed. The salad in the photograph is not included in the kit.','Traces of Lactose',5,45,'<ol><li>Heat the oven to 200 degrees Celsius.</li><li>Bring a big pot of salted water to the boil and boil the butternut for 15 minutes - it should be very soft.</li><li>Dissolve the vegetable stock powder&nbsp; in the specified amount of boiling water.</li><li>Drain the butternut and mash with salt, pepper and nutmeg. Use as much of the veg stock above to make the mixture sloppy.&nbsp; It needs moisture for the lasagne sheets to absorb.</li><li>Grease a baking dish and layer as follows:</li><li>Layer of butternut, 3 sheets of lasagna, layer of shredded spinach, half of the nuts and some cheese. Repeat twice and then cover with a thin layer of butternut. You should leave some cheese to sprinkle on the top.</li><li>Cover with foil and cook in the oven for 30 minutes.&nbsp;</li><li>Take foil off and put under the grill to brown the cheese - about 5 minutes.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 08:28:42','2022-08-05 09:54:59',NULL),(96,'tgszwo','Dotti Biscotti’s Homemade Spaghetti with Ratatouille & Feta','There is nothing like homemade pasta - those Italian mama’s know what they are doing. Here we take homemade spaghetti and instead of adding the normal tomato sauce and grated cheddar we have added a veggie-filled tomato-based ratatouille and some creamy feta. Delicious.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Start with the ratatouille: Heat some oil in a pot and fry the onion for a few minutes. Add the red pepper, aubergine and marrows and fry for 5 minutes stirring frequently. Then add the garlic and fry for 2 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the tomato paste, balsamic vinegar and 1/2 teaspoon of sugar per person you are cooking for ie 2 teaspoons for 4 people.</li>\n<li>Add the sprigs of thyme.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Put in the tomatoes, both types, mix well, put the lid on and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring frequently. Taste and season with salt and black pepper.</li>\n<li>Grate your lemon to make lemon zest and stir in to the pot.</li>\n<li>Roughly break the basil leaves into the pot. Stir well and take off the heat.</li>\n<li>While the ratatouille is cooking, bring a big pot of salted water to the boil. Add a tablespoon of oil to stop the spaghetti from sticking. When the water is boiling, put the spaghetti in and gently break it apart with a fork. Boil for 3 to 5 minutes, gently stirring now and again- the spaghetti should rise to the top of the water when it&rsquo;s done. Drain and set aside.</li>\n<li>Serve the ratatouille on the spaghetti, with the feta over the top.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 08:44:13','2022-10-19 19:08:20',NULL),(97,'zldjpb','Chicken Tikka Masala Naan Pizza','Easy pizza with a delicious Asian twist - spicy chicken, onion and green peppers, tempered with plain yoghurt and coriander, spread onto a delicious naan bread and served with chutney.','Gluten, lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Heat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.</li>\n<li>Toss the red onion with the red wine vinegar and a good pinch of salt and set aside (the vinegar will soften the onion slightly).</li>\n<li>Meanwhile, heat some oil in a pan and add the chicken, peppers and curry paste, and fry over a high heat for 5 minutes and then turn the heat to low and let it continue to cook the moisture off a bit.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>While that is cooking, put the naan breads on a baking tray, sprinkle with a little water, then put in the oven for 2 mins to heat up.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Chop the coriander.</li>\n<li>Take the naans out of the oven, spread each one with crushed garlic, yogurt and then top with the chicken, red onion, coriander and chutney. Serve immediately.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 08:56:27','2022-11-30 10:41:48',NULL),(98,'mcmvlz','Halloumi Tikka Masala Naan Pizza','Easy pizza with a delicious Asian twist - spicy halloumi, onion and green peppers, tempered with plain yoghurt and coriander, spread onto a delicious naan bread and served with chutney.','Gluten, lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Heat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Toss the red onion with the red wine vinegar and a good pinch of salt and set aside (the vinegar will soften the onion slightly, and give it a lovely flavour).</li>\n<li>Meanwhile heat some oil in a pan. Add the halloumi&nbsp; and peppers to the pan with the curry paste, toss together, then fry over a high heat for 5 minutes. Stir frequently. Add a bit more oil if you need to.</li>\n<li>While that is cooking, put the naan breads on a baking tray, sprinkle with a little water, then put in the oven for 2 minutes to heat up.</li>\n<li>Chop the fresh coriander.</li>\n<li>Take the naans out of the oven, spread each one with crushed garlic, the yogurt and then top with the halloumi, red onion, coriander and chutney. Cut each one in half to make one serving.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 09:47:20','2022-03-30 12:23:23',NULL),(99,'uvoyct','Chicken in Lemon & Dill Cream Sauce','Chicken, lemon, honey, cream and fresh dill come together in a grand symphony of flavour, so good you will want to lick the pan. Serve these baked chicken thighs with their delectable sauce over mashed potato with a side of green beans.','Traces of lactose',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.</li>\n<li>Chope the potatoes into small pieces. Put them on to boil in salted water and boil them until they are soft enough to mash, about 20 minutes.</li>\n<li>Mash the potatoes with salt, pepper and a little milk. Do not make them too soft because the sauce of the chicken is fairly runny and needs to soak into the potato. Keep the potato warm.</li>\n<li>Steam the beans or boil in salted water for 10 minutes. Keep warm.</li>\n<li>Season the chicken with salt, pepper, and the Garlicky Herbs. Heat the butter and a little oil in a large pan and when melted add the honey and stir together. Add the chicken to the pan and cook for 2 to 3 minutes on each side. Take the chicken out and place in an oven proof dish.</li>\n<li>Make the chicken stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Using the juices in the pan, fry the garlic for 1 minute. Then add the stock with the cream, lemon juice and half the fresh dill. Stir over a medium heat for 5 minutes, and then pour over the chicken.</li>\n<li>Bake the chicken and sauce for 30 minutes in the oven.</li>\n<li>Serve on the mashed potato, garnished with the remaining fresh dill, with a side of green beans.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 09:58:11','2022-10-04 10:10:10',NULL),(100,'tyqbyi','Tomato and Meatball Soup','Did you know that cooking tomatoes makes them healthier than eating them raw? The cooking process releases lycopene which is a powerful antioxidant protecting our cells from damage.\nThis soup boasts plenty of tomatoes, green peppers and spinach to boost your health. Add juicy, plump meatballs and couscous and you have a very satisfying and tasty dish.','Gluten',10,35,'<ol>\n<li>Mix all meatball ingredients in a bowl - the beef mince, onion powder, garlic powder, cheddar cheese and the beaten egg.</li>\n<li>If you are cooking for 1 or 2 people, then beat the egg and add slowly. Once mixture starts to get too sloppy, discard the rest of the egg.</li>\n<li>Shape into small balls and fry until cooked through in olive oil. About 5 minutes per batch. Set aside.</li>\n<li>Make the chicken stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of water specified on the package. Set aside.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a big pot and fry the onion and peppers for 5 minutes. Add the garlic and chilli flakes and fry for another 1 minute.</li>\n<li>Add the tomatoes, stock and couscous and bring to a simmer. Simmer for 10 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the meatballs, spinach, balsamic vinegar and one&nbsp; teaspoon of sugar per person you are cooking for (ie 4 teaspoons for 4 people) and simmer for a further 5 minutes, seasoning with salt and pepper to taste.</li>\n<li>Chop the fresh basil.</li>\n<li>Stir the chopped basil through the soup and serve with grated parmesan on top.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 10:08:45','2022-03-31 12:14:17',NULL),(101,'mysrsn','Gnocchi with Roasted Butternut, Mushrooms & Ricotta','Gnocchi is so often paired with a tomato sauce and mozzarella or cheddar. Here we go off the beaten path a bit by pairing it with butternut and mushrooms roasted with garlic and olive oil and then tossed with the gnocchi, baby spinach or rocket and a goodly portion of chopped ricotta.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Heat oven to 200 degrees C.</li>\n<li>Put the butternut and the mushrooms into an oven dish. Add a dash of oil, garlic, salt and black pepper and toss together.</li>\n<li>Don\'t wait for the oven to finish heating - pop the butternut and mushrooms in and roast for 40 to 45 minutes - the butternut should be soft.</li>\n<li>While the veg is roasting, bring a big pot of salted water to the boil. Add the gnocchi. When they float to the top they are ready - this should take 2 - 3 minutes.</li>\n<li>Take the gnocchi off the heat and drain.</li>\n<li>Roughly chop the rocket.</li>\n<li>Stir the rocket and the ricotta into the gnocchi while it is still hot, allowing the spinach or rocket to wilt.</li>\n<li>When the veg is roasted, add to the gnocchi mix and toss well.</li>\n<li>Taste and add salt and black pepper accordingly.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 10:30:14','2022-08-25 11:49:42',NULL),(102,'hecfyq','Vegetarian Bobotie with Rice','The old Cape Malay favourite gets a  healthy make-over.  We lose the gluten but not the taste - you still get the mild curry flavour with high notes of fruit and spice, just like grandma used to make. Instead of using beef mince we use lentils.','Lactose',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat the oven to 190 degrees C.</li>\n<li>Put the rice on to cook. Place rice in a pot, add salt and cover with water. Bring to the boil. Time 20 minutes from the boiling point and it should be done. Don&rsquo;t let the water run dry. Drain the rice and keep warm.</li>\n<li>Heat oil in a medium pot and saut&eacute; the onion for 2 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the garlic and the spice mix and stir fry for 1 minute.</li>\n<li>Add the lentils, grated carrot, raisins, salt and pepper and saut&eacute; for 2 minutes stirring frequently.</li>\n<li>Add the butter beans along with the chutney. Stir into the mixture.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Place the mixture into an oven dish.</li>\n<li>Beat together the milk, eggs, a big pinch of salt and nutmeg for the custard and pour over the top of the lentil mix in the oven dish. Tuck the bay leaves into the lentil mix through the custard.</li>\n<li>Bake uncovered for 35 minutes - the custard should be set.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 10:44:41','2021-10-21 12:33:38',NULL),(103,'gzvppj','Pork Sausage, Cherry Tomato and Rosemary Stovetop Casserole','This stovetop casserole is so simple to put together but deliciously tasty with its tomatoes, rosemary, mushrooms and butterbeans. Serve with sweet potato mashed with a little milk and seasoning for a satisfying family meal. There will definitely be squabbles over any leftovers!','None',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil and cook the sweet potato chunks for 20 minutes or until soft enough to mash. Roughly mash with a little milk or butter and salt and pepper to taste. Put aside and keep warm.</li>\n<li>While the sweet potatoes are cooking, heat oil in a big pot and fry the sausages for 10 minutes - they are now half-cooked.</li>\n<li>Remove the sausages and thickly slice. Set aside.</li>\n<li>To the same pot add the mushrooms, cherry tomatoes, chilli flakes, rosemary, salt and pepper to taste and cook for a few minutes while stirring.</li>\n<li>Add the sausages back to the pot with the butter beans, tomatoes, the balsamic vinegar and 1/4 teaspoon of sugar per person you are cooking for.</li>\n<li>Stir all together and simmer on low for 20 minutes.</li>\n<li>Serve the casserole on the mashed sweet potato.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 11:06:25','2023-01-16 13:17:20',NULL),(105,'nlvctd','Paprika Pork with Egg Noodles','Pork strips and mushrooms simmer in a smokey paprika sauce with a hint of tomato. Add sour cream and you have a fabulous way to dress a bowl of egg noodles. Simple to put together and really delicious.','Gluten & Lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Heat oil in a large pan, tip in the onions and cook for 5 minutes until soft and golden. Add the pork and mushrooms and cook on a high heat for 3-4 minutes until browned. Turn down the heat a little. Add the paprika and cook for 1 minute more.</li>\n<li>Stir in the tomato paste.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Dissolve the chicken stock in the amount of water stipulated on the label and then pour the stock into the pan and simmer for 8 minutes or until the pork is cooked through.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>While the pork is simmering, cook the egg noodles. Bring a pot of salted water to the boil with a dash of oil and boil the noodles for 3 minutes. Test one to see if cooked otherwise add another couple of minutes. Drain and set aside</li>\n<li>Remove the pork from the heat and mix in the sour cream and some salt and pepper.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Serve the pork on the egg noodles.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 11:34:33','2022-03-29 14:13:42',NULL),(106,'sgqwog','Easy One Pan French Onion Chicken','This dish does not take long to put together but gives the impression you spent hours in the kitchen. The chicken and sauce features green beans for a pop of colour and onion, thyme, Worcestershire sauce and Parmesan cheese to give it a  wonderful flavour. Served on oven roasted pumpkin.','None',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 180 C. Place your pumpkin or butternut in a baking dish, drizzle with oil and season with salt and pepper. When the oven is ready, pop it in.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken. Cook, turning, for 10 minutes or until chicken is cooked through. Transfer to an ovenproof baking dish.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Make up your stock by adding the powder to the specified amount of boiling water.</li>\n<li>Melt butter in the same pan over medium-high heat. Add onion and thyme. Cook, stirring, for 10 minutes or until golden brown. Add the green beans and cook for another 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Stir in the flour and mix well. Add the stock and Worcestershire sauce to the pan. Simmer, uncovered, stirring, for a few minutes until the sauce thickens. Season to taste.</li>\n<li>Top the chicken with the onion mixture in the baking dish. Sprinkle the cheese over the top. Place in the oven until the cheese is melted and golden, about 15 minutes.</li>\n<li>Chop the parsley. When you remove the chicken from the oven, garnish with the fresh parsley and serve with the roasted pumpkin.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 11:49:10','2022-10-10 11:05:33',NULL),(107,'rptkvf','Cheesy Beef Quesadillas','Learn to make your own quesadilla, a Tex-Mex restaurant favourite. Layer an easily made Mexican mince with black beans and grated cheddar on tortillas, fold them and dry-fry them until the cheese is nice and gooey. Cut them into wedges and serve with lime and sour cream.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>In a large pan over medium-high heat, heat oil and add the onion. Cook until soft, about 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the beef mince and brown, breaking up with a wooden spoon. Season with salt and pepper.</li>\n<li>Chop the fresh coriander.</li>\n<li>Add the garlic, paprika and cumin, tomato paste and black beans; cook on medium-low for 5 minutes. If mixture is too dry while cooking add a little water. Turn off heat and mix in coriander. If you only have 1 pan, then remove the mince and use the pan for the tortillas.</li>\n<li>Warm a large non-stick pan over medium heat - you do not need to add any oil if your pan is non-stick. Place a flour tortilla in the dry pan and sprinkle half with cheese, beef mixture and more cheese - be careful not to put too much on the tortilla else it will be difficult to fold. Fold the tortilla over and fry lightly on both sides until the cheese is melted. Repeat with remaining tortillas.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Cut into wedges and serve with lime wedges and sour cream.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 12:17:36','2022-03-31 12:09:23',NULL),(108,'zzymhu','Vegetable Cottage Pie','No need for the vegetarians to forego a good Cottage Pie - here we use a delicious mixture of brinjal, sun-dried tomatoes, garlic, oregano and spinach cooked in a cheesy sauce and then topped with the traditional mash and extra melty cheese for good measure.','Lactose and Gluten',5,40,'<div>Heat oven to 200 degrees C<br>Cut the potatoes into chunks - we like to leave the skin on for extra nutrition. Bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Put the potatoes into the boiling water and cook for 20 minutes or until the potatoes are soft enough to mash.&nbsp; Mash them with the butter, half the oregano, salt, pepper and a little milk so it is soft enough to spread on your cottage pie.<br>While the potatoes are boiling, heat oil in a large pot and cook the aubergine over a high heat for 4 to 5 minutes, adding extra oil as you need to. Add the garlic and sun-dried tomatoes and the other half of the oregano and cook for 1 minute, stirring. Stir in the spinach, turn the heat down, cover the pot and leave the spinach to wilt for 1 minute.<br>Add the flour to the aubergine mix and stir through. Pour in the milk and stir while the sauce thickens and comes to a simmer. Let it cook for 2 minutes, stirring and then add two thirds of the cheese and stir until it has melted. Take off the heat.<br>Place the aubergine mix into an oven dish. Layer the mash on top and sprinkle with the remaining cheese. Bake for 15 minutes or until golden.<br><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 12:19:12','2021-02-15 08:14:13',NULL),(109,'rpqllc','Vegetarian Thai Green Curry','A green curry is the mildest of the Thai curries but could easily be the tastiest, using their green curry paste, lime, coriander and coconut milk. This vegetarian version boasts shallots or spring onions, butternut, red pepper, sugar snap peas and baby corn. Served with rice and a drizzle of lime juice, it is sure to please!','None',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Place rice and salt into a pot of water. Bring to the boil and time 20 minutes from boiling point. Drain and keep warm.</li>\n<li>While the rice is cooking, heat some oil in a big pot and fry the spring onions with a large pinch of salt for 8 minutes, using a medium heat. They should be golden brown.</li>\n<li>Add the red pepper strips and fry for a few minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the curry paste and chilli flakes and fry for 2 minutes, stirring.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add the butternut cubes and stir through.</li>\n<li>Add your coconut milk with the amount of water written on the label of the coconut milk.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Using the fine side of a grater, grate a pinch of lime zest off the lime. Add the lime zest, cover the pot and cook for 20 minutes or until the butternut is soft.</li>\n<li>Add the sugar snap peas and the baby corn, stir into the mixture, cover the pot and cook for a further 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Chop the coriander.</li>\n<li>Taste the curry for seasoning, adding salt if you want to and then stir in half the coriander.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Serve with rice, sprinkle with the remaining coriander and serve with the lime wedges to squeeze over the top.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 12:29:29','2023-04-24 12:26:30',NULL),(110,'pofzil','Paprika Soya with Egg Noodles','Soya and mushrooms simmer in a smoky paprika sauce with a hint of tomato. Add sour cream and you have a fabulous way to dress a bowl of egg noodles. Simple to put together and really delicious.','Gluten & Lactose',5,35,'<ol><li>Soak the soya in boiling water for 10 minutes, the same volume of water as you have of soya.</li><li>Make up your stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li><li>Heat some oil in a large pan, tip in the onions and cook for 5 minutes until soft and golden. Add the soya mince and mushrooms and cook on a high heat for 3-4 minutes. Add the paprika and cook for 1 minute more.</li><li>Stir in the tomato paste, then pour on the stock and simmer for 8 minutes.&nbsp;</li><li>While the soya mince is simmering, cook the egg noodles. Bring a pot of salted water to the boil with a dash of oil and boil the noodles for 3 minutes. Drain and set aside.</li><li>Remove the soya mince from the heat and mix in the soured cream and some salt and pepper to taste.</li><li>Serve the soya mixture on the egg noodles.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 12:42:24','2021-05-21 14:42:05',NULL),(111,'xjzmqw','Mushroom Bourguignon','Based on the classic French recipe but simplified for our busy lives, Mushroom Bourguignon is a hearty vegetarian stew with loads of mushroom, baby onions, carrots and fresh thyme. We have replaced the usual red wine with some balsamic vinegar and extra vegetable stock.','None',5,45,'<ol><li>In a large pot place the rice and some salt and cover with hot water. Bring to the boil and simmer, timing 45 minutes from when you put the pot on the stove. Drain and keep warm.</li><li>Make up your stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li><li>While the rice is cooking, heat some oil in a big pot and add the mushrooms, baby carrots and baby onions. Put the lid on and sweat them for 10 minutes, stirring frequently. In the last 2 minutes add the garlic and stir.</li><li>Add the balsamic vinegar, the stock, the tomato paste, the thyme, the bay leaves and a good grinding of black pepper. Stir together well.</li><li>Simmer with the lid on for 40 minutes. Check the seasoning and serve on the brown rice.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 12:48:05','2020-12-30 14:02:12',NULL),(112,'jruioi','Cheesy Black Bean Quesadillas','Learn to make your own quesadilla,  vegetarian style. Layer Mexican spiced black beans and grated cheddar on tortillas, fold them and dry-fry them until the cheese is nice and gooey. Cut them into wedges and serve with lime and sour cream.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>In a pot over medium-high heat, heat some oil and add the onion. Cook until soft, 5 - 8 minutes.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add the garlic, paprika and cumin, tomato paste and black beans. Cook on medium-low for 5 minutes. Chop the fresh coriander. Turn off heat and mix in coriander. Taste for seasoning and add salt and black pepper if necessary.</li>\n<li>Warm a large non-stick pan over medium heat - you do not need to add any oil unless your pan is not non-stick. Place a tortilla in the dry pan and sprinkle half with cheese, bean mixture and more cheese - be careful not to put too much on the tortilla or it will be difficult to fold. Fold the tortilla over and fry lightly on both sides until the cheese is melted. Repeat with remaining tortillas.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Cut into wedges and serve with lime wedges and sour cream.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 13:02:10','2022-02-24 10:15:11',NULL),(113,'uaquzn','Baked Tomato, Bacon, Spinach and Mozzarella Gnocchi','Gnocchi always makes for satisfying comfort food, but here we add plenty of tomato, spinach, garlic & cheese for a healthy dose of nutrients and fabulous flavour. For the meat-lovers, you can look forward to the addition of bacon in this comforting dish.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat the oven to 220 degrees C.</li>\n<li>Bring a large saucepan of salted water to the boil and cook the gnocchi for 2 &ndash; 3 minutes, or until they float to the surface. Drain and tip into an oven-proof baking dish. Mix in a bit of oil to keep it moist. &nbsp;</li>\n<li>Heat some more oil in the now empty saucepan and gently fry the bacon, garlic and chilli flakes (if using). Add the tomato passata and spinach and heat through, seasoning to taste with salt and pepper.<br />Add the tomato passata and spinach&nbsp; mix to the baking dish with the gnocchi in, and stir everything together. Scatter with the grated mozzarella and bake for 15 minutes until the cheese is melted and is bubbling.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 13:37:22','2022-07-09 17:09:14',NULL),(114,'gdqruu','Chicken and Broccoli Cheese Bake','This is a classic combination, creamy and delicious. We take all the hard work out of it for you, leaving you to assemble the dish and have it on the table in 35 minutes tops!','Gluten, lactose',5,30,'<ol>\n<li>Heat your oven to 180 degrees C.</li>\n<li>Pan-fry your chicken cubes in a little oil for 10 minutes, turning frequently.</li>\n<li>Place the chicken in an oven-proof baking dish. Sprinkle the chicken spice, the garlic and salt and pepper over the top of the chicken.</li>\n<li>Add the chopped broccoli on top of the chicken.</li>\n<li>Warm the cheese sauce slightly until spreadable and spread over the top of the broccoli. Sprinkle the mozzarella over the top.</li>\n<li>Place in the oven and bake for 25 minutes.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 13:53:39','2022-07-09 18:22:33','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">BASIC BECHAMEL SAUCE WITH CHEESE</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You will need:</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">60 grams butter</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">50 ml flour</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 cups full cream milk</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">100 grams of cheddar grated</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tsp salt or to taste (start with half)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">pinch of nutmeg</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Instructions:</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Melt the butter and stir in the flour with a wooden spoon until a smooth paste forms. Stir while this cooks for a minute.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add the milk in four dollops, stirring out lumps in between each addition. Keep a whisk on hand for beating smooth if necessary. Let the sauce come to a simmer and simmer for about 4 minutes while it thickens. Make sure to stir constantly to avoid lumps. Add salt and nutmeg. When sauce is the right consistency, take off the heat and stir in the cheese.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This makes 500ml cheese sauce.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(115,'euhunq','Meatballs in a Spicy Tomato Sauce served on Rice Pilaf','Meatballs in tomato sauce is a universal comfort food. We use a combination of beef and pork mince to make our meatballs extra juicy. Take it up a notch with a touch of spice and serve it on a delicious pilaf with onions, garlic, mushrooms and red pepper.','None',10,45,'<ol>\n<li>Place the pork, beef and chutney in a large bowl. Season with salt. Mix well with your hands until thoroughly combined. With your hands gently form meatballs with the mince mixture. The key is to not make the balls too &ldquo;tight&rdquo; otherwise they dry out when cooking.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a large, shallow saucepan or saut&eacute; pan over a medium heat. Add the meatballs and fry gently for about 8 minutes or until browned all over, turning carefully. Sprinkle the chilli flakes (if using) over them and fry for a further 2 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add a little more oil if you need to.</li>\n<li>Add the tomatoes. Simmer for about 10 minutes. Chop the basil and then add the basil and cook for a further 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.</li>\n<li>Taste the sauce to see if it needs a bit of salt or a pinch of sugar.</li>\n<li>While the meat balls are simmering, make the pilaf.</li>\n<li>First make up your stock by dissolving the powder in the specified amount of boiling water.</li>\n<li>Melt butter in a large pot over medium heat. Cook and stir onion, red pepper, mushrooms, and garlic until tender, about 10 minutes.</li>\n<li>Stir in rice and fry for a minute.&nbsp; Add chicken stock. Cover and boil until liquid is absorbed and rice is soft,&nbsp; 20 -25 minutes. Season with salt and black pepper.<br />Serve the meatballs and sauce on the pilaf.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 14:04:49','2023-01-23 09:26:26',NULL),(117,'mmuzog','Creamy Courgette Pasta Bake','Cream cheese and our own special marinara sauce make this pasta bake delectably more-ish! It is also packed with veggie goodness so you know you are taking care of your health while you indulge yourself. Note: the salad in the pic is not included in the kit.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 200 C.</li>\n<li>Chop the ends off the courgettes and grate&nbsp; into a bowl (the reason we didn\'t do this for you is we don\'t want the courgettes going off before you get to the meal!)</li>\n<li>In a pot, heat some oil and saut&eacute; onion for about 5 minutes. Add the garlic and stir. Add the courgettes and cook for a few minutes while stirring.</li>\n<li>Stir in 2/3 of the cream cheese and 2/3 of the grated cheddar. Combine well. Season with salt and black pepper to taste.</li>\n<li>In a dish, layer half the courgette mix, then put down half the lasagne sheets, then a layer of half the marinara sauce. Repeat with the rest of the courgette mix, the rest of the lasagne sheets and the rest of the marinara sauce.</li>\n<li>Blob the rest of the cream cheese on top, and sprinkle with the rest of the cheddar.</li>\n<li>Bake in the oven for 10 &ndash; 15 minutes. While still hot, use the back of a spoon to spread the cream cheese over the top.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 14:35:07','2023-01-16 12:58:11','<p>Marinara sauce</p>\n<p><br />1 onion, finely chopped<br />1 tsp crushed garlic<br />a little oil<br />2 tbsp tomato paste (1 sachet)<br />2 tbsp balsamic vinegar&nbsp;<br />1 tin crushed tomato<br />1 tsp dried basil<br />1 tsp dried oregano&nbsp;<br />&frac12; tsp salt<br />Pepper, to taste</p>\n<p>Fry the onions in the oil until soft.<br />Add tomato paste, garlic, vinegar, crushed tomato and bring to a boil.<br />Add the herbs, salt and pepper.<br />Let it simmer on low for 20 minutes plus.</p>'),(118,'ozjucf','Khatta Meetha Baingan (Sweet & Sour Eggplant Curry)','Khatta Meetha Baingan is a North Indian eggplant curry. Khatta means sour and Meetha means sweet and the sweet and sour flavours along with the curry spices and tomato base make a wonderful combination. Round off the meal with rotis, or leave them out for a low carb meal. The rotis are included in the kit.','Gluten (rotis)',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Heat oil in a large pot and add the curry leaves and cumin seeds. Stir until the seeds splutter and then add the minced ginger and chilli flakes. Fry for a minute while stirring. It should be light brown.</li>\n<li>Then add the spice mix and stir together before adding the vinegar, 3/4 of a teaspoon of sugar per person you are cooking for, chopped tomatoes and tomato puree. Stir well together and cook for 1 minute.</li>\n<li>Add the eggplant and 1/2 teaspoon of salt per person you are cooking for and cook until tender.</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Chop the fresh coriander and stir half of it into the pot before taking off the heat.</li>\n<li>Sprinkle the remaining fresh coriander on top and serve with roti.<br />If you prefer to have a low carb meal, leave out the roti.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-25 14:50:34','2022-11-22 15:33:50',NULL),(119,'ayvizg','Cajun Sausage and Vegetable Bake','This good looking dish is almost too simple to be true. Easy to put together, it boasts a wonderful Cajun flavor and a healthy nutrient boost from all the colourful veggies.','None',5,45,'<div>Preheat the oven to 200 degrees C and lightly grease a large grill pan.</div>\n<div>In a frying pan, heat a little oil and cook the sausages for 20 minutes. Put aside to cool before cutting into rounds.</div>\n<div>While the sausages are cooking parboil or steam the sweet potato cubes for 10 minutes to soften them.</div>\n<div>In a large bowl combine the chopped vegetables, the sweet potato and the sausage rounds with the Cajun spice and a dash of oil - just enough to coat everything. Mix thoroughly so that the spice and oil coats everything.</div>\n<div>Place in the grill pan and roast for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-26 06:34:26','2022-03-19 13:27:49',NULL),(120,'rcosmn','Stir-fried Beef with Egg Noodles','Bring a touch of the East to your table with our marinated beef strips stir-fried with lots of colourful veg and Chinese egg noodles. Serve with a drizzle of soy sauce for a healthy, satisfying and tasty meal.','Gluten',30,15,'<div>In a Tupperware, mix together the beef strips and the marinade and refrigerate for 30 minutes.</div>\n<div>When the beef has been in the fridge for 20 minutes, bring a pot of water to the boil. Add the egg noodles and boil for 4 minutes. Drain and rinse under cold water. Add a drizzle of oil to the noodles to prevent them from sticking to each other.</div>\n<div>Heat some oil in a non-stick pan or wok until very hot. Add the ginger and all the veggies and fry for a few minutes. Remove from the pan and place in a dish with a lid so that they can keep warm.</div>\n<div>Remove the beef from the marinade (keep the marinade) and use the same pan as you cooked the veggies in to brown the meat on all sides. This should only take five minutes. Add the marinade that the beef was in.</div>\n<div>Add the egg noodles to the pan with the meat and stir to heat through.</div>\n<div>Serve some veggies into each person&rsquo;s bowl and top with the meat and noodles. Add a little extra soy sauce if desired.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-26 06:45:00','2022-01-11 15:45:09',NULL),(121,'rfydpw','Summer Chicken and Rice','Easy to cook and bursting with flavor, this creamy chicken with fresh rosemary and tomato is served on rice with wilted spinach. The taste combination is so good that even the spinach-haters will not complain about eating Popeye’s secret strength potion.','Gluten',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Place the rice and some salt in a pot and cover well with water. Place on the stove and bring to a boil. Once boiling take the lid off and boil for 20 minutes. Keep an eye on the water level. When the rice is cooked take it off the stove and drain it. Add the spinach and allow the heat from the rice to wilt it while you stir it in. Add the lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste. Keep warm.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a large pot over medium-high heat. Sprinkle chicken with a little salt and pepper. Add chicken to pot. Cook, without stirring, until chicken begins to brown, about 4 minutes. Add tomatoes, onion, garlic, and rosemary. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is tender and tomatoes begin to soften, about 3 minutes.</li>\n<li>Make up the stock by adding the specified amount of boiling water to the stock powder.</li>\n<li>Add the flour to the pot stirring all the time to avoid lumps and cook for 1 minute. Add the chicken stock, stirring and scraping browned bits off the bottom of the pot. Bring to a boil and cook, stirring often, until sauce thickens, 3 to 4 minutes. If you think your sauce is too thick add a little hot water.</li>\n<li>On each plate serve some rice and spinach, topped with the creamy chicken.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-26 07:07:48','2021-09-17 15:25:09',NULL),(123,'qiqbop','Chana Masala','In Indian cuisine chana means “chickpeas” and masala means “spices” so, along with onion, tomato, ginger, garlic and cilantro, we have a hearty chickpea curry which both vegetarians and non-vegetarians will love. Served with rice and garnished with fresh coriander.','None',5,25,'<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<ol>\n<li>Heat olive oil in a large pot and fry the bay leaves for half a minute.</li>\n<li>Pour the masala paste into the pot and cook for 3 minutes or until it turns a golden brown.</li>\n<li>Season with the spice mix and salt to taste. Cook and stir on a high heat for 3 minutes.</li>\n<li>Stir in enough water to make a thick gravy, bring to the boil and add the chickpeas. Cook for 5 to 7 minutes to heat the chickpeas right through.</li>\n<li>Chop your fresh coriander.</li>\n<li>Serve with rice, garnished with the fresh coriander.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-26 07:48:17','2021-11-02 11:27:51',NULL),(124,'xhezcz','Summer Vegetable Tostadas','A Mexican tostada is a crisped-up tortilla that is normally spread with spicy refried beans and then heaped with all sorts of toppings and grated cheese. Fun to make and fun to eat, our tostadas take advantage of our colourful summer veggies to pack a healthy punch of micronutrients.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',10,35,'<div>Heat the oven to 200 C.<br />Place the tortillas on one or two greased or lined baking sheets.<br />Rub some oil over each side of the tortilla and season with salt.&nbsp;<br />Bake for 5 minutes, flip them over and bake for another 5. They should be crispy. Remove from the oven and allow to cool. Keep the oven on.</div>\n<div>Heat some oil in a pan and add the onions and a pinch of salt. Cook the onions for 3 minutes and then add the garlic, baby marrow, red pepper, corn, cumin, paprika, and salt and black pepper to taste.<br />Cook all of this for 8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until tender.</div>\n<div>Pop your beans in a microwave-safe bowl with a drop of oil and heat for 1 minute. Smoosh them with a fork.</div>\n<div>Spread each baked tortilla (now called a tostada!) with some of the smooshed black beans, some of the vegetable mix and a bit of grated cheese. Place back on the baking sheet and bake for five minutes until beans are heated through and cheese is melted.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-26 08:01:21','2022-01-20 15:38:48',NULL),(125,'cwytuz','Sweet and sour pork kebabs with apple pecan slaw','Have fun skewering these colourful kebabs. Pair them with a slaw made with ready-shredded cabbage, apple, pecans and our homemade tangy sauce.','Nuts, Lactose',10,35,'<div>Heat the oven to 180 C.</div><div>Place the pork in a dish and pour the marinade over it. Place in the fridge for 20 minutes.<br>While you are waiting for the pork to marinate, make the slaw:&nbsp;<br>Cut your apple into thin strips. Mix the apple with the cabbage, tangy mayo dressing and pecan nuts. Let it sit to allow the flavours to develop.&nbsp;</div><div>Once the pork has marinated for 20 minutes, thread your skewers: alternate a piece of pork with the pineapple, red pepper and onion.<br>Once all your skewers are threaded, place them on a baking sheet lined with baking paper, drizzle with any remaining marinade, and bake for 10 – 14 minutes, turning over once.</div><div>Serve one or two pork kebabs with a side of slaw.</div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-26 08:13:56','2021-04-21 13:25:10',NULL),(126,'szedxd','Honey and Mustard Chicken Curry','Creamy and mildly spicy, this chicken curry packs everything you need into one pot - lots of veg for your health, baby potatoes for heartiness and, of course, the all-time favourite honey and mustard flavour.','Lactose',5,40,'<div>Heat the oil over a medium heat in a pot. Saut&eacute; the onions and green pepper for about five minutes.</div>\n<div>Add the chicken and brown.</div>\n<div>Add the curry powder, turmeric, honey, mustard, sugar, green beans, and carrots.</div>\n<div>Season with salt and pepper.</div>\n<div>Halve or quarter the baby potatoes (depending on the size). Add these and the evaporated milk. Cover with a lid and cook over a low heat for 20 &ndash; 30 minutes until the potatoes are tender.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Serve in bowls.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-26 08:28:20','2022-10-24 10:54:14',NULL),(127,'kraemo','Moroccan Mushrooms and Couscous','The Moroccans love to mix spices and sweetness into their savoury dishes and this mushroom dish is no exception. Cumin and cinnamon blend wonderfully with the honey and dried apricots giving the chickpea, couscous and mushroom mix a delightful Middle Eastern flavour.','Gluten',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>In a pot, heat some oil over a medium heat. Add the onion and soften for about five minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the cinnamon and cumin and stir for 1 minute.</li>\n<li>Add the mushrooms and cook for 2 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the tomatoes, chickpeas and honey and simmer on low for about 10 minutes.</li>\n<li>While that is simmering, put the couscous, apricots and a sprinkle of salt and pepper in a bowl.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Pour boiling water over the couscous mix. Use 1/4 cup boiling water per person you are cooking for i.e. 1 cup for 4 people. Stir with a fork to combine. Cover with a cloth while your mushroom mix is simmering.</li>\n<li>Add the couscous mixture to the pot and stir to combine.</li>\n<li>Chop the parsley.</li>\n<li>Serve in bowls with some fresh parsley sprinkled over the top.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-26 08:38:31','2021-11-02 11:44:47',NULL),(128,'lhijgh','Sweet & Sour Halloumi Kebabs with Apple Pecan Slaw','Enjoy threading your own skewers or, better still, let the family get involved. The dried apricot, mushroom, cherry tomato, pepper and halloumi make for a colourful and nutritious kebab which pairs beautifully with the apple and pecan slaw.','Traces of Lactose',15,15,'<ol>\n<li>Heat oven to 200 degrees C.</li>\n<li>Soak the skewers in water until you need them. This stops them from burning.</li>\n<li>Tip the marinade into a bowl and add all the skewer ingredients - gently stir and allow to stand for 10 minutes.</li>\n<li>Make your slaw by chopping the apple into tiny pieces and mixing with the cabbage and pecan nuts. Add the dressing and allow to stand at room temperature.</li>\n<li>Thread your kebabs - be careful with the halloumi but don&rsquo;t worry about small cracks or splits. Alternate bits of halloumi, mushroom, cherry tomatoes, red pepper and dried apricots. If your cherry tomatoes are a bit big for the skewer you can halve them.</li>\n<li>Place the kebabs in a shallow oven dish or oven tray with a rim.</li>\n<li>Pour half the marinade over the top, turn the skewers and pour the rest onto them.</li>\n<li>When the oven has heated, place kebabs in the oven for 20 minutes. Turn them carefully halfway through the cooking time.</li>\n<li>The cheese should look golden brown and crispy. If not turn your grill on and give them a few minutes under there.</li>\n<li>Serve the kebabs with a side of slaw.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-26 08:51:49','2022-06-16 15:39:39','<p>Tangy Mayo Dressing</p>\n<p>125 ml cream or sour cream</p>\n<p>125 ml mayonnaise</p>\n<p>60 ml white vinegar</p>\n<p>1 Tbsp sugar</p>\n<p>1/2 tsp salt</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Shake together in a jar until well mixed.</p>'),(130,'qqarb','Beef Goulash with Roasted Butternut and Green Beans','What could be heartier on a crisp evening than a Beef Goulash, a rich tomato-based stew originating from Hungary? Paired with butternut and green beans for glorious colour and, of course, your health.','None',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 180 C. Place your pumpkin in a baking dish, drizzle with some oil and season with salt and pepper. When the oven is ready, pop it in.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a large pot over a medium heat and saut&eacute; the onions until glossy, about 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the mustard powder and stir into the onions.</li>\n<li>Add the beef goulash and sprinkle with the flour. Sprinkle the stock powder over. Stir to brown the meat for a few minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the Goulash Mix and stir it in well. Add enough water to just cover the meat.</li>\n<li>Lower the heat and simmer for 15 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the mushrooms and oregano and season with salt and pepper. Stir and simmer for another 15 minutes.</li>\n<li>While the beef is simmering, take the pumpkin out of the oven and add the beans on top of it. Place back in the oven &ndash; they will be ready by the time the beef and mushrooms have simmered.</li>\n<li>Serve each person some pumpkin and beans with a serving of the beef goulash.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-27 06:21:23','2021-08-16 11:43:23',NULL),(131,'layzna','Garlicky Pasta with Spinach and Pulled Pork','Simple to put together, this pasta dish features Gemelli pasta, spinach, loads of garlic and Parmesan cheese. The pulled pork is ready made for you to just simply toss in and enjoy.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Bring a big pot of salted water to the boil. Put in a dash of oil and the pasta. Boil for 12 minutes and drain. Reserve 1/2 cup pasta cooking water when draining your pasta.</li>\n<li>While the pasta is cooking, heat a generous amount of oil on a medium-high heat in another big pot and fry the garlic, stirring, for 1 minute, no more.</li>\n<li>Add the spinach, peas and pulled pork and cover the pot. Cook for 3 minutes.</li>\n<li>Stir in the pasta and the grated parmesan and enough of the reserved pasta water to loosen the mixture. Season to taste with salt and black pepper.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-27 06:35:56','2022-11-15 10:20:03','<p><strong>Pulled Pork in BBQ Sauce</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>10 ml olive oil</p>\n<p>1 tsp crushed garlic</p>\n<p>3 Tbsp onion flakes or 1 Tbsp onion powder</p>\n<p>125 ml apple cider vinegar</p>\n<p>125 ml tomato sauce</p>\n<p>125 ml water</p>\n<p>125 ml sugar</p>\n<p>2 Tbsp mustard</p>\n<p>1 Tbsp Worcestershire Sauce</p>\n<p>2 tsp chilli powder</p>\n<p>2 Tbsp cornstarch mixed with 2 Tbsp water</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Heat oil and fry the garlic for 1 minute before adding all the other ingredients. Let the sauce cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.</p>\n<p>Slow cook your pork in the above.</p>\n<p>Remember if the bone is in then 2,5 raw pork shoulder equals 1.2 kg pulled pork.</p>'),(132,'ldoqxe','Simple Sweet & Spicy Chicken Wraps','A healthy, easy-to-make version of the takeaway wrap that everyone loves. You can even let the family join in the wrapping!','Gluten',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Turn the oven on to 100 C. Wrap the wraps in the foil and place in the oven to warm. Alternatively, leave the foil off and warm for a few seconds in the microwave when you need them.</li>\n<li>Mix together the mayonnaise, cucumber, half of the honey, half of the cayenne pepper, and black pepper in a bowl until smooth.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a pan on medium-high heat, and cook and stir the chicken breast strips until they are beginning to turn golden and are no longer pink in the middle, about 8 minutes. Stir in the salsa, the other half of the honey, and the other half of the cayenne pepper. Reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the flavours have blended, about 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Remove the wraps from the oven or heat in the microwave. Spread each wrap with some of the mayonnaise-cucumber mixture, top with a layer of baby spinach leaves/mixed lettuce, and arrange some of the chicken salsa on the leaves.</li>\n<li>Fold the bottom of each wrap up from the bottom, and start rolling the wrap from the right side. When the wrap is half-rolled, fold the top of the wrap down, enclosing the filling, and continue rolling to make a tight, compact cylinder.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-27 07:13:38','2023-01-23 09:23:06',NULL),(133,'sxjwuv','Garlicky Pasta with Spinach and Halloumi','A rustic Italian dish which lets fresh garlic sautéed in plenty of olive oil and cubes of fried halloumi set the tone. Add spinach and peas for your greens and toss with parmesan and gemelli pasta to make a delectably healthy meal.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,25,'<ol><li>Bring a large pot of salted water to the boil, add a dash of oil and the pasta and boil for 12 minutes. Drain the pasta &amp; reserve half a cup of pasta water.</li><li>While the pasta is cooking, heat some oil in a frying pan and fry the halloumi cubes. They are best fried quickly on a high heat, turning frequently. They should be nicely browned on the outside. This should only take 4 to 5 minutes, or even less. Put the fried halloumi cubes to one side, keeping warm if possible.</li><li>Heat the Olive Oil &amp; Garlic Mix in a big pot. Add the spinach and peas, cover the pot and cook for 3 minutes.&nbsp;</li><li>Stir in the cooked pasta and parmesan. If the mixture is too dry add a little of the pasta water to give it a nice consistency. Season with salt and pepper to taste and then gently stir in the halloumi cubes, letting them heat through.</li><li>Serve immediately.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-27 07:38:07','2021-04-23 16:16:56',NULL),(134,'zfzbpo','Simple Sweet & Spicy Vegetable Wraps','Have fun making and rolling these easy-to-prepare vegetarian wraps. Who needs takeaways when you can produce something so much nicer, and healthier?','Gluten',10,20,'<ol><li>Turn the oven on to 180 C.&nbsp;</li><li>Place aubergine and baby marrow into a baking dish.</li><li>In a bowl, mix together the salsa, a little salt and pepper, half of the honey, and half of the cayenne pepper. Pour this over the aubergine and marrow and place in the oven to cook – it should take about 20 minutes for the veggies to be softened and cooked through.&nbsp;</li><li>When the aubergine and marrow have about 5 minutes left in the oven, wrap the wraps in the foil and place in the oven to warm.</li><li>Chop the cucumber into small cubes.&nbsp;</li><li>Mix together the mayonnaise, cucumber, the other half of the honey, the other half of the cayenne pepper, and black pepper in a bowl.&nbsp;</li><li>If you want your meal less spicy, add less cayenne pepper or leave it out.&nbsp;</li><li>Remove the wraps from the oven and remove from the foil. Spread each wrap with some of the mayonnaise-cucumber mixture, top with a layer of baby spinach/rocket, and arrange some of the aubergine, marrow and salsa mix on the leaves.</li><li>Fold the bottom of each wrap up from the bottom, and start rolling the wrap from the right side. When the wrap is half-rolled, fold the top of the wrap down, enclosing the filling, and continue rolling to make a tight, compact cylinder.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-27 07:57:47','2021-03-09 08:43:18',NULL),(135,'gonpuq','Creamy Pesto Chicken with Garlic Roasted Carrots','Get a good dose of beta carotene and potassium from Bugs Bunny’s favourite food, in the most delicious way possible. These garlic roasted carrots almost overshadow the chicken - but not quite. The secret is in the creamy sauce and the basil pesto!','Gluten, lactose',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 200 degrees C. Line a baking sheet with your baking paper.</li>\n<li>Chop the parsley.</li>\n<li>In a bowl mix one or two teaspoons of oil with half the garlic, two thirds of the parsley, salt &amp; pepper and herbs.&nbsp; Put carrot slices into the bowl and coat thoroughly with the mixture. Lay on the baking tray in an even layer.</li>\n<li>When the oven is the right temperature, bake the carrots for 25 minutes. Check on them after 15 - 20 minutes - they should be slightly caramelised, but not burnt. Take them out early if necessary.</li>\n<li>In a bowl rub salt, pepper and two-thirds of the basil pesto onto the chicken.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a big pot on a medium to high heat and fry the chicken pieces for ten minutes, turning them so they cook evenly.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Halve the cherry tomatoes.</li>\n<li>Remove chicken from the pot and add the tomatoes. Add the butter and let the tomatoes cook for a minute until just starting to soften.</li>\n<li>In a small bowl prepare the sauce ingredients, by mixing the other half of your garlic, the remaining basil pesto, salt and pepper to taste and evaporated milk until it is thoroughly combined. Put aside.</li>\n<li>Add the flour to the tomatoes in the pot and stir well so that the flour mixes with the tomatoes. Stir while cooking for a minute.</li>\n<li>Add the bowl of sauce ingredients and bring to a simmer - stir while the sauce thickens so that it does not catch on the bottom of the pot.</li>\n<li>Add the chicken back to the pot and let it cook for five minutes, stirring gently now and again.</li>\n<li>Remove from heat and garnish with parmesan and the remaining fresh parsley.</li>\n<li>Serve the chicken with some of the roasted carrots on the side.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-28 06:55:47','2022-09-05 14:27:57',NULL),(136,'hkubvh','Pork Chops in a Garlic Mushroom Sauce, with Roasted  Green Beans and Beetroot','A delicious garlicky mushroom sauce which is easy to cook turns these pork chops into something special. Serve them with beetroot and green beans roasted with herbs and balsamic vinegar for a lovely splash of colour.','Gluten',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>Put the oven on to 200 degrees C. &nbsp;</li>\n<li>Once the oven has heated, put the beetroot into a suitable oven dish, uncovered.</li>\n<li>Sprinkle with oil, the Italian herbs and balsamic vinegar, toss together, and roast for 30 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the green beans to the beetroot and keep roasting for another 10 mins.</li>\n<li>Season both sides of the pork chops with the paprika, salt and pepper. Melt about one third of your butter in a big pot on a medium to high heat and fry the chops 4 minutes per side. Take out of the pot and set aside.</li>\n<li>Make up your stock by mixing the stock powder with the specified amount of boiling water.</li>\n<li>Melt the rest of the butter in the same pot mixing with the juices already there. Add the sliced mushrooms and fry for 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the garlic and the mustard and fry for a further minute.</li>\n<li>Add the flour to the pan stirring well to avoid lumps. Slowly add the beef stock stirring or whisking until it is incorporated.</li>\n<li>Reduce heat and let this sauce simmer until it thickens, stirring often. It should take about 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Check for seasoning and add salt and black pepper to taste.</li>\n<li>Return the pork chops to the pan and cook until they are heated through.</li>\n<li>Serve with the roasted beetroot and green beans.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-28 07:35:09','2022-08-15 15:50:54','<p>Italian Seasoning</p>\n<p>2 tablespoons dried basil<br />2 tablespoons dried oregano<br />1 tablespoons dried rosemary<br />2 tablespoons dried parsley<br />1 tablespoon dried thyme<br />1 tablespoon red chili flakes<br />1 teaspoon garlic powder</p>\n<p><br />1. Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.<br />2. Pour into an air tight container and store in a cool dark place for up to 6 months.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(137,'lgoxtj','Butterbean and Mushroom Casserole','A hearty vegetarian casserole with mushrooms, red onions and spinach, a tasty thick sauce with mustard and sour cream, all pulled together with a crusty topping of butter beans mashed with olive oil and rosemary.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 180 C.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a pot. Fry the onions for 10 minutes until soft, then add the mushrooms and fry for another 5 minutes until golden.</li>\n<li>Stir in the flour and cook for 2 minutes more.</li>\n<li>Make your stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Gradually pour the stock into the pot, then bring to the boil and bubble for 2 minutes. Add the spinach and cook for another 5 minutes, then stir in the mustard, sour cream, half the rosemary and the lemon juice. Spoon into a baking dish.</li>\n<li>Mix the butter beans with a little oil and the rest of the rosemary. If it&rsquo;s too thick add a tiny bit of water.</li>\n<li>Spoon the butter bean mixture over the filling, smoothing with the back of a spoon. Bake for 20-25 mins until golden. Leave to cool slightly, then serve.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-28 08:08:30','2022-02-09 15:35:36',NULL),(138,'vxkfcm','Aubergine Lasagne','A vegetarian twist on a firm favourite with everyone, Italian or not. Here we swap out the mince for cubes of aubergine, but we promise you lose none of that classic lasagne heartiness!','Gluten, lactose',5,55,'<ol><li>Heat your oven to 180 C.</li><li>In a pot, heat some oil and fry the aubergine cubes.</li><li>Add wine and cook for a few minutes, stirring occasionally.</li><li>Add marinara sauce and simmer for 10 minutes.</li><li>Taste and add salt and pepper if necessary.</li><li>In another pot, gently heat the cheese sauce until it is warm enough to spread.</li><li>In an oven dish put a thin layer of aubergine sauce on the bottom. Then a layer of pasta sheets. Then a layer of cheese sauce. Repeat these three layers until your sauces run out, finishing either with cheese sauce or aubergine sauce. Sprinkle the top with your grated cheddar cheese.<br>Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes. Take the foil off and bake for a further 15 minutes to brown the cheese.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-28 08:25:09','2022-11-02 10:56:44','<p><strong>Marinara sauce</strong></p>\n<p><br />1 onion, finely chopped<br />1 tsp crushed garlic<br />a little oil<br />2 tbsp tomato paste (1 sachet)<br />2 tbsp balsamic vinegar&nbsp;<br />1 tin crushed tomato<br />1 tsp dried basil<br />1 tsp dried oregano&nbsp;<br />&frac12; tsp salt<br />Pepper, to taste</p>\n<p>Fry the onions in the oil until soft.<br />Add tomato paste, garlic, vinegar, crushed tomato and bring to a boil.<br />Add the herbs, salt and pepper.<br />Let it simmer on low for 20 minutes plus.</p>\n<p>Makes about 450 ml.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(139,'mfnqul','Sweet Potato and Coconut Curry','Who would have thought that the humble sweet potato would make such a delicious curry? With cabbage and bell pepper for extra nutrition and an unusual medley of passata, coconut cream and peanut butter adding fabulous flavour, this meal is sure to satisfy.','Nuts',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Place rice and salt into a pot of water and bring to the boil. Time 20 minutes from boiling point, keeping an eye on the water level. Drain and keep warm</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a large pot and add the onion. Fry gently for 5 minutes until soft then add the garlic and ginger and cook for 1 minute.</li>\n<li>Stir in the Curry Spice Mix and cook for another minute.</li>\n<li>Add more oil along with the red pepper, shredded cabbage and potato cubes. Cook for 4-5 minutes&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Pour the passata and the coconut cream into the pot, stir to mix everything together and cover and cook until sweet potatoes are tender, probably 30 to 40 minutes.</li>\n<li>Stir the peanut butter through the curry and season with salt and black pepper.</li>\n<li>Chop the coriander and use to garnish the curry which you will serve on the rice.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-28 08:34:55','2022-11-02 10:46:54','<p><strong>Passata</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong><br />4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped<br />1 large onion<br />2 TBSP olive oil<br />4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic<br />8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)<br />1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste<br />2 tsp ground black pepper<br />2 TBSP tomato paste<br />Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</p>\n<p><br /><strong>Method:</strong><br />Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.<br />Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.<br />Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.<br />Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.<br />Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(140,'bpyiyz','Chilli Con Carne with Homemade Mealie Bread','Here we bring you an old favourite with wonderfully rich flavours and colours.  Mop up this deliciousness with your own homemade mealie bread served fresh from the oven. It’s easy – we’ll show you how!','Gluten, lactose',10,50,'<ol>\n<li>Start with the bread: preheat the oven to 170 C. In a large mixing bowl, add the sweet corn, beaten eggs, milk and&nbsp; melted butter together and stir. Mix in the flour, paprika and 1/4 teaspoon of salt per person you are cooking for (i.e 1 teaspoon for 4 people) and combine to form a dough. If using a metallic or glass bread tin, grease with a little non-stick spray. Place dough in bread tin and bake for around 45 minutes or until a skewer or butter knife comes out clean. Let the bread cool.</li>\n<li>While the bread is baking, make the chilli con carne: Heat some oil in a big pot. Add the onion and cook, stirring fairly frequently, for about 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Tip in the garlic, red pepper and the chilli spices.</li>\n<li>Give it a good stir, then leave it to cook for another 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.</li>\n<li>Add the beef, turn the heat up a bit, and break it up with your spoon or spatula.</li>\n<li>Make sure you keep the heat hot enough for the meat to fry and become brown, rather than just stew.</li>\n<li>Make up your stock by adding the beef stock powder to the specified amount of water. Add the beef stock to the pot.</li>\n<li>Add the chopped tomatoes. Tip in the dried marjoram, a pinch of sugar and salt and pepper. Add the tomato paste and stir the sauce well.</li>\n<li>Bring the pot to the boil, give it a good stir and put a lid on it. Turn down the heat until it is gently bubbling and leave it for 20 minutes.</li>\n<li>Stir occasionally to make sure the sauce doesn&rsquo;t catch. After simmering gently, the saucy mince mixture should be thick but not dry. Add a little water if it is too dry.</li>\n<li>Add the kidney beans, bring to the boil again, and gently bubble without the lid for another 10 minutes, adding a little more water if it looks too dry.</li>\n<li>Taste a bit of the chilli and season. Add more salt and pepper if needed.</li>\n<li>Now replace the lid, turn off the heat and leave your chilli to stand for 10 minutes before serving. This is really important as it allows the flavours to mingle.</li>\n<li>Serve with&nbsp; a dollop of sour cream and a slice of mealie bread.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-28 15:07:32','2022-07-08 18:56:29',NULL),(141,'hnomiv','Sweet Potato & Pork Mince Medley','This dish will warm the cockles of your heart - creamily satisfying with just enough spiciness to please the discerning palate. Sweet potatoes are a great source of fibre, vitamins and minerals, especially potassium and the tomato and bell pepper provide a whole lot of vitamin C.','Lactose',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>In a large pot over medium heat, heat oil. Add onion and green pepper and cook until soft, 5 minutes. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute more, then add tomato paste and stir until well coated.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add pork mince and cook, breaking up meat with a wooden spoon until no longer pink, 7 minutes. Add the spice mix and stir in well. Season with salt and pepper.</li>\n<li>Make up your stock by adding the stock powder to the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Add the stock, sweet potatoes and tomatoes and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and let simmer, uncovered, until sweet potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes.</li>\n<li>Chop the fresh parsley.</li>\n<li>When the meal is ready, remove from the heat, stir in the yoghurt and garnish with the chopped parsley before serving.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-28 15:33:23','2022-03-29 13:54:59',NULL),(142,'gajcrk','Rigatoni with Tomato & Vegetable Sauce','Do you have childhood memories of spaghetti, tomato sauce and melty cheese? Well here we have a slightly more sophisticated version with added veggies and rigatoni, but we lose none of that classic comfort food flavour.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>In a medium pot heat some oil over a medium-high heat and cook onion until soft, about 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add courgettes and mushrooms and cook for 4 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add garlic and continue to fry for 1 minute.</li>\n<li>Add tomato puree, salt and pepper to taste and the oregano. Add 1 tsp of sugar per 4 people i.e if you are cooking for 2 it will be 1/2 a teaspoon.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Bring the pot to a boil and then reduce heat to a vigorous simmer and cook until the courgette is crisp and tender, about 8 minutes.</li>\n<li>In the meantime bring a big pot of salted water to the boil. Add a splash of oil and the rigatoni and let it boil for 12 minutes.</li>\n<li>Drain the pasta and keep aside 1 cup of the pasta water.</li>\n<li>Add the pasta to the sauce, adding enough of the reserved pasta water to loosen the mixture and make a sauce that coats the pasta nicely.</li>\n<li>Serve immediately with grated cheddar cheese.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-28 15:49:13','2021-11-30 11:08:44',NULL),(143,'ullzb','Kung Pao Cauliflower with Halloumi & Pita','Kung Pao is a Chinese favourite - it involves a spicy sweet and sour sauce and peanuts and can be applied to chicken or vegetables. Here we use cauliflower for our Kung Pao, dress it up a bit with flash-fried halloumi cubes and stuff all that goodness into a pita bread.','Nuts, gluten',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Your soy sauce, vinegar, chili powder, red wine, sugar, and flour is already mixed together for you, labelled as Kung Pao sauce. Pour this into a bowl, stir and set it aside.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Cook cauliflower until golden brown and charred in places, about 15 minutes. You might need to use two pans or do this part in two batches if your pan is not big enough. Reduce heat to low. Stir in the Kung Pao sauce mixture and cook until sauce starts to thicken, about 2 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add peanuts and garlic and cook for 2 minutes more.</li>\n<li>Transfer from the pan into a bowl to keep warm and stir in the spring onions.</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Heat some more oil on a high heat and brown your halloumi bits on each side, 1 - 2 minutes a side.</li>\n<li>Warm your pita breads for a few seconds in the microwave (you can alternatively do this on a pan at a low heat in the oven).</li>\n<li>Cut a slit in each pita on the side, gently prize it open and spoon in some of the cauliflower and some halloumi bits.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-29 10:50:54','2022-05-12 17:50:05',NULL),(144,'jcmltg','Vegetarian Chilli Con Carne with Homemade Mealie Bread','Here we bring you an old favourite with wonderfully rich flavours and colours, using extra beans instead of beef mince.  Mop up this deliciousness with your own homemade mealie bread served fresh from the oven. It’s easy – we’ll show you how!','Gluten, lactose',10,50,'<ol>\n<li>Start with the bread: preheat the oven to 170 C. Melt the butter. In a large mixing bowl, add the sweet corn, beaten eggs, 1/4 teaspoon of salt per person you are cooking for, and the melted butter. Add some warmed milk, 60 ml for 4 servings, 30 ml for 2 servings. Stir to combine. Mix in the flour and paprika. Combine to form a dough. If using a metallic or glass bread tin, grease with a little non-stick spray. Place dough in bread tin and bake for around 45 minutes or until a skewer or butter knife comes out clean. Leave to cool.</li>\n<li>While the bread is baking, make the chilli bean con carne: Add some oil to a large pot and heat it up. Add the onion and cook, stirring fairly frequently, for about 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Tip in the garlic, red pepper and the chilli spices. Give it a good stir, then leave it to cook for another 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.</li>\n<li>Add the kidney and butter beans, turn the heat up a bit, and stir. Keep stirring for at least 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Make your vegetable stock by adding the powder to the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Add the vegetable stock to the pot. Add the chopped tomatoes. Tip in the dried marjoram, a big pinch of sugar and add a good shake of salt and pepper. Add the tomato paste and stir the sauce well.</li>\n<li>Bring the whole thing to the boil, give it a good stir and put a lid on the pan. Turn down the heat until it is gently bubbling and leave it for 20 minutes. Check on the pan occasionally to stir it and make sure the sauce doesn&rsquo;t catch on the bottom of the pan or isn&rsquo;t drying out. If it is, add a couple of tablespoons of water and make sure that the heat really is low enough. After simmering gently, the saucy bean mixture should look thick but not dry.</li>\n<li>Add more salt and pepper if needed.</li>\n<li>Now replace the lid, turn off the heat and leave your chilli to stand for 10 minutes before serving. This is really important as it allows the flavours to mingle. Serve with a drizzle of sour cream and a slice of mealie bread.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-29 11:20:36','2023-05-17 16:20:57',NULL),(145,'wempdi','Homemade Beef Patties with Salsa and Tortilla','Drop the bun and grab a tortilla! Pop in a couple of homemade beef patties with a creamy mayo salsa. A fun way to get your protein and veg.','Gluten, lactose',10,30,'<div>Beat your egg in a separate bowl.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Mix the mince, salt, onion powder, garlic powder, chutney and grated cheddar into a bowl and work them together thoroughly. The amount of salt is 1/4 teaspoon per person you are cooking for.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Then add your beaten egg. If you are cooking for 1 person you may not need all the egg. Don\'t let the mixture get too sloppy.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Heat some oil in a pan. Form the mince mix into patties using your hands. Fry the patties for 3 minutes on each side, putting aside to keep warm.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>While the patties are frying, make the salsa: chop the tomatoes into small cubes. Roughly chop the basil leaves. Mix the tomato &amp; basil together with the onion and green pepper. Add some tangy mayo dressing and then salt and pepper to taste.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Heat the unwrapped tortilla for about 15 seconds in the microwave just to make them warm.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Place one or two patties and salsa onto one half of the tortilla. Add more dressing if you desire. Fold over and enjoy.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-29 15:53:34','2022-07-17 16:32:22',NULL),(146,'duofjy','Spinach & White Bean Soup with Fried Halloumi Cubes','This is a very hearty soup and the halloumi cubes instead of croutons are a nice touch - both for the taste and for your health. Along with the soup, we show you how to make the easiest white rolls ever using a one bowl mix and a muffin pan.','Gluten, lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Heat oven to 180 degrees Centigrade. Grease a muffin pan.</li>\n<li>Mix all the bread ingredients together well to form a dough and place big spoonfuls of the dough into the muffin pan - the number of dough balls you make depends on how many people you are cooking for.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>When the oven is hot enough, bake for 16 minutes. Allow to cool for a few minutes and then turn them out of the pan and set aside.</li>\n<li>While the rolls are baking heat oil in a medium pot and add the onions, garlic, bay leaves and cumin. Stir fry for a few minutes then put the lid on and let them &ldquo;sweat&rdquo; on a medium heat for at least 5 minutes for the flavours to mingle nicely and the onions to get soft.</li>\n<li>Make your vegetable stock by mixing the powder with the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Stir the vegetable stock and the beans into the onion, garlic and spices in the pot. Add salt and pepper to taste. Bring to the boil, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes. Stir in spinach and check seasoning again. Turn the pot off and allow it to cool while you fry the halloumi cubes.</li>\n<li>Heat a little butter or oil in a frying pan, non-stick if you have, over a fairly high heat. Fry the cubes of halloumi, turning often, until brown. This process is quick so be careful not to burn it.</li>\n<li>Serve a bowl of soup with cubes of fried halloumi on top along with buttered rolls.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-29 16:10:28','2021-11-29 12:01:51',NULL),(147,'nvibly','Sweet Potato Patties with Fresh Salsa & Tortilla','Veg burgers with a difference for our vegetarians - homemade sweet potato patties with freshly-made salsa and a creamy mayo dressing, all wrapped up in a tortilla.','Gluten',10,30,'<ol>\n<li>Place sweet potatoes in a pot of water with salt and bring to the boil. Cook until soft enough to mash - probably 20 minutes.</li>\n<li>Mash the potatoes. Then add the flour, soy sauce and salt &amp; pepper to taste. Keep your hands wet while shaping the patties - this stops the mixture from sticking to you.</li>\n<li>Heat a little oil in a pan on medium heat and fry the patties until they are golden brown both sides. An electric frying pan is good for this because you can do all at once but if you do not have one, do them in batches.</li>\n<li>While the patties are frying, make the salsa.</li>\n<li>Chop the basil and combine it with the chopped tomatoes, onion and green pepper. Add the tangy mayo dressing and then salt and pepper to taste.</li>\n<li>Spread each tortilla/wrap with 2 tablespoons of sweet chilli sauce.</li>\n<li>Place a couple of patties and salsa onto a tortilla/wrap. Fold and enjoy.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-30 06:31:32','2022-06-23 09:00:09',NULL),(148,'ciyuvd','Spicy Paneer and Rice','This vegetarian one-pot dish is easy, fairly quick to the table and packs a healthy punch with its red pepper, green beans, and aromatic spices. Using rice and made like a pilaf, we add cubes of paneer to give you a satisfying meal.','Traces of Lactose',5,40,'<ol><li>Heat the oil in a medium sized pot.</li><li>Fry the onion for 3 minutes, stirring regularly.</li><li>Add the garlic, cumin, coriander and chilli powder and fry whilst stirring for one minute.</li><li>Add the red pepper, green beans and rice and stir fry for two minutes.</li><li>Make up your stock by adding the powder to the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li><li>Add the stock and bring to the boil.</li><li>Simmer for 20 minutes and then add the paneer cubes. Stir very gently and cook for a further10 minutes.</li><li>The liquid should be absorbed and the rice and veg should be cooked.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-30 06:53:13','2021-02-06 13:34:57',NULL),(150,'zcfche','Vegetable Fried Rice','Transport yourself to Thailand as you prepare this fragrant Eastern fried rice. It is simple to prepare and is a wonderful low-fat option for our vegetarians and non-vegetarians alike.','None',5,35,'<ol><li>The key to good fried rice is using rice that has been cooked and then cooled down. So even though it seems crazy, make sure you follow the next step properly!</li><li>Place the rice in a pot and cover well with water. Add salt. Place on the stove and bring to a boil. Once boiling take the lid off and boil for 20 minutes. Keep an eye on the water level, it should always be covered with some water. When the rice is done, drain it, spread it out on a baking sheet and pop in the freezer for 10-15 minutes.</li><li>Heat a large pan over high heat until very hot, about 2 minutes. Add some oil.</li><li>Beat eggs with a little water and a pinch of salt and add to the hot pan. Cook, stirring to form large soft curds, about 30 seconds. Transfer to a plate.</li><li>Return the same pan (don’t worry about washing in between) to high heat and add double the amount of oil than in the previous step.</li><li>Add the carrots, mushrooms and ¾ of the spring onions. Cook for about 2 minutes. Add garlic and ginger and cook, stirring, until fragrant, for 1 minute.</li><li>Add rice, peas, and cooked eggs to the pan. Pour in half of the soy sauce and cook, stirring until heated through, 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper and stir in the spring onions.</li><li>Serve into bowls and add extra soy sauce to taste, if desired.&nbsp;</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-30 07:28:47','2022-09-27 09:25:12',NULL),(151,'cdppsr','Stuffed Sweet Potatoes (Vegetarian)','Oven roasted sweet potatoes stuffed with richly flavoured beans and topped with sour cream, rocket and an optional dash of mild peri peri sauce. This dish looks very impressive when served and its good looks are only surpassed by its tastiness.','Lactose',5,55,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat oven to 200C/180C fan forced. Rub the sweet potatoes with some oil and place on an oven rack in the oven. Roast for 45 minutes or until tender.</li>\n<li>Meanwhile, heat the oil in a large pot over high heat. Add the onion. Reduce heat to low. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes. Stir in the garlic and the spice mix and cook for 1 minute.</li>\n<li>Increase heat to medium-high. Add the beans to the pan. Cook for 5 minutes. Add the bay leaf, marjoram and tomato puree. Add water in the same quantity as you have tomato puree. Bring to the boil. Season well. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 15 -20 minutes or until the sauce has reduced.</li>\n<li>Slice the potatoes almost in half (don&rsquo;t cut all the way through). Divide the bean mixture among potatoes. Drizzle with a little sour cream and peri-peri sauce if using and top with the rocket/baby spinach.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-30 08:17:58','2022-03-17 08:02:01',NULL),(152,'fcogha','Vegetable & Tofu Noodle Soup','Here we have taken our heartwarming chicken noodle soup and substituted cubes of tofu which is baked until golden to give you a vegetarian version. Your veggies are spring onion, garlic, green beans, red pepper and carrots with lime and coriander adding the Asian twist.','Gluten',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 180 degrees C. Line a baking sheet with the baking paper. Toss the tofu with a little of oil and place it on the baking sheet. Bake for 15 minutes, or until slightly golden in colour. Transfer the tofu to a bowl, and set aside.</li>\n<li>In a large pot, heat some more oil. Add the red pepper, carrots, green beans, spring onions, and garlic and season with salt and pepper. Cook until soft, 6 to 8 minutes.</li>\n<li>Make your stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Add the vegetable stock to the pot and bring to a simmer. Add the egg noodles and cook until tender, 2 to 3 minutes, then stir in the tofu and coriander. Simmer until heated through.</li>\n<li>Serve with a squeeze of lime juice in each bowl.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-30 08:29:24','2021-10-08 11:09:27',NULL),(153,'cbqmtw','Pork Mince, Cauliflower & Spinach Bake','This delicious family-style dish is actually cauliflower cheese on steroids.  Apart from loads of flavour and its comfort-food style, it will give you adequate protein and lots of calcium - cheers to your good health!','Gluten, lactose',5,40,'<ol><li>Heat oven to 200 degrees C.</li><li>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil, add the cauliflower and boil for 6 minutes, adding the spinach at 5 minutes so it only gets one minute in the pot. Drain well and set aside.</li><li>Use the same pot to very gently heat the cheese sauce just so that it is pourable and set aside.</li><li>Heat oil in a frying pan and add the pork mince, thyme, sage and salt and pepper to taste. Break up the mince with a wooden spoon while it is frying so it does not form big clumps. Fry for 5 minutes - it should be nicely browned.</li><li>Place the cauliflower and spinach into an oven dish, scatter the pork mince over that, pour the cheese sauce&nbsp; on top and scatter with your grated cheddar.</li><li>Pop in the oven for 30 minutes - it should be nicely&nbsp; browned.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-30 09:14:41','2022-08-26 11:49:41','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">CHEESE SAUCE</span></p>\n<p><br /><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You will need:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">60 grams butter</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">50 ml flour</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 cups full cream milk</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">100 grams of cheddar grated</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tsp salt or to taste (start with half)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">pinch of nutmeg</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Instructions:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Melt the butter and stir in the flour with a wooden spoon until a smooth paste forms. Stir while this cooks for a minute.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add the milk in four dollops, stirring out lumps in between each addition. Keep a whisk on hand for beating smooth if necessary. Let the sauce come to a simmer and simmer for about 4 minutes while it thickens. Make sure to stir constantly to avoid lumps. Add salt and nutmeg. When the sauce is the right consistency, take off the heat and stir in the cheese.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This makes 500ml cheese sauce.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(154,'nctzqa','Chunky Vegetable Soup with Smoked Chicken and Whole Wheat Flatbread','Learn to make your own healthy flatbread. It’s really easy, promise. Pair that with a chunky vegetable soup with lots of veggies and smoked chicken for protein and you have a very satisfying meal.','Gluten',5,40,'<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<ol>\n<li>Mix the whole wheat flour mix with the yoghurt in a plastic bowl. You may need a little extra flour for your hands. Knead the dough well on a floured counter top. Wrap in plastic or cover with a cloth and let it rest, while you start the soup.</li>\n<li>In a large pot heat some oil and once hot put in all the veg except the tomatoes. Put the lid on the pot and &ldquo;sweat&rdquo; the veg for 10 minutes, stirring frequently to stop any sticking.</li>\n<li>Put in the paprika, oregano, garlic and bay leaf. Stir.</li>\n<li>Make your stock by mixing the stock powder with the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Pour the stock and the tomatoes into the pot.&nbsp; Stir well and allow to simmer for 25 minutes.&nbsp; Add the chicken and simmer for a further 5 minutes. The butternut should be nice and soft. Taste and season with salt and pepper if necessary. Keep warm.</li>\n<li>Heat a little oil to a high heat in a pan. Take a biggish ball of your dough and flatten to fit your pan, or as flat as you can get! Put the dough in the pan and then immediately flip over so that both sides have oil on. Then cook for about 1 minute a side, or until a good colour. Repeat with the rest of the dough, keeping the flatbread warm.</li>\n<li>Use a potato masher to semi-blend the vegetables into the soup to thicken slightly but leave enough chunks to make it hearty.</li>\n<li>Serve with flatbread.</li>\n</ol>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-30 11:54:39','2023-04-01 14:39:06','<h3>To Make Self-Raising Whole Wheat Flour</h3>\n<p>1 cup whole wheat flour</p>\n<p>1,5 tsp baking powder</p>\n<p>0,5 tsp salt</p>\n<p>Mix together</p>'),(155,'bwyfho','Beef Mince & Cabbage Wraps','This meal is quick to make and fun to put together, while still giving you all the protein and veg that you need to stay healthy. There is onion, green pepper and corn in the mince and a big portion of shredded cabbage and grated carrot gets rolled into each wrap. A yummy barbecue sauce pulls it all together.','Gluten',5,15,'<ol><li>Wrap your wraps in foil and heat in a 180 degree C oven for 10 minutes and then keep warm. If you have a microwave it is easier to pop them in there for 15 seconds. Wraps need to be warm to work with. When they get cold they split easily, so if you use the microwave method do it just before you actually need them.</li><li>Heat a bit of oil in a pot and cook the onion and green pepper for a few minutes to soften. Add the mince and break down with a wooden spoon so there are no clumps.&nbsp;</li><li>Cook for about 10 minutes stirring often until the meat is brown all over. Stir in the corn and half of the barbecue sauce. Cook whilst stirring until heated through.</li><li>Put the cabbage and carrot into a bowl, lay out the mince mixture and the rest of the barbecue sauce.</li><li>At this stage microwave the wraps, or take them from the oven.</li><li>Lay a warm wrap on a plate, put some barbecue sauce, some slaw and some mince mixture onto the wrap and start wrapping! You could lay everything out and let each person wrap their own.&nbsp;</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-30 12:18:11','2022-10-24 11:34:08','<p>Homemade Barbecue Sauce</p>\n<p>10 ml olive oil<br />1 tsp crushed garlic<br />3 Tbsp onion flakes or 1 Tbsp onion powder<br />125 ml apple cider vinegar<br />125 ml tomato sauce<br />125 ml water<br />125 ml sugar<br />2 Tbsp mustard<br />1 Tbsp Worcestershire Sauce<br />2 tsp chilli powder<br />2 Tbsp cornstarch mixed with 2 Tbsp water</p>\n<p>Heat oil and fry the garlic for 1 minute before adding all the other ingredients. Let the sauce cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.</p>\n<p>Should make approx 400 ml</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(156,'yplsvj','Soya Mince, Cauliflower & Spinach Bake','This delicious family-style dish is actually cauliflower cheese on steroids.  Apart from loads of flavour and its comfort-food style, it will give you adequate protein and lots of calcium - cheers to your good health!','Gluten, lactose',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>Heat oven to 200 degrees C.</li>\n<li>Rehydrate your soya, in a 1:1 ratio soya to water, cover and leave to stand for 10 minutes while you par cook the cauliflower and spinach.</li>\n<li>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil, add the cauliflower and boil for 6 minutes, adding the spinach at 5 minutes so it only gets one minute in the pot. Drain well and set aside.</li>\n<li>Use the same pot to very gently heat the cheese sauce just so that it is pourable or spreadable and set aside.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a frying pan and add the well-drained soya mince, thyme, sage, salt and pepper to taste. Stir fry for 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Place the cauliflower and spinach into an oven dish, scatter the soya mince over that, spread the cheese sauce&nbsp; on top and sprinkle with your grated cheddar.</li>\n<li>Pop in the oven for 25 to 30 minutes - it should be nicely&nbsp; browned.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-30 12:35:16','2022-06-12 07:42:10',NULL),(157,'lnhcqp','Chunky Vegetable Soup with Black Beans and Whole Wheat Flatbread','Learn to make your own healthy flatbread. It’s really easy, promise. Pair that with a chunky vegetable soup with lots of veggies and black beans for protein and you have a very satisfying meal.','Gluten',5,40,'<ol><li>Mix the whole wheat flour mix with the yoghurt in a plastic bowl. You may need a little extra flour for your hands. Knead the dough well on a floured counter top. Wrap in plastic or cover with a cloth and let it rest, while you start the soup.</li><li>In a large pot heat a large dollop of oil and once hot put in all the veg except the tomatoes and black beans. Put the lid on the pot and “sweat” the veg for 10 minutes, stirring frequently to stop any sticking.</li><li>Make up your stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li><li>Add the paprika, oreganum, garlic and bay leaf to the soup pot and stir for a minute. Then put in the stock and the tomatoes.</li><li>Stir well and allow to simmer for 25 minutes. &nbsp;</li><li>Add the beans and simmer for a further 5 minutes. The butternut should be nice and soft. Taste and add salt and black pepper to your liking. Keep warm.</li><li>Heat a little oil to a high heat in a non-stick pan. Take a biggish ball of your dough and flatten to fit your pan, or as flat as you can get! Put the dough in the pan and then immediately flip over so that both sides have oil on. Then cook for about 1 minute a side, or until a good colour. Repeat with the rest of the dough, keeping the flatbread warm.</li><li>Use a potato masher to semi-blend the vegetables into the soup to thicken slightly but leave enough chunks to make it hearty.</li><li>Serve with flatbread.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-30 12:42:55','2021-04-23 10:52:31',NULL),(158,'vqgpqo','Black Bean & Cabbage Wraps','This meal is quick to make and fun to put together, while still giving you all the protein and veg that you need to stay healthy. Black beans are cooked up with onion, green pepper, corn and barbeque sauce and then rolled into a wrap along with a portion of shredded cabbage and carrot. Serve with an additional sprinkling of the sauce.','Gluten',5,15,'<ol>\n<li>Wrap your wraps in foil and heat in a 180 degree C oven for 10 minutes and then keep warm. If you have a microwave it is easier to pop them in there for 15 seconds. Wraps need to be warm to work with. When they get cold they split easily, so if you use the microwave method do it just before you actually need them.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a pot and cook the onion and green pepper for a few minutes to soften.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add the beans, the corn and half of the barbecue sauce. Cook whilst stirring for a few minutes.</li>\n<li>Put the cabbage and carrot into a bowl, lay out the bean mixture and the rest of the barbecue sauce.</li>\n<li>At this stage microwave the wraps, or take them from the oven.</li>\n<li>Lay a warm wrap on a plate, put some barbecue sauce, some slaw and some bean mixture onto the wrap and start wrapping! You could lay everything out and let each person wrap their own.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-30 12:53:52','2023-03-27 16:45:51','<p>Homemade BBQ Sauce</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>10 ml olive oil</p>\n<p>1 tsp crushed garlic</p>\n<p>1 Tbsp onion powder</p>\n<p>125 ml apple cider vinegar</p>\n<p>125 ml tomato sauce</p>\n<p>125 ml water</p>\n<p>125 ml sugar</p>\n<p>2 Tbsp mustard</p>\n<p>1 Tbsp Worcestershire Sauce</p>\n<p>2 tsp chilli powder</p>\n<p>2 Tbsp cornstarch mixed with 2 Tbsp water</p>\n<p>Heat oil and fry garlic for 1 minute. Then add all other ingredients and stir together well. Cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.</p>\n<p>This makes approx 400 ml</p>'),(159,'gcphjn','Enchilada Rice with Beef','Ground beef, Mexican spices, black beans, red pepper, onion, tomato and corn make this mince and rice dish a fiesta of flavours and all in one pot. Topped with lots of cheese and grilled until golden - delicious!','Traces of Lactose',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oil in a pot and fry the onion until soft.</li>\n<li>Add the mince and fry until browned, breaking up the bits with a wooden spoon. Add salt and black pepper to taste.</li>\n<li>Add the&nbsp; red pepper, chilli and spices and fry for 1 min.</li>\n<li>Make your stock by adding the stock powder to the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>To the mince mixture, add the tomatoes, stock, rice, beans, corn and bring to the boil. Lower heat and simmer for 30-35 minutes without covering.</li>\n<li>Chop the fresh coriander.</li>\n<li>When the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked, stir in the coriander.</li>\n<li>Pour the mixture into an oven dish, top with the cheese, switch on your oven grill and grill until golden.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-30 13:05:11','2022-03-11 11:19:08',NULL),(160,'iryph','Thai-style Chicken Noodle Soup','Take your classic chicken noodle soup and give it a taste of Thai with a mild red curry paste, garlic and ginger, spring onions, coconut milk, lime juice and fish sauce. We add plenty of noodles, chicken and some cubed pumpkin to make the meal extremely satisfying.','Gluten',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Cook noodles in boiling salted water for 3 minutes then drain, mix a little oil in with them to stop them sticking and set aside.</li>\n<li>Make your stock by adding the stock powder to the amount of boiling water specified on the pakage. Set aside.</li>\n<li>Heat some more oil in a large pot over medium-high heat. Add the chicken pieces and cook for a few minutes to brown. Remove and set aside.</li>\n<li>To the pot, add spring onion and garlic and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute. Add ginger and curry paste and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add stock, coconut milk, butternut and a 1/4 teaspoon of sugar per person you are cooking for.&nbsp; Bring to a boil, add chicken back, reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until butternut is just tender, 20 minutes.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Stir in the peas and cook for 1 minute. Stir in lime juice and fish sauce.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Pick the basil leaves off the stems and roughly chop them.</li>\n<li>Divide noodles between four serving bowls. Top with soup and basil.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-30 13:20:06','2021-11-12 10:10:33',NULL),(161,'ptmrul','Pork Bangers with Veg & Mozzarella Bake','This is one for the low-carbers, but is so deliciously satisfying that even the most hardened of carb addicts will not miss their fix. Plenty of taste, plenty of good nutrition - it’s what TasteBox is all about!','Traces of Lactose',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat the oven to 170 degrees C.</li>\n<li>Grease an oven dish -&nbsp; about 20 x 20 cm.</li>\n<li>In a small pot combine the cream cheese, cream, onion powder and garlic powder, salt and pepper and heat gently until it is all melted and well combined.</li>\n<li>In the baking dish layer your ingredients as follows:</li>\n<li>Baby marrow, red onion, red &amp; green pepper, mozzarella cheese, repeating until you run out of ingredients and reserving a handful of mozzarella for the top. Spread the sauce in the pot over the top of the veg and sprinkle remaining mozzarella on top.</li>\n<li>Bake in the oven for 40 minutes.</li>\n<li>While the veg bake is in the oven, fry your pork sausages in a pan with a little oil on a medium high heat. Turn them often. They should be done in 20 minutes.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-30 13:36:39','2021-07-08 14:12:07',NULL),(162,'nfkmvg','Enchilada Rice with Soya Mince','Mexican spices, black beans, red pepper, onion, tomato and corn make this soya mince and rice dish a fiesta of flavours and all in one pot. Topped with lots of cheese and grilled until golden - delicious!','Traces of Lactose',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>Soak your soya mince in boiling water for 10 minutes, 1 cup of water to 1 cup of soya ratio.</li>\n<li>Heat the oil in a pot and fry the onion until soft.</li>\n<li>Add the pepper, chilli and spices and fry for 1 min.</li>\n<li>Make your stock by adding the powder to the amount of boiling water specified on its package.</li>\n<li>Add the soya mince, tomatoes, stock, rice, beans and the corn to the pot and bring to the boil. Lower heat and simmer for 30-35 minutes without covering.</li>\n<li>Chop the fresh coriander.</li>\n<li>When the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked, stir the coriander into the pot.</li>\n<li>Pour the mix into an oven dish, top with cheese and grill until golden.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-30 13:48:02','2022-10-18 10:18:35',NULL),(163,'tuizkq','Thai-style Soya Noodle Soup','Take your classic vegetable noodle soup and give it a taste of Thai with green curry paste, garlic and ginger, spring onions, coconut milk, lime juice and fish sauce. We add plenty of noodle, soya mince and some cubed butternut to make the meal extremely satisfying.','Gluten',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Soak soya mince in boiling water in a one to one ratio, for 10 minutes.</li>\n<li>Cook noodles in boiling salted water for 3 - 4 minutes then drain, drizzle with oil to stop them getting sticky, mix the oil in and set aside, keeping warm.</li>\n<li>Make the stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Set aside.</li>\n<li>Heat some more oil in a big pot. To the pot, add the garlic and ginger and cook, stirring, for 1 minute. Add the spring onions and the curry paste and cook, stirring, for a further 1 minute.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add the stock, coconut milk, butternut and 1/4 teaspoon sugar per person you are cooking for. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer adding the soya as soon as it&rsquo;s 10-minute soak is up. Stir occasionally while simmering until the butternut is tender,&nbsp; about 20 minutes.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Stir in the peas and cook for 1 minute. Stir in the lime juice and fish sauce.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Chop the fresh basil leaves.</li>\n<li>Divide the noodles between four serving bowls. Top with soup and the basil leaves.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-30 14:00:02','2022-04-13 09:46:20',NULL),(164,'vszjlk','Marrow & Mozzarella Bake with Butter Beans','We have taken our rich and cheesy Baby Marrow, Red Onion, Green Pepper & Mozzarella Bake which is a meal in itself and we have added plenty of butter beans for protein, making an excellent vegetarian meal.','Traces of Lactose',5,40,'<ol><li>Preheat the oven to 170 degrees and grease an oven dish of approx 20 x 30 cm.</li><li>Add the cream cheese, cream, onion powder, garlic powder and salt &amp; pepper to a pot and heat gently until it forms a sauce. This will only take a few minutes. It can also be done on medium in the microwave. Watch it and stir frequently.</li><li>In the oven dish put down a layer of marrow, red onion, green pepper and butter beans and sprinkle some mozzarella over it. Continue layering until you run out of ingredients, reserving a small handful of mozzarella for the top.</li><li>Pour your sauce over the layers and sprinkle the remainder of the mozzarella on top.</li><li>Bake for for 40 minutes</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-30 14:10:57','2022-04-13 10:10:04',NULL),(165,'hqriim','Moroccan Beef & Pumpkin Bake with Crispy Cornmeal Topping','Beef mince, pumpkin, red pepper, onion, garlic and corn are cooked with couscous and a Moroccan spice blend for the base of this hearty pie but it is the golden, crispy topping made with  traditional corn meal that will steal your heart.','Gluten, lactose',5,45,'<p>Heat oven to 200 degrees centigrade.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a big pot and fry the onion for 2 minutes. Add the pumpkin, garlic and red pepper and fry for another 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the beef mince and break up nicely with a wooden spoon. Season with salt and black pepper. Cook for 10 minutes, keeping the mince from clumping up.</p>\n<p>Add the corn, couscous and spices and stir in for 1 minute.</p>\n<p>Make up your stock by adding the powder to the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</p>\n<div>Add the stock and cream cheese to the pot. Mix well and allow to cook for another 5 minutes. Taste and season with salt and pepper if you need to.</div>\n<p>Spoon mixture into an oven dish.</p>\n<p>Now make the corn meal topping: Crack the egg into a bowl and beat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Add the following amount of milk:</p>\n<p>- If cooking for 4 people, add 125 ml of milk</p>\n<p>- If cooking for 2 people add 30 ml of milk</p>\n<p>-&nbsp; If cooking for 1 person, don\'t add any milk.</p>\n<p>Pour your corn meal mixture into a bowl. Add the egg/milk/oil mixture bit by bit. Mix together until you have a nice spreading consistency. Discard some of the liquid if it is too much. The consistency doesn\'t have to be smooth. Spread it over the mince. Don&rsquo;t worry if it looks messy!</p>\n<p>Bake for 30 minutes. The topping should be slightly risen and golden.</p>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-31 07:39:45','2023-03-06 11:02:07',NULL),(166,'qimtmg','Garlic-Ginger Chicken with Pumpkin & Cauliflower Mash','Your kitchen will smell like an upmarket Thai restaurant while this beauty is in the oven. Chicken on the bone is baked in a sauce of red onion, garlic, ginger, soy sauce, orange juice and lemon grass - sublime flavours. Serve it on a delicious mash of pumpkin, cauliflower, butter and chives.','None',5,55,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 200 C. Place the chicken pieces in a roasting dish and season with salt and pepper.</li>\n<li>Combine the onion and garlic-ginger sauce in a bowl. Pour the sauce over the chicken. Place in the oven and cook for 45 minutes. Check that the chicken is cooked through.</li>\n<li>While the chicken is cooking, bring a pot of salted water to the boil.</li>\n<li>Add the pumpkin to the boiling water and after 5 minutes add the cauliflower &ndash; boil them together for another 10 minutes. They should be soft enough to mash.</li>\n<li>Drain and mash them together with the butter and salt and black pepper to taste. Stir in the chopped chives.</li>\n<li>Serve each person with some mashed pumpkin and cauliflower topped with 1 &ndash; 2 pieces of chicken.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-31 07:53:11','2021-10-25 13:32:59',NULL),(167,'sijfzq','Sausage & Bean Casserole with Mashed Potato','A hearty, stick-to-your ribs meal that is easy to put together. Tomato, celery, peppers and beans are all in the mix to make sure you get good nutritional value too.','None',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Heat some oil on a medium heat in a large heavy-based pan. Add the onion and cook gently for 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the celery, pepper and green beans and cook for a further 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the pork sausages and fry for 10 minutes. Take the sausages out of the pan after 10 minutes and slice thickly. Set aside.</li>\n<li>Stir in the garlic and the Spice Mix. Continue cooking for 1 &ndash; 2 minutes.</li>\n<li>Pour in the white wine and use a wooden spoon to remove any residue stuck to the pan.</li>\n<li>Add the tomatoes and tomato paste. Bring to a simmer.&nbsp; Add 1 teaspoon of sugar per 4 people i.e. if you are cooking for 2 it will be 1/2 a teaspoon.</li>\n<li>Add the chicken stock powder and stir. Add back the thick sausage slices.</li>\n<li>If at any time the mixture seems too dry just add a little hot water and stir in. Cook for 20 minutes.</li>\n<li>While that is cooking, do the potatoes: chop the potatoes into small cubes, and while you are doing that bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Add the potatoes and boil for 15 - 20 minutes or until potatoes are soft enough to mash.</li>\n<li>Mash the potatoes with a little milk and salt and black pepper to taste.</li>\n<li>Add the butter beans to the sausage mix and cook for a further five minutes.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Season the sausage casserole with salt &amp; black pepper.</li>\n<li>Serve the casserole on the mashed potato.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-31 08:08:34','2021-11-30 11:27:09',NULL),(168,'qzwowv','Moroccan Lentil & Pumpkin Bake with Crispy Cornmeal Topping','Black lentils, pumpkin, red pepper, onion, garlic and corn are cooked with couscous and a Moroccan spice blend for the base of this hearty pie but it is the golden, crispy topping made with  traditional corn meal that really makes this a meal worth cooking.','Gluten, lactose',5,45,'<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\n<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 200 degrees Celsius.</li>\n<li>Make your stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a big pot and fry the onion for 2 minutes. Add the pumpkin, garlic and pepper, put the lid on and let them &ldquo;sweat&rdquo; for 12 minutes, stirring often to stop the mixture sticking to the pot.</li>\n<li>Add the lentils and stir in well along with salt and pepper to taste.</li>\n<li>Add the corn, couscous and Moroccan spice and stir in for 1 minute.</li>\n<li>Add the stock and cream cheese. Mix well and allow to cook for another 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Spoon mixture into an oven dish.</li>\n<li>Now make the corn meal topping: Crack the egg into a bowl and beat. Add 2 tablespoons of oil. Add the following amount of milk: for four people add 125 ml milk, for two people, add 30 ml milk, for one person, do not add any milk.</li>\n<li>In a separate bowl mix the corn meal and flour. Add 1/4 teaspoon of salt for each person you are cooking for and 1 teaspoon of sugar for each person you are cooking for.</li>\n<li>Add the egg/milk/oil mixture to the flour mix until you have a nice spreading consistency.&nbsp;It does not have to be smooth. Spoon onto the lentil mixture, spreading to form a topping. Don&rsquo;t worry if it looks messy!</li>\n<li>Bake for 30 minutes. The topping should be slightly risen and golden.</li>\n</ol>\n</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-31 08:29:51','2022-08-08 14:41:41',NULL),(169,'zsldjh','Garlic Ginger Paneer with Pumpkin, Cauliflower & Bean Mash','Your kitchen will smell like an upmarket Thai restaurant while this beauty is in the oven. And there’s nothing like a fusion of nationalities as  Paneer (a firm Indian whey cheese) is baked in a sauce of red onion, garlic, ginger, soy sauce, orange juice and lemon grass - sublime Thai flavours. Serve it on a delicious veggie mash.','Lactose',5,35,'<ol><li>Heat the oven to 200 C.&nbsp;</li><li>Place the paneer in a roasting dish.</li><li>Combine the onion, the Garlic Ginger Sauce and pepper to taste in a bowl.&nbsp;</li><li>Pour the sauce over the paneer.&nbsp;</li><li>Place in the oven and cook for 30 minutes.</li><li>While the paneer is cooking, bring a pot of salted water to the boil.</li><li>Add the pumpkin to the boiling water and after 5 minutes add the cauliflower and beans – boil them together for another 10 minutes. They should be soft enough to mash, though the beans won’t mash completely.</li><li>Drain and mash them roughly together with the butter and salt and black pepper to taste.&nbsp;</li><li>Serve each person with some mashed pumpkin, cauliflower and beans topped with the garlic-ginger paneer.<br><br></li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-31 08:44:07','2021-04-28 15:31:10',NULL),(170,'uxmmfs','Halloumi, Tomato and Bean Casserole with Mashed Potato','A hearty, stick-to-your ribs meal that is easy to put together and perfect for vegetarians. Tomato, celery, peppers and beans are all in the mix to make sure you get good nutritional value along with the protein from the Halloumi.','Traces of Lactose',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Heat some oil in a large pot. Add the onion and cook gently for 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the celery, pepper and green beans and cook for a further 5 mins.</li>\n<li>Stir in the garlic and the herbs and spices. Continue cooking for 1 &ndash; 2 mins or until the aromas are released.</li>\n<li>Pour in the diluted white wine vinegar. Use a wooden spoon to remove any residue stuck to the pan.</li>\n<li>Add the tomatoes, tomato paste and a 1/4 tsp of sugar per person that you are cooking for. Bring to a simmer.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add the stock powder and stir.</li>\n<li>Add the halloumi cubes and stir in gently.</li>\n<li>Add the green beans.</li>\n<li>If at any time the mixture seems too dry just add a little hot water and stir in. Cook for 20 minutes.</li>\n<li>While that is cooking, do the potatoes: chop your potatoes into small pieces. Bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Add the potatoes and boil for 15 - 20 minutes or until potatoes are soft enough to mash.</li>\n<li>Mash the potatoes with salt, pepper and a little milk. Season the casserole with salt &amp; pepper</li>\n<li>Add the kidney beans to the halloumi mix and heat through for 5 minutes</li>\n<li>Serve the casserole on the mashed potato.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-31 08:53:50','2022-09-29 14:11:28',NULL),(171,'rijhmv','Baked Leek, Mushroom & Feta Pasta','A baked pasta dish involving tomato and cheese is always yummy and this is no exception. We douse sautéed leeks, mushrooms, zucchini and garlic in our special tomato passata, mix it with penne pasta and give it a generous sprinkling of creamy feta cheese before popping it into the oven. Quick, easy, nutritious and delicious!','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 180 degrees C.</li>\n<li>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Pour in a dash of oil and the pasta and boil for 12 minutes. Drain and pour the pasta into a baking dish. &nbsp;</li>\n<li>While the pasta is boiling, heat some more oil in a pan. Add the leeks and the garlic and fry for 5 minutes. Add the mushrooms and courgettes. Season well with salt and pepper and fry for another 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Tip your leeks, mushrooms and marrow on top of the pasta and use a spoon to combine. Pour the passata sauce over the top and combine all ingredients.</li>\n<li>Sprinkle the feta cheese over the top and pop in the oven for 20 minutes.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-31 10:31:38','2022-07-09 18:27:14','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Passata</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ingredients:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 large onion</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp ground black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS tomato paste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Method:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(172,'jjyebx','Lemon Chicken with Orzo','A tangy one-pot dish where an unusual fusion of flavours works like a dream. The chicken and orzo pasta simmers in chicken stock and white wine, along with lots of leek, garlic, thinly sliced lemon and green olives. Served with a little  dill and crumbled feta.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Make your stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Set it aside.</li>\n<li>Slice your lemon into thin slices with the skin on. Set aside.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a large pot and cook the chicken pieces for 10 minutes. Set the chicken aside.</li>\n<li>In the same pot that you cooked the chicken in, adding a little more oil if you need to, fry the leeks until they are soft, making sure to scrape up any bits that stick to the bottom (these add to the flavour).</li>\n<li>Add the garlic and fry for a minute. Add the wine, stir well and let it bubble for a few minutes.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add the orzo, lemon slices, olives and stock to the pot. Stir together well</li>\n<li>Lay the chicken pieces (skin side up) on top of the orzo, season with salt and pepper and bring to the boil. Turn down the heat, cover the pot and simmer for 20-25 minutes until orzo is tender, stock is absorbed and chicken is cooked.</li>\n<li>Scatter the feta and dill over the top and serve.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-31 10:42:39','2022-07-17 16:13:13',NULL),(173,'mzzjun','Sweet Potato & Soya Medley','This dish will warm the cockles of your heart - creamily satisfying with just enough spiciness to please the discerning palate. Sweet potatoes are a great source of fibre, vitamins and minerals, especially potassium and the tomato and bell pepper provide a whole lot of vitamin C.  Soya mince is added for a punch of protein.','Lactose',5,50,'<ol>\n<li>Soak your soya in boiling water at a 1:1 ratio ie 1 cup soya to 1 cup water for 10 minutes. Drain.</li>\n<li>In a large pot over medium heat, heat some oil. Add the onion and green pepper and cook until soft, 5 minutes.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add the crushed garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute more, then add tomato paste and stir until well coated.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add the Spice Mix and season with salt and pepper. Stir together well for a minute.</li>\n<li>Make your stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Add sweet potatoes, vegetable stock, soya and tomatoes, stirring, and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and let simmer, uncovered, until sweet potatoes are tender,&nbsp; 30 to 40 minutes. Stir from time to time to make sure the mixture is not sticking on the bottom of the pot.</li>\n<li>Chop the fresh coriander and the parsley.</li>\n<li>Remove from heat and stir in the yoghurt and chopped coriander.&nbsp; Garnish with parsley to serve.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-31 10:56:09','2022-05-13 15:18:46',NULL),(174,'eoufie','Lemon Paneer','We love  our Lemon Chicken dish. The tanginess produced by leeks, garlic, white wine, lemon and olives is sublime. We wanted to make a vegetarian version and who would have thought how well Paneer, the Indian whey cheese, would blend. We used creamy risotto rice as a backdrop to the show and WOW we loved the outcome!','Traces of Lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>In a big pot heat some oil and fry the leeks until they are soft, making sure to scrape any bits that stick to the bottom (these add to the flavour).</li>\n<li>Add the garlic and fry for a minute. Add the wine, stir well and let it bubble for a few minutes.&nbsp; &nbsp;</li>\n<li>Make the stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Add the risotto rice, lemon, olives and stock to the leeks and garlic in the pot. Stir together well.</li>\n<li>Lay the pieces of paneer on top of the mixture and bring to the boil. Turn down the heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes until risotto rice is nice and creamy and the stock is absorbed. Gently mix the pieces of paneer into the rice mixture.</li>\n<li>Taste the dish and add salt and pepper if required.</li>\n<li>Scatter the feta and dill over the top and serve.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-31 11:08:33','2022-05-13 12:52:40',NULL),(175,'vayggq','Beef Stroganoff and Rice','An old classic that never fails to please, we have given it a bit of a twist to add some more veg without taking anything away from the fabulous stroganoff flavour. You’ll have a nutritious meal on the table in no time.','Gluten, lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Place rice and salt into a pot of water. Bring to the boil and time 20 minutes from boiling point. Drain and keep warm.</li>\n<li>While the rice is cooking, melt half of the butter in a pot, add the onion and cook for 5 minutes until soft. Add the mushrooms and baby marrows and cook for another 5 minutes. Remove from the pot and set aside for now.</li>\n<li>Make your beef stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>In the same pot (don&rsquo;t bother to wash!), melt the rest of the butter and add the beef strips. Cook while stirring them until browned, about 10 minutes. Sprinkle&nbsp; the flour over the meat and stir. Slowly add the beef stock and then the sour cream, while stirring. Keep the heat low so it doesn&rsquo;t catch.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add back the onion, baby marrow and mushroom mixture as well as the butter beans.</li>\n<li>Season well with salt, pepper and the parsley. Let it simmer for about 10 minutes.</li>\n<li>If you need to thin the sauce slightly use a dash of milk.</li>\n<li>Serve with the rice, or if you are wanting a low carb meal, serve without rice, or with just 2 tablespoons.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-31 11:26:22','2023-01-09 09:45:13',NULL),(176,'biyjse','Pork Koftas with Mexican Corn Salad','This Mexican Corn Salad is a version of Esquites, a favourite Mexican street food. It is so delicious that you will want to serve it with absolutely everything. We have paired it with Pork Koftas which are basically large pork mince balls made with chutney and spices.','Lactose',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>Heat oven to 180 degrees Celsius.</li>\n<li>Mix together the mince, chutney, chilli flakes, onion powder, garlic powder and salt and pepper to taste.</li>\n<li>Form the mixture into large meatballs.</li>\n<li>Place the meatballs on the baking paper on a baking tray and bake for 35 minutes.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>While the meatballs are in the oven you can put together your corn salad.</li>\n<li>Melt the butter in a large pot and the stir in the garlic, cooking for a few seconds before you add your corn kernels. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring every now and again. Add salt and pepper half way through this process.</li>\n<li>Transfer corn into a heat resistant serving bowl and immediately add the mayonnaise, sour cream, Parmesan and lime juice. Mix together well so that the heat of the corn melts and blends the &ldquo;dressing&rdquo; ingredients.</li>\n<li>Chop the coriander.</li>\n<li>Add the coriander, spring onion and red onion and toss again.</li>\n<li>Crumble your feta over the top.</li>\n<li>Serve 1 - 2 meatballs with a side of the salad.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-31 11:34:51','2022-11-07 10:51:45',NULL),(177,'wndood','Vegetables Roasted in a Thai-style Peanut Sauce with Chicken','And yet another way to enjoy roasted veggies! Bake them in our easily put together peanut sauce for something different and delicious. Cook chicken thighs and drumsticks coated with olive oil and Italian herbs at the same time - voila,  your meal is ready!','Nuts',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.</li>\n<li>Put the Thai-Style Peanut Sauce into a small pot and heat gently while stirring. Slowly add as much water as you need to give it a nice pouring consistency.</li>\n<li>Place the butternut, baby marrow, mushrooms and green pepper into an oven dish. Pour the peanut sauce over the top and then mix it into the veg.</li>\n<li>Place the chicken pieces in a bowl Add some oil, salt, black pepper and Italian herbs and mix until pieces are nicely coated. Place them on a baking tray.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Place the baking tray with the chicken and the oven dish with the veg into the oven.</li>\n<li>Bake for 45 minutes or until you are happy the chicken is cooked through and the butternut is soft.</li>\n<li>Serve chicken, roasted veg and a portion of leafy greens.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-31 12:59:58','2021-10-26 11:59:59',NULL),(178,'eboepu','Soya Stroganoff with Rice','An old classic that never fails to please, we have added more veg and replaced the beef with soya without taking anything away from the fabulous stroganoff flavour. You’ll have a nutritious meal on the table in no time.','Gluten, lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Place rice and salt into a pot of water. Bring to the boil and time 20 minutes from boiling point. Drain and keep warm.</li>\n<li>Soak your soya in boiling water for 10 minutes, drain and set aside. Have a 1:1 ratio of soya and water.</li>\n<li>Make the stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Set aside.</li>\n<li>While the rice is cooking, melt the butter in a pot, add the onion and cook for 5 minutes until soft. Add the mushrooms and baby marrows and cook for another 5 minutes.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Sprinkle the flour into the pot and stir in well. Slowly add the stock and then the sour cream, while stirring. Keep the heat low so it doesn&rsquo;t catch.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Season well with salt, pepper and the parsley. Add the drained soya and the butter beans. Let it simmer for about 10 minutes. If you need to thin the sauce, add a little milk.</li>\n<li>Serve with the rice.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-31 13:16:16','2022-07-17 16:15:04',NULL),(179,'dyhwwi','Layered Lentil Cottage Pie with Sun-dried Tomato Pesto','A new take on a vegetarian Cottage Pie - cheesy sweet potato is good enough to eat out of the bowl on its own but add the layer of carrots and a lentil mix that has been cooked up with onion, tomato paste, balsamic vinegar and a strong vegetable stock and you have a winner. Served with an absolutely delicious sun-dried tomato pesto.','Gluten, nuts and traces of lactose',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees C.</li>\n<li>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil and cook the sweet potato cubes until soft enough to mash - 20 minutes.</li>\n<li>Chop the chives.</li>\n<li>Mash the sweet potato with the butter, salt &amp; pepper, chives and half the cheese. Set aside.</li>\n<li>While the sweet potato is cooking, bring another pot of salted water to the boil and cook the carrots for 20 minutes. Drain and roughly mash. Set aside.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a pot and cook the chopped onion for 5 minutes to soften, add the lentils and mix.</li>\n<li>Add the flour and stir in well. Add the tomato paste and balsamic vinegar and stir in well.</li>\n<li>Make your stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Add the stock and stir while the mixture thickens, about 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Taste the lentil mix and add salt and pepper if you want to.</li>\n<li>Layer your three mixtures in an oven dish. Start with some lentil mix, then some carrot and then some sweet potato. Repeat, trying to end with the sweet potato.</li>\n<li>Sprinkle the rest of the cheese on top and bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.</li>\n<li>Serve with the pesto on the side.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-31 13:26:20','2022-02-17 13:52:51',NULL),(180,'nmdcwq','Vegetables Roasted in a Thai-style Peanut Sauce with Pan-fried Halloumi','And yet another way to enjoy roasted veggies! Bake them in our easily put together peanut sauce for something different and delicious. Serve with pan-fried slices of golden Halloumi. A meal that is different, delicious and easy to put together - we think we have ticked all the boxes, including the one that says “good for you”.','Nuts, Lactose',5,40,'<ol><li>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.</li><li>Put the peanut sauce into a small pot and heat up while stirring. Slowly add as much water as you need to give it a nice pouring consistency.</li><li>Place the butternut, baby marrow, mushrooms and green pepper into an oven dish. Pour the peanut sauce over the top and then mix it into the veg.</li><li>Bake for 45 minutes or until the butternut is soft.</li><li>While the veg is roasting, heat a little oil in a pan on a high heat and fry the halloumi - it only needs a minute or so each side to make it nice and golden brown.</li><li>Serve the halloumi, roasted veg and a portion of leafy greens.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-10-31 13:38:11','2021-04-12 14:54:00',NULL),(181,'sfxewg','Cordon Bleu Chicken Bake','You don’t have to be a French chef to put this together, whatever the name says! It’s really simple. Chicken breasts are cut open and flattened, covered with ham and cheddar cheese and rolled up. Fit them snugly into an oven dish, cover with our pre-made white sauce and grated cheddar and bake. The richness of this dish is offset by broccoli on the side.','Gluten, lactose',5,45,'<ol><li>Preheat the oven to 180°C and grease a 20cm x 20cm square baking dish.</li><li>Butterfly the chicken breasts by slicing in half lengthways.</li><li>Place the butterflied breasts in a plastic bag and use a rolling pin or the bottom of a pot to beat the breasts out until they are around 1 to 2 cm thick. Take out of the plastic bag and lay on a board. Season with salt and pepper.</li><li>Lay 2 slices of ham over each breast, followed by grated cheese. Leave enough cheese to sprinkle on the top of the dish. Roll up length-ways and place the roll-ups in an oven dish fitting snugly so they don’t roll open.</li><li>Heat the white sauce gently, just enough to make it pourable/spreadable and spread over the chicken roll-ups.</li><li>Sprinkle the remaining cheese over the white sauce.</li><li>Bake for 40 minutes, or until the chicken has cooked through and the cheese is golden brown. Use the grill for a few minutes if need be to brown it off.</li><li>While the chicken is cooking bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Add the broccoli&nbsp; and cook for 4 minutes. Drain and keep warm.</li><li>When the chicken is done serve a portion with some broccoli on the side. Use the sauce in the bottom of the oven dish to spoon over the broccoli.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-01 07:26:45','2022-08-25 11:44:45','<p>WHITE SAUCE</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You will need:</p>\n<p>60 grams butter<br />50 ml flour<br />2 cups full cream milk<br />1 tsp salt or to taste (start with half)<br />pinch of nutmeg</p>\n<p>Instructions:</p>\n<p>Melt the butter and stir in the flour with a wooden spoon until a smooth paste forms. Stir while this cooks for a minute.<br />Add the milk in four dollops, stirring out lumps in between each addition. Keep a whisk on hand for beating smooth if necessary. Let the sauce come to a simmer and simmer for about 4 minutes while it thickens. Make sure to stir constantly to avoid lumps. Add salt and nutmeg. When the sauce is the right consistency, take off the heat.</p>\n<p>This makes 500ml sauce.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(182,'iojczv','Loaded Broccoli Cheese Bake','A more nutritious and more filling version of your normal broccoli cheese, this dish is loaded with extra veg, a bit of Parmesan to pop the flavour of the cheddar and hidden cubes of baked halloumi. This deliciousness is topped with wholewheat breadcrumbs that bake to a golden crust. Please note that the leafy greens in the photo are not included in the kit.','Gluten, lactose',5,50,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.</li>\n<li>Lightly grease a 24 x 20 cm oven dish.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a big pot&nbsp; and cook the onion, bell pepper, baby marrow and mushrooms, salt and pepper, stirring frequently - 8 to 10 minutes.</li>\n<li>Sprinkle the flour over the vegetable mix and cook for 1 minute stirring all the time so the flour is mixed in well.</li>\n<li>Add the milk, a dollop at a time, stirring constantly, and bring to the boil. The sauce should thicken in about 3 minutes.</li>\n<li>Stir in the cheddar, half the parmesan, the broccoli and the little cubes of halloumi.</li>\n<li>Pour mixture into baking dish.</li>\n<li>Mix the other half of the parmesan with the breadcrumbs and sprinkle over the top, dotting little bits of butter onto it.</li>\n<li>Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, when the crumbs should be golden and the casserole&nbsp; bubbling.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-01 07:27:34','2023-03-03 11:40:10',NULL),(183,'kdhevu','Pork Medallions in Marsala Wine Sauce','Marsala wine sauce is a classic that can make an old shoe taste good. Learn how to make it from our simple recipe card and let us chop and measure all the necessary ingredients for you. It lends itself particularly well to pork medallions cut from the tenderloin. Lightly steamed or boiled broccoli adds a wonderful pop of colour as well as nutrients.','Traces of Lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil, put the broccoli in and cook for 4 minutes from when it comes back to the boil. Drain and keep warm.</li>\n<li>Make the stock by dissolving the pwder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Set aside for now.</li>\n<li>Mix the flour, salt and pepper in a bowl and dredge the pork medallions very well in the flour mixture.</li>\n<li>Heat the oil in a big pot and fry the flour-coated pork for 3 minutes on each side until nicely browned. Remove from the pot and set aside.</li>\n<li>Melt the butter in the same pot and fry the mushrooms until golden, about 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Add the spring onions and garlic and fry for another minute.</li>\n<li>Add the pork back to the pot and pour in the stock and the wine. Mix together well.</li>\n<li>Bring to a strong simmer uncovered for two minutes, stirring everything together and allowing the sauce to thicken.</li>\n<li>Cover and reduce heat to low, cooking for 10 minutes more.</li>\n<li>Stir in the cream and serve with some broccoli on the side.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-01 08:44:30','2022-06-23 08:39:33',NULL),(184,'ztspmv','Chickpea & Broccoli Salad Wraps','Take a delicious chickpea and broccoli salad with red onion, cranberries, sunflower seeds and feta, mixed into a sweet and sour yoghurt-based dressing and wrap it in a flour tortilla. What is not to enjoy? Easy to make, nutritious and fun to eat.','Gluten, lactose',5,15,'<ol>\n<li>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Drop in the chopped broccoli and leave for 2 minutes. Drain and run cold water over it while draining to stop it cooking.</li>\n<li>Put the yoghurt dressing in a bowl.</li>\n<li>Stir in the broccoli, chickpeas, cranberries, red onion and sunflower seeds.</li>\n<li>Warm the wraps for a few seconds in the microwave - it makes them easier to handle.</li>\n<li>Place a wrap on each plate, top with greens and then spoon about 3/4 cup of the salad on top of that. Crumble feta over the top and wrap.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-01 09:07:47','2021-11-15 10:48:39',NULL),(185,'ivzzzm','Soya Mince in Marsala Wine Sauce','Marsala wine sauce is a classic that can make an old shoe taste good. Learn how to make it from our simple recipe card and let us chop and measure all the necessary ingredients for you. We have used soya mince as the protein in the sauce for our vegetarians. Lightly steamed or boiled broccoli adds a wonderful pop of colour as well as nutrients.','Traces of Lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Soak your soya mince in boiling water in a ratio of 1 cup water to 1 cup soya. Leave for 10 minutes and then drain well.</li>\n<li>Make the stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Set aside.</li>\n<li>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil, put the broccoli in and cook for 4 minutes. Drain and keep warm.</li>\n<li>Melt the butter in the same pot and fry the mushrooms until golden, about 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Add the spring onions and garlic and fry for another minute.</li>\n<li>Add the drained soya, a little salt and black pepper and the flour.</li>\n<li>Mix the flour into the other ingredients well and then pour in the stock and the wine. Mix together well.</li>\n<li>Bring to a strong simmer uncovered for two minutes, stirring everything together and allowing the sauce to thicken.</li>\n<li>Cover and reduce heat to low, cooking for 10 minutes more.</li>\n<li>Stir in the cream and taste to see whether you need extra salt and black pepper.</li>\n<li>Serve with some broccoli on the side.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-01 09:23:08','2022-08-05 09:56:41',NULL),(186,'amgstp','Mince and Aubergine Pasta Bake','A hearty and rich beef mince and aubergine dish featuring our homemade tomato sauce - no preservatives, no nasties - baked with penne pasta and topped with melted mozzarella.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Heat oven to 180 degrees and grease an oven dish.</li>\n<li>Place aubergine in a bowl and salt it well. Let it stand for 5 minutes while you get other stuff ready.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Bring salted water to the boil and boil the pasta for 12 minutes. Drain and set aside.</li>\n<li>In another pot heat the oil and fry the onion for two minutes until softened. Add the mince and brown it, breaking it up so that it does not form clumps.</li>\n<li>Add aubergine, tomatoes, tomato sauce, basil, oregano, salt and chilli flakes. Stir well and let this simmer vigorously for 15 minutes. Stir in the pasta and transfer the mixture to the oven dish. Place the grated mozzarella on top of the meat mixture and bake uncovered for 30 minutes.</li>\n<li>Chop the fresh parsely and sprinkle over the top of the dish.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-01 09:39:16','2022-07-09 09:33:10','<p>Homemade Tomato Sauce</p>\n<p>50 grams tomato paste</p>\n<p>240 g tub tomato puree&nbsp;</p>\n<p>80 grams honey</p>\n<p>4 Tablespoons apple cider vinegar</p>\n<p>2 Tablespoons onion powder</p>\n<p>1 teaspoon garlic powder</p>\n<p>1 teaspoon salt</p>\n<p>1 teaspoon cinnamon</p>\n<p>1 teaspoon black pepper</p>\n<p>Pinch of nutmeg</p>\n<p>Pinch of chilli flakes</p>\n<p>Place all in a Nutribullet or blender and whizz until a smooth texture is reached.</p>\n<p>This can be kept in the fridge for two weeks, probably longer because of the vinegar in it.</p>\n<p>Makes about 400 ml</p>'),(187,'jtebgz','West African Chicken & Peanut Stew','This tasty dish packs a nutritious punch with kidney beans, bell pepper, sweet potatoes, ginger and garlic. An unusual but incredibly tasty sauce featuring peanut butter, tomato puree and coconut cream takes chicken stew to a new level.','Nuts',5,40,'<ol><li>Heat some oil in a large pot over medium to high heat, add the thighs and drumsticks, and cook until brown all over. Remove the chicken and set aside for now.</li><li>To the same pot, add some more oil, then fry the onion until golden brown. Add the ginger, garlic, chilli, red pepper and tomato puree and fry for 2 mins before stirring in the coconut cream, peanut butter and 100 ml of water per person that you are cooking for, ie 400 ml for 4 people.</li><li>Add the chicken and cubed sweet potatoes. Bring to the boil, cover and simmer for 15 minutes.&nbsp;</li><li>Remove the lid, stir in the kidney beans and continue to simmer on a low heat for about 20 minutes until the sauce is thick and the chicken and sweet potato are cooked through.&nbsp;</li><li>Season to taste with salt and pepper before serving.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-01 09:55:25','2021-02-13 16:37:39',NULL),(188,'jmbskp','Greek Halloumi & Cauliflower Gyros','The word gyro is derived from the Greek word for sandwich, but this is no ordinary sandwich. It is a tower of texture, taste and colour with a homemade flatbread base. Pile on the greens, some crunchy grilled cauliflower, radish, cucumber, halloumi and olives and pull it all together with a good drizzle of full cream Greek yoghurt.','Gluten, lactose',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Make the flatbreads. Whisk flour (the packet marked \"for flatbreads\") and a big pinch of salt in a bowl. You should use 1/4 teaspoon of salt per person you are cooking for.&nbsp; Add the yoghurt that is marked for the flatbreads. Use a wooden spoon to mix. Get in there with your hands and knead it into a well-combined dough. If too stiff to work add a little water. Turn onto a lightly floured surface (use the flour marked \"for kneading\"). Knead until smooth. Return to the bowl. Cover with plastic wrap. Set aside while you cook the cauliflower and halloumi.</li>\n<li>Place the lemon &amp; garlic mix in a large bowl.&nbsp; Add cauliflower. Toss to coat. Stand for 10 minutes.</li>\n<li>Preheat the oven grill. Cook cauliflower on a baking tray, turning, for 5 to 6 minutes or until lightly charred and just tender. Transfer to a plate. Cover to keep warm.</li>\n<li>While the grill is on, grill the halloumi slices on the same baking tray for a few minutes, turning and watching carefully. Put aside when nicely grilled.</li>\n<li>Divide dough into 4 equal portions. Shape each into a ball. On a lightly floured surface, roll or press out to form 4mm-thick ovals.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Heat a little oil in a pan on a high heat and fry the flatbreads flipping over to get oil on both sides, and then cook for 1 minute each side or until lightly charred and cooked through. Transfer to a baking tray. Cover loosely with foil to keep warm.</li>\n<li>Spread flatbread with a little yoghurt. Top with leafy greens, radish, cucumber, cauliflower, halloumi and olives. Serve with lemon wedges and remaining yoghurt drizzled on top.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-01 12:00:34','2023-01-30 10:51:38',NULL),(189,'gwiznm','Tomato & Courgette Stew with Parmesan & Nutty Wheat Bread','A lovely stew featuring tomatoes, black beans and courgettes made even more flavoursome by the addition of grated parmesan and fresh basil. Pair it with nutty wheat bread hot from your oven - so easy with the ready made dough that comes in your kit.','Gluten, lactose',5,55,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 180 C. Unwrap the dough from the plastic wrap. Squish it into a greased bread tin. Once the oven is heated, bake the bread for 50 &ndash; 60 minutes. You will know the bread is cooked if you stick a skewer or bread knife into it and it comes out clean. Remove from the tin and leave to cool.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>While the bread is cooking heat some oil in a large pot over a medium heat. Add the onion and cook for 8 to 10 minutes until softened and starting to go golden brown. Add the garlic and cook for another minute.</li>\n<li>Add the courgettes and cook 5 minutes until starting to soften. Tip in the tomatoes and beans and give everything a good stir. Simmer for 35 to 40 minutes or until tomatoes are reduced and courgettes soft.</li>\n<li>Chop the basil and stir it in along with the Parmesan.</li>\n<li>Taste to see whether you would like to add some salt and black pepper, or maybe a pinch of sugar to counteract the acidity of the tomato.</li>\n<li>Serve in bowls with slices of buttered homemade nutty wheat bread on the side.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-01 12:22:37','2022-09-05 10:39:01',NULL),(190,'hxqdaw','Cheesy Tomato & Spinach Gnocchi Bake','Gnocchi in any form is a winner but this bake has three different cheeses not just for deliciousness but for your protein. Plenty of tomato and spinach also give it a nutritious punch. Feel virtuous when asking for more!','Gluten, lactose',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 180 degrees C.</li>\n<li>Cook the gnocchi in salted boiling water for 2 minutes. They rise to the top of the water when they are done.&nbsp; Pour drained gnocchi into an oven dish.</li>\n<li>Fry the onion and garlic in some oil for a few minutes, until translucent.</li>\n<li>Chop the fresh basil.</li>\n<li>Add all the tomatoes, the balsamic vinegar, the oregano, the basil and season with salt and pepper.&nbsp; Add 1 teaspoon of sugar per person that you are cooking for. Stir well together.</li>\n<li>Simmer for 10 minutes and then stir in the spinach.</li>\n<li>Stir the ricotta through the sauce.</li>\n<li>Mix the flour with a little milk to form a paste and add to the sauce, stirring to thicken.</li>\n<li>Stir the mozzarella into the gnocchi in the oven dish.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Pour the sauce over the gnocchi and mozzarella.</li>\n<li>Place grated parmesan over the top.</li>\n<li>Sprinkle the dish with breadcrumbs and bake at 180 degrees for 20 minutes.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-01 12:41:44','2022-03-03 15:14:17',NULL),(191,'thbivx','Chicken Stroganoff with Rice','Get back beef! Chicken wants a turn in the stroganoff. A stroganoff is defined as a dish in which the main ingredient is cooked in a sauce containing sour cream. Hard to tell actually whether our main ingredient is chicken or mushroom but be sure that together they make this a stroganoff worth talking about.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Place the rice in a pot and cover well with water. Add salt. Place on the stove and bring to a boil. Once boiling take the lid off and boil for 20 minutes. Keep an eye on the water level, it should always be covered with some water, do not let it burn dry. When the rice is done drain it and keep it warm.</li>\n<li>Make your stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Set aside for now.</li>\n<li>In a large pot over medium heat, heat some oil. Add the chicken and sear for 10 minutes, until golden on all sides, and season with salt and pepper. Work in batches if needed. Remove chicken and place in a large bowl.</li>\n<li>Lower heat to medium and add some more oil. Add mushrooms and cook until golden and tender, 5 minutes. Remove from the pot and place in the bowl with chicken.</li>\n<li>Add more oil and cook the onion until softened, 4 minutes. Add garlic and thyme and cook until fragrant, 2 minutes more.</li>\n<li>Add back the chicken and mushrooms.</li>\n<li>Add the flour and stir in well.</li>\n<li>Stir in the stock, mustard, and Worcestershire sauce and bring to a simmer.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Stir and continue to simmer while the sauce thickens. This should take about 10 minutes.</li>\n<li>Remove from heat and stir in the sour cream. Season with salt and pepper.</li>\n<li>Chop the parsely.</li>\n<li>Spoon the chicken mixture over rice and garnish with parley to serve.</li>\n</ol>\n<div><br /><br /></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-02 05:59:00','2022-01-20 15:32:52',NULL),(192,'enzqvv','Easy Shepherd\'s Pie','Rock this family classic - no mess, no fuss. Beefy mince with added veggies for your good health topped with golden mashed potato made with sour cream. You don’t need to look to junk food for comfort food.','Gluten, lactose',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat the oven to 200&deg; C. Leaving the skin on, chop the potatoes into smallish pieces.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n<li>In a pot, cover chopped potatoes with water and add a generous pinch of salt. Bring to a boil and cook until totally soft, 15 to 20 minutes. Drain and return to the pot.</li>\n<li>Use a potato masher to mash potatoes with the butter and sour cream. Add a little milk until you are happy with the consistency. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.</li>\n<li>Make the stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of water specified on the package. Set aside.</li>\n<li>Start the beef mixture while the potatoes are boiling: In a large pot over medium heat, heat some oil. Add the onion, carrots, garlic, and thyme and cook until fragrant and softened, 5 minutes. Add the beef mince and cook until no longer pink, breaking it up with a wooden spoon, for 5 minutes. Season well with Italian herbs, salt and pepper.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Stir in the baby marrow and peas and cook for 3 minutes. Taste and season again with salt and pepper if necessary.</li>\n<li>Sprinkle meat with flour and stir it in well. Cook for 1 minute more and then add the stock. Bring to a simmer and cook for 10 minutes or until the mixture has thickened.</li>\n<li>Place the beef mixture in an oven dish and top it with an even layer of mashed potatoes. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until there is very little liquid visible and the mashed potatoes are golden.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-02 06:32:11','2022-05-13 14:27:22',NULL),(193,'wugxyo','Lentil Moussaka','Baked layers of roasted aubergine, a tomato lentil sauce and béchamel with grated parmesan makes a tasty moussaka for the vegetarians. The tomato lentil sauce uses onion, garlic, dry white wine and delightful hints of cinnamon and fresh mint to make it really special.','Gluten, lactose',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 200 degrees C.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Brush both sides of your aubergine slices with a bit of oil. Place on a baking sheet (or two if need be) and pop in the oven when it has heated. Bake for 20 minutes. Turn the slices once during this time.</li>\n<li>When the aubergine is done baking take it out and let it cool but leave the oven on at 200 degrees.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Make your stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Set aside.</li>\n<li>While the aubergine is baking, heat some more oil in a medium size pot and fry the chopped onion for 2 minutes. Add the garlic and fry for 1 minute and then add the cinnamon. Stir the cinnamon into the onion and garlic for 30 seconds.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add the chopped tomatoes, the white wine and stock and bring to a good simmer.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Simmer for 10 minutes without a lid and then add the lentils and simmer for a further 10 minutes.</li>\n<li>Chop the parsely and the mint leaves and stir them into the pot.</li>\n<li>Check the mixture for seasoning and add salt and black pepper to taste.</li>\n<li>Layer your aubergine and lentil mix, ending with the lentil mix, in an oven dish.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Gently heat the white sauce until it is pourable/spreadable. Do not boil. Stir in the parmesan and then spread over the top of the layers in the oven dish.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Bake for 25 minutes in the oven. The dish should look golden and bubbly.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-02 07:05:58','2021-11-12 11:56:32',NULL),(194,'tskdsk','Gnocchi with Mushrooms and Cream Cheese','Gnocchi is the King of Pasta - these little dumplings made from just potato, egg and flour soak up any flavour you throw at them and deliver the best in comfort food. Here we combine it with sautéed onion, green pepper, lots of mushrooms and cream cheese. Sprinkle with parsley for a nice splash of colour.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,10,'<ol>\n<li>Bring a big pot of salted water to the boil. Add the gnocchi. When they float to the surface they are cooked - it takes about 2 minutes. Drain and set aside.</li>\n<li>Heat the oil in a big pot on medium to high heat. Add the onion and green pepper and fry until soft, about 2 minutes. Lower the heat to medium. Add the mushrooms, stir into the onion and pepper, put the lid on and cook for 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Take the lid off, add the garlic. Cook for 2 minutes. Add the gnocchi and blobs of cream cheese, heating it through and letting the cream cheese melt into the mixture.</li>\n<li>Chop the parsley.</li>\n<li>Take the pot off the heat and scatter generously with the parsley.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-02 07:28:32','2022-01-10 08:44:28',NULL),(195,'luwuxp','Mushroom Stroganoff with Rice','Loads of mushrooms sautéed with onion and garlic and smothered in a delicious concoction of stock, sour cream, Dijon mustard, Worcestershire sauce and thyme. Served with rice and garnished with fresh parsley. Please note that the fresh tomato in the photograph is not included in the kit.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Place the rice in a pot and cover well with water. Add salt. Place on the stove and bring to a boil. Once boiling take the lid off and boil for 20 minutes. Keep an eye on the water level, it should always be covered with some water, do not let it burn dry. When the rice is done drain it and keep it warm.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a pot on a medium heat and add the onions and mushrooms. Cook for 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the garlic and thyme and cook until fragrant, 2 minutes more.</li>\n<li>Add the flour and stir in well.</li>\n<li>Make your stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Stir the stock into the pot, along with the mustard and Worcestershire sauce and bring to a simmer.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Stir and continue to simmer while the sauce thickens, 10 to 12 minutes.</li>\n<li>Remove from heat and stir in sour cream. Season with salt and pepper.</li>\n<li>Chop the parsley.</li>\n<li>Spoon some mushroom mixture over rice and garnish with the parsley to serve.</li>\n</ol>\n<div><br /><br /></div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-02 07:31:21','2023-03-27 17:30:56',NULL),(196,'splkeg','Creamy Chicken & Mushroom Pasta','You cannot go wrong with this classic. It’s topped with grated Parmesan for a touch of sophistication, and has added parsley and spinach to ensure that you get your greens.','Gluten, lactose',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>In a large pot of salted boiling water, cook pasta for 12 minutes. Drain and reserve 1/2 cup of the pasta water. Put aside.</li>\n<li>In a large pot over medium-high heat, heat some oil. Season chicken with salt and pepper. Fry chicken until golden and no longer pink,&nbsp; 8 to 10 minutes. Place in a bowl and set aside.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Make your chicken stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Return the pot to medium-high heat and melt the butter. Cook the&nbsp; mushrooms until golden, 5 minutes, then add the garlic and onions and cook, stirring occasionally, for 4 to 5 minutes.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Chop the parsley.</li>\n<li>Add the flour and stir until incorporated. Add the milk and cream, chicken stock, almost all the Parmesan and all the parsley. Season with salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes. Add the chopped spinach for the last 3 minutes.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Fold cooked pasta and chicken into the sauce. If the sauce is too thick, add pasta water until you reach desired consistency. Top with remaining Parmesan and serve.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-02 08:59:51','2022-06-16 15:29:28',NULL),(197,'icxgrk','Coconut & Butternut Dhansak','A vegetarian dhansak is an Indian dish from the Parsi community which combines lentils, veggies and spices. It is traditionally eaten on caramelised rice but we think a warm naan bread is a better option to accompany this delicious dish.','Gluten, lactose',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Add some water to a pot and bring to the boil. Add the cubed butternut and the lentils and boil for 20 minutes. Do not add salt - it makes the lentils tough. Drain and set aside.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>In the same pot (don&rsquo;t bother to wash it in between!), heat the oil and add the onion. Cook for a few minutes until soft. Add the curry paste, tomatoes and coconut milk, and simmer for 10 mins until thickened to a rich sauce.</li>\n<li>Add the butternut and lentils to the pot.</li>\n<li>Stir in the spinach (don&rsquo;t panic, it looks like a lot of spinach but it shrinks very quickly!) and season with some salt and pepper. Simmer for a further 2-3 mins to wilt the spinach, and then stir in the yoghurt.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Serve with warm naan bread.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-02 09:39:46','2022-01-10 08:32:08',NULL),(198,'uvtzjp','Sausage & Mash Pie','Bangers & Mash with a difference - a hearty pork sausage & gravy pie featuring leeks and mushrooms with a mashed potato & cheese topping. Paired with oven roasted green beans, this is a healthy family meal that everyone will enjoy.','Gluten, lactose',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Put the oven on to heat to 180 degrees Centigrade.</li>\n<li>Place the beans in an oven dish, drizzle&nbsp; with olive oil and season with salt and black pepper. When the oven is ready roast the beans for 20 minutes. Keep warm.</li>\n<li>Heat some salted water in a pot until boiling. Cut the potatoes into small chunks and boil them for 15 minutes, or until soft enough to mash. Drain and mash them with the mustard, milk and salt and black pepper to taste. Set aside.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a pot and fry the sausages for 10 minutes on a medium to high heat. Turn them once or twice. Take them out and let them cool. They will cook further later on.</li>\n<li>Add the leeks and mushrooms to the same pot you used for the sausages. Stir them around in the juices and then let them cook for 5 minutes on a medium heat.</li>\n<li>Make your stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Set aside.</li>\n<li>Use a sharp knife to cut the sausages up into rounds. Add them to the pot with the leeks and mushrooms.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add the flour and use a wooden spoon to mix it in well with the sausage, mushroom and leeks.</li>\n<li>Slowly add the stock stirring all the time, to make a gravy.&nbsp; Season to taste with salt, pepper and mixed herbs.</li>\n<li>Allow to simmer for 15 minutes to thicken, stirring from time to time to keep it from catching on the bottom of the pot.</li>\n<li>Spoon the sausage mixture into a casserole dish and then spoon the potato over the top of that. Sprinkle the cheese over the top of the potato. Turn on the grill in your oven (the beans should be out by now). Place the sausage and mash pie under the grill for 3 &ndash; 5 minutes or until bubbling and golden.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-03 06:36:35','2021-11-29 11:25:10',NULL),(199,'fdoimt','Creamy Mushroom Pasta with Fried Halloumi Cubes','A creamy pasta chock full of mushrooms cooked in butter, some garlic and Parmesan for flavour and  some baby spinach because, hey, never neglect your greens. All this goodness is topped with golden pan-fried Halloumi cubes.','Gluten, lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>In a large pot of salted boiling water, cook pasta for 12 minutes until al dente. Drain, reserve 1/2 cup pasta water, and set aside.</li>\n<li>In a frying pan with a little oil, fry halloumi cubes for one to two minutes until golden and set aside.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Make your stock by adding the powder to the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>In a large pot melt the butter and cook mushrooms until golden, 5 minutes, then add garlic and onions and cook, stirring occasionally, 4 to 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Chop the parsley.</li>\n<li>Add the flour to the pot and stir until incorporated. Add the milk and cream, stock, Parmesan, parsley and season with salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Fold cooked pasta into mushroom sauce along with the baby spinach/rocket. If the sauce is too thick, add pasta water until you reach the desired consistency.<br />Serve topped with halloumi cubes.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-03 06:58:17','2022-03-30 16:10:05',NULL),(200,'jivskf','Spinach & Feta Quiche with Mushrooms','Fabulously cheesy and very filling thanks to the cream & the yoghurt, this quiche is crustless and packed with healthy spinach, onions, garlic and mushrooms. It is just as good, if not better, eaten cold, so leftovers for lunch the next day are a win.','Lactose',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Heat oven to 180 degrees Centigrade.</li>\n<li>Grease an oven dish, approximately 30 x 20 cm.</li>\n<li>Heat a little oil in a pan over medium high heat and fry the onion for 3 minutes. Add the garlic and fry for a further 1 minute. Add the mushrooms and fry for a further 3 minutes. Put the spinach in for just 1 minute to wilt it.Turn heat off and leave in pan to cool slightly while you mix the other ingredients.</li>\n<li>Beat the eggs together and then add the cream and yoghurt. Stir in the cheddar cheese and half the feta as well as the onion &amp; veg mix in the frying pan.</li>\n<li>Pour into the oven dish and sprinkle remaining feta on top.</li>\n<li>Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, depending on your oven. It should be firm and browning on the edges.</li>\n<li>Slice or roughly chop your tomatoes. Drizzle them with the Balsamic Vinegar Dressing and serve alongside the quiche.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-03 07:25:46','2022-10-10 10:42:58','<p>Balsamic Vinegar Dressing</p>\n<p>For 75 ml (4 people):</p>\n<p>3 Tbsp olive oil</p>\n<p>1 Tbsp Balsamic Vinegar</p>\n<p>1 Tbsp honey</p>\n<p>Mix and shake vigourously.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(201,'wxxoaz','Sausage Ragu with Creamy Polenta','Tired of the same old sausage and mash? Why not pop the sausage into a ragu of spicy tomato sauce with butter beans, stir in some spinach, and serve on a bed of creamy Polenta, the staple of all good Italians from the North?','Lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Heat some oil in a pot over medium heat. Cook the sausages for 10 minutes - they will be half cooked.</li>\n<li>Take the pan off the heat. Take the sausages out of the pan and slice into rounds with a sharp knife. Put sausage rounds aside.</li>\n<li>Add a splash more oil to the pan if necessary, heat it and fry the onion for 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the garlic and cook for 30 seconds.</li>\n<li>Add the sausage rounds back to the pot and cook for a further few minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the tomato paste, chopped tomatoes, 1/4 teaspoon of sugar for each of the number of people you are cooking for and the herb and spice mix.</li>\n<li>Add the butter beans and season with salt and pepper. Cook for 10 minutes over a low heat.</li>\n<li>While that is cooking, make your stock by mixing the powder with the amount of boiling water specified on the pack.</li>\n<li>Put your milk and stock in a large pot and bring to the boil. Once it is boiling, turn down the heat and, using a whisk to stir, slowly add the polenta bit by bit, all while stirring with the whisk. It will slowly start to thicken up. The process should take 5 &ndash; 8 minutes. Once it has thickened, turn the heat off and stir through the cream cheese with a wooden spoon.</li>\n<li>Add the spinach into the sausage dish and stir through to allow the heat to wilt it. Cook for another 2 minutes and then turn the heat off.</li>\n<li>Serve a dollop of polenta, topped with the sausage ragu in bowls.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-03 07:35:35','2022-03-30 16:05:50',NULL),(203,'fsyppp','Stuffed Jacket Potatoes with Bacon & Tangy Coleslaw','An old family favourite - baked potatoes stuffed with cream cheese, cheddar cheese, bacon bits, mushrooms and red pepper. Add more melty cheese on top and serve them with a tangy coleslaw - it’s all in the kit!','Traces of Lactose',10,45,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 200C.</li>\n<li>Remove the foil from the parboiled potatoes and place them on a baking sheet in the oven and bake for 20 &ndash; 25 minutes. You will know they are cooked when you can stick a knife easily through them. Remove from the oven and allow them to cool enough to be able to handle them.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n<li>While the potatoes are cooling, heat some oil in a pan on a medium high heat and add the bacon bits. Cook for 3 minutes. Add the mushrooms and red pepper and cook for 5 minutes more. Season with salt, pepper and Italian herbs.</li>\n<li>Once the potatoes are cool enough to handle, slice them in half. Gently holding a potato half in one hand (use a clean cloth to hold if it is still quite warm), use a spoon to scoop out the flesh of each into a bowl. Don&rsquo;t worry about scooping out all the flesh, it is OK to leave a thin border of flesh around the skin.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Use a potato masher to mash the potato flesh in the bowl. Once mashed, stir in the cream cheese and 2/3 of the cheddar cheese. Add the crushed garlic and some salt and pepper. Now take your bacon and veggie mix and stir this in as well.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Using a spoon, scoop the flesh mixture back into the skins. Top each with the remaining grated cheese and place back in the oven for 10 minutes or until the cheese is nicely melted.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>While the potatoes are in the oven, make your coleslaw: combine the cabbage and carrots with the raisins and tangy mayo and mix together.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-03 08:22:51','2023-04-06 14:47:11',NULL),(205,'ulzcay','Vegetarian White Chilli with Mealie Bread','White chilli is the most tasty comfort food that this planet has to offer. It just wouldn’t be fair to forget the vegetarians and this is what we have come up with. All the Tex-Mex spices, white beans, corn and cream cheese but instead of using shredded chicken we use potato cubes which absorb the fabulous flavour. Serve with mealie bread fresh from your oven.','Gluten, lactose',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Start with the bread: Heat the oven to 170 C. In a large mixing bowl, add the sweet corn, beaten eggs and melted butter. Add the milk and a 1/4 of a tsp of salt per person (i.e. 1 tsp for 4 people) and stir. Mix in the flour and the paprika and combine to form a dough. If using a metallic or glass bread tin, grease with a little non-stick spray. Place dough in bread tin and bake for around 45 minutes or until a skewer or butter knife comes out clean. Leave to cool.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>While the bread is baking, bring a pot of salted water to the boil, chop the potatoes into small chunks (no need to peel) and boil until soft, about 15 minutes. Set aside.</li>\n<li>Heat oil in another pot over medium-high heat. Add onion and saut&eacute; for 4 minutes. Add garlic and saut&eacute; 30 seconds longer.</li>\n<li>Make the vegetable stock by dissolving the stock powder with the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Add the stock and the spice mix to the pot with the onion and garlic and season with salt and pepper to taste. Bring mixture just to a boil then reduce heat to medium-low and simmer for 15 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add cream cheese to soup along with potato, corn, whole beans and mashed beans and stir well. Simmer 5 - 10 minutes longer.</li>\n<li>Chop the fresh coriander.</li>\n<li>Stir in lemon juice and half the fresh coriander. Use the other half of the coriander to sprinkle over the bowls of chilli when serving.</li>\n<li>Serve a bowl of chilli with some mealie bread.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-03 08:38:22','2023-02-16 09:50:43',NULL),(206,'rknwya','White Chicken Chilli with Mealie Bread','This White Chicken Chilli is a variation of the well known Tex-Mex Chilli Con Carne, but is  a show-stopper in its own right.  It boasts all the usual spices, poached & shredded chicken, white beans, corn kernels and cream cheese. Add a South African twist by serving it with your own homemade mealie bread - it’s all in the kit!','Gluten, lactose',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Start with the bread: Heat the oven to 170 C.</li>\n<li>In a large mixing bowl, add the sweet corn, beaten egg(s), a teaspoon of salt (half a teaspoon if you are cooking for 1 or 2 people), melted butter and stir. Mix in 60 ml of warm milk if you are cooking for 4 people. If you are cooking for 1 or 2 people use 30 ml of milk.</li>\n<li>Mix in the flour and the paprika and combine to form a dough. Place dough in a greased bread tin and bake for around 45 minutes or until a skewer or butter knife comes out clean. Leave to cool.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Make your stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Set aside.</li>\n<li>Heat oil in another pot over medium-high heat. Add onion and saut&eacute; for 4 minutes. Add garlic and saut&eacute; 30 seconds longer.</li>\n<li>Add the stock, the chilli spice mix and season with salt and pepper to taste. Bring mixture just to a boil then reduce heat to medium-low and simmer for 15 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add cream cheese to soup along with chicken, corn, whole beans and mashed beans and stir well. Simmer 5 minutes longer.</li>\n<li>Chop the fresh coriander.</li>\n<li>Stir in lemon juice and half the fresh coriander. Use the other half of the coriander to sprinkle over the bowls of chilli when serving.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-03 09:03:24','2021-11-12 11:18:42',NULL),(207,'sxcgab','Mushroom Ragu with Creamy Polenta','We break with tradition here - instead of using meat in our rich tomato ragu, we use mixed mushrooms and butter beans. We add spinach because we hate you to forget your greens and we serve it on creamy polenta.','Lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Heat some oil in a pot over medium heat and add the onion. Cook for 5 minutes until softened.</li>\n<li>Add the garlic, thyme, basil, chilli flakes, salt and pepper and cook for 2 minutes more.</li>\n<li>Add the mushrooms and cook for a further 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the tomato paste, chopped tomatoes, butter beans and 1/4 teaspoon of sugar per person you are cooking for. Season with a little more salt and pepper. Cook for 10 minutes over a low heat.</li>\n<li>Make the stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>While the mushroom ragu is cooking, put the milk and stock into another large pot and bring to the boil. Once it is boiling, turn down the heat and, using a whisk to stir, slowly add the polenta bit by bit, all while stirring with the whisk. It will slowly start to thicken up. The process should take 5 minutes. Once it has thickened, turn the heat off and stir the cream cheese through the polenta with a wooden spoon.</li>\n<li>Add the spinach to the mushroom dish and stir through to allow the heat to wilt it. Cook for another 2 minutes and then turn the heat off.</li>\n<li>Serve a dollop of polenta in a bowl, topped with the mushroom ragu.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-03 09:12:51','2021-07-05 11:41:27',NULL),(208,'fohgpq','Stuffed Jacket Potatoes with Coleslaw','Baked potatoes stuffed with cream cheese, mushrooms, bell pepper and zucchini and topped with melted cheddar. Serve them with our fresh and tangy coleslaw for a healthy vegetarian meal.','Traces of Lactose',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 200C.</li>\n<li>Bring a pot of water to the boil and place the whole unpeeled potatoes into the water. Boil for 20 minutes.</li>\n<li>Carefully remove the potatoes from the water with a pair of tongs and place on a lined or greased baking sheet. Drizzle a little oil over each potato and roll it around to coat. Place in the oven and bake the potatoes for about 20 &ndash; 25 minutes. You will know they are cooked when the skins are a nice golden colour and you can stick a knife easily through them. Remove from the oven and allow them to cool enough to be able to handle them.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>While the potatoes are cooling, heat some oil and add the mushrooms, pepper and baby marrows and cook for about 5 minutes. Season with salt, pepper and Italian herbs.</li>\n<li>Once the potatoes are cool enough to handle, slice them in half. Gently holding a potato half in one hand (use a clean cloth to hold if it is still quite warm), use a spoon to scoop out the flesh of each into a bowl. Don&rsquo;t worry about scooping out all the flesh, it is OK to leave a thin border of flesh around the skin.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Use a potato masher to mash the potato flesh in the bowl. Once mashed, stir in the cream cheese, crushed garlic and some salt and pepper. Now take your veggie mix and stir this in as well.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Using a spoon, scoop the flesh mixture back into the skins. Top each with some of the grated cheese and place back in the oven for 10 minutes or until the cheese is nicely melted.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>While the potatoes are in the oven, make your coleslaw: combine the cabbage and carrots with the raisins and tangy mayo and mix together.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-03 09:23:22','2023-02-07 09:39:25','<h3>Tangy Mayo Dressing</h3>\n<p>The following mixed together makes 300 ml:</p>\n<p>125 ml cream or sour cream</p>\n<p>125 ml mayo</p>\n<p>60 ml white spriti vinegar</p>\n<p>15 ml sugar</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(209,'evleii','Beef & Feta Burgers with Creamy Tomato Sauce & Butter Fried Cabbage','These are the plumpest, juiciest burgers - must be the feta. Drop the bun and add dollops of your own homemade creamy tomato sauce and a side of cabbage flash-fried in butter. Burgers have never been this healthy!','Traces of Lactose',5,40,'<ol>\n<li>Place beef mince, salt &amp; pepper to taste and feta into a bowl. Beat the egg, add to the bowl and mix well. If you are cooking for 1 person then add half the egg. For 2 or 4 people the whole egg is fine. Use wet hands to form patties, two per person.</li>\n<li>Heat the oil in a large pan (if you do not have a large pan, do two batches) and fry the patties for 10 minutes, flipping them carefully after 3 to 4 minutes.</li>\n<li>While the patties are frying, whisk together the tomato paste and the cream. When the patties are done put them aside to keep warm and using the juices in the same pan, cook the tomato and cream mixture for a few minutes stirring well.</li>\n<li>Chop the parsley. Just before you take the creamy tomato sauce off the stove, stir in the chopped parsley. Taste to see if you would like to add any further salt and pepper.</li>\n<li>Using a fresh pan, melt the butter and stir fry the cabbage until it softens, leaving a little crunch in it, about 5 minutes. Add salt and pepper to taste.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Serve two patties with a good dollop of the sauce alongside the fried cabbage.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-03 09:36:49','2022-02-09 14:30:39',NULL),(210,'bmdakp','Vegetable Pilaf with Paneer','Paneer is an Indian cheese that makes a wonderful substitute for meat in spicy Eastern dishes. It absorbs the flavours particularly well while adding a good whack of protein to the meal. We combine it here with a spicy but not hot vegetable and rice pilaf for a well-rounded vegetarian meal.','Traces of Lactose, nuts',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Wash the rice in fresh water three times to remove the starch and then let it soak in a bowl of water while you are busy with the spices and veggies.</li>\n<li>Heat the oil over medium to high heat in a pot and fry the cumin seeds for one minute to release the fragrance.</li>\n<li>Add the onion and fry until transparent.</li>\n<li>Add the whole spices, garlic and ginger. Fry for 30 seconds.</li>\n<li>Add the ground spices and stir continuously while frying for 1 minute. If the spices are sticking to the pot add a dash more oil. Keep stirring.</li>\n<li>Add all your veggies and salt to taste and stir so that they are coated with the spice mixture.</li>\n<li>Add the amount of water specified on the rice package.</li>\n<li>Bring to the boil, then drain your soaking rice and add the drained rice to the pot. Cover the pot and reduce the heat so that the pot is simmering nicely.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Cook for 15 minutes checking water levels now and again. The aim is for the rice and veg to absorb all the water. After 15 minutes it should not be completely dry. Take off the heat.</li>\n<li>Put the paneer cubes into the pot and stir in gently. Put the lid back on and allow it to stand and steam gently in its own heat for 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Uncover the pot and add the lemon juice, fluffing up the rice with a fork.</li>\n<li>Chop the fresh coriander.</li>\n<li>Remove the cinnamon stick, pods and bay leaves and stir in the chopped coriander.</li>\n<li>Serve with a small handful of cashews over the top.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-04 06:11:59','2022-04-13 10:05:35',NULL),(211,'ukwlib','Sweet Corn Fritters with Black Bean Salsa','Our sweet corn fritters are good enough to eat straight from the oven with a knob of butter so try not to steal them before they get to the table. Add some fresh tomato and black bean salsa, a sprinkle of chopped coriander and a dollop of our special peri-mayonnaise to make a tasty and well-rounded meal.','Gluten',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 200C/180C fan and line a large baking tray with baking paper.</li>\n<li>Heat the oil in a small pan and fry the onion and&nbsp; the green pepper for 5 mins until softened. Meanwhile, mix the flour and spices in a bowl. Add the onions, green pepper, sweetcorn and beaten eggs, then mix together well. If you are cooking for 1 person then add the egg last, slowly. If it starts getting too sloppy, discard the rest of the egg.</li>\n<li>Spoon eight mounds of the mixture onto the baking tray, well spaced apart, then flatten slightly with the back of the spoon. Bake for 20 mins until set and golden.</li>\n<li>Meanwhile, mix together the salsa ingredients -&nbsp; onion, chopped tomatoes, black beans and lime juice and the fresh coriander. Taste for seasoning and add salt and black pepper to taste.</li>\n<li>Serve 1 &ndash; 2 fritters with a side of salsa and a dollop of peri-mayo for each person.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-04 06:14:30','2021-08-26 14:22:23',NULL),(213,'thidcn','Bobotie with  Rice','The old Cape Malay favourite gets a healthy make-over.  We lose the gluten but not the taste -you still get the mild curry flavour with high notes of fruit and spice, just like grandma used to make.','Lactose',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat oven to 190 degrees .C</li>\n<li>Grate the skin off your lemon to make the lemon zest.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a pot on a medium to high heat and saut&eacute; the onion.</li>\n<li>Add the meat and fry until brown, breaking up the lumps with a wooden spoon</li>\n<li>Add the grated carrot, garlic, raisins, spice mix and salt to taste. Saut&eacute; for 2 minutes.</li>\n<li>Stir in chutney, lemon zest and mashed butter beans and season generously with black pepper.</li>\n<li>Place in an oven dish.</li>\n<li>Beat together the eggs, milk, the nutmeg, salt and pepper and pour over the top of the meat. Tuck the bay leaves into the meat.</li>\n<li>Bake uncovered for 30 to 35 minutes &ndash; the custard should set.</li>\n<li>While the above is cooking bring a pot of water, salt and the rice to the boil. Time 20 minutes from when it boils. It should be done. Keep an eye that there is always enough water in the pot. Drain and serve topped with bobotie when it is ready.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-04 07:39:18','2022-10-04 14:49:58','<p>Not Cooking For Four?</p>\n<p>For 2 people use 2 eggs and 95 ml of milk.</p>\n<p>For 1 person use 1 egg and 50 ml of milk.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(214,'guptjn','Lemon Garlic Chicken served with Corn on the Cob and Broccoli Slaw','The chicken is marinated and baked in soy sauce, lemon, chilli flakes and garlic and then served with corn on the cob and a fabulously light but tasty broccoli salad with almond flakes and raisins.','Nuts',5,55,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Place drumsticks in a baking dish and pour on the marinade. Refrigerate and let marinate for 30 minutes, turning every now and again.</li>\n<li>While the chicken is marinating, prepare your broccoli slaw:&nbsp; Bring a pot of salted water to the boil and boil the broccoli for 2 minutes. Plunge it into icy cold water to stop it cooking further.</li>\n<li>Toss the broccoli, chopped onion, raisins and almonds together in a salad bowl with the dressing. Let it sit for 30 minutes at room temperature to let the flavours develop.</li>\n<li>Once the chicken has marinated, place the baking dish in the oven for 25 minutes, flipping the chicken halfway through. Leave the marinade in the baking dish.</li>\n<li>While the chicken is cooking, bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Add the corn and turn down the heat. Simmer for 20 minutes.</li>\n<li>Serve 1 &ndash; 2 drumsticks, corn with an optional knob of butter and salt and a serving of broccoli salad.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-04 07:41:43','2022-11-07 10:41:00','<p>Tangy Mayo Dressing</p>\n<p><br />1/2 cup cream or sour cream<br />1/2 cup mayo<br />1/4 cup white spirit vinegar<br />1 TBS sugar<br />1/2 tsp salt</p>\n<p><br />Mix all together well.</p>'),(216,'qvuvqy','Peach, Cucumber & Chickpea Salad with Roasted Chicken Pieces','The peach and cucumber add freshness and colour to this nutritious salad with its base of pearled barley and chickpeas. Serve with roasted chicken drumsticks and thighs for a satisfying and delicious meal.','None',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 220 C.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Put the barley in a pot, cover with the amount of boiling water stipulated on the stock package and add the stock powder. Stir to mix. Bring to a boil and then turn heat down. Simmer, covered with a lid, for 40 &ndash; 45 minutes, checking the water level regularly. Check the barley is cooked, drain it and place in a large salad bowl to cool.</li>\n<li>While the barley is cooking you can cook your chicken pieces: pat each&nbsp; dry with a paper towel and place them in a bowl. Rub them with some oil and season with salt, pepper and Italian herbs. Toss well to coat.</li>\n<li>Line a baking pan with foil. If you do not have foil then lightly grease the tray. Place your chicken pieces on it and into the oven. Bake for 30 &ndash; 40 minutes. They are ready when the juices run clear and there is no more pink meat at the bone.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Cut the tomatoes in half if you prefer them small.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Once the barley has cooled, add the cucumber, peaches, tomatoes, and chickpeas. Season with salt and pepper. Toss until well combined.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Stir in the dressing.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Serve the salad alongside your roasted chicken pieces.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-04 07:51:14','2022-07-09 09:24:25',NULL),(217,'hzvpqw','Lentil, Tomato & Feta Salad with Pan Fried Halloumi','This lovely looking salad is as tasty as it is colourful, with mint, sun-dried tomatoes and olives adding a punch of flavour. Pan-fried halloumi is added, along with some feta to make it a well rounded meal.','Traces of Lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Make your stock by adding the powder to the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Bring the stock to a simmer in a pot, add the lentils and simmer very gently for 15 minutes. If you boil the lentils too hard they will be mushy. The pot should be barely bubbling. When done, drain and allow to cool.</li>\n<li>Fry the halloumi in a little oil for about 4 minutes in a hot pan. Toss the cubes a little to brown all sides.</li>\n<li>Chop the apple into small bits. Pick the mint leaves off any stem and chop the leaves. Discard the stem.</li>\n<li>When the lentils are cool enough, toss them together with the tomatoes, apple, mint, olives, feta and sun dried tomatoes. Pour the dressing over the top and toss lightly. Arrange the halloumi on top and serve.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-04 07:51:53','2022-09-26 17:29:33','<p>Lemon Mint Dressing</p>\n<p>1/2 cup extra-virgin olive oil</p>\n<p>1/2 cup lemon juice&nbsp;</p>\n<p>1/4 cup packed fresh mint leaves</p>\n<p>3 tablespoons honey</p>\n<p>1 tablespoon Dijon mustard</p>\n<p>2 cloves garlic, roughly chopped</p>\n<p>&nbsp;1/4 teaspoon fine sea salt&nbsp;</p>\n<p>10 twists of freshly ground black pepper</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Mix all together well. This dressing will keep in the fridge for a week.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(218,'lomblm','Mediterranean Style Pasta with Fried Halloumi','Our homemade tomato passata gives this dish it’s rich Mediterranean flavour. Top with halloumi pan-fried in butter for a satisfying and delicious meal.','Traces of Lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Bring a pot of water to the boil. Add salt and the penne pasta. Boil for 11 minutes and then drain and set aside.</li>\n<li>While the pasta is cooking fry the halloumi over a medium to high heat in a tiny bit of oil. It should be nicely browned on both sides. This should take 3 - 5 minutes. Set aside.</li>\n<li>Heat some more oil in a pot and fry the onion for a few minutes. Add the mushrooms and cook for another few minutes stirring occasionally. Add the paprika and chilli flakes and stir in well for about 30 seconds.</li>\n<li>Pour the passata into the onion and mushroom mixture and cook for a few minutes until heated through. Add a pinch of sugar and salt and pepper to taste.</li>\n<li>Chop the basil leaves roughly.</li>\n<li>Stir in the drained pasta and the chopped basil leaves.</li>\n<li>Serve topped with the fried halloumi pieces.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-05 07:00:48','2023-03-03 11:52:53','<h3>Passata</h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Ingredients:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped</p>\n<p>1 large onion</p>\n<p>2 TBS olive oil</p>\n<p>4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic</p>\n<p>8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)</p>\n<p>1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste</p>\n<p>2 tsp ground black pepper</p>\n<p>2 TBS tomato paste</p>\n<p>Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Method:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.</p>\n<p>Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.</p>\n<p>Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.</p>\n<p>Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.</p>\n<p>Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</p>'),(219,'ripxho','Peach, Cucumber & Chickpea Salad with Cubed Feta','A highly satisfying barley and chickpea salad for the vegetarians.  Yellow cling peach and cucumber add freshness with cubes of feta adding the protein.','Traces of Lactose',5,45,'<ol><li>Put the barley in a pot. Dissolve the stock powder with the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Pour onto the barley and stir to mix. Bring to a boil and then turn heat down. Simmer, covered with a lid, for 40 – 50 minutes, checking the water level regularly. Check the barley is cooked, drain it and place in a large salad bowl to cool.</li><li>Cut the tomatoes in half if you prefer them small.&nbsp;</li><li>Once the barley has cooled, add the cucumber, peaches, tomatoes, and chickpeas. Season with salt and pepper. Toss until well combined.&nbsp;</li><li>Stir in the dressing.&nbsp;</li><li>Serve with cubes of feta on top.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-05 07:03:52','2022-03-30 16:00:07',NULL),(220,'foyzpg','Lentil Salad with Chopped Chorizo & Feta','This lovely looking salad is as tasty as it is colourful, with mint, sun-dried tomatoes and olives adding a punch of flavour. To this we add pieces of chorizo, a spicy pork sausage that has been cured and smoked, a lovely fresh lemon mint dressing and pieces of feta cheese.','Traces of Lactose',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Make your stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Bring the stock to a simmer in a pot, add the lentils and simmer very gently for 15 minutes. If you boil the lentils too hard they will be mushy. The pot should be barely bubbling. When done, drain and allow to cool.</li>\n<li>Chop the apple into small bits.</li>\n<li>Pick the mint leaves off the stem and chop them.</li>\n<li>When the lentils are cool enough, toss them together with the tomatoes, apple, mint leaves, olives, sun dried tomatoes and chopped chorizo.</li>\n<li>Pour the dressing onto the lentil salad and toss lightly. Arrange the feta on top and serve.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-05 07:43:30','2023-04-13 09:20:59','<p>Lemon Mint Dressing</p>\n<p>1/2 cup lemon juice</p>\n<p>1/2 cup olive oil</p>\n<p>1/4 cup fresh chopped mint leaves</p>\n<p>3 Tbsp honey</p>\n<p>1 Tbsp Dijon mustard</p>\n<p>2 tsp crushed garlic</p>\n<p>1/4 tsp salt</p>\n<p>10 twists black pepper</p>\n<p>Put all ingredients into a food processor and blend until smooth. This makes about 300 ml and keeps for a week or two in the fridge.</p>'),(221,'ffnunn','Honey & Mustard Chicken on Roasted Vegetables','Honey, mustard and dry white wine – these are the basics for a heavenly sauce. Add chicken thighs, veggies and the fact that everything is cooked in only one pan and you’re winning!','None',5,55,'<ol>\n<li>Pre-heat the oven to 180 C.</li>\n<li>In a large baking dish, spread out all your vegetables.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Lay the chicken over the vegetables and season with salt, pepper and parsley</li>\n<li>Pour the honey mustard sauce into a bowl and mix. Add a tiny bit of hot water to get it to mix better if needed.</li>\n<li>Spoon the honey mustard sauce over each piece of chicken and then pour the rest of the sauce over the vegetables.</li>\n<li>Place in the oven and cook for 50-60 minutes, or until chicken is cooked and the vegetables are soft.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-05 08:25:27','2022-02-04 10:25:17',NULL),(222,'lolpcu','Minestrone Verde with Homemade Nutty Wheat & Seed Loaf','A tasty summer vegetable soup with white kidney beans served with warm buttered seed loaf fresh from the oven. This is one for the vegetarians but will definitely please everyone.','Gluten, lactose',5,55,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 180 C. Unwrap the dough from the plastic wrap. Squish into a greased bread tin. Once the oven is heated, bake the bread for 50 &ndash; 60 minutes. You will know the bread is cooked if you stick a skewer or bread knife into it and it comes out clean. Remove from the tin and leave to cool.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Once the bread has been baking for 30 minutes, start with the Minestrone Verde: place a large pot on the stove. Add some oil and allow to heat on a medium high heat.</li>\n<li>Add the leeks to the pot and soften for 5 &ndash; 6 minutes. Add the baby marrow and soften for 4 &ndash; 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Make up your vegetable stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Add the stock to the pot with the leeks and baby marrow.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add the white kidney beans, along with a generous sprinkle of salt and pepper. Allow to simmer for about 10 minutes.</li>\n<li>Mix in the spinach and peas. Simmer for 3 minutes.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Serve the Minestrone Verde in bowls, drizzle with a little lemon juice and basil pesto, and if desired season with a little more salt and pepper.&nbsp; Serve with a slice of warm, buttered seed bread.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-05 08:28:31','2022-03-30 08:57:01',NULL),(223,'jjanhx','Chickpea Korma','A vegetarian version of a mild, fragrant curry with a taste of Thai  - this dish will fill your kitchen with an exotic spicy aroma -  and it tastes as good as it smells! You won’t believe how easy it is to put together.  Note: The salad in the picture is not included.','None',5,25,'<ol>\n<li>Place rice and salt into a pot of water and bring to the boil. Time 20 minutes from boiling and it should be cooked. Keep an eye on the water level, don&rsquo;t let it burn dry.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Chop the coriander and set aside for now.</li>\n<li>While the rice is cooking you can start with the chickpea korma. Add the butter to a pot and melt it on a medium heat. Add the onion, ginger and garlic and fry for 5 minutes. Add the Korma powder and fry for another 1 minute.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Add the yellow pepper, baby marrow and half of the fresh coriander to the pot and cook until golden in colour, about 8 minutes.</li>\n<li>Add the coconut cream, chickpeas and shredded coconut to the pot. Add ⅔&nbsp; of the yoghurt to the mix to loosen it a little. Bring to a boil, then lower heat to a simmer, cover and cook, stirring occasionally for 30 minutes. You can use the rest of the yoghurt to thin the mixture if necessary.</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Check for seasoning before serving, adding salt and pepper if needed. Serve with rice. Top with a dollop of extra&nbsp; yogurt if you have not used it all and the rest of the fresh coriander.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-05 08:32:16','2022-10-04 15:06:14',NULL),(224,'luolvn','Cheesy Pork Sausage & Broccoli Casserole','This is another one for the low carbers - low in carbs but very high in flavour. Pork sausages, broccoli, mushrooms, some mixed herbs and our own homemade cheese sauce makes a healthy and satisfying family meal.','Gluten, lactose',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a pan and semi-cook the sausages until they are firm enough to remove and cut into thick slices. This should only take about 5 minutes. Use a sharp knife to slice them when they are cool enough to handle.</li>\n<li>Boil or steam the broccoli for 2 minutes only. When you drain it run cold water over it to stop the cooking process.</li>\n<li>Place the broccoli, raw mushroom chunks and semi cooked sausage into an oven dish.</li>\n<li>Gently heat your cheese sauce until it is pourable/spreadable. Do not let it boil.</li>\n<li>Spread the cheese sauce onto the other ingredients, sprinkle with the mixed herbs and gently mix together. The cheese sauce is already seasoned but add salt and pepper to your own taste if you would like to.</li>\n<li>Sprinkle with the grated cheddar and bake in the oven for 20 to 30 minutes.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-09 06:56:48','2021-06-25 14:16:15',NULL),(225,'yzpuvw','Summer Chicken & Peach Bake','A delightful combination of floured chicken and peach slices cooked in orange juice, honey, soy sauce, vinegar and chicken stock. So easy to put together, it can be served with just beans for those watching their waistlines and there is the option of adding rice for those that aren’t.','Gluten',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 180 C.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Cook the rice if you choose to serve rice. If you prefer to minimise your carbs, leave it out. Bring it to the boil covered in salted water. Time 20 minutes from boiling point and it should be done. Drain and keep warm. Do this while the chicken is baking.</li>\n<li>Place your chicken pieces in the brown bag with the seasoned flour. Shake around to coat.</li>\n<li>Heat some oil in a pot/pan or if you have a dish that can be used on the stove and in the oven, then use that.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Brown the chicken pieces on all sides. If you are using a pot or pan to do this, then remove the chicken into a baking dish.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Pour the Orange Sauce over the chicken and place the dish in the oven for 40 minutes. Remove from the oven and dot the peach slices in amongst the chicken. Put back in the oven for 5 more minutes.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Steam or boil the green beans for 5 - 10 minutes, depending on how crunchy you like them.</li>\n<li>Serve the chicken with green beans. If you choose to have rice, serve it on the rice.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-09 07:59:07','2022-11-15 10:14:17','<p>Save Washing!</p>\n<p>Place your seasoned flour in a brown paper bag if you have one and then toss the chicken pieces in the bag.</p>'),(226,'gxtbwa','Creamy Tomato & Ground Beef Pasta Bake','This dish may sound rather run-of-the-mill but the secret is in the sauce! Our own homemade tomato sauce is, even if we say so ourselves, just fabulous. And it contains no unhealthy ingredients and no nasty chemicals. Add sour cream to that and you have a winner. We layer bow-tie pasta with the creamy tomato mince, wilted spinach and grated mozzarella. Delicious and nutritious!','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,45,'<ol><li>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.</li><li>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil, add the pasta and boil for 8 minutes. Drain and place into an oven dish.</li><li>Heat some oil in a pan or pot and fry the mince until evenly browned. Use a wooden spoon to keep breaking up the clumps and moving the mince around to fry evenly.</li><li>Add the tomato sauce, sour cream and thyme. Mix well and take the pot off the heat.</li><li>Wilt the spinach by putting it into a bowl and pouring boiling water over it. Drain, let it cool slightly and then squeeze as much water out as you can.</li><li>Pour mince and tomato mix over the pasta and then arrange the spinach over that.</li><li>Top the dish with the grated mozzarella.</li><li>Bake for 30 minutes.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-10 09:08:42','2022-07-17 09:32:55','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">5-Minute Tomato Sauce</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">50 grams tomato paste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">240 g tub tomato puree&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">80 grams honey</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 Tablespoons apple cider vinegar</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 Tablespoons onion powder</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 teaspoon garlic powder</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 teaspoon salt</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 teaspoon cinnamon</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 teaspoon black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of nutmeg</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of chilli flakes</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Place all in a Nutribullet or blender and whizz until a smooth texture is reached.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This can be kept in the fridge for two weeks, probably longer because of the vinegar in it.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(228,'cyybbe','Creamy Tomato & Soya Pasta Bake','This dish may sound rather run-of-the-mill but the secret is in the sauce! Our own homemade tomato sauce is, even if we say so ourselves, just fabulous. And it contains no unhealthy ingredients and no nasty chemicals. Add sour cream to that and you have a winner. We layer bow-tie pasta with the creamy tomato soya, wilted spinach and grated mozzarella. Delicious and nutritious!','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius.</li>\n<li>Soak the soya in boiling water in a 1:1 ratio for 10 minutes.</li>\n<li>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil, add the pasta and boil for 8 minutes. Drain and place into an oven dish.</li>\n<li>When the soya is finished its 10-minute soak, heat some oil in a pan or pot on a medium high heat and fry the soya for two minutes, stirring.</li>\n<li>Add the tomato sauce, sour cream and thyme. Mix well and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes. Take the pot off the heat.</li>\n<li>Wilt the spinach by putting it into a bowl and pouring boiling water over it. Drain, let it cool slightly and then squeeze as much water out as you can.</li>\n<li>Pour soya and tomato mix over the pasta and then arrange the spinach over that.</li>\n<li>Top the dish with the grated mozzarella.</li>\n<li>Bake for 30 minutes.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-10 09:23:22','2022-09-26 17:46:00','<p>Homemade Tomato Sauce</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>4 Tbsp tomato paste (2 sachets)</p>\n<p>1 x 410g tin tomato puree</p>\n<p>80 g sugar</p>\n<p>60 ml apple cider vinegar</p>\n<p>2 Tbsp onion powder</p>\n<p>1 tsp garlic powder</p>\n<p>1 tsp salt</p>\n<p>1 tsp cinnamon</p>\n<p>pinch of nutmeg</p>\n<p>pinch of chilli flakes</p>\n<p>Mix all in a nutrbullet or blender and store in the fridge. This makes 400 ml.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(229,'uupxio','Crustless Broccoli Quiche with Tomato Pesto & Leafy Greens','This is a delicious way to eat your broccoli - that superfood that packs such a health punch. So easy to put together, you may find it becomes a family favourite.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,45,'<ol>\n<li>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees Celsius and lightly grease an oven dish of about 20 x 24 cm.</li>\n<li>Bring a pot of lightly salted water to the boil. Put the broccoli in and time 2 minutes only. Take out, drain and run cold water over it to stop it cooking.</li>\n<li>Melt the butter.</li>\n<li>In a large bowl beat the eggs and add the melted butter. Stir in the flour, then the cottage cheese, cream, grated cheddar and grated Parmesan. Gently stir in the broccoli.</li>\n<li>Season with salt and black pepper, stir again and pour into the oven dish.</li>\n<li>Bake for 40 to 45 minutes. It should be golden on top, going brown around the edges and firm to the touch.</li>\n<li>Serve with 1 tablespoon of pesto and some leafy greens on the side.</li>\n</ol>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-11 09:35:47','2022-05-13 13:23:08',NULL),(230,'jbnqnp','Crispy Tofu Barley Bowl with Roasted Cashews','Learn how to make crispy tofu easily in a pan and you will want to use it in all sorts of meals. It makes a lovely topping, accompanied by roasted cashews, for our barley salad bowl. The barley is cooked in stock for extra flavour and tossed with cherry tomatoes and cucumber in a sweet and sour dressing of red wine vinegar and sweet chilli sauce.','Nuts',5,35,'<ol>\n<li>Make your stock by adding the vegetable stock powder in your kit with the specified amount of boiling water.</li>\n<li>Place the barley and the vegetable stock in a pot and bring to the boil. Reduce to a simmer and cook with the lid on for 35 minutes. The barley should have absorbed most of the liquid. Keep an eye on the pot to make sure it is not dry. Drain when it is ready.</li>\n<li>Carefully toss the tofu with the seasoned cornflour and fry in hot oil until the pieces are&nbsp; golden brown. Drain on paper towels.</li>\n<li>Halve the cherry tomatoes and add them and the cucumber to the Sweet Chilli dressing. Add the barley and toss all together.</li>\n<li>Serve the barley mix in a bowl topped with crispy tofu and cashew nuts.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-11-12 07:26:37','2023-01-02 12:48:22',NULL),(231,'kjsblh','One Pot Italian Pork Mince and Gnocchi','This easy one pot dish sees pork mince fried with an Italian herb mix, an addition of lots of chopped tomatoes with their juice which is used to simmer the gnocchi in, a couple of handfuls of fresh spinach wilted into the mix and then finished off with wonderfully melty mozzarella and parmesan on the top.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,25,'<div>Heat some oil in a big pot or skillet and add the onion, cooking it for 3 minutes, medium to high heat.</div><div>Add garlic and fry for 30 seconds before adding the pork mince.</div><div>Use a wooden spoon to break up the pork mince so that it does not form clumps and it fries evenly. Add the Italian herbs and salt and pepper to taste. Let it fry for 5 to 7 minutes so that it is well browned.</div><div>Add the gnocchi, tomatoes, basil, oregano, a pinch or two of sugar and salt and pepper to taste. If the sauce is too thick add a little water.</div><div>Cover the pot and simmer for 5 minutes. Keep checking that nothing is catching on the bottom of the pot.</div><div>Stir in spinach and the pinch of nutmeg and keep simmering until the spinach is wilted. This should only take 2 minutes.</div><div>Sprinkle both cheeses on top. Cover the pot and let the cheese melt - 2 to 3 minutes.</div><div>Let it cool for a couple of minutes and then serve immediately.</div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-12-08 07:51:37','2021-04-18 14:47:21',NULL),(232,'khubqk','Gnocchi & Soya in a Tomato Sauce with Cheese Topping','Gnocchi, soya and couscous is simmered in a herby tomato sauce. A couple of handfuls of fresh spinach is then wilted into the mix which is finished off with a wonderfully melty mozzarella and parmesan topping.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,25,'<div>Soak your soya in boiling water for 10 minutes. Drain well.</div>\n<div>Heat some oil in a big pot or skillet and add the onion, cooking it for 3 minutes, medium to high heat.</div>\n<div>Add the drained soya and cook for 3 minutes.</div>\n<div>Add garlic and fry for 30 seconds.</div>\n<div>Add the gnocchi, couscous, tomatoes, basil, oregano and salt &amp; pepper to taste. Add 1/2 teaspoon of sugar for each person you are cooking for i.e. for 2 people 1 teaspoon, for 4 people 2 teaspoons.</div>\n<div>Cover the pot and simmer for 8 minutes. Keep checking that nothing is catching on the bottom of the pot. If the mixture is too thick add a little water.</div>\n<div>Stir in spinach and a pinch of nutmeg and keep simmering until the spinach is wilted. This should only take 2 minutes.</div>\n<div>Sprinkle both cheeses on top. Cover the pot and let the cheese melt - 2 to 3 minutes.</div>\n<div>Let it cool for a couple of minutes and then serve immediately.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-12-10 07:19:27','2023-03-27 17:23:25',NULL),(233,'vthrvx','Layered Aubergine, Lentil & Mozzarella Bake','This dish tastes as good as it looks when it comes out of the oven, golden and bubbling. The aubergines are pre-baked with a brushing of oil and the lentil mix contains brown lentils, onion, garlic, tomatoes and roughly mashed butternut. Topped with mozzarella, this bake is delicious served with leafy greens.','Traces of Lactose',15,45,'<div>Heat oven to 220 degrees Celsius.</div>\n<div>Place lentils in a pot, cover with water, bring to the boil, turn the heat down and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes. Keep an eye on the water level and check the consistency of the lentils. Do not overcook.</div>\n<div>Bring another pot of lightly salted water to the boil, pop the butternut cubes in and boil for 15 minutes. Drain &amp; mash roughly.</div>\n<div>Brush your slices of aubergine with a little oil and place on a baking tray in the oven. Bake for 15 minutes, turning once. Take out and set aside to cool.</div>\n<div>Heat some oil in a big pot. Cook the onion for 3 minutes. Add the garlic and fry for a further 30 seconds. Then tip in the tomato and the butternut and stir. Add a little water if very thick and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring frequently to stop the mixture thickening.</div>\n<div>Add 1/4 tsp of sugar for each person that you are cooking for, ie 1 tsp for 4 people.</div>\n<div>Chop the fresh basil. Add the drained lentils, the basil and salt &amp; black pepper to taste.</div>\n<div>Using a 20 x 20cm (approx) oven dish, create layers starting with the lentil mix, topping with aubergine slices. Repeat this and end with aubergine slices. Place the mozzarella on top and bake for 15 minutes. The dish should be golden and bubbling.</div>\n<div>Cool for 5 minutes and serve with leafy greens.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-12-10 08:22:35','2021-05-24 14:21:13',NULL),(234,'jlaprm','Chicken Stir Fry with Thai Peanut Sauce','The mildly spicy and rich peanut sauce takes an ordinary chicken stir fry and makes it really sublime. The substantial amount of chicken and veggies together with the thick peanut sauce makes this dish satisfying enough to leave out the usual rice - good news for those trying to cut carbs!','None',5,25,'<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Heat some oil in a large pot over medium-high heat and add the chicken, ginger and garlic. Stir fry for 7 minutes. Chicken should no longer be pink in the centre. Remove from the pot and set aside.</div>\n<div>Into the same pot - no need to wash - place the broccoli, carrot and green beans with some hot water - the water should be 40 ml per person you are cooking for. Put the lid on and steam for two minutes. Remove and drain the veg.</div>\n<div>Give the pot a quick rinse and dry it. Add some more oil, heat on medium-high heat and stir-fry the onion and red pepper for 4 minutes.</div>\n<div>Add the steamed broccoli, green beans and carrot to the pot. Add a little more oil if you need to and stir-fry for 3 to 5 minutes more. The veggies should be tender but crisp.</div>\n<div>Turn the heat down to medium-low and add the chicken. Stir in the Thai peanut sauce until everything is heated through.</div>\n<div>Chop the fresh parsley and use it to garnish each serving. Serve in bowls.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-12-19 12:06:49','2022-07-09 09:49:28',NULL),(235,'oygtqi','Bolognese Mince with Zoodles','Our Bolognese mince is no ordinary mince. It has exceptional depth of flavour thanks to mushrooms, red wine and our very special homemade Marinara sauce. Paired with zoodles instead of spaghetti, this makes an excellent low carb meal.','Traces of Lactose',5,45,'<div>In a pot, heat the olive oil. Add the onion and soften. Add the mushrooms and soften.</div><div>Add the mince, and break apart with a wooden spoon and allow it to brown.<br>Season to taste with salt and black pepper.</div><div>Add the red wine and marinara sauce. Turn the heat down and allow it to simmer for about 15 minutes.</div><div>In a pan heat a little oil and flash-fry the zoodles for 2 minutes.</div><div>Serve a portion of zoodles into each bowl, serve the mince over the zoodles and sprinkle a bit of grated cheese over each helping.</div>',790,55,58,34,1,'2020-12-20 12:34:16','2020-12-20 13:04:17',NULL),(236,'iblyku','Caramelised Onion & Butternut Quiche','Caramelised onion is always a top notch addition to any dish but takes ages to make. We make it for you to add to this rich crustless quiche along with butternut and grated cheddar.','Lactose',15,45,'<div>Heat oven to 180 degrees Celsius and grease an oven dish.</div><div>Put a pot of lightly salted water on to boil. When boiling add the butternut, bring back to the boil and then time 10 minutes. Drain and set aside to cool.</div><div>Beat the eggs.</div><div>Pour in the cream and yoghurt and mix well,</div><div>Stir in the grated cheese.</div><div>Add the caramelised onions and the butternut and stir into the mixture, distributing evenly.</div><div>Add salt and black pepper to taste</div><div>Pour into the oven dish and bake for 40 to 45 minutes. The quiche should be a golden colour and firm in the middle.</div><div>Cool for 5 minutes and serve with a few greens on the side.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2020-12-21 07:43:39','2022-06-30 12:04:04','<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>How to Caramelize Onions</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Makes 500 ml</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Several (3 to 5 depending on sizd) medium or large onions, yellow, white, or red</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Extra virgin olive oil</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Butter, optional</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Kosher salt</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Sugar, optional</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Balsamic vinegar, optional</p>\n<p>Method</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Cut the onions root to tip:<br />Slice 1/2-inch off the stem ends of the onions and the roots off of the root end. Place the onions cut side down on</p>\n<p>the cutting board. Cut them in half through the root end. Peel back the peels from the onions.</p>\n<p>Lay the onions cut side down and make angled cuts into each onion, aimed at the center, cutting almost all the way, but not completely through the root end. Make the cuts to your desired level of thickness.</p>\n<p>The root end will help hold the onion together as you cut it, making it easier to cut. Then cut a V in the root end to cut out the tough root holding the slices together.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 2\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Heat the olive oil and add the onion:<br />Use a wide, thick-bottomed sauté pan for maximum pan contact with the onions. Coat the bottom of the pan with olive oil, or a mixture of olive oil and butter, (about 1 teaspoon per onion).</p>\n<p>Heat the pan on medium high heat until the oil is shimmering. Add the onion slices and stir to coat the onions with the oil. Spread the onions out evenly over the pan and let cook, stirring occasionally.</p>\n<p>Depending on how strong your stovetop burner is you may need to reduce the heat to medium or medium low to prevent the onions from burning or drying out.</p>\n<p>After 10 minutes, sprinkle some salt over the onions, and if you want, you can add some sugar to help with the caramelization process. (I add only about a teaspoon of sugar for 5 onions, you can add more.) One trick to keeping the onions from drying out as they cook is to add a little water to the pan.</p>\n<p>Stir the onions every few minutes:<br />Let the onions cook for 30 minutes to 1 hour more, stirring every few minutes. As soon as the onions start stickingto the pan, let them stick a little and brown, but then stir them before they burn.</p>\n<p>The trick is to leave them alone enough to brown (if you stir them too often, they won\'t brown), but not so long so that they burn. After the first 20 to 30 minutes you may want to lower the stove temperature a little, and add a little more oil, if you find the onions are verging on burning.</p>\n<p>A metal spatula will help you scrape up the browned bits from the bottom of the pan as the caramelization proceeds. As the onions cook down, you may find you need to scrape the pan every minute, instead of every few minutes.</p>\n<p>Continue to cook and scrape, cook and scrape, until the onions are a rich, browned color. At the end of the cooking process you might want to add a little balsamic vinegar or wine to help deglaze the pan and bring some additional flavor to the onions.</p>\n<p>Store refrigerated for several days in an air-tight container.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>'),(237,'dnrker','Creamy Mustard Chicken Bowl','Is it a soup? Is it a stew? No, it’s low carb super-chicken! Cubes of chicken breast are simmered in cream and whole grain mustard, along with red onion, green beans and mushrooms. So simple, full of flavour and easy to prepare - it\'s a winner.','Lactose',5,25,'<div>Heat a little oil in a pot and add the mushrooms. Soften for a few minutes.</div><div>Add the red onion, the green beans and the chicken to the mushrooms and cook for 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Season well with salt and pepper.&nbsp;</div><div>Add the cream and mustard and stir all together well. Simmer for 15 minutes.&nbsp;</div><div>Serve immediately in bowls.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-01-06 10:38:12','2021-03-20 14:57:33',NULL),(238,'qeuafr','Sausage Carbonara','Don’t let the plain name or the short cooking time fool you! This is a winner. Tagliatelle pasta and black pepper encrusted pork sausage balls are tossed together in a traditional egg and Parmesan based sauce. Chopped rocket adds a lovely pop of green.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,25,'<div>Bring a big pot of salted water to the boil, add a bit of oil and the tagliatelle. Boil without the lid for 9 minutes. Stir every now and again to stop the pasta sticking together. When the time is up take the pot off the stove and dip a mug in to reserve some pasta cooking water for later. Half to 3/4 of a mug should be plenty. Then drain the pasta and set aside.</div>\n<div>Squeeze the sausages out of their skin and, with wet hands to stop stickiness, form little sausage balls. Lay them out on a board and sprinkle with black pepper - pat to make the pepper stick. Turn the balls over and repeat on the other side.</div>\n<div>Heat some oil in a big non-stick pot and fry the sausage balls until done. Being small, this should only take 5 minutes or so. Add more oil if needed.</div>\n<div>While the balls are frying, beat the eggs, add the chopped rocket and most of the parmesan to the egg mixture. Add a dash of the pasta water to loosen. Set aside.</div>\n<div>When the sausage balls are done, put the pasta into the sausage pot and toss gently while heating through.</div>\n<div>Take off the heat and stir in the egg mixture for 1 minute. The egg cooks in the residual heat and forms a lovely sauce. Add some of the reserved pasta water to loosen the mixture as required.</div>\n<div>Season to taste with salt. Serve with a little of the remaining grated parmesan on top.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-01-07 10:56:16','2022-09-05 10:30:37',NULL),(239,'snozdk','Crusty Peanut Chicken with Creamed Spinach','It is amazing what you can do with chicken breast! Here it is grilled with a peanut, lime, garlic and chilli topping and served with creamed spinach. We show you a way to make spinach that is easy and so delicious that it should even convert the spinach haters out there!','Gluten & Lactose',5,25,'<div>With a sharp knife cut a criss-cross pattern into the chicken breasts on both sides. No need to be too artistic here!</div>\n<div>Mix together two pinches of salt, some coarsely ground black pepper into some olive oil. Rub this mixture onto the chicken breasts.</div>\n<div>Fry them with a little oil in a frying pan on one side for 5 minutes.</div>\n<div>Take the chicken out and place into an oven dish.</div>\n<div>Put the peanut butter, lime juice, crushed garlic and chilli flakes mix into a bowl. Add enough water to give you a spoonable consistency.</div>\n<div>Spoon the peanut mixture over the top of the chicken breasts. Heat your grill and grill the chicken about 10 cm from the element for 5 minutes or a bit longer if you are not sure if the chicken is cooked.</div>\n<div>In a pot melt the butter. Stir in the flour to make a paste. Turn your heat down to medium and add the milk bit by bit stirring all the time to keep lumps from forming. Add the vegetable stock powder and keep stirring as the sauce thickens.</div>\n<div>When the sauce is thickened put in the spinach and keep stirring for another minute or two so that the spinach is completely wilted down.</div>\n<div>Taste for seasoning and add salt and pepper if you require.</div>\n<div>Serve each person with a crusty chicken breast and some creamed spinach.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-01-21 10:11:21','2022-08-26 08:32:08',NULL),(240,'gweidy','Marinated Tofu with Fried Rice','Tofu is one of the most versatile and easy to cook vegetarian options. Here we marinate it in a sweet and sour marinade and then use the marinade to make a sauce for your pan-fried tofu. Fried rice, with its peas, corn, carrots, onion and garlic is the perfect accompaniment.','None',5,35,'<div>Place the marinade into a bowl with the diced tofu, stir it in gently, and let it sit, covered, in the fridge for 15 minutes while your rice is cooking.</div>\n<div>Place the rice and some salted water into a pot and bring to the boil. Time 20 minutes from when it boils and your rice should be ready. Drain into a colander and then pour cold water through it to cool it. Cold rice makes better fried rice than hot rice.</div>\n<div>Strain the tofu but do not discard the marinade.</div>\n<div>Heat a little oil in a pan and fry the tofu until it is golden brown, stirring occasionally. This should only take 5 minutes</div>\n<div>Add the cornstarch to the marinade in a bowl and stir until very well combined. Pour into the frying pan with the tofu and cook until it thickens. Take off the heat and keep warm.</div>\n<div>In a large pot heat some more oil and add the onion, carrots and garlic. Add more oil if you need to and fry for 2 minutes. Add the peas and corn kernels and fry for 2 minutes more. Add the rice and soy sauce and cook for 3 minutes or until the rice is hot.</div>\n<div>Serve a portion of fried rice topped with the marinated tofu. Top with chopped chives.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-01-22 09:09:50','2021-09-10 09:27:29',NULL),(241,'takyxu','Wholewheat Penne Arrabbiata','Arrabbiata sauce consists of tomato, garlic and chillies cooked in olive oil. We send the chilli in olive oil to make things easier for you and we add aubergine and mushroom. The wholewheat penne is freshly homemade. Parmesan and rocket are stirred through the pasta before serving. Delicious!','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,25,'<div>Bring a big pot of salted water to the boil. Put in the pasta and time for 4 minutes. Stir now and again to make sure it&rsquo;s not sticking together. When you drain it, reserve a mug of pasta water which you will use later on. Put the pasta to one side.</div>\n<div>In a big pot (preferably non-stick) heat the chilli oil. In this oil cook the mushrooms, the brinjal and the garlic for 5 minutes.</div>\n<div>Add the tomato. Bring back to a nice simmer and cook for 10 minutes. Taste and add salt if needed. Check if the brinjal is soft enough. If not add a few more minutes of cooking.</div>\n<div>Toss the pasta into this sauce, using the reserved pasta water if necessary to loosen it enough to make a nice consistency for a pasta dish.</div>\n<div>Chop the fresh rocket.</div>\n<div>Heat the pasta through, take off the heat and then stir in the Parmesan and the rocket.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-01-22 11:59:28','2022-11-15 10:11:32',NULL),(242,'ozldpb','Whole Wheat Penne with Pork & Mushrooms','A light and delicious wholewheat pasta dish using a sauce made with pork mince, onion and mushroom fried together and then simmered in a bit of water and red wine vinegar. Everything is tossed together with grated parmesan and fresh parsley.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,25,'<div>Put a big pot with salted water on to boil. When boiling tip in the pasta and boil it for 10 minutes.</div>\n<div>When draining the pasta reserve a mug of pasta water to be used later in the recipe. Set the pasta aside.</div>\n<div>While the pasta is boiling heat some oil in another big pot and fry the pork mince for 5 minutes, on a medium to high heat, breaking it up with a wooden spoon so as not to form clumps. Add the sage, the thyme and salt and pepper to taste.</div>\n<div>Add the onion and the mushroom and fry, stirring occasionally for another 5 minutes.</div>\n<div>Add the red wine vinegar and some of the pasta water to form a sauce and simmer for 10 minutes on a low heat.</div>\n<div>Chop the parsley.</div>\n<div>Tip the cooked pasta into the pork pot and toss. Add as much of the pasta water as you need to give the pasta a nice consistency. Add salt and black pepper to taste and stir through the parmesan and the parsley.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-01-26 10:21:24','2022-07-17 09:49:56',NULL),(243,'trhyrr','Lamb Chops with Cheesy Creamed Spinach and Broccoli','Broccoli and spinach are both known as \"superfoods\", low in calories and containing a wealth of vitamins and minerals. Dress it up in a  delicious cheesy sauce and it makes a wonderful side for lamb chops seasoned with garlic and rosemary.','Gluten and Lactose',5,35,'<div>Put a pot of salted water on to boil. When boiling tip in the broccoli and cook for 4 minutes. Drain and place in an oven proof dish.</div>\n<div>Melt the butter in a big pot on medium high heat and then stir in the flour to make a smooth paste. Let it cook for 1 minute.</div>\n<div>Adjust the heat to medium and add the milk in small dollops, stirring continuously, and allowing the milk to blend before adding the next dollop.<br />A whisk is useful here but not absolutely necessary.</div>\n<div>Stir in salt to taste and a pinch of nutmeg.</div>\n<div>Once the sauce is the desired thickness add the spinach and cook for a minute or two just to wilt it down. Take off the heat and stir in two thirds of the cheese. Transfer the spinach and sauce into the same dish as the broccoli. Sprinkle the remainder of the cheese on top and place the dish under the grill just long enough to brown off the top.</div>\n<div>Season your lamb chops with salt and black pepper, garlic powder and rosemary. Heat some oil in a pan on a fairly high heat and fry your lamb chops until done to your taste - around 5 minutes per side should be medium.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-01-27 09:24:41','2021-10-26 12:30:44',NULL),(244,'uqaegq','Garlicky Crumbed Chicken with Sweet Potato, Butternut & Coriander Salad','Make your own garlicky chicken schnitzel, slice and drizzle with lemon juice and serve with an unusual but delicious salad of sweet potato, butternut pieces, chopped coriander and sweet chilli.','Gluten',10,20,'<div>Put a pot of salted water on to boil. When boiling, add the sweet potato and butternut and time for 20 minutes. Drain well. Add the coriander and sweet chilli sauce. Mix all together and leave to cool.<br>Take one piece of baking paper. Lay your chicken breasts on it and cover with the other piece of baking paper. Take a heavy frying pan and smack those breasts to make them as thin as you can. If you\'ve had a frustrating day this is very therapeutic!&nbsp;<br>Then take the breadcrumbs and press them into both sides of the chicken, put the paper back on top and beat again. This makes the breadcrumbs stick.<br>Heat some oil in the frying pan and fry the chicken pieces 4 minutes per side, less if you think it\'s done. You can press any extra crumbs that fell off on your paper onto the chicken while it is in the pan. If you are cooking for four, you will probably have to do two pieces at a time.<br>Place a piece of cooked chicken onto a plate and slice it into strips. Add salt and black pepper and use a wedge of lemon per person to squeeze onto it. Add a side of the salad.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-02-17 09:44:29','2021-02-17 11:00:01',NULL),(245,'nooiod','Greek Sheet Pan Chicken with Garlic Sauce','Sheet pan meals are so quick and easy and this one boasts all the classic Greek flavours - olives, feta, tomato and herbs. The chicken is marinated in olive oil, lemon juice, crushed garlic and oregano and baked along with onion, green pepper, tomato, olives and feta. Served with a generous dollop of creamy garlic sauce.','Lactose',5,45,'<div>Turn oven on to 200 degrees C.<br />Place chicken and marinade into a bowl and toss well so that chicken is well coated. Leave for 15 minutes, tossing every now and again.<br />Place the onion and green and yellow pepper on a greased sheet pan (or shallow oven dish if you don\'t have a sheet pan).<br />Once the chicken is marinated, place it on top of the onion and peppers and pour any extra marinade in the bowl over the top. Season with a little salt and black pepper.<br />Bake for 20 minutes.</div>\n<div>Slice the tomato(es) thinly and chop the basil.<br />Remove the pan from the oven and place the tomato slices, olives and crumbled feta over the top. Bake for another 10 minutes and then put under the grill for a few minutes to brown off the cheese.<br />While the main dish is cooking, mix the yoghurt, mayonnaise and crushed garlic well in a bowl.Serve the chicken and veg with a generous dollop of garlic sauce on top and sprinkle with some of the chopped fresh basil.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-02-18 09:54:18','2021-11-15 10:57:40',NULL),(246,'llasgh','Tofu Sweet Potato Bowl with a Peanut Sauce','Tofu is a powerhouse of protein but one never quite knows how to serve it. Here it is fried up with spices until crispy, spinach is wilted into it and then the mix is tossed together with baked sweet potato chips and brown rice. A delicious peanut sauce pulls it all together.','Nuts',5,40,'<div>Turn the oven on to 220 degrees C.<br />Put a pot of salted water on to boil. Once boiling add the brown rice and time 40 minutes. It should be cooked - drain and set aside.<br />Add the stock powder to the amount of boiling water specified on the package and mix with the sweet potato bits in a bowl. Mix well and drain off the excess stock.<br />Line a baking sheet with the baking paper and place the bits of sweet potato in a single layer onto it. When the oven is hot enough bake them for 20 minutes and check. If not soft enough give them another 5 to 10 minutes. Keep warm.<br />Meanwhile place the tofu into the same bowl (no need to rinse) with the cornflour, garlic powder &amp; paprika mix. Add salt and pepper to taste. Using your hands gently toss all together so tofu is well coated but retains it shape.<br />Heat oil in a wok or suitably sized pot and, over a medium to high heat, fry the tofu for 10 minutes or until it is brown and has crispy bits. Turn every now and again.<br />Add the spinach and allow it to wilt into the tofu mix. This should only take a minute.&nbsp;<br />Keep the tofu mixture warm until the rice is ready. Add the rice and the sweet potato to the tofu mixture and serve in bowls drizzled with the peanut sauce.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-02-25 11:41:56','2021-10-13 11:31:01',NULL),(247,'jeeuvn','Chilli Con Carne','Here we bring you an old favourite - Mexican-inspired and found deep in the heart of Texas! Think wonderfully rich flavours and colours - think beef, chilli, paprika, red kidney beans, tomato and sour cream.','Traces of Lactose',5,30,'<ol>\n<li>Heat some oil in a big pot. Add the onion and cook, stirring fairly frequently, for about 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Tip in the garlic, red pepper and the chilli spices.</li>\n<li>Give it a good stir, then leave it to cook for another 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.</li>\n<li>Add the beef, turn the heat up a bit, and break it up with your spoon or spatula.</li>\n<li>Make sure you keep the heat hot enough for the meat to fry and become brown, rather than just stew.</li>\n<li>Make up your stock by adding the beef stock powder to the specified amount of water. Add the beef stock to the pot.</li>\n<li>Add the chopped tomatoes. Tip in the dried marjoram, 1/4 tsp of sugar per person you are cooking for and salt and pepper. Add the tomato paste and stir the sauce well.</li>\n<li>Bring the pot to the boil, give it a good stir and put a lid on it. Turn down the heat until it is gently bubbling and leave it for 20 minutes.</li>\n<li>Stir occasionally to make sure the sauce doesn&rsquo;t catch. After simmering gently, the saucy mince mixture should be thick but not dry. Add a little water if it is too dry.</li>\n<li>Add the kidney beans, bring to the boil again, and gently bubble without the lid for another 10 minutes, adding a little more water if it looks too dry.</li>\n<li>Taste a bit of the chilli and season. Add more salt and pepper if needed.</li>\n<li>Now replace the lid, turn off the heat and leave your chilli to stand for 10 minutes before serving. This is really important as it allows the flavours to mingle.</li>\n<li>Serve with&nbsp; a dollop of sour cream and a slice of mealie bread.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-02 10:51:20','2021-10-08 11:30:53',NULL),(248,'jpbecy','Home Baked Mealie Bread','Mop up your delicious meal with your own homemade mealie bread served fresh from the oven. It’s easy – we’ll show you how!','Gluten, lactose',5,45,'<ol><li>Preheat the oven to 170 C. In a large mixing bowl, add the sweet corn, beaten eggs, salt, milk and&nbsp; melted butter and stir. Mix in the flour and combine to form a dough. If using a metallic or glass bread tin, grease with a little non-stick spray. Place dough in bread tin and bake for around 45 minutes or until a skewer or butter knife comes out clean. Let the bread cool and then turn out of the tin.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-02 10:52:05','2021-03-02 11:00:23',NULL),(249,'khzopg','Lamb & Aubergine Curry','A mild and tasty curry of deboned lamb shoulder and aubergine with plain yoghurt stirred through to take the bite off it! Served with rice.','Lactose',5,25,'<div>Place the rice and some salt in a pot of water and bring to the boil. Time 20 minutes from the boiling point and your rice should be done. Drain and keep warm.<br />In a large pot, on a medium to high heat, heat the oil and fry the onion until soft. Add the meat and brown it all over for a few minutes.<br />Add the the aubergine, season with salt and black pepper, then add the curry paste and the red wine vinegar. Stir it all together well.&nbsp;<br />Turn the heat down slightly, put the pot lid on and allow to simmer vigorously for 20 minutes. Stir every now and again and add a little water or oil if it is sticking to the pot.<br />The meat should be cooked but take a piece out and test. When done to your liking, take the pot off the heat and stir the yoghurt through.<br />Serve with rice for those that want rice or in a bowl without rice for those that are watching their carbs.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-04 10:35:59','2021-09-28 15:44:29',NULL),(250,'auyfli','Beef Gnocchi Bake','Comfort food de luxe this is and oh so delicious! It involves ground beef, marinara sauce, cheese sauce and gnocchi - need we say more?','Gluten and Lactose',5,30,'<div>Heat oil in a skillet or pot and fry the onion until soft. Add the beef mince, salt and black pepper to taste, and break up with a wooden spoon to avoid clumps. Fry for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.<br>Add the mushrooms and the baby marrow and fry for another few minutes.<br>Add the marinara sauce. Stir in well and bring back to a simmer.<br>Taste for extra seasoning and add if you wish. Leave to simmer for 15 minutes.<br>While the mince is cooking, cook the gnocchi.<br>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil, add the gnocchi and cook for two minutes. Drain well and place in an oven proof dish.<br>Heat the cheese sauce very gently - it should just be warm enough to be spreadable.<br>When the mince is done place it on top of the gnocchi and spread your cheese sauce over the top. It does not have to look neat! Sprinkle the grated cheese on top of that and bake for 30 minutes. It should be a nice golden colour.<br>Serve with leafy greens on the side.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-04 11:42:28','2021-03-04 12:04:23',NULL),(251,'szaawf','Creamy Tikka Beef and Vegetable Bake','Stir-fried beef in a tikka curry sauce is added to a colourful vegetable bake toward the end of it\'s cooking time giving you a one dish meal that is low in carbs and high in nutrients. If you have family members that need a bit of carb, just add a bit of rice (not included).','Lactose',5,45,'<div>Heat the oven to 180 degrees C. Put the roasting veg in an oven proof dish and toss with oil and salt and black pepper. Put this in the oven, even if it has not fully heated yet. Time for 45 minutes.<br>Heat some oil in a skillet or pot and fry the onion until soft. Add the garlic and the beef strips and stir fry until the beef strips look cooked. This should only take 5 minutes.<br>Add the curry paste, stir in well. Then add your cream, stir in and allow to simmer for 3 to 5 minutes to blend the flavours. Take this off the heat.<br>When the veg have been in the oven for 45 minutes add the beef tikka mix to the roast veg. Stir together gently and put back into the oven for 5 minutes for the meat to heat through.<br>Serve sprinkled with the almond flakes.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-09 10:57:37','2021-03-11 08:15:49',NULL),(252,'mbxjfu','Beef Massaman','Creamy and spicy without being too hot for the family, this dish features beef strips, Masssaman paste, tomato passata, yoghurt, cream and ground almonds. It is served with rice but can be adapted to a low carb meal by minimising the rice. Also served with green beans for a lovely splash of colour.','Lactose & Nuts',5,30,'<div>Make your rice: Place rice and salt in a pot of water and bring to the boil.Time 20 minutes from boiling point and your rice should be done. Drain and keep warm.</div>\n<div>Make the beans: Bring a pot fo boiling water with salt to the boil. Dro[p the beans in and boil for 5 minutes. Drain and keep warm.<br />Heat some oil in a skillet or pot on a medium to high heat and fry the beef strips for 10 minutes.<br />Take the meat out of the pot and set aside. Add a splash more oil to the meat juices and fry the onion until it is starting to go brown.<br />Add the garlic and ginger and fry for 30 seconds.<br />Add the Massaman paste, stir in and fry for 1 minute.<br />Add the passata, stir in and add the meat back.<br />Turn the heat down to medium.<br />Mix the yoghurt, cream and ground almonds together and add to the pot.<br />Stir until heated through.&nbsp; Taste and add salt and pepper if you wish. Serve with rice (minimal if you want a low carb meal) and the green beans.<br /><br /></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-12 10:21:49','2022-07-16 09:45:34','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Passata</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ingredients:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 large onion</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp ground black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS tomato paste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Method:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(253,'bgxcus','Harissa Lamb Koftas with Whole Wheat Flatbread','Lamb mince  and Harissa paste are fried into delicious little meat balls and served on a layer of flavoured cottage cheese and \"pickled\" slaw, topped with a drizzle of plain yoghurt. This burst of flavour is served on a freshly made whole wheat flatbread.','Gluten and Lactose',10,30,'<ol><li>Mix the whole wheat flour mix with the yoghurt marked for the flatbreads in a plastic bowl. You may need a little extra flour for your hands. Knead the dough well on a floured counter top. Wrap in plastic or cover with a cloth and let it rest, while you start the meat.</li><li>Mix the lamb mince and the harissa paste (marked \"for lamb\") together very well - use your hands for this. Form the mixture into little balls - four for each person you are cooking for ie eight&nbsp; balls for two people.</li><li>Heat a little oil in a pan and fry your meatballs turning occasionally until nicely browned and cooked, 8 to 10 minutes. If you are cooking for four, you may have to do two lots depending on the size of your pan. Set aside.</li><li>Place the shredded cabbage in a bowl, sprinkle with a little salt and black pepper and then mix together with the red wine vinegar. Scrunch the cabbage together with the red wine vinegar to give a quick pickle effect.</li><li>Mix the cottage cheese with the harissa paste (marked \"for cheese\") and set aside.</li><li>Heat a little olive oil to a high heat in a pan. Take a biggish ball of your dough and flatten to fit your pan, or as flat as you can get! Put the dough in the pan and then immediately flip over so that both sides have olive oil on. Then cook for about 1 minute a side, or until a good colour. Repeat with the rest of the dough, keeping the flatbread warm.</li><li>Assemble your meal: Spread the flatbreads with the cottage cheese mixture, top with the slaw, arrange four meat balls on each and drizzle with the yoghurt marked for that purpose. Tuck in and enjoy.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-13 11:35:20','2021-04-20 08:36:09',NULL),(254,'wqvhin','Keto Tex-Mex Casserole','All the classic Tex-Mex flavours without the carbs. Ground beef is fried with our own home made Tex-Mex spice and chopped tomatoes. Topped with pickled jalapeno peppers and grated cheddar, the baked casserole is served with a mix of chopped spring onions and sour cream and some leafy greens.','Lactose',5,35,'<div>Preheat oven to 200 degrees C.<br>Heat some oil in a skillet or pot and fry the mince, breaking up with a wooden spoon, for about 10 minutes. It should no longer be pink.<br>Add the spice and chopped tomatoes, stir and simmer for 10 minutes - the liquid should reduce slightly. Taste to see whether you need salt and pepper.<br>Place in an oven dish with the pickled jalepenos on top and the grated Cheddar on top of that.<br>Bake for 20 minutes - the dish should be golden and bubbling. Take out and cool slightly.<br>While it bakes mix the spring onions and sour cream in a bowl and break up your greens ready to serve. Serve a portion of the Tex-Mex Casserole with a dollop of the sour cream and spring onion mixture on top and some greens alongside.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-14 15:42:10','2022-08-21 17:10:14','<p>Tex Mex Seasoning</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul class=\"ckdc-recipe-ingredients-list\">\n<li><span class=\"ckdc-ingredient plural-us plural-metric\"><span class=\"ingredient-value ingredient-value-metric\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" data-servings=\"{&quot;1&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&lt;sup&gt;1&lt;\\/sup&gt;&frasl;&lt;sub&gt;8&lt;\\/sub&gt; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;2&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&frac14; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;\\/sup&gt;&frasl;&lt;sub&gt;5&lt;\\/sub&gt; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;4&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&frac12; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;5&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;\\/sup&gt;&frasl;&lt;sub&gt;3&lt;\\/sub&gt; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;6&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&frac34; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;7&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&lt;sup&gt;4&lt;\\/sup&gt;&frasl;&lt;sub&gt;5&lt;\\/sub&gt; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;8&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;1 tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;singular-metric empty&quot;},&quot;9&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;: