>1 pinch</span>&nbsp;ground cloves</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"ckdc-ingredient ingredient-optional plural-us plural-metric\"><span class=\"ingredient-value ingredient-value-metric\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" data-servings=\"{&quot;1&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&lt;sup&gt;1&lt;\\/sup&gt;&frasl;&lt;sub&gt;8&lt;\\/sub&gt; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;2&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&frac14; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;\\/sup&gt;&frasl;&lt;sub&gt;5&lt;\\/sub&gt; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;4&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&frac12; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;5&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;\\/sup&gt;&frasl;&lt;sub&gt;3&lt;\\/sub&gt; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;6&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&frac34; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;7&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&lt;sup&gt;4&lt;\\/sup&gt;&frasl;&lt;sub&gt;5&lt;\\/sub&gt; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;8&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;1 tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;singular-metric empty&quot;},&quot;9&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;1&frac14; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;10&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;1&frac14; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;11&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;1&lt;sup&gt;1&lt;\\/sup&gt;&frasl;&lt;sub&gt;3&lt;\\/sub&gt; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;12&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;1&frac12; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;13&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;1&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;\\/sup&gt;&frasl;&lt;sub&gt;3&lt;\\/sub&gt; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;14&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;1&frac34; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;15&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;2 tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;16&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;2 tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;}}\">1 tbsp</span>&nbsp;sea salt (optional)</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"ckdc-ingredient ingredient-optional plural-us plural-metric\">Mix together well and store in an airtight container.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(255,'tfyrfa','Italian Meatballs with Mozzarella','Delicious Italian flavour with beef mince, grated Parmesan, tomato, fresh basil and pieces of mozzarella. If you leave out the whole wheat bread (included in the kit) then you have Keto Italian Meatballs ie a meal with negligible carbs in it.','Gluten (bread) and traces of Lactose',5,30,'<div>Place beef mince, grated Parmesan, Italian seasoning and salt and ground black pepper into a bowl. Add the beaten egg slowly. If you are cooking for less than 4 people you probably will not need the whole egg, just enough to make a nice consistency for meat balls. Mix well.&nbsp; Use your hands if necessary. Form the mixture into meatballs the size of golf balls.<br />Heat a generous amount of oil in a large skillet or pot and fry the meatballs four minutes on each side on a fairly high heat. Turn carefully but don\'t worry if they break up a little - it\'s all about the taste, not the looks! If you are cooking for more than two people you may have to do this in two batches.<br />Add the whole tomatoes, using your wooden spoon to stir them in very gently, breaking them roughly in half as you go. Add salt and black pepper to taste.<br />Turn the heat down and simmer for 15 minutes. Very gently stir now and again to see that nothing is catching on the pot.</div>\n<div>Chop the fresh basil and stir it in towards the end of the simmering time.<br />In a separate pan melt the butter marked for the spinach and fry the spinach for one minute. It should be wilted.<br />Add the spinach to the other pot when its 15 minutes is up and arrange the mozzarella on the top to get slightly melty. Take off the heat.<br />Serve in bowls with the bread and butter on the side for those that want it.<br /><br /></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-15 08:14:49','2022-01-10 13:21:50',NULL),(256,'ufbwur','Easy Chicken Marsala with Peas & Sweet Potato','Chicken done in a lovely Marsala and cream sauce with spring onions, mushrooms and peas. Served on a mound of mashed sweet potato.','Lactose',5,40,'<div>Put a pot of salted water on to boil and when boiling add the sweet potato. Boil for 20 minutes or until soft enough to mash. Drain and roughly mash with a little milk and salt and black pepper.<br />Start the chicken while the sweet potato is boiling. Heat some oil in a large skillet, pot or electric frying pan and fry the chicken for 20 minutes. Season with salt and pepper to taste. If you are cooking for four and you do not have a big pan you may have to do two batches. Once the chicken is cooked through, take it out of the pan and set aside.<br />Add a dash more oil to the same pan and add the spring onions and mushrooms. Cook until soft, 3 to 5 minutes. Add the Marsala wine and use it to scrape all the flavoursome bits off the bottom of the pan and then add the cream and peas. Stir well, letting everything blend nicely and then add back the chicken. Cook all together for 5 minutes. Test to see whether you would like to add additional salt and pepper.<br />If you would like this to be a low carb dish then serve without or with a small serving of sweet potato.&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-18 14:57:31','2022-10-18 09:35:04',NULL),(257,'uyxnxb','Curried Chicken & Dhal Bake','The wonderful aromas that will fill your kitchen while you cook this meal are only matched by the experience of eating it.\nThe curried chicken is baked in dhal (red split lentils with cauliflower, red onion, ginger, garlic and spices). Fresh tomato and spinach is stirred through at the end and a drizzle of plain yoghurt and squeeze of fresh lemon completes your masterpiece- plenty of nutrition in this dish!','Lactose',5,45,'<div>Heat the oven to 200 degrees C.<br />Into a large roasting dish place the lentils, the onions, the cauliflower, garlic, ginger, turmeric and cumin seeds. The amount of boiling water that you need to pour over this will be specified on the lentil package. Mix everything together well.<br />Put a little oil in a bowl along with the chicken pieces, the curry powder and a little salt and pepper. Toss all together well so the chicken is nicely coated.<br />Nestle the chicken pieces into the lentil mixture and cook in the oven for 40 minutes.<br />Remove the chicken pieces and keep warm. Stir the tomato and spinach through the lentil mix and return to the oven for a few minutes for the spinach to wilt. Season to taste.<br />Cut the lemon into wedges.<br />Serve with the chicken, a tablespoon of yoghurt and a squeeze of lemon drizzled over the top.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-20 10:24:26','2022-03-03 15:26:28',NULL),(258,'baroyg','Curried Paneer and Dhal Bake','The wonderful aromas that fill your kitchen while you cook this meal will transport you to the east!\nThe curried paneer, an Indian whey cheese, is baked in dhal (red split lentils) with cauliflower, red onion, ginger, garlic and spices. Fresh tomato and spinach is stirred through at the end and a drizzle of plain yoghurt and squeeze of fresh lemon completes your masterpiece- plenty of nutrition in this dish!','Lactose',5,45,'<div>Heat the oven to 200 degrees C.<br>Into a large roasting dish place the lentils, the onions, the cauliflower, garlic, ginger, turmeric and cumin seeds. Dissolve the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package and pour it over this mixture. Add salt and pepper to taste and&nbsp; mix everything together well.<br>In a bowl pour a little oil and place the paneer pieces, the curry powder and a little salt and pepper in it. Toss all together well, heat a little oil in a pan and fry the paneer pieces until they are golden - 2 to 3 minutes per side.<br>Nestle the fried paneer pieces into the mixture in the oven dish stirring any left over curry powder in the bowl in as well. Bake for 40 minutes. Check at about 30 minutes that the lentil mix is not too dry. You can add a little water if you need to.<br>After 40 minutes stir the tomato and spinach carefully through the lentil and paneer mix and return to the oven for a few minutes for the spinach to wilt. Season to taste.<br>Cut the lemon into wedges.<br>Serve with a tablespoon of yoghurt&nbsp; and a squeeze of lemon drizzled over the top.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-20 14:33:31','2022-01-20 15:09:18',NULL),(259,'cngezz','Coq Au Vin','The traditional Coq Au Vin was made in France using an old rooster that had to be slow cooked in wine to make it tender before adding onion, mushroom and bacon.  We\'ve dropped the old rooster and replaced it with chicken breast to give you all the traditional flavour in just one hour. Serve as is for the carb-conscious or with couscous for those who are not.','Gluten and Lactose',5,55,'<div>Heat the oven to 180 degrees C.<br />Then make your stock by adding the powder to the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Add the tomato paste, the Bovril and the red wine to the stock, stir well and put to one side.<br />Heat some oil in a pot and fry the bacon bits for 5 minutes. Transfer to an oven dish, preferably with a lid but foil will do.<br />Put the flour and some salt and pepper into a big bowl, mix and toss the chicken pieces in it so that each one is coated. Discard any excess flour.<br />In the same pot that you cooked the bacon saute the chicken pieces for a few minutes each side just so that they are golden brown. You may need to add a bit more oil. Transfer the chicken pieces to the oven dish.<br />In the same pot saute the onion and garlic for two minutes and add the apricot juice. Stir and allow to boil.<br />Now take your stock mixture and pour into the onion and garlic pot, adding the thyme and bay leaves. Pour the pot mixture over the chicken and bacon bits and cover with a lid or foil. Place in oven for 30 minutes.<br />To make your couscous, put the amount of water specified on the couscous package into a pot with some oil and salt. Use 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon oil per person that you are cooking for. Bring to the boil. Add the couscous, stir in and take off the heat. Let it sit with the lid on for 5 minutes. Fluff it up with a fork.</div>\n<div>Chop the parsley.<br />Serve your chicken on couscous or, if you want a low carb meal, leave the couscous out. Garnish with the chopped parsley.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-22 10:09:50','2023-03-03 11:32:46',NULL),(260,'rvkemy','Chicken with Creamy Sun-Dried Tomato Sauce','Sauteed chicken pieces and rounds of baby marrow are simmered in a gorgeous creamy sauce featuring garlic, white wine, Dijon mustard, sun-dried tomatoes, parmesan and of course cream. Fresh basil leaves are stirred through near the end of the cooking time and the dish is served on pumpkin, mashed with butter, salt and pepper.','Lactose',5,40,'<div>Put a pot of salted water on to boil and boil the pumpkin pieces for 20 minutes. They must be soft enough to mash. Drain and mash with the butter and salt and pepper. Keep warm.<br />Cut each piece of chicken in half horizontally to make 2 thin steaks and sprinkle with salt and pepper.<br />Drain the oil from the sun-dried tomatoes and heat this oil in a big skillet or pot on a medium to high heat. Fry the chicken pieces until brown on both sides - 5 to 7 minutes depending on how thick the pieces are. You may have to do them in two batches.<br />Remove the chicken onto a plate and add the garlic to the same pot. Add a dash more oil if you need to. Stir it for only 15 seconds before adding the baby marrow to cook for 2 minutes.<br />Add the wine, using it to scrape all the yummy bits off the bottom of the pot and let it simmer for 1 minute.<br />Dissolve the stock powder in the amount of boiling water stipulated on the package and mix the mustard into the stock. Add this to the pot.<br />Then add the cream, parmesan and sun-dried tomatoes.<br />Stir everything together, bring to a simmer, reduce the heat to medium and simmer for 5 minutes until the sauce thickens. Stir regularly.<br />Taste the sauce to see if you need to add some more salt and pepper.</div>\n<div>Roughly chop the fresh basil.<br />Stir the basil through the mixture, add the chicken back and simmer for a minute or two.<br />Serve the mashed pumpkin topped with the chicken and sauce.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-22 10:23:20','2022-03-30 08:47:24',NULL),(261,'pcizal','Stir-Fried Tofu with Egg Noodles','Bring a touch of the East to your table with our specially marinated tofu stir-fried with lots of colourful veg and Chinese egg noodles. Serve with a drizzle of soy sauce for a healthy, satisfying and tasty meal.','Gluten',30,15,'<div>In a Tupperware, mix together the tofu cubes and the marinade ingredients and refrigerate for 30 minutes.</div><div>When the tofu has been in the fridge for 20 minutes, bring a pot of water to the boil. Add the egg noodles and boil for 4 minutes. Drain and rinse under cold water. Add a drizzle of oil to the noodles to prevent them from sticking to each other.<br>Drain the marinade from the tofu and set the marinade aside for use later. Add some salt and pepper to the flour in a bowl, add the tofu and gently toss until coated. Heat some oil in a wok or non-stick pan and fry the tofu on a medium to high heat until nicely browned. Take out of the pan and set aside.</div><div>Heat a little more oil until very hot in the same pan or wok. Add the ginger and all the veggies and fry for about 8 minutes.</div><div>Add the egg noodles, the leftover marinade and the tofu and stir fry gently for a few minutes</div><div>Serve in bowls with a little extra soy sauce if desired.</div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-22 14:30:36','2021-03-22 14:48:07',NULL),(262,'kyfjvd','Vegetarian White Chilli','White chilli is the most tasty comfort food that this planet has to offer. It just wouldn’t be fair to forget the vegetarians and this is what we have come up with. All the Tex-Mex spices, white beans, corn and cream cheese but instead of using shredded chicken we use potato cubes which absorb the fabulous flavour. Serve with mealie bread fresh from your oven.','Gluten, lactose',5,45,'<div>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil, chop the potatoes into small chunks and boil until soft, about 15 minutes. Set aside.<br>Make your vegetable stock by mixing the powder with the amount of water specified on the package</div><ol><li>Heat oil in another pot over medium-high heat. Add onion and sauté for 4 minutes. Add garlic and sauté 30 seconds longer.</li><li>Add vegetable stock, chilli flakes, cumin, paprika, oregano, ground coriander, cayenne pepper and season with salt and pepper to taste. Bring mixture just to a boil then reduce heat to medium-low and simmer for 15 minutes.</li><li>Add cream cheese to soup along with potato, corn, whole beans and mashed beans and stir well. Simmer 5 - 10 minutes longer.</li><li>Stir in lemon juice and half the fresh coriander. Use the other half to sprinkle over the bowls of chilli when serving with your fresh mealie bread.</li></ol><div><br></div><div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-22 15:48:08','2021-03-22 16:04:52',NULL),(263,'rwuetl','Self-Saucing Roast Chicken Drumsticks with Savoury Rice','Let the chicken make its own gravy - all you do is whisk it before serving. The rice cooks with its spices and is then generously buttered and served alongside - with broccoli for a pop of colour and more than a pop of nutrition.','Gluten',5,50,'<div>Heat oven to 200 degrees C.<br>Place chicken in a baking pan, drizzle with oil, rub the oil in and then the chicken spices, most spice being on the side with most skin and place chicken skin side up.<br>Make up your beef stock by adding the powder to the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Put a third of this stock into a separate bowl, add the flour and whisk into a lump free paste. Then whisk in the remaining stock and pour into the pan around the chicken. Bake the chicken uncovered for 50 minutes.<br>Place the rice and the specified amount of cold tap water into a pot and add the rice spices, stirring well. Place pot on medium high heat without lid and wait for it to be simmering properly. Put the lid on, turn heat to medium or medium low, depending on your stove, and time 13 minutes without lifting the lid.&nbsp;<br>After 13 minutes, peek inside, tilt the pot to make sure no water is left, and remove from stove. Let the pot stand with the lid on for 10 minutes. After that fluff it up with a spoon and add the butter. Keep warm.<br>Steam or boil the broccoli for 3 to 4 minutes. Keep warm.<br>After the 50 minutes take the chicken out, place on a serving dish and whisk the gravy to make it smooth. Add a little boiling water if necessary. Pour gravy into a jug and serve with the chicken, rice and broccoli.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-24 07:08:11','2021-03-24 07:50:00',NULL),(264,'eaeymi','Pork Rarebit with Roasted Baby Potatoes, Green Beans & Cherry Tomatoes','Boneless pork chops with a lovely cheese, wholegrain mustard and sour cream topping served with crispy baby potatoes and roasted green beans and cherry tomatoes,','Traces of Lactose',5,40,'<p>Preheat the oven to 200 degrees.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Halve the parboiled baby potatoes. Put the baking paper on a baking tray and place the baby potatoes, cut side facing down, on the baking tray. Melt the butter and drizzle this over the potatoes. Season well with salt and pepper. Place in the oven.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Place the pork chops flat in a baking dish or on a tray. Season well with salt and pepper. Place these in the oven and cook for 15 minutes.</p>\n<div>While the potatoes and pork chops are in the oven, halve your cherry tomatoes. Place the green beans and cherry tomatoes in a baking dish, sprinkle with some oil and season with salt and pepper. Put in the oven with the potatoes once the potatoes have been in for 20 minutes.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>Mix the cheese, sour cream and mustard together in a bowl. Once the chops have been in for 15 minutes, take them out. Spread the cheese mixture over the top of each chop. Place the chops back in the oven for ten minutes.&nbsp;<br />When the chops are done everything should be ready. You may need to take the beans and tomatoes out slightly before - don\'t overcook them.</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-30 16:10:55','2022-08-15 15:57:40',NULL),(265,'kdytb','Beef Strips in Creamy Peppercorn Sauce with Savoury Pilaf','A really delicious and creamy peppercorn sauce coats your stir-fried beef strips while an easy but very tasty rice pilaf serves you your veg. Simple, satisfying and nutritious.','Lactose',5,35,'<div>Start with the pilaf: Melt the butter marked for the pilaf in a pot and fry the onion on a medium to high heat for 5 minutes. Add the green and red pepper and the green beans and fry for a further 5 minutes.<br>Add the rice and fry it for a few minutes whilst stirring so nothing sticks.<br>Make the stock for the pilaf by dissolving the pilaf stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Add this stock to the pot, stir everything together and bring to the boil.&nbsp;<br>Turn the heat down to low and put the lid on. Simmer without taking the lid off for 15 minutes. Remove from heat and let it stand with the lid on for 5 minutes before you fluff the pilaf up with a fork.<br>While the pilaf is cooking, melt the butter for the beef in a big pan and stir fry the beef for 10 minutes, or until no longer pink. Remove the beef and set aside on a plate.<br>In the pan juices fry the spring onion for two minutes. Add the garlic and crushed pepper and fry for 1 minute. Add the red wine and as it simmers use it to scrape any yummy bits off the bottom of the pan and into the mixture.<br>Make your beef stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.&nbsp;<br>Add the Worcestershire sauce and the beef stock to the pan and then pour in the cream. Stir well and bring to a nice simmer. Let it simmer for 5 to 8 minutes to thicken. Stir frequently.<br>Add the beef strips back to the pan and simmer for a few more minutes.<br>Serve the beef and sauce on a helping of pilaf.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-03-30 17:36:59','2021-03-30 18:07:21',NULL),(266,'fcwvdk','Bacon Carbonara','Carbonara is basically just sophisticated comfort food involving egg and tagliatelle pasta - add bacon, cheddar and parmesan with a bit of wild rocket on the side and you have a winner!','Gluten and Lactose',5,25,'<div>Bring a big pot of salted water to the boil and boil the pasta for 11 minutes. When you drain it keep back a little of the pasta water for use later.<br>Beat your eggs and add the cheddar cheese.<br>While the pasta is boiling heat some oil in a pot and fry the bacon bits on a fairly high heat with a pinch of black pepper until fairly crispy. Just before the pasta is ready take the bacon pot off the heat.<br>Add the drained pasta to the bacon pot and toss together. Pour in the egg and cheese mixture and toss all together with a little pasta water to give a nice consistency.&nbsp;<br>The trick with making carbonara is that the pot that the egg mixture is being poured into has cooled for a minute or two - you don\'t want the egg to scramble but the heat of the mixture will cook the egg into a creamy sauce.<br>Sprinkle each serving with parmesan and place some rocket alongside.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-04-05 11:54:52','2023-01-09 09:27:12',NULL),(267,'ebepun','Mushroom & Cheese Casserole with Herbed Tomato Salad','The casserole is super-tasty with it\'s two types of cheese, mushrooms, garlic, cream and spinach baked to golden yumminess. We have paired it with a simple tomato, red onion and herb salad with our home made vinaigrette. Definitely a low carb winner for the vegetarians.','Lactose',10,30,'<div>Turn oven on to 190 degrees C. Lightly grease an oven dish of approximately 23 x 23 cm.<br />Beat the eggs and the cream together and put one side.<br />Heat some oil in a pot on a medium high heat and put in the mushrooms with salt and black pepper to taste. Let the mushrooms fry for 3 minutes.<br />Add the garlic and fry for 1 minute.<br />Add the spinach, mix all together and cook until the spinach is properly wilted - about 2 minutes. Take off the heat.<br />Stir in the cream cheese until it has melted in to the mixture. Add the egg and cream mixture and half the grated cheddar cheese. Stir all together until well combined.<br />Pour into the oven dish and sprinkle the rest of the cheese on top. Bake for 30 minutes. The middle should be golden and set and the edges light brown.<br />While the casserole cools a bit, chop your cherry tomatoes in half, roughly chop the rocket and the basil and toss with the red onion and enough vinaigrette for your taste. Place a portion of the casserole and a bit of salad on each plate.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-04-06 09:10:14','2022-04-13 09:59:13',NULL),(268,'zgbyxi','Creamy Halloumi Salad','A generous amount of golden fried halloumi cubes are tossed with fresh tomato, sun dried tomato, basil leaves, red onion and green pepper in a creamy garlic dressing. If you are trying to cut carbs eat this as is but for those that aren\'t, toss with couscous.','Gluten (couscous) and traces of Lactose',10,10,'<div>Fry your halloumi in a little oil on a high heat - it only takes a few minutes to get golden brown and a little crispy so watch it carefully. Take off the heat and set aside.</div>\n<div>Roughly chop the basil leaves.<br />Tip your tomatoes, green pepper, sun dried tomatoes, red onion and basil leaves into a bowl. Add the cooled halloumi and toss together.<br />Put the amount of water specified on the couscous package into a pot and bring to the boil. When boiling take it off the heat, add a splash of oil and a big pinch of salt and the couscous. Stir together, put the pot lid on and leave for 5 minutes. Once 5 minutes has passed take the lid off and fluff up the couscous with a fork.<br />Dress the salad with the creamy garlic dressing, tossing well. For those that are cutting carbs, serve the salad as is or with a very small amount of couscous. For those that prefer to eat carbs, toss the rest of the couscous into the salad.<br /><br /></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-04-08 09:32:52','2022-03-31 06:18:20',NULL),(269,'angyrr','Balti Chicken Bake','Balti is a mildy spicy curry paste that blends very well with yoghurt and cream and makes a lovely sauce for a chicken, red onion, sweet potato and spinach bake. Topped with slivered almonds, this makes a very good low carb meal.','Nuts and Lactose',5,50,'<div>Heat the oven to 180 degrees C.<br>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil and parboil the sweet potato for 15 minutes. Drain and set aside.<br>In a big pot, heat some oil on medium high heat and brown the chicken thighs on both sides, adding salt and black pepper to taste.<br>Remove them to an oven proof dish.<br>Add more oil if necessary and fry the red onion for 3 to 4 minutes. Add the garlic and fry for a further 1 minute.<br>Add the Balti paste and fry for 2 minutes.<br>Add the cream and the yoghurt, stir well, and simmer for 5 minutes.<br>Add the drained sweet potato.<br>Add the spinach, allow to wilt, and then pour the mixture over the chicken in the oven proof dish.<br>Bake for 30 minutes, then sprinkle the slivered almonds over the top and put back for a further 5 minutes.<br><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-04-13 10:23:42','2021-04-23 17:43:51',NULL),(270,'lpfffd','Lamb, Feta & Barley Bowl with Minted Yoghurt Dressing','This delightful barley bowl conjures up the Middle East with its  cumin and lamb mince fried until crispy and its minted yoghurt dressing. We then get carried away internationally speaking by adding cubes of Greek feta and fresh deseeded cucumber. Enjoy!','Gluten and Lactose',5,45,'<div>Dissolve the stock in the amount of boiling water specified on its package and place in a pot with the barley.<br />Bring the barley to the boil and then turn down the heat to let it simmer slowly with the lid on for 45 minutes. Take a peek every now and then to make sure the water has not boiled dry. Add a little if necessary.<br />While the barley is cooking, heat a little oil in a pan, medium to high heat and fry the cumin for 30 seconds, no longer or it burns. Add the lamb mince and break down with a wooden spoon mixing it well into the cumin. Add some salt and pepper to taste and keep stir-frying until the lamb looks cooked and slightly crispy - 8 to 10 minutes, depending on your heat. Once done, keep warm.<br />When the barley is cooked, drain it and mix it with the lamb in a serving bowl. Let it cool slightly.</div>\n<div>Chop the mint roughly and then add the cucumber, mint, feta and most of the dressing and toss together.&nbsp; This dish is eaten warm, not hot.<br />Serve into bowls with the remaining dressing in a swirl on top.<br /><br /></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-04-17 12:30:03','2022-01-10 08:22:48',NULL),(271,'hpaiwr','Mutton Keema with Rice','Keema is a traditional South East Asian curry made from ground meat, onions, garlic, ginger, tomato and lots of spices. We have made it easy for you by bundling the whole spices and the spice powders and giving you an easy to follow recipe card. Using mutton mince, this is the quickest way to get all the flavour of a mutton curry without the hours of cooking. Spice up your week!','None',5,35,'<div>You will need 2 smaller pots and one larger pot.<br />In one of the smaller pots place your rice, cover with salted water and bring to the boil. Time 20 minutes from boiling point and your rice will be done. Drain well and keep warm.<br />In the other smaller pot do the same with the sweet potato cubes and time 15 minutes from boiling point. They should be soft. Drain and set aside.<br />In the larger pot add a good dollop of oil and heat it on a high heat. When the oil is hot add the whole spices and stir fry for 1 minute.<br />Turn the heat down to medium and add the green chillies and the onions and fry until the onion is golden, about 5 minutes.<br />Add the garlic and ginger and fry for 1 minute, stirring in well.<br />Add the mutton mince and fry for 3 minutes breaking up the clumps with a wooden spoon.<br />Add salt to taste and the ground spices and turn your heat down to low.&nbsp;<br />Chop the mint and add it to the pot and fry together for 4 minutes, stirring.<br />Put the pot lid on and cook on low for 8 minutes.<br />Add the tomato puree and 1/2 teaspoon of sugar per person you are cooking for (ie 1 tsp for two) and fry without the lid for 5 minutes.<br />Add the amount of water specified on the tomato puree and add the sweet potatoes, bring to a simmer, and cook uncovered until the consistency suits you.</div>\n<div>Chop the fresh coriander.<br />Stir the fresh coriander through the keema and serve with rice. If you want a low carb meal leave out the rice or only use a spoonful.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-04-21 08:43:59','2022-07-16 17:31:24',NULL),(272,'aokpgl','Parmesan & Spinach Risotto with Chicken Steaks','For some reason the word \"Risotto\" strikes fear into the heart of the amateur cook. The trick is to focus on it and not try to do two or more things at once. Follow our step by step instructions and you will have the creamiest risotto with spinach, parmesan cheese and butter stirred through it. The perfect accompaniment to simple pan-fried chicken steaks.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,40,'<div>Cut your chicken breasts horizontally into thin \"steaks\". Heat some oil on a fairly high heat. Mix the flour with as much salt and black pepper as you see fit in a big bowl and dredge the chicken pieces, covering them as much as possible. Place them in the pan. They will need about 3 minutes on each side and should be a golden colour.<br />Keep the chicken warm while you make your risotto.<br />Make your stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water stipulated on the stock package. Pour the stock into a small pot and keep it at a low simmer on the stove. This way when you add the stock to the risotto in small amounts it will not cool down the cooking process.<br />In another pot heat a good dollop of oil and fry the onion for 3 minutes.<br />Add the garlic and fry for 1 minute.<br />Add the rice and stir-fry for 3 minutes. The rice grains should change colour a bit but not burn.<br />Add the wine and cook until absorbed by the rice. Stir frequently.<br />Add the hot stock a half cup at a time, allowing it to be absorbed before adding the next bit of stock. Stir frequently and make sure the heat is not high but rather medium-low. The pot is uncovered. The process should take 20 to 25 minutes.<br />Take the pot off the heat while there is still a little moisture on top of the rice and stir in the spinach and then the butter and parmesan. If the mixture is too stiff stir in a little water to give it the consistency you like.<br />Serve immediately with the chicken.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-04-22 09:40:30','2022-05-12 14:16:47',NULL),(273,'rsdfhd','Sticky South African Chicken with Broccoli','Chicken cooked in a chutney and mayo sauce is as South African as a braai on Sunday and very, very tasty. We\'ve added a few twists to make it ours and to enhance its nutrition factor.  Broccoli on the side adds a lovely pop of colour and good health.','Lactose',5,50,'<div>Heat oven to 200C.<br>Halve your baby potatoes.</div><div>Bring a pot of water to the boil and boil the potatoes for ten minutes to par cook them. Drain and set aside.</div><div>Heat the oil in a pot or frying pan over a medium heat and cook the onion and garlic for a few mins until softened. Add the mushrooms and marrow and cook for about five minutes.</div><div>Add the sticky sauce and stir.</div><div>Place the chicken pieces in a large baking dish. Season well with salt and pepper. Put the potatoes in the dish surrounding the chicken. Pour the sauce with the mushrooms and marrow over the chicken and make sure the chicken is well coated. Place in the oven and cook for 45 minutes.<br>While the chicken is cooking, bring a pot of salted water to the boil and cook the broccoli for 3 to 4 minutes. Drain and keep warm.<br>Serve the chicken dish with its sauce along with a side of broccoli.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-04-28 09:03:35','2021-04-28 09:16:48',NULL),(274,'zdsywj','Quick Lamb and Veg Stew','A nice stew is always welcome on a chilly evening but after a long day there is never time for that slow process that they usually entail. We cut corners by using tender lamb pieces and parboiling the stew veg. We definitely don\'t cut corners with quality and taste though and this delicious stew along with its mashed pumpkin should be on your table in under an hour.','Gluten (minimal flour)',5,30,'<div>You will need three pots.<br>Bring salted water to the boil in two of the pots. To one add the pumpkin and to the other add the sweet potato.&nbsp;<br>After 15 minutes add the beans to the sweet potato pot.<br>After 20 minutes everything should be soft enough. Drain the sweet potato and beans and set aside.<br>Drain the pumpkin and mash it with a little salt and pepper. Keep warm.<br>Make your stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.<br>While the veg are boiling, heat some oil in the third pot and fry the onion for 3 minutes. Add the pieces of lamb and salt and black pepper. Keep on a medium to high heat and cook the meat with the onion for 5 minutes so that it is browned.<br>Add the flour and stir in well. Lower the heat to medium low.<br>Add the red wine and stir in well to avoid lumps and scrape any bits off the bottom of the pot to add to the flavour.<br>Add the stock and keep stirring.<br>Add the Worcestershire, tomato, sugar and Dijon mustard mix.<br>Add the sweet potato and beans, and the dried thyme.<br>Stir in well, bring to a simmer, make sure the stove is not too hot, and put the lid on. Allow to simmer for 20 minutes, stirring every now and then to prevent the mix sticking on the bottom of the pot. If the gravy is too thick for your liking you can add a splash of water.<br>Taste for seasoning, adding salt and pepper if necessary. Serve with mashed pumpkin.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-05-04 09:39:29','2021-05-04 10:24:23',NULL),(275,'ykissn','Chicken Fried Rice','Make a classic Chinese takeaway in your own kitchen with fresh ingredients! Delicious and quick to make with spring onion, red pepper and carrot. The veg is stir-fried into onion, garlic and ginger before adding the rice.  Soy sauce and sesame oil drizzled through at the end finishes off the lovely Asian flavour.','None',5,20,'<div>Cook your rice - place the rice and some salt into a pot of water and bring to the boil. Time 20 minutes from start of boiling and your rice should be done. Drain and spread it out on a sheet pan or plates for moisture to evaporate and for the rice to cool.</div>\n<div>Heat some oil in a pan and fry the salted chicken strips for about 8 minutes or until the pink bits are gone. Take out of the pan and set aside for now.</div>\n<div>In the same pan add a little more oil and fry the onion for 2 minutes. Then add the garlic and ginger and fry for 30 seconds before adding the carrot and red pepper. Add some salt to taste and fry for 2 minutes more.</div>\n<div>Add the cooked rice and the spring onions. Stir in well, breaking down any clumps of rice and adding a little more oil if everything is sticking.</div>\n<div>Stir in the soy sauce mix and then add the chicken back and cook until everything is heated through.<br />Serve immediately.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-05-06 10:41:07','2023-05-23 09:53:34',NULL),(276,'sackcu','One Pot Tomato Gnocchi with Parmesan & Cheddar','The gnocchi is simmered with spinach in a tomato, onion, garlic and mushroom mix, spiced with Italian seasoning and flavoured with a good portion of grated Parmesan. Serve with a sprinkling of grated cheddar - nutritious and junk-free comfort food in under half an hour!','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,10,'<p>Heat some oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add the onion and mushrooms and fry for about 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the garlic and fry for 30 seconds before adding the tomato.</p>\n<p>Stir well and add the Italian seasoning plus a pinch of salt and 1/2 tsp of sugar per person you are cooking for.</p>\n<p>Bring back to simmer. Add the spinach and cook for 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the uncooked gnocchi and stir all together. Simmer for 3 to 4 minutes to cook the gnocchi.</p>\n<p>Stir in the Parmesan cheese and serve with a scattering of grated cheddar on each portion.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-05-08 08:15:57','2021-05-11 09:52:10',NULL),(277,'qhceng','Pork Sausages with Tomato & Spinach Gnocchi','The gnocchi is simmered with spinach in a tomato, onion, garlic and mushroom mix, spiced with Italian seasoning and flavoured with a good portion of grated Parmesan. Serve with pork sausages for a quick but really good meal.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,20,'<p>Heat some oil in a frying pan and cook the pork sausages on a medium heat for 20 minutes, turning occasionally.</p>\n<p>While the sausages are cooking, heat some more oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add the onion and mushrooms and fry for about 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the garlic and fry for 30 seconds before adding the tomato.</p>\n<p>Stir well and add the Italian seasoning plus a pinch of salt and 1/2 tsp of sugar per person you are cooking for.</p>\n<p>Bring back to simmer. Add the spinach and cook for 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the uncooked gnocchi and stir all together. Simmer for 3 to 4 minutes to cook the gnocchi.</p>\n<p>Stir in the Parmesan cheese and serve with the pork sausages.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-05-08 08:33:44','2022-04-11 10:20:44',NULL),(278,'nxlroi','Lamb Flatbreads with a Mint Yoghurt Drizzle','Make your own wholewheat flatbreads and then top with fried ground lamb with a Middle Eastern flavour. We send you a ready made minted yoghurt dressing to drizzle over the top. Really delicious.','Gluten and Lactose',5,40,'<p class=\"p1\">Mix the whole wheat flour mix with the yoghurt marked for the flatbreads in a plastic bowl. You may need a little extra flour for your hands. Knead the dough well on a floured counter top. Wrap in plastic or cover with a cloth and let it rest, while you start the meat.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">Cook the lamb mince for 5-6 mins in a non-stick frying pan over a high heat. When starting to brown, stir in the garlic and spices, then cook for 2-3 mins more until the mince is brown and there is no liquid left in the pan. Chop the fresh mint. Stir in the chopped tomatoes , the mint and salt and pepper.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">Heat a little oil to a high heat in another non-stickpan. If you have only one pan, remove the lamb mince and keep warm. Take a biggish ball of your dough and flatten to fit your pan, or as flat as you can get! Put the dough in the pan and then immediately flip over so that both sides have oil on. Then cook for about 1 minute a side, or until a good colour. Repeat with the rest of the dough, keeping the flatbread warm. Add a splash more oil to the pan when you need to.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">To serve: assemble some lamb mince on a flatbread and drizzle with yoghurt and mint dressing.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-05-09 06:55:42','2021-05-24 14:22:46',NULL),(279,'zvphyj','Pork and Peanut Thai Curry','Very easy to put together - the secret is in the Thai Peanut Sauce which we send to you ready made. Pork strips, spring onions, red pepper, butternut and peas complete this nutritious, extremely tasty Thai curry. Eat it with rice (included) or without if you are looking for a low carb meal.','None',5,25,'<p class=\"p1\">Put a pot of salted water on to boil. Add the rice. Time 20 minutes from when the rice is boiling and it should be done. Drain and keep warm</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">Heat some oil in another pot. Add the spring onions and coriander and cook for 1 min. Add the pork and cook for 5 mins until starting to brown.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">Add the Thai curry sauce, the red pepper and the butternut. Mix well, put a lid on and leave to simmer for 15 mins, stirring occasionally.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">Remove the lid, add the peas and increase the heat. Bubble for 3 mins until the peas are cooked and the sauce has thickened a little. Stir in the lemon juice.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">Serve with the rice (or without if you are cutting carbs).</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-05-10 09:41:11','2021-05-10 09:53:21',NULL),(280,'bdqlvo','Mongolian Beef Strips with Spring Onion','A beef dish with a strongly Asian flavour, featuring sweetened soy sauce, garlic, ginger and lots of spring onions. The beef strips are tossed in cornflour to give a nice thick sauce which is mopped up by  lightly fried cabbage. This is one for the low carbers looking for something different.','None',5,25,'<p>Lightly season the beef strips with salt and pepper and toss them in the cornflour. Let them sit while you make the sauce.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil, in a small pot, medium heat and fry the garlic and ginger for 30 seconds, before adding the soy sauce mix. Raise the heat to medium high and simmer for 4 minutes whilst stirring. Take off the heat.</p>\n<p>In a bigger pot heat some more oil and stir fry the beef strips until they are no longer pink, about 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the sauce and stir well, scraping the bottom of the pot. Add the spring onions and cook for a further 2 to 3 minutes. Keep warm.</p>\n<p>Add a little oil to a big skillet or electric frying pan, let it heat, add the cabbage and stir fry it for 5 minutes. Do not overcook. It\'s better to have it slightly crunchy. Add salt and black pepper to taste.</p>\n<p>Serve the beef strips on a bed of cabbage.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-05-13 09:52:04','2021-05-13 10:08:43',NULL),(281,'xhzihp','Sweet Potato & Bean Wraps','Kidney beans are cooked up with onion, garlic, chilli and cumin, mustard and soy sauce and then mixed with mashed sweet potato to make an addictively good filling. Place this plus grated cheddar cheese on your wraps, roll them up and heat them through in the oven. Serve with sour cream and spring onions.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,35,'<p>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Add salt to a pot of water and bring to the boil. Add the sweet potato and boil for 20 minutes. It should be soft enough to mash. Drain and mash.</p>\n<p>While the sweet potato is boiling, add some oil to another pot, heat it on a medium heat and fry the onion for 5 minutes or until softened. Add the garlic and fry for 30 seconds before adding the beans, the soy sauce, the mustard, chilli powder and cumin.</p>\n<p>Mash the beans roughly and add a little water to the pot to make a good stirrable consistency. Cook together for 2 minutes, stirring.</p>\n<p>When the sweet potatoes are ready and mashed add them to the bean mixture, adding a little water again if you need to thin the mixture.</p>\n<p>If you have refrigerated your wraps (which is not recommended) warm them for a few seconds in the microwave to make them easier to roll.</p>\n<p>Place the wraps on a flat surface and spoon some bean and potato mixture onto each, covering with grated cheddar.</p>\n<p>Roll the wraps as tight as you can and snuggle them into an oven dish. Bake for 12 minutes to heat everything through.</p>\n<p>Serve the wraps each with a tablespoon of the sour cream with spring onions on top.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-05-14 10:32:34','2021-05-14 11:03:44',NULL),(282,'jaknmt','Egg Fried Rice with Beef Mince','We\'ve given the classic fried rice another twist. First of all we use brown rice which we send to you ready cooked. The mince is fried with garlic, ginger and spices, before adding the egg and then the rice. Instead of using the normal spring onions we soak chopped red onion in wine vinegar and add it at the end. It has a lovely crunch without the raw onion flavour. Green beans are added for extra nutrition and nice colour.','None',5,25,'<p>Pour the red wine vinegar over the red onion in a bowl and leave to soak, stirring now and again.</p>\n<p>Put a pot of salted water on to boil. When boiling add the green beans and boil for 10 minutes. Drain and set aside.</p>\n<p>While the beans are cooking, heat a generous dollop of oil in a big skillet. Add the cumin, paprika, garlic and ginger and fry for one minute.</p>\n<p>Add the beef mince, breaking into little pieces with a wooden spoon. Stir fry for 5 minutes or until the mince appears cooked. Stir in salt to taste.</p>\n<p>Break the eggs into the mince and leave to cook for a minute or two. Then break apart and swirl into the mince. Cook for 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the beans and rice and fry until heated through.</p>\n<p>Add the onion and stir through.</p>\n<p>Add a pinch of sugar to your soy sauce and pour it over the fried rice, heating through again.</p>\n<p>Serve in bowls.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-05-20 10:22:38','2021-05-20 10:49:08',NULL),(283,'cjjvnf','Baked Pumpkin Risotto with Smoked Pork Fillet','Baking a risotto is definitely the way forward - it cuts out all that stirring and anxiety that risottos generally cause! This creamy risotto includes leeks, pumpkin, mushrooms, parmesan and a generous portion of chopped smoked pork fillet. A deliciously comforting dish, served with some baby spinach alongside.','Traces of Lactose',5,40,'<p>Heat the oven to 180 degrees C.</p>\n<p>For this dish an oven-proof skillet with a lid is ideal. You can also use a pot for the stove top and then transfer to an oven dish with a lid if you do not have an oven proof skillet.</p>\n<p>In your ovenproof skillet or your pot, heat some oil on a medium heat and fry the leeks and the smoked pork fillet for 5 minutes. Add the mushrooms and fry until golden, about 3 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the garlic and fry for 30 seconds before adding the pumpkin and rice. Add a dash more oil if you feel it needs it. Fry the mixture, stirring now and again for a few minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the wine and allow to simmer for 2 minutes, still stirring frequently.</p>\n<p>Make the stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Add the stock to the skillet and stir all together.</p>\n<p>Put the lid on and place in oven. If you are cooking in a pot that is not oven-proof transfer the mixture to an oven dish that has a lid.</p>\n<p>Bake for 25 minutes and the the rice and pumpkin should be cooked.</p>\n<p>Stir the grated Parmesan through the risotto and serve with some rocket alongside.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-05-25 08:23:04','2022-12-09 09:17:50',NULL),(284,'ysjltv','Leek & Mushroom Quiche with Polenta Crust','The polenta crust makes a nice solid quiche giving us a satisfying and healthy meal. There are plenty of mushrooms and leeks along with chives and parsley on that base which is covered with a cottage cheese, parmesan and egg mixture. Top with more parmesan and grated cheddar and bake until golden.','Lactose',5,45,'<p>Heat the oven to 180 degrees C. Grease an oven dish.</p>\n<p>Make your stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Place the stock in a pot and bring to the boil.</p>\n<p>Turn the heat down to medium and slowly pour the polenta into the stock whisking all the time. It will thicken as you go and after a few minutes you will have a thick consistency that comes away from the sides of the pot. Take it off the heat and stir in half the parmesan. Spread the polenta into the greased oven dish using a plastic spoon or spatula to smooth and press it down.</p>\n<p>Bake the polenta crust for 20 minutes while you make the topping.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a pan and fry the leeks and mushrooms for about 10 minutes on a medium heat. Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute more. Take off the heat and spread on top of the polenta crust when it comes out of the oven.</p>\n<p>Whisk the eggs, add milk (1 tablespoon of milk per person you are cooking for) the cottage cheese and half the parmesan. Whisk together well but don\'t worry about the odd lump of cottage cheese. Chop the parsley and chives. Add the chives and parsley. Season well with salt and pepper.</p>\n<p>Pour the egg and cottage cheese mixture over the top of the quiche and sprinkle the cheddar cheese over that. Bake for 35 minutes - the middle should be set. Leave to cool for 5 minutes before serving.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-05-27 10:31:06','2022-07-17 09:25:00',NULL),(285,'hwtxkq','Herbed Pumpkin & Mushroom Bake','This heartwarming dish has layers of pumpkin mashed with Italian herbs and olive oil, a tomato and mushroom mix, and baby spinach leaves. It is topped with cottage cheese mixed with egg and parmesan. Loads of nutrition packed into this tasty bake.','Lactose',5,45,'<p>Heat the oven to 180 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil and boil the pumpkin for 20 minutes. It should be soft enough to mash but not overdone. Drain the pumpkin and mash it with the olive oil and herb mix. Season to taste with salt and pepper.</p>\n<p>While the pumpkin is cooking, heat some oil in a pan and fry the onion and mushrooms for 10 minutes on a medium heat. Add the garlic, stir in well, and cook for another minute. Add the tomato paste, the balsamic vinegar, the Italian seasoning, and the tomatoes. Add half a teaspoon of sugar for each person you are cooking for and stir well. Cook for 10 minutes to thicken slightly. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Take off the heat.</p>\n<p>Whisk together the egg and cottage cheese and add 1 tablespoon of milk for each person you are cooking for. Season to taste with salt and pepper and add half the parmesan.</p>\n<p>Place a layer of pumpkin on the bottom of an oven dish, cover with some baby spinach leaves and then some tomato and mushroom mix. Repeat this and then spread the cottage cheese mixture over the top. Sprinkle the remaining parmesan over that.</p>\n<p>Bake for 25 minutes. Allow to stand for 5 minutes or so before serving.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-05-27 11:05:50','2021-05-27 11:43:21',NULL),(286,'xorxfb','Honey Soy Steak with Roasted Veg Noodles','Porterhouse steak is given an Asian twist with our marinade. Sear it, slice it thin and toss it with roasted pumpkin, broccoli and egg noodles. Add more of the marinade and serve with sliced spring onions and toasted sesame seeds.','Gluten',5,35,'<p>Heat the oven to 200 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Place the pieces of steak in a dish and brush with marinade both sides. Leave some marinade for serving.</p>\n<p>Place the pumpkin pieces in a single layer on the baking paper on a baking tray and place in oven. Time for 20 minutes. When the 20 minutes is up, take the tray out, shift the pumpkin up and place broccoli florets on the tray. Put the pumpkin and broccoli back into the oven and time for 15 minutes.</p>\n<p>While the veg is roasting, prepare your noodles and steak.</p>\n<p>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil, add the noodles and boil for 4 minutes. Drain and keep warm. Add a touch of oil to stop them sticking together.</p>\n<p>Heat a pan on medium heat. When hot add the sesame seeds and dry-fry for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring. They should be golden brown and aromatic when they are ready. Place in a bowl to cool.</p>\n<p>To the same pan, add oil and turn the heat up to medium high. When the oil is hot, add the steaks and fry for 6 to 8 minutes, turning now and again and seasoning with salt and black pepper to taste.</p>\n<p>When the steaks are to your liking, take them out of the pan and use a sharp knife to slice them thinly. Keep warm.</p>\n<p>When the veg is done, use a large bowl to toss the noodles, veg, steak and marinade. Serve topped with the spring onions and the sesame seeds.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-06-02 10:35:53','2021-06-02 10:57:03',NULL),(287,'fpqvxs','Steak Strips on a Roasted Pumpkin, Mushroom & Kale Salad','Pumpkin, red onion, mushrooms and kale are first drizzled with olive oil and seasoning and roasted to perfection. The veg is then tossed in a Dijon mustard dressing and topped with pan-fried Porterhouse cut into strips. A delicious low-carb dinner with loads of colour and taste.','None',5,45,'<p>Heat the oven to 200 degrees C. Place the two pieces of baking paper on two oven trays.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Coat the pumpkin and red onion with oil and salt and pepper and place in a single layer on one of the baking trays. Place in oven and time for 30 minutes.</p>\n<p>Place the kale on the other baking tray. Coat the mushrooms in a little of the Dijon Mustard dressing and place on top of the kale. Season with salt and pepper. When the pumpkin and onion has been in for 30 minutes, put the kale and mushrooms in for 15 minutes, i.e the pumkin and onion roast for 45 minutes and the kale and mushroom for 15 minutes.</p>\n<p>While the veg is roasting, heat some oil in a pan on a medium high heat. Season your steak with salt and black pepper and fry for 3 to 4 minutes per side, or to your own liking. When done let the steak rest for a minute or two then use a sharp knife to cut the steak into strips. Keep warm.</p>\n<p>When the veg is ready place in a large serving bowl and toss with the rest of the dressing. Arrange the steak strips on top, or, alternatively, toss them with the salad and serve while still hot.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-06-03 06:44:12','2021-09-21 15:48:48',NULL),(288,'khkmei','Spicy Steak Burritos','Spread the middle of your tortilla with smooshed red kidney beans fried with onion, garlic and spices. Then add a fresh salad of shredded cabbage, chopped tomato, fresh coriander and lemon juice. Top this with slices of perfectly fried rump steak, also spiced, and a dollop of plain yoghurt. Wrap into a burrito - or any shape that takes your fancy!','Gluten and Lactose',5,20,'<p>Heat some oil in a pot and fry the onion for 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the garlic, half the cumin and half the paprika and fry for a further 1 minute.</p>\n<p>Add the beans and some water. Add 1 tablespoon of water per person that you are cooking for. Bring to a nice simmer and let it simmer for 2 to 3 minutes. It should thicken. Remove from the heat and mash roughly. Keep the bean mixture warm.</p>\n<p>Place the cabbage, tomato, fresh coriander and lemon juice in a bowl and mix together. Season to taste with a little salt and pepper.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a pan. Rub the steak with the other half of the cumin and paprika, chilli flakes and some salt. When the pan is hot fry the steak about 4 minutes each side or to your liking.</p>\n<p>Take the steak off the heat and let it rest for a minute or two before slicing into thin slices with a sharp knife.</p>\n<p>If the tortillas are too cold to fold nicely then pop them in the microwave for a few seconds to warm them.</p>\n<p>Place a tortilla on a plate. Put some fried beans in the centre, leaving space at the top, bottom and sides. Top this with cabbage salad and then with slices of steak. Finish with a dollop of yoghurt.</p>\n<p>Fold the top and bottom in, then roll from one side to the other, tucking and compressing as you go. Don\'t worry if your burrito isn\'t perfect - it will be delicious anyway!</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-06-08 10:10:00','2021-06-08 10:36:05',NULL),(289,'wpifrf','Cheesy Haddock Pie','Fish Pie has always been a family favourite. Layers of mash potato with real butter, poached haddock and peas are baked with a cheese sauce giving us good old fashioned comfort food while also being a healthy meal. Easy to make, wonderful to eat.','Gluten & Lactose',5,50,'<p>Heat the oven to 180 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Put a pot of salted water on to boil. Cut your potatoes into 8 bits each. We like to leave the skins on for added nutrition. When the water is boiling, pop in the potato pieces and time for 25 minutes. They should now be soft enough to mash.</p>\n<p>Mash with half the butter and salt and pepper. Place in the bottom of an oven dish.</p>\n<p>While the potato is cooking, pour the milk into a pan and place the pieces of haddock into the milk. Bring to a simmer. Once the pan is simmering, time 10 minutes.</p>\n<p>When the 10 minutes is up drain the haddock over a bowl or jug to catch the milk. You will use this milk to make the cheese sauce. Then break up the haddock into chunks and lay over the potato in the oven dish. Sprinkle the peas over the top of the fish.</p>\n<p>In a small pot, melt the rest of the butter over a medium heat. When it is melted add the flour and stir into a paste that will pull away from the sides of the pot. Cook, stirring, for 1 minute. If your paste is too thick a few drops of oil will sort it out.</p>\n<p>Top up the milk from the poaching fish to make 125 ml per person you are cooking for as some may have evaporated off. For example, if you are cooking for 2 it is 125 ml x 2 = 250 ml. Pour the milk onto the paste, bit by bit. Take a whisk and whisk the mixture continuously until it thickens. While you are doing this, add salt to taste and a few grinds of black pepper.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>When the sauce is thickened, take off the heat and add 2/3 of your grated cheese, stirring until it is melted in nicely.</p>\n<p>Pour the sauce over the other ingredients in the oven dish and then sprinkle the remaining grated cheese on the top.</p>\n<p>Bake for 25 minutes or until golden and bubbling.</p>\n<p>Chop the parsely and use it to garnish each serving.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-06-10 11:07:32','2022-01-10 13:32:56',NULL),(290,'tmhxse','Chicken & Mushroom Casserole','A delicious casserole for anyone, but especially those watching their carbs. This chicken dish features mushrooms, spinach, cauliflower and mozzarella wrapped in a creamy thyme sauce and sprinkled with more mozzarella before being baked until golden.','Lactose',5,45,'<p>Heat oven to 180 degrees C and grease an oven dish.</p>\n<p>Place the chicken in a big bowl with half the garlic powder, all the onion powder and some salt and pepper. Toss it around so the chicken is nicely coated.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a pan and fry the seasoned chicken until golden, 8 minutes. Remove from heat.</p>\n<p>In the same pan, in the chicken juices, fry the mushrooms, spinach and the other half of the garlic powder. Season with salt and pepper. Fry, stirring now and then, for 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Place the chicken in the oven dish, along with the cauliflower. Add the mushroom and spinach mix and 1/3 of the mozzarella. Mix all together.</p>\n<p>Now make your sauce. First dissolve the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</p>\n<p>Place the cornstarch in a small pot along with a dash of the stock to make a paste. Use a wooden spoon and stir the paste until smooth. Then add the rest of the stock and the cream and stir over a medium heat until thick. Do not boil. The sauce should thicken quickly.</p>\n<p>Take off the heat and add the thyme and salt and pepper to taste.</p>\n<p>Pour the sauce over the contents of the oven dish and sprinkle the remaining mozzarella on top.</p>\n<p>Bake until golden - 25 minutes.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-06-10 11:30:49','2021-07-19 14:41:50',NULL),(291,'basoac','Sesame Beef Stir Fry','Strips of beef are coated in sesame seeds in this quick and easy stir fry. Julienne carrots, sliced green beans and baby corn are your veggies, adding colour and nutrients. Crushed garlic, minced ginger, oyster sauce, soy sauce and sesame oil add flavour and an Eastern touch. Serve with rice.','None',5,25,'<p>Place rice in a pot of salted water and bring to the boil. Time 20 minutes from the start of the boiling and your rice should be ready. Drain and keep warm.</p>\n<p>While the rice is cooking, heat some oil in a pan or wok. Toss the beef strips with the sesame seeds. On a high heat stir fry the beef strips for 2 minutes. If you are cooking for more than 2 people then you will need to do the meat in two batches otherwise it makes moisture and \"stews\" instead of fries.</p>\n<p>Take the beef out of the pan and set aside. Add a bit more oil and the garlic and ginger. Fry for one minute before adding the beans, carrots and baby corn. Stir fry the veg with the garlic and ginger for 3 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the beef back to the pan or wok along with the Oyster Sauce Mix and stir fry all together for 2 to 3 minutes.</p>\n<p>Serve with rice.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-06-22 09:20:08','2021-06-23 06:21:39',NULL),(292,'dyueeh','Dijonnaise Chicken Rice Wraps','Combine the shredded cabbage with our home-made Dijonnaise dressing. Place the cabbage, some sprouts and pan-fried chicken bits onto a rice wrap and wrap like a bambino! Serve some more Dijonnaise on the side for dipping - delicious!','None',10,10,'<p class=\"p1\">&nbsp;</p>\n<ol class=\"ol1\">\n<li class=\"li2\">In a pan, heat some oil. Add the chicken and cook for about 10 minutes until the chicken is cooked through. Season well with salt and pepper. Set aside.</li>\n<li class=\"li2\">In a large bowl, mix the cabbage and 2/3 of the Dijonnaise. Put the rest of the Dijonnaise in a bowl for dipping at the table.</li>\n<li class=\"li2\">When you are ready to eat, place the bowl of cabbage, the sprouts, the Dijonnaise for dipping and the cooked chicken on the table.</li>\n<li class=\"li2\">Pour some lukewarm water into a pan large enough to fit a rice wrap into it without it snapping. Dip one rice wrap into the water and hold it there for ten seconds, remove and immediately put it onto a plate (don&rsquo;t let it sit in the water for more then 10 seconds).</li>\n<li class=\"li2\">Once it\'s on the plate, immediately load it with some cabbage, a sprinkle of sprouts and some chicken. Wrap it up by folding the bottom up and then each side in, like swaddling a baby. Pick it up, dip it in the extra Dijonnaise and devour!</li>\n</ol>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-06-28 15:44:25','2022-07-17 16:25:59',NULL),(293,'txgqua','Chicken Tacos','Shredded chicken in a spicy marinara sauce forms the base of the taco. Top it with a fresh tomato, red onion & coriander salsa, grated cheddar cheese, jalapeno and sour cream. Heat the taco shells to make them nice and crispy, load them up, and enjoy!','Lactose',5,25,'<p>Heat the oven to 180 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Put the whole chicken breasts into salted water, just covering them, and bring to a boil. Turn down the heat and let them simmer for 12 minutes.</p>\n<p>Remove the chicken from the pot. Place the chicken on a board and use a sharp knife and a fork to shred it into pieces. Do not worry if the chicken is still a bit pink - it will be cooked further.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Using the same pot (tip out the water) heat some oil and add the shredded chicken.</p>\n<p>Add the spice and stir well, cooking for 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the marinara sauce, stir well and let the pot simmer for 5 minutes more.</p>\n<p>While the chicken is simmering, hang the taco shells over the grid of the oven shelf. Let them crisp up for 3 or 4 minutes and then remove.</p>\n<p>Put the salsa into a bowl and add salt and pepper if you would like to.</p>\n<p>Take the chicken off the heat and taste for seasoning, adding salt and pepper if needed.</p>\n<p>Let everyone assemble their own tacos by spooning in some chicken, some salsa, jalapenos (for those that like the heat), grated cheddar and sour cream.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-06-30 11:14:40','2021-07-09 14:42:40',NULL),(294,'brugmw','Rump Steak in A Creamy Red Wine Sauce with Cauli-Rice','Pan-fried rump steak, thinly sliced and finished in a creamy red wine sauce. Serve on a bed of cauli-rice cooked in butter with a good twist of freshly ground black pepper and some leafy greens. A meal that is low in carbs and high in nutritious flavour.','Lactose',5,30,'<p>Make your stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Set aside.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a pan and on a fairly high heat pan fry your steak for 15 minutes, or to your liking, seasoning well with salt and black pepper. Remove the steak onto a board and let it rest for 2 minutes before thinly slicing with a sharp knife. Set the slices aside for now.</p>\n<p>Heat the remaining juices in the pan and add the red wine. Allow to simmer for 3 minutes, scraping the pan with a wooden spoon to get all the yummy bits off and into the sauce.</p>\n<p>Add the stock to the pan, stir in well, and simmer for 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the cream to the pan, stir in well, and allow to simmer until the sauce thickens. This can take 5 to 10 minutes.</p>\n<p>Once the sauce is thickened add the steak slices back to the pan and cook in the sauce for a few minutes.</p>\n<p>While the sauce is cooking, heat the butter in another pan or pot and, on a medium to high heat, saute the cauli-rice for a few minutes - 3 to 5 minutes should be plenty. Add salt to taste. Keep warm.</p>\n<p>When the steak and sauce is ready, serve it on a bed of cauli-rice. Grind a bit of black pepper over the top and serve some leafy greens on the side.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-07-01 08:34:27','2021-07-01 08:59:35',NULL),(295,'iwjvzw','Pork Strips in Mustard Sauce','Pork strips cooked in a white sauce, flavoured and textured with whole grain and Dijon mustard, nutmeg, and marjoram, then served with sweet potato and green beans smashed with butter and salt.\nA very satisfying meal that is quick and easy to prepare.','Gluten and Lactose',5,25,'<p>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Add the sweet potato chunks and boil for 15 minutes. Then add the beans to the same pot and cook for a further 5 minutes. The sweet potato should be soft.</p>\n<p>Drain and place the veg in a bowl and roughly \"smash\" with half the butter and some salt. Keep warm.</p>\n<p>While the veg is cooking, start the pork.&nbsp; Heat some oil in a large skillet or pot and fry the onion for 3 minutes on a medium heat.</p>\n<p>Add the pork strips and salt &amp; pepper to taste. Fry the pork and onion together for 8 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the other half of the butter to the pork and onions and let it melt into the juices already in the pan. Add the flour and stir well. Cook for 2 minutes, stirring frequently.</p>\n<p>Heat the milk, on the stovetop or in the microwave - careful it does not boil. Add the hot milk to the pot of pork and keep stirring while the sauce thickens. When the sauce is starting to boil, turn the heat down to medium low.</p>\n<p>Add the two different types of mustard, the marjoram and half a teaspoon of sugar for each person you are cooking for ie 2 teaspoons for 4 people.</p>\n<p>Blend everything well and stir while it cooks for 5 minutes. Then sprinkle the nutmeg on top and stir it in well. Taste for seasoning, adding salt and pepper to your own liking.</p>\n<p>Serve the pork on the \"smashed\" sweet potato and beans.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-07-02 11:28:38','2021-08-26 14:07:08',NULL),(296,'turktx','Orange & Honey Chicken Tray Bake','Fresh orange juice, a touch of honey and some garlic give this chicken and veg tray bake a wonderful burst of flavour. Orange slices baked on the chicken make it impressive to look at and extra yummy! Very easy to put together, the dish is served with buttery polenta. If you need to adapt to low-carb replace the polenta with a salad or some cauli-rice (not included).','None',5,45,'<p>Preheat the oven to 200 degrees C. Use a bit of oil or butter to grease a large baking tray.</p>\n<p>Place the pumpkin, carrots and red onion into a bowl. Add the dried rosemary, salt and pepper and a drizzle of oil. Toss all together amd place on the baking tray.</p>\n<p>Nestle the pieces of chicken in amongst the vegetables. Decant the honey, soy sauce and garlic mixture into a bowl. Cut your orange in half and squeeze juice from one half into this mix and stir.&nbsp; Pour the sauce over the pieces of chicken.</p>\n<p>Place in the oven and bake for 25 minutes. Take the baking pan out and use the pan juices to baste the chicken. Slice the second half of your orange into thin slices (leaving the skin on). Place the orange slices on top of the chicken and bake for a further 15 minutes.</p>\n<p>While the chicken is cooking, make the polenta.</p>\n<p>Place the chicken stock powder in a pot and cover with the amount of boiling water specifed on the package of stock powder. Bring the stock to a boil on a medium to high heat and slowly add the polenta bit by bit, using a whisk to constantly stir. The polenta will thicken up and start pulling away from the side of the pot. This will only take a few minutes.</p>\n<p>Take the polenta off the heat and stir in the butter. Keep it warm until your chicken is ready to serve.</p>\n<p>When the chicken comes out of the oven let it stand for 5 minutes and then serve it on the polenta. If you prefer a low-carb option, leave out the polenta and add a side salad or some cauli-rice (not in the kit).</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-07-07 11:59:42','2022-06-23 09:05:09',NULL),(297,'przybj','Quinoa with Sweet Potato, Mushrooms & Pecan Nuts','Quinoa, superfood of the ancient Incas, makes a delicious and nutrient-packed base for many dishes, savoury and sweet. Here it is combined with sweet potatoes, mushrooms, onion, garlic and a touch of cayenne pepper. Topped with plenty of chopped pecan nuts, this is a really tasty vegetarian meal.','None',5,25,'<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Put a pot on the stove and add the amount of water specified on the stock package. Add the stock powder and bring to a boil.</p>\n<p>Add the quinoa to the pot, turn the heat down so that it just simmers, put the lid on and leave for 20 minutes. Check from time to time that there is still a little liquid in the pot.</p>\n<p>Take the pot off the stove and leave it with the lid on to gently steam until your sweet potato mixture is ready.</p>\n<p>While the quinoa is cooking, heat some oil in a skillet with a lid.</p>\n<p>Cook the onion for 5 minutes. Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute more.</p>\n<p>Add the mushrooms and sweet potato to the skillet and stir in the cayenne pepper. Add salt and pepper to taste.</p>\n<p>Put the lid on the skillet, reduce the heat to medium low and cook the veg until the sweet potato is soft, about 20 minutes. The vegetables should cook in their own steam but if they are sticking put a splash of water in the skillet.</p>\n<p>When everything is ready, toss the quinoa with the sweet potato &amp; mushroom mix and top with the pecan nuts. Serve in bowls.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-07-08 06:51:41','2022-01-11 14:34:43',NULL),(298,'caxqrv','Low Carb Spicy Chicken','Fry cubed chicken fillets with our Taco spice mix and add our Marinara sauce for an easy to put together low carb main. The Spicy Chicken is served with green beans and cauli-rice fried in a generous portion of butter.','None',5,25,'<p>Heat some oil in a skillet or pot on a medium to high heat. Add the chicken pieces and salt and pepper to taste. Cook for 8 minutes, stirring frequently.</p>\n<p>Add the taco spice and stir in well. Cook, stirring, for another 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the marinara sauce, stir all together, turn the heat down and simmer for 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>While your chicken is cooking, start the beans and cauli-rice. Melt half the butter in another pot on a medium heat and add the beans. Put the lid on and let the beans \"sweat\" in the butter for 10 minutes. Stir every now and again to check nothing is burning or catching on the bottom of the pot.</p>\n<p>After 10 minutes of the beans \"sweating\" add the other half of the butter and the cauli-rice. Let the two \"sweat\" together, stirring now and then for a further 5 minutes. Add salt to taste. Keep warm.</p>\n<p>When the chicken is ready, serve it on a bed of beans and cauli-rice.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-07-09 14:54:50','2022-08-21 16:29:30','<p>Marinara Sauce</p>\n<p>1 onion, chopped<br />2 tsp crushed garlic<br />1 tin chopped tomatoes<br />1 Tbsp tomato paste<br />1 tsp sugar<br />1 tsp dried basil<br />1 tsp dried oregano<br />salt and pepper to taste</p>\n<p>Fry the onion for 3 minutes. Add the garlic and fry for 1 minute more.<br />Add the tomatoes and the tomato paste, the sugar, the basil, and the oregano.<br />Bring to a simmer for 20 minutes or until the consistency and taste is good.<br />Add salt and pepper if need be.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(299,'amdlze','Thai Chicken & Mushroom Noodle Soup','This is a substantial soup with plenty of egg noodles, a little shredded chicken, sliced mushrooms, sugar snap peas and lots of fresh coriander and basil. Add to that the fabulous taste of Thai from the curry paste, garlic, ginger, coconut milk, lime juice and fish sauce and you have a soup to remember!','Gluten',5,25,'<p>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil and add the egg noodles. Boil for 3 to 4 minutes and then drain. Mix a few drops of ol into them to stop them sticking. Set aside.</p>\n<p>Make your stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Set aside for now.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a big pot on a medium heat and fry the onion for 3 minutes. Then add the garlic and curry paste and cook for another 2 minutes while stirring to stop it catching or burning.</p>\n<p>Add the ginger, the stock and the coconut milk and bring the mixture to a simmer.</p>\n<p>Add the chicken breast and put a lid on the pot. Let it simmer for 10 minutes. Take the chicken out and place on a board.</p>\n<p>Add the mushrooms and noodles and let them cook for 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>While they are cooking use a knife and fork to shred the chicken.</p>\n<p>Chop the fresh coriander, basil and spring onions.</p>\n<p>Add the chicken back to the pot, along with the Fish Sauce &amp; Lime Mix and the chopped herbs and spring onions.</p>\n<p>Bring back to the simmer and add the sugar snap peas. Cook for 2 minutes. Add the noodles and heat right through and then remove from the heat.</p>\n<p>Let it cool for 5 minutes before serving in bowls.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-07-11 16:00:59','2022-11-02 11:09:11',NULL),(300,'nubzsk','Sweet Potato, Spinach & Halloumi Curry','A mild but  extremely tasty curry of sweet potato, tomato, spinach, coconut milk, our spice mix and chickpeas. A dash of chutney stirred in gives a lovely touch. Serve in a bowl topped with crispy fried halloumi - delicious.','Traces of Lactose',5,35,'<p>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil and parcook the sweet potato cubes for 8 minutes. Drain and put the drained sweet potatoes back into the pot.</p>\n<p>Add the tomato and the spice mix and bring to a simmer.</p>\n<p>Add the coconut milk and the spinach, stirring the spinach in until it wilts down and the mixture is simmering nicely. Add the chutney and let everything simmer together and thicken, 15 minutes should do it.</p>\n<p>Add the chick peas, stirring them in and letting them heat through.</p>\n<p>While the curry is simmering, heat a little oil on a fairly high heat in a pan. Fry the halloumi cubes until crispy. This happens quickly so watch carefully. If the halloumi sticks together, don\'t panic. Let it finish crisping and browning and then take it out of the pan and recut it into bits on a board.</p>\n<p>Serve the curry in bowls with the crispy pieces of halloumi on top.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-07-14 08:09:34','2021-07-14 08:35:21',NULL),(301,'knqcxl','Pesto Chicken Casserole with Sweet Potato & Spinach','Chicken pieces are baked with cream, red pesto, garlic, pitted olives and cubes of feta cheese until golden and bubbling. It\'a a fabulous low carb taste explosion that is nicely balanced by a sweet potato and spinach smash.','Lactose',5,50,'<p>Preheat the oven to 200 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a skillet on a medium to high heat. Season the chicken thighs to taste with salt and black pepper and fry them for 10 minutes until golden brown.</p>\n<p>Place the thighs in an oven dish. Set aside the skillet with the chicken juices for use later.</p>\n<p>Arrange the olives and the cubes of feta in the oven dish with the chicken.</p>\n<p>Mix the cream, the pesto and the garlic in a bowl and then pour it over the chicken, olives and feta.</p>\n<p>When the oven is hot enough bake the chicken for 40 minutes. The dish should be bubbly and golden around the edges and the chicken should be cooked through.</p>\n<p>While the chicken is cooking boil the sweet potatoes in salted water until soft enough to mash - 15 to 20 minutes.</p>\n<p>Heat the chicken juices in the skillet, adding more oil if it is a bit dry. Add the spinach and swish it around the skillet with a wooden spoon for 3 to 5 minutes. It needs to wilt down and become more tender. When done set aside and wait for the potato to be done.</p>\n<p>Mash the potato roughly with a little milk or butter, salt and pepper and stir the sauteed spinach into your \"smash\", but feel free to serve the two separately if you prefer.</p>\n<p>Serve two chicken pieces with a serving of the spinach mash and plenty of sauce.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-07-20 13:03:19','2023-05-24 07:23:12',NULL),(302,'fwyzsm','Creamy Parmesan Chicken','Chicken thighs are smothered in herbs and spices and cooked in the juices left by butter-fried mushrooms and garlic. The pan is then deglazed using a cream and Parmesan mix which simmers down into a beautiful sauce. Served with broccoli, this is a really special dish.','Lactose',5,50,'<p>Melt half the butter in a large skillet on a medium to high heat. Add the mushrooms and fry them in the butter for 3 minutes. Season with salt and black pepper. Add the garlic and fry for 1 minute further.</p>\n<p>Scoop the mushrooms out of the pan and set aside.</p>\n<p>Pat the Herb &amp; Spice Mix onto the pieces of chicken and place them in the mushroom juices in the skillet on a medium to high heat. Add the rest of your butter. Sprinkle a little salt and pepper onto the chicken.</p>\n<p>Put the lid on and let the chicken cook for 40 minutes or until the chicken is no longer pink inside. Lift the lid every now and then to check that nothing is burning. Turn the heat down if necessary.&nbsp; Turn the chicken pieces half way.</p>\n<p>While the chicken is cooking bring a pot of salted water to the boil and boil the broccoli for 4 minutes. Drain and keep warm.</p>\n<p>When the chicken is cooked scoop the pieces out of the pan, leaving the juices. Put the chicken aside with the mushrooms.</p>\n<p>Pour the cream into the pan and use a wooden spoon to scrape the brown bits off the bottom of the pan and into the sauce. Bring to a simmer.</p>\n<p>Add the parmesan and simmer for a minute or two until the sauce looks thick enough. Add back the mushrooms and stir in and then place the chicken pieces in the sauce long enough for it all to warm through together.</p>\n<p>Serve two pieces of chicken with a portion of broccoli and a generous amount of sauce.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-07-22 07:58:14','2022-06-12 07:52:40',NULL),(303,'ajqkxw','Black Beans with Quinoa','Spicy black beans with corn and rice is a common vegetarian meal. We have dropped the rice and added quinoa, a South American grain (seed to be technically correct) which is a great source of protein, fibre, vitamins and minerals. The quinoa is simmered with onion, garlic, spices and vegetable stock before adding corn and black beans. Fresh coriander is stirred through before serving with sliced tomato and spring onions.','None',5,30,'<p>Make the stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a pan on a medium to high heat and fry the onion for 3 minutes. Add the garlic and fry for 1 minute further.</p>\n<p>Add the cumin, cayenne, salt and black pepper to taste and stir into the onion while frying for 30 seconds. Then add the quinoa and stir fry for another 30 seconds.</p>\n<p>Pour in the stock, stir and bring to a boil. Cover the pot and turn the heat down so the quinoa mixture is simmering gently. Let it simmer for 20 minutes. The stock should be absorbed and the quinoa tender.</p>\n<p>Add the corn and the black beans and cook, stirring gently and frequently, for a few minutes - everything should be heated through.</p>\n<p>Chop the fresh coriander.</p>\n<p>Stir in most of the chopped coriander, reserving a little for the top when serving.</p>\n<p>Slice the tomatoes. Serve a portion of black beans and quinoa with sliced tomatoes on the side. Sprinkle the reserved coriander on the black beans and the spring onions onto the tomato.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-07-24 08:14:02','2022-03-31 07:49:07',NULL),(304,'jldlir','Broccoli & Quinoa Casserole','This broccoli bake has a creamy, cheesy quinoa base. The quinoa is simmered in broth, seasoned and mixed with milk and grated cheese before stirring in the blanched broccoli. It is then baked topped with more grated cheese and garlicky breadcrumbs and served with sun-dried tomato pesto. Delicious!','Gluten & Lactose',5,50,'<p>Heat the oven to 180 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Make the stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</p>\n<p>Put the stock into a pot and bring to the boil. Add the quinoa, lower the heat and put the lid on. The quinoa must simmer for 20 minutes or until the stock has been absorbed. Lift the lid every now and then to check.</p>\n<p>While the quinoa is cooking, blanche the broccoli. Put another pot on the stove with salted water. Bring to the boil and then pop the broccoli in for just 2 minutes. Drain and run cold water over it to stop it cooking. Set aside.</p>\n<p>Also while the quinoa is cooking, make your garlicky breadcrumbs. Melt the butter in a small pot and fry the garlic for 1 minute. Add the breadcrumbs and stir fry for another 2 minutes. Don\'t allow them to catch on the bottom of the pot. When done, set aside.</p>\n<p>When the quinoa is ready add some salt and black pepper to taste and the chilli flakes. Stir in 3/4 of the cheese and the milk. Stir well to make a nice creamy mixture.</p>\n<p>Pour this mixture into an oven dish. Stir in the broccoli and sprinkle the rest of the cheese on top. Finish off by covering with the garlicky breadcrumbs.</p>\n<p>Bake for 25 minutes. It should be bubbling and golden.</p>\n<p>Serve each portion with 2 tablespoons of sundried tomato pesto.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-07-25 08:10:07','2023-01-09 09:57:47',NULL),(305,'lphfiv','Easy Low Carb Moussaka','Inspired by the Greek classic but oh so much easier to make. We don\'t faff around with the separate baking of slices of aubergine - we cook it with the minced beef in little cubes. We keep all the traditional spices and pull it together with a delicious tomato sauce. Top it with a cheesy cream sauce and bake until bubbling and golden. You\'ll want to make this again and again.','Lactose (minimal)',5,40,'<p>Preheat oven to 180 degrees C.</p>\n<p>In a large frying pan or a stove-top to oven skillet, heat a generous portion of oil and fry the aubergine cubes and the onion for a few minutes until they start to soften and change colour.</p>\n<p>Add salt and pepper, the garlic and the spice mix.</p>\n<p>Add the mince and fry, breaking it up with a wooden spoon until it is cooked through ie no longer pink.</p>\n<p>Add the tomato sauce, stir in and simmer for a few minutes. If your skillet is not oven proof then transfer this mixture into an oven dish.</p>\n<p>For the cheese sauce place all the ingredients in a small pot but save 1/2 of the grated cheese for the top. Place pot on a medium heat and stir while the sauce comes together and then reaches a nice consistency.</p>\n<p>Pour the sauce over the meat mixture and sprinkle the rest of the cheese on top.</p>\n<p>Bake for 20 minutes or until nicely golden.</p>\n<p>Thinly slice the tomatoes and serve the slices on the side.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-07-30 12:37:18','2023-05-22 06:41:32','<p><strong>Marinara sauce</strong></p>\n<p><br />1 onion, finely chopped<br />1 tsp crushed garlic<br />a little oil<br />2 tbsp tomato paste (1 sachet)<br />2 tbsp balsamic vinegar&nbsp;<br />1 tin crushed tomato<br />1 tsp dried basil<br />1 tsp dried oregano&nbsp;<br />&frac12; tsp salt<br />Pepper, to taste</p>\n<p>Fry the onions in the oil until soft.<br />Add tomato paste, garlic, vinegar, crushed tomato and bring to a boil.<br />Add the herbs, salt and pepper.<br />Let it simmer on low for 20 minutes plus.</p>'),(306,'zvicml','Sirloin Steak with Mushroom Sauce & Green Beans','Our best mushroom sauce ever - guaranteed! And incredibly easy to make. A wonderful accompaniment to a nicely fried sirloin steak and some green beans. Good for the low carbers too.','Lactose (minimal)',5,35,'<p>Your steaks should be room temperature before you cook them so take them out of the fridge in advance. If they are in the freezer take them out in the morning and let them defrost out of the fridge for that evening.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a pan on a high heat. Salt your steak(s) and when the oil is very hot, sear the steaks for 2 minutes on each side to seal the juices in. Then turn down the heat and let the steaks cook, turning now and again, for 15 to 20 minutes, depending on how you like your steak.</p>\n<p>While the steak is cooking, prepare the green beans. Bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Add the beans and boil for 5 to 10 minutes, depending on how crunchy/soft you like your beans. When they are done, drain and keep warm.</p>\n<p>When the steaks are done set them aside to keep warm. Always let a cooked steak \"rest\" for 5 minutes before serving.</p>\n<p>In the same pan, using the juices and fat from the steak, fry the onion on a medium heat for 5 minutes. Add the mushrooms and salt and pepper to taste and fry for 5 minutes more.</p>\n<p>Add the cream and the dijon mustard and stir in well. Bring the pan to a simmer and let the sauce simmer for 5 minutes or until the consistency looks right.</p>\n<p>Serve a steak with a side of beans and smother it all with the delicious mushroom sauce.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-07-31 19:02:36','2021-08-03 07:36:37',NULL),(307,'hwajpw','Parmesan Crusted Chicken with Green Beans','This dish is similar to a Chicken a la King, only this time we stir through some cauli-rice, pop it in an oven dish, top it with Parmesan bread crumbs and bake until golden. We serve it with fresh green beans.','Gluten & Lactose',5,45,'<p>Heat the oven to 180 C.<br />Heat some oil in a medium size pot and fry the onion until just golden.<br />Add the chicken and the garlic and fry for about 10 minutes stirring frequently.<br />Add the flour and stir into the mixture. Cook for a few minutes whilst stirring so the flour doesn&rsquo;t catch on the bottom of the pot.<br />Slowly, bit by bit, add the milk and keep stirring until the sauce thickens. This should be done at a low to medium heat.<br />Add the stock powder and stir it through. Tip in the cauliflower and mix it in. Then allow the mixture to simmer for 5 - 10 minutes. If it appears to be too thick, add a little extra milk.<br />Turn the heat off. If you are not using an oven proof dish, &nbsp;transfer the mixture to one now. Sprinkle the parmesan crumb mixture over the top of the chicken and then place in the oven for 10 &ndash; 15 minutes.&nbsp;<br />While that is in the oven, prepare the green beans. Bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Add the beans and boil for 5 to 10 minutes, depending on how crunchy/soft you like your beans. When they are done, drain and keep warm.<br />Serve some parmesan crusted chicken with a side of the green beans.&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-08-02 13:20:11','2021-08-26 14:16:26',NULL),(308,'qhxbtq','Pulled Pork Shepherds Pie','We have come up with a really delightful version of an old favourite. Instead of the ground beef, we use pulled pork, mushrooms and baby marrow cooked in our home made passata. The topping is sweet potato with a dash of Dijon mustard and grated cheddar.','Traces of Lactose',5,45,'<p class=\"p1\">Preheat oven to 180 C.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">In a large pot, bring enough water to cover the sweet potato to the boil. Add some salt and the sweet potato and boil until soft enough to mash, 15 to 20 minutes. Once boiled, drain the water. Use a potato masher to mash until soft. Stir the mustard through the sweet potato and season to taste with salt and pepper. Stir the grated cheddar cheese through the mashed potato.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">Using the same or another pot, heat some oil and saut&eacute; the marrow and mushrooms for about 5 minutes until soft. Add the pulled pork and cook for 2 minutes before adding the passata and salt and pepper. Turn the heat low and let it simmer for 10 minutes.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">Pour the pulled pork mix into a baking dish. Spoon the mashed potato and cheese mixture over the pulled pork and use the back of a spoon to smooth it over.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">Place in the oven and bake for 25 minutes.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>While that&rsquo;s cooking, halve or quarter the cherry tomatoes. Serve some Shepherds pie with a side of the leafy greens and cherry tomatoes.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-08-02 13:30:24','2021-08-02 13:40:57',NULL),(309,'aaiofx','Dotti Biscotti\'s Fresh Spaghetti with a Tomato & Bacon Sauce','Dotti Biscotti\'s fresh spaghetti is made just down the road from us so you really cannot get fresher! The sauce is made with onion, garlic, mushrooms, bacon, tomato, basil and oregano - delicious and nutritious! We top it with grated cheddar.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,25,'<p>In a large pot, heat some oil over a medium heat. Add the onion and cook for 3 minutes. Add the garlic and mushrooms and cook for another 3 minutes.<br />Add the bacon bits and cook for 4 minutes before adding the tomatoes, beef stock powder, Worcestershire sauce, basil and oregano. Season well with salt and pepper. Simmer on low for 10 minutes.<br />While that is simmering, bring another pot of water to the boil. Add a dash of oil and the spaghetti. Use a fork to stir the spaghetti through the water to break it up. Boil for 3 minutes and then remove from the stove and drain the water.<br />Add the spaghetti and the chopped spinach to the tomato and bacon mix and stir well. Heat through for another 2 to 3 minutes before serving in bowls with a bit of grated cheese sprinkled over the top.&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-08-02 13:52:12','2022-11-30 10:50:57',NULL),(310,'pfitun','Beef Gozleme','A gozleme is a Turkish flatbread traditionally stuffed with spiced ground beef or lamb and then fried. The flatbread itself is made from flour, olive oil, salt and water. We have used spicy beef mince and feta for our filling and we serve a simple dressed salad on the side.','Gluten',10,30,'<p>Start with the Gozleme dough. In a bowl, mix the flour, oil and salt. The label on your flour will tell you how much water to add. Use a wooden spoon to mix the dough together and then use your hands to knead the dough. Knead it for 5 &ndash; 6 minutes until nice and smooth. Cover the bowl with a dish towel and let it sit while you cook your mince.</p>\n<p>On a medium heat, heat some oil in a pot and add the onion and garlic. Cook for a few minutes and then add the pepper. Cook for five minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the mince, breaking it up with a wooden spoon so there are no clumps. Add the spice mix and a &frac14; of a TBSP of water per person you are cooking for and simmer on a low heat for 10 minutes.</p>\n<p>While the mince is simmering, take the Gozleme dough from the bowl and break it into 4 pieces if you are cooking for 4, or 2 pieces if you are cooking for 1 or 2 people. &nbsp;Use a rolling pin (if you don&rsquo;t have a rolling pin you can use a wine bottle, a glass jar or a tin) to roll your pieces out until they are thin but not thin enough to create holes in the dough.</p>\n<p>You are going to top one or two pieces of dough (depending on how many pieces you have) with some mince, and then some crumbled feta, and then cover the top of that with your remaining piece(s) of dough. Use your fingers to pinch together the edges so that your mince and feta can&rsquo;t fall out.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil over a low to medium heat in a non-stick frying pan. Carefully slide your Golzeme into the frying pan and cook for 7 &ndash; 8 minutes before flipping it over to cook the other side &ndash; it should look crunchy and golden.</p>\n<p>Pop the salad ingredients into a bowl and toss with the dressing.</p>\n<p>Serve pieces of Gozleme with a side of salad.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-08-02 14:30:32','2021-08-03 06:47:38',NULL),(312,'uvcrsp','Spicy Thai Basil Chicken','This classic Thai dish is known as Pad Krapow Gai and is a popular street food in Thailand. Ground chicken or small chicken pieces are fried with garlic, spring onion or shallots and minced chilli. The pan is then deglazed with a mix of oyster sauce, soy sauce, fish sauce and a little sugar which forms a delicious coating for the chicken. Plenty of fresh basil is stirred through at the end and the dish is served with a mix of spinach and rice.','None',5,20,'<p>Place your rice in a pot of salted water and bring to the boil. Time 20 minutes from when it starts to boil and the rice should be done. With 2 minutes to go, pop the chopped spinach into the rice pot so the spinach wilts into the rice. Drain and keep warm.</p>\n<p>In a large plastic bowl, mix the corn flour with some salt and black pepper and toss the cubes of chicken in the corn flour mix.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a large skillet or pan on a fairly high heat and stir fry the coated chicken for 5 minutes or until the raw pink colour has gone. If you are cooking for 4 or more and your pan is not big you may have to do this step in two batches and then return all the chicken to the pan.</p>\n<p>Stir in the chopped spring onions, the chilli and the garlic and continue to cook, stirring, for 2 to 3 minutes. Turn down the heat if the bottom of the pan is burning.</p>\n<p>Add a tablespoon or two of the soy sauce mix and cook, still stirring, for 1 minute before adding the rest of the sauce and cooking for a further 2 minutes, still stirring.</p>\n<p>Chop the basil.</p>\n<p>Remove from the heat and stir the basil into the chicken dish.</p>\n<p>Serve with the rice and spinach mix.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-08-12 08:37:29','2022-05-13 12:45:59',NULL),(313,'xkazit','Cheesy Cauliflower Casserole with Bacon Bits','This cauliflower casserole is loaded with bacon bits, cheddar cheese and spring onions - a classic flavour combo. The cauliflower is softened by a few minutes in the pot and then mashed with butter, cream cheese and sour cream before adding the bacon, cheddar and spring onions. It is then baked to golden perfection.','Traces of Lactose',5,40,'<p>Heat the oven to 180 derees C.</p>\n<p>Heat a llittle oil in a pan on a fairly high heat and fry the bacon bits until nice and crispy. Set aside.</p>\n<p>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Add the caulfilower and boil for 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Tip the hot cauliflower into a large bowl with the butter, cream cheese and sour cream and mash it together with a potato masher, leaving some bits whole. Add salt and black pepper to taste.</p>\n<p>Add the bacon bits, the spring onions and two thirds of the cheddar cheese and stir all together.</p>\n<p>Place in an oven dish and top with remaining cheddar cheese.</p>\n<p>Bake for 35 minutes until golden brown on the top.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-08-16 08:01:08','2021-09-13 13:40:14',NULL),(314,'hdxwee','Spinach & Feta Gozleme with Balsamic Roast Veg','A gozleme is a stuffed flatbread originating in Turkey. The flatbread itself is made from flour, olive oil, salt and water. We stuff it with creamed spinach and feta before frying it to make it nice and crispy on the outside. The gozleme is served with balsamic roasted peppers, tomato and mushroom.','Gluten',10,30,'<p>Preheat your oven to 200 degrees C.</p>\n<p>In a bowl, mix the flour, oil and salt (1/2 tsp per person) for the dough. Add the amount of water specified on the flour package little by little, you do not want your dough too sticky. Use a wooden spoon to mix the dough together and then use your hands to knead the dough. Knead it for 5 &ndash; 6 minutes until nice and smooth. Cover the bowl with a dish towel and let it sit while you prepare your veg.</p>\n<p>For the veg, pour the Balsamic Mix into a bowl. Add the peppers, cherry tomatoes and mushrooms and toss together. Put the veg and the marinade into an oven dish and when the oven is ready roast the veg for 30 minutes.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Take the Gozleme dough from the bowl and break it into 4 pieces if you are cooking for 4, or 2 pieces if you are cooking for 1 or 2 people. &nbsp;Use a rolling pin (if you don&rsquo;t have a rolling pin you can use a wine bottle, a glass jar or a tin) to roll your pieces out until they are thin but not thin enough to create holes in the dough.</p>\n<p>You are going to top one or two pieces of dough (depending on how many pieces you have) with some creamed spinach, and then some crumbled feta, and then cover the top of that with your remaining piece(s) of dough. Use your fingers to pinch together the edges so that your spinach and feta can&rsquo;t fall out.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil over a low to medium heat in a non-stick frying pan. Carefully slide your Golzeme into the frying pan and cook for 7 &ndash; 8 minutes before flipping it over to cook the other side &ndash; it should look crunchy and golden.</p>\n<p>Slice the gozleme into wedges and serve with the roasted veggies.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-08-18 15:55:19','2022-05-24 11:21:00',NULL),(315,'jpmjzw','Pulled Pork Tacos with BBQ Sauce','Tacos are always fun to construct and to eat and even more so when we send your pulled pork and your BBQ sauce ready made. Stuff your taco with the saucy pork and a pineapple coriander slaw and enjoy!','None',10,10,'<p>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Heat the BBQ sauce in a pot and add the pulled pork. Stir until hot and then keep warm.</p>\n<p>Chop the fresh coriander and place in a bowl along with the cabbage, the pineapple, the red onion and the chilli flakes. Squeeze the lime juice over the top and mix together. Add salt and black pepper to taste.</p>\n<p>Stand the taco shells on a baking tray upside down or hang them over the oven grid bars to heat.&nbsp; This should take 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Set out the shells, the saucy pulled pork and the pineapple slaw and construct your tacos.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-08-24 15:45:17','2022-06-16 15:19:37','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Homemade BBQ Sauce</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">10 ml olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tsp crushed garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">3 Tbsp onion flakes or 1 Tbsp onion powder</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">125 ml apple cider vinegar</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">125 ml tomato sauce</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">125 ml water</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">125 ml sugar</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 Tbsp mustard</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 Tbsp Worcestershire Sauce</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp chilli powder</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 Tbsp cornstarch mixed with 2 Tbsp water</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heat oil and fry the garlic for 1 minute before adding all the other ingredients. Let the sauce cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Should make approx 400 ml</span></p>'),(316,'gcxval','Bacon Wrapped Chicken Stuffed with Tomato, Basil & White Cheddar','We send you the chicken breasts already butterflied and marinated in our homemade marinade. All you need do is stuff them with the basil, tomato and white cheddar, close them up, roll them in bacon slices and bake them in a hot oven. Tender and oh so delicious! Serve the chicken with buttered green beans on the side.','Traces of Lactose',10,35,'<p>Let your chicken thaw at room temperature and then pour off the excess marinade.</p>\n<p>Preheat the oven to 260 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Slice the tomato into thin slices. Open the butterflied chicken breasts and salt and pepper lightly. Place some basil leaves, a slice of tomato and 1/4 of the cheddar cheese into each.&nbsp; Fold over the top of the chicken and wrap 2 slices of bacon around each breast, securing with toothpicks. This can be messy but don\'t sweat it - it does not have to be perfect. It\'s the taste that counts!</p>\n<p>Place the chicken in an oven dish.&nbsp; Bake for 30 minutes.&nbsp;Take the dish out and sprinkle the parmesan cheese over the chicken and bake for a further 3 minutes to melt the cheese.</p>\n<p>While the chicken is in the oven, bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Add the green beans and cook for 5 to 10 minutes depending on how you like your beans. Drain and stir in the butter and some salt and pepper to taste. Keep warm and serve with the chicken.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-08-24 16:42:37','2021-08-26 10:07:50',NULL),(317,'vakxsr','Butter Chicken with Roasted Cauliflower','The best way to cook cauliflower? Roast it with coriander seeds, turmeric and butter - absolutely delicious! We pair it with a classic Butter Chicken made easy. We make the masala paste for you and the rest is a breeze.','Lactose',5,40,'<p>Preheat your oven to 200 degrees C.</p>\n<p>In a bowl, mix the masala paste with the larger amount of cream and then place the chicken cubes in the mixture.&nbsp; Place in the fridge for 20 minutes to marinate.</p>\n<p>Place the cauliflower, turmeric, coriander seeds and salt and pepper to taste in a bowl. Melt the butter marked for the cauliflower and pour it over, tossing everything together well. Place in a flat oven dish or pan tray in a single layer. When the oven has heated bake the cauliflower for 15 minutes. Take out and keep warm.</p>\n<p>Once the chicken has marinated, melt a third of the butter marked for the chicken. Scoop the chicken pieces out of the marinade and fry in the butter for 5 minutes. Reserve the marinade.</p>\n<p>Pour the reserved marinade over the chicken in the pot and add the rest of the butter, stirring together well.</p>\n<p>Simmer the chicken for 15 minutes or until the cubes are cooked through and the sauce slightly thickened. Add salt to taste.</p>\n<p>Chop the fresh coriander.</p>\n<p>Place the Butter Chicken in a serving bowl. Garnish with fresh chopped coriander and drizzle the cream marked \"for serving\" over the top.</p>\n<p>Serve the Butter Chicken with the Roasted Cauliflower.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-09-02 08:15:33','2022-04-13 10:20:09',NULL),(318,'vtbeiw','Marinara Chicken Bowl','Very easy to put together, very tasty and it boasts lots of hidden veg for the picky eaters - they won\'t even know they are there! Onion, marrow and mushrooms are sauteed, cubes of chicken breast added and once that is nice and golden, we add our homemade marinara sauce and some butter beans along with a splash of Worcestershire Sauce. Serve in bowls with crumbled feta for a delicious family friendly meal.','Traces of Lactose',5,35,'<p>Heat some oil in a big skillet or pot, medium to high heat, and fry the onion for 5 minutes. Then add the baby marrow and mushrooms and fry for a further 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the cubed chicken and salt and pepper to taste and fry, stirring frequently for 10 minutes. The chicken should lose its pink colour.</p>\n<p>Add the Italian seasoning, mix in well and then add the marinara sauce and the Worcestershire sauce, again mixing everything together well.</p>\n<p>Add the butter beans, stir in, put a lid on the pot, and allow to simmer gently for 10 minutes. You may have to turn the heat down.</p>\n<p>Serve the chicken in bowls topped with crumbled feta.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-09-03 10:53:52','2023-02-18 17:09:41','<p>Marinara sauce</p>\n<p><br />1 onion, finely chopped<br />1 tsp crushed garlic<br />a little oil<br />2 tbsp tomato paste (1 sachet)<br />2 tbsp balsamic vinegar&nbsp;<br />1 tin crushed tomato<br />1 tsp dried basil<br />1 tsp dried oregano&nbsp;<br />&frac12; tsp salt<br />Pepper, to taste</p>\n<p>Fry the onions in the oil until soft.<br />Add tomato paste, garlic, vinegar, crushed tomato and bring to a boil.<br />Add the herbs, salt and pepper.<br />Let it simmer on low for 20 minutes plus.</p>'),(319,'crbmkg','Marinated Chicken with Sweet Chilli Cabbage','This meal is incredibly quick and easy and once you have tasted cabbage like this you will never want to eat it any other way. Saute it in butter for a few minutes before adding a bunch of fresh coriander and sweet chilli sauce. The chicken breasts are sent ready marinated for maximum taste and tenderness. All you have to do is fry them in a little oil.','None',5,30,'<p>Heat some oil in a pan, medium high heat, and fry the chicken breasts for 20 minutes, turning them every 5 minutes. Check with a sharp knife to see that the inside is cooked. Take out of the pan and keep warm.</p>\n<p>Heat the butter in the pan on a medium high heat and stir fry the cabbage for 5 minutes. It must keep some of its crunchiness so don\'t overcook.</p>\n<p>Chop the fresh coriander. Add the coriander and stir fry for 1 minute more. Stir in the sweet chilli sauce and leave on the heat until everything is heated through.</p>\n<p>Serve 1 to 2 pieces of chicken with a helping of sweet chilli cabbage.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-09-07 09:59:24','2022-06-16 15:51:33','<p>Chicken Marinade - enough for 2.5 kg chicken breasts</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>125 ml olive oil</p>\n<p>1 tsp salt&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&frac12; tsp black pepper</p>\n<p>&frac12; tsp paprika</p>\n<p>&frac12; tsp cumin</p>\n<p>&frac14; tsp cayenne pepper</p>\n<p>2 tsp crushed garlic</p>\n<p>3 Tbsp onion flakes</p>\n<p>3 Tbsp dried parsley</p>\n<p>375 ml dry white wine</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Place all ingredients in a bowl and mix thoroughly</p>\n<p>Place chicken in a ziploc bag and pour the marinade in, keeping the air out as much as possible and letting the marinade cover the chicken.</p>\n<p>Place in the fridge overnight or at least 1 hour.</p>\n<p>The chicken can be frozen in the marinade. When you need it, thaw it out and pour off the marinade.</p>'),(320,'moewsz','Butter Chicken Marrow Bowl','Our Butter Chicken is so tasty and so easy to put together that we decided to use it again but in a different way. Here we saute a heap of baby marrow slices in butter and salt and stir it into the delectably saucy Butter Chicken and serve it in bowls.','Lactose',5,40,'<p>In a bowl, mix the masala paste with the cream and then place the chicken cubes in the mixture.&nbsp; Place in the fridge for 20 minutes to marinate.</p>\n<p>Chop the fresh coriander and set aside.</p>\n<p>Melt the smaller amount of butter (for the baby marrow) in a pan on a medium to high heat. Saute the baby marrow, adding salt to taste, for 10 minutes. Take off the heat and set aside.</p>\n<p>Once the chicken has marinated, melt a third of the butter marked for the chicken in a big pot or skillet. Scoop the chicken pieces out of the marinade and fry in the butter for 5 minutes. Reserve the marinade.</p>\n<p>Pour the reserved marinade over the chicken in the pot and add the rest of the butter, stirring together well.</p>\n<p>Simmer the chicken for 15 minutes or until the cubes are cooked through and the sauce slightly thickened. Add salt to taste.</p>\n<p>At this stage, add the baby marrow and half of the chopped fresh coriander to the chicken. Heat the mixture until it is hot right through.</p>\n<p>Serve in bowls garnished with the rest of the fresh coriander.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-09-07 10:46:18','2022-08-03 09:04:07',NULL),(321,'iglfpw','Zucchini Lasagna','A low carb version of our classic favourite, with all of the flavour, in fact we think it may be nicer! You will slice baby marrows lengthwise to make zucchini sheets and layer them with the classic meat and cheese sauces. Sprinkle with cheddar and bake until golden and bubbling!','Traces of Lactose',10,35,'<p>Heat the oven to 200 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Thinly slice the baby marrows lengthwise (do not peel) and place them on paper towel in a single layer. Sprinkle them with salt. This draws the water out to prevent your lasagna from being watery at the bottom. Leave them for 10 minutes and then use more paper towel to dry the water off.</p>\n<p>While the baby marrow is prepping itself you can start your meat sauce: Heat some oil in a pot and fry the onion for 3 minutes. Then add the garlic marked for the meat sauce and fry for 1 minute more.</p>\n<p>Add the beef mince, salt and pepper to taste and the Italian seasoning. Use a wooden spoon to break the clumps of mince down and fry for 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Stir in the tomato paste and some water: Use 45 ml water for 4 people, 22 ml for 2 people and 11 ml for 1 person. Combine well and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Turn the heat off when done.</p>\n<p>Make your cheese sauce:&nbsp; Take your cornstarch and add a little cold water to make a smooth paste. Set aside.</p>\n<p>Place the cream and half of the cheese in a saucepan and heat on a medium heat, stirring frequently. Add the crushed garlic marked for the cheese sauce and some salt and pepper to taste.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>When the cheese sauce starts to bubble, let it simmer, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes. Then add the cornstarch paste. This will thicken the sauce. Add a bit at a time so you can control the thickness. Discard what you don\'t need. When the sauce is to your liking, take it off the heat.</p>\n<p>Assemble the lasagna: Put a thin layer of meat sauce at the bottom of an oven dish. Then layer some cheese sauce on top of this, followed by a single layer of baby marrow slices. Repeat until you run out of ingredients and then sprinkle the rest of the cheese on top.</p>\n<p>Bake for 18 to 20 minutes, until golden and bubbling.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-09-09 10:36:03','2021-09-09 11:02:42',NULL),(322,'paqdxd','Vegetarian Chilli Con Carne','Here we bring you an old favourite with wonderfully rich flavours and colours, using extra beans instead of beef mince. Mop up this deliciousness with your own homemade mealie bread served fresh from the oven. It’s easy – we’ll show you how!','Traces of Lactose',5,30,'<ol>\n<li>Heat some oil in a big pot. Add the onion and cook, stirring fairly frequently, for 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Tip in the red pepper, garlic and the spice mix.</li>\n<li>Give it a good stir, then leave it to cook for a minute or two while you make up the stock. Dissolve the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specifed on the package.</li>\n<li>Add the stock to the pot. Then add the chopped tomatoes and stir in well.</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Add the tomato paste. Stir in well. Add the dried marjoram and a quarter teaspoon of sugar for each person you are cooking for (ie for 4 people you will use 1 teaspoon).&nbsp;.</li>\n<li>Bring the pot to the boil, give it a good stir and put a lid on it. Turn down the heat until it is gently bubbling and leave it for 20 minutes.</li>\n<li>Stir occasionally to make sure the sauce doesn&rsquo;t catch. After simmering gently, the sauce should be thick but not dry. Add a little water if it is too dry.</li>\n<li>Add both types of beans and simmer for a further 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Taste a bit of the chilli and season with salt and pepper if needed.</li>\n<li>Now replace the lid, turn off the heat and leave your chilli to stand for 10 minutes before serving. This is really important as it allows the flavours to mingle.</li>\n<li>Serve with&nbsp; a dollop of sour cream and a slice of mealie bread.</li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-09-09 15:17:06','2021-09-09 15:41:38',NULL),(323,'yozcej','Chorizo & Tomato Bake','With it\'s generous portion of spicy chorizo, cherry tomatoes, baby spinach, paprika, feta and cream, this crustless quiche is filling and delicious. It\'s quick and easy to put together, making it perfect for a weekday supper. Serve it topped with fresh basil leaves.','Traces of Lactose',5,30,'<p>Preheat the oven to 200 degrees C. Grease a suitably sized oven dish, 20 x 30 cm if you are cooking for 4 people.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a skillet or pan over a medium to high heat. Add the onion and fry for 3 minutes, stirring frequently. Add the whole cherry tomatoes and lightly season with salt. Stir fry for about 3 minutes or until their skins start to blister.</p>\n<p>Then add the sliced chorizo and stir fry for a further 3 minutes. Add the spinach and let it wilt before taking the pan off the heat.</p>\n<p>Place this mixture in the oven dish.</p>\n<p>Beat the eggs, cream and paprika in a bowl and season with salt and pepper to taste.</p>\n<p>Pour the cream mixture over the onion/tomato/chorizo/spinach mixture in the oven dish. Sprinkle the feta over the top.</p>\n<p>Bake for 20 minutes. The mixture should be golden and firm to the touch.</p>\n<p>Roughly chop the fresh basil and serve it over the top of the bake.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-09-16 09:37:40','2021-09-18 16:48:33',NULL),(324,'gfaijm','Cauliflower Cheese with a Twist','Layer your cauliflower florets in an oven dish, nestle plump sun-dried tomatoes in between and cover with a blended broccoli, cream and cream cheese sauce. Finish it off with grated cheddar, bake until golden and you have a cauliflower cheese like no other. The flavours are superb.','Traces of Lactose',5,50,'<p>Preheat the oven to 180 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Put the broccoli into a pot of salted water and bring to the boil. Cook until fork tender because you will need to \"mash\" it, 4 to 5 minutes should be fine.</p>\n<p>Drain the broccoli and place the hot broccoli back into the hot pot. Add the cream cheese, the cream, the butter, the garlic powder and some salt &amp; pepper to taste. Stir all together, letting the heat of the pot and the broccoli help blend the ingredients. If you have a stick blender, use it to blend everything together. If you do not it is fine to use a wooden spoon and a potato masher.</p>\n<p>Add half of the cheddar to your blended broccoli sauce and stir in well.</p>\n<p>Place the cauliflower florets in an oven dish. Place the sundried tomatoes in between the cauliflower. Spoon the broccoli sauce over the top of the cauliflower and tomato. Top with the rest of the grated cheddar.</p>\n<p>Bake in the oven for 40 minutes. The cauliflower should be fork tender and the top golden brown.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-09-16 09:39:09','2021-09-18 15:53:44',NULL),(325,'xuhvmk','Hawaiian Pork Stir Fry','Pineapple chunks and our home made BBQ sauce are added to pork strips, matchstick carrots, green beans and corn kernels in this quick and healthy stir fry with its Hawaiian twist. We send rice as an accompaniment but the quantities are generous enough to leave the rice out if you are following a low carb way of eating.','None',5,25,'<p>Place the rice into a pot and cover with water. Add some salt. Bring to the boil and time 20 minutes from when the pot boils. Your rice should be ready. Drain and keep warm.</p>\n<p>While the rice is cooking, start the stir fry by heating some oil in a wok or a skillet and frying the onion for 2 minutes.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Add the green beans and carrots, stir together and put the lid on to let them \"sweat\" for 10 minutes. Stir the veggies frequently.</p>\n<p>Take the lid off and add the pork. Stir fry everything together for 5 minutes or until the pork is no longer pink.</p>\n<p>Add the corn kernels and stir fry for a further 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the pineapple pieces and the barbeque sauce and stir while everything heats through.</p>\n<p>Serve on rice, or, if you want to cut carbs, serve on its own.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-09-18 14:41:30','2021-09-18 15:26:50',NULL),(326,'agwbmx','Broccoli Cheddar Soup with Homemade Rolls','A creamy broccoli and cheddar soup - leave it chunky or blend it smooth - either way it is absolutely delicious with just a touch of paprika and cayenne. Serve it with rolls fresh from your oven, crispy on the outside and soft on the inside - irresistible with butter!','Gluten and Traces of Lactose',10,30,'<p>Preheat the oven and prepare your rolls as per the recipe card for them.</p>\n<p>When the oven is heated then pop the rolls in for the specified amount of time.</p>\n<p>Make your vegetable stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</p>\n<p>Heat one third of your butter with a bit of oil on a medium heat in a pot and add the onion and broccoli stalks. Fry for 10 minutes. Put the lid on the pot but stir frequently.</p>\n<p>Add the garlic and fry for a further 1 minute. Add the parika, cayenne pepper and salt and pepper to taste and cook for another minute.</p>\n<p>Add the stock, stir well, cover the pot and simmer for 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Remove the mixture from the pot to a bowl. If you have a stick blender then blend the mixture until smooth and creamy. If you do not have a stick blender then use a potato masher and wooden spoon to break down the bits slightly. Whether this soup is smooth or chunky, the taste is just as nice. Leave this mixture aside for now.</p>\n<p>In the same pot heat the rest of the butter and fry the broccoli florets in it. Only stir occasionally and the broccoli will have a roasted flavour. It should be fork tender so let it fry for about 6 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the mixture in the bowl back into the pot, combine well and add more salt and pepper to taste if needed.</p>\n<p>Allow to simmer for 2 minutes and then add the cream and the cheese, stirring well. Cook until the cheese melts.</p>\n<p>Serve hot with your homemade bread rolls.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-09-23 11:00:23','2023-03-08 14:35:11',NULL),(327,'zipeva','Easy Homemade Bread Rolls','Making your own homemade rolls has never been easier! If you select the Broccoli Cheddar Soup, the ingredients and recipe card for the rolls will be added to that meal.','Gluten and Lactose',5,30,'<p>Preheat your oven to 200 degrees C. Grease a baking tray.</p>\n<p>Pour the flour mix into a bowl.</p>\n<p>Melt the butter and mix through the dry ingredients with a fork.</p>\n<p>Add the yoghurt and mix until well combined.</p>\n<p>Have a bowl of water at the ready to wet your hands - it stops the mixture from sticking to you.</p>\n<p>Shape roll-size balls of dough and place them on the baking tray.</p>\n<p>When your oven is hot enough bake the rolls for 30 minutes. The outside of the rolls should be crisp and when you stick a skewer into a roll it comes out clean. This means they are cooked through.</p>\n<p>Serve warm from the oven with butter.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-09-23 12:48:52','2023-01-30 10:34:34',NULL),(328,'newtwn','Creamed Spinach, Mushroom & Aubergine Bake','Creamed spinach is layered with baked aubergine slices and mushroom, onion and garlic fried with a touch of paprika and tomato. This is then topped with mozarella  and baked until golden to give you a tasty and nutritious vegetarian meal.','Traces of Lactose',10,50,'<p>First take the cream cheese out of the fridge - it\'s easier to use if it comes to room temperature.</p>\n<p>Preheat the oven to 190 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Set the aubergine slices out in a single layer on a baking tray and sprinkle both sides with salt. Let them stand for the time you need to cook the mushroom mixture below.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a pan and add the onion. Fry for 1 minute. Then add the garlic and fry for 1 minute. Your heat should be medium.</p>\n<p>Add the mushrooms and fry for 8 minutes to get rid of their moisture and then add the paprika and tomato paste. Now add 1/4 teaspoon of sugar per person you are cooking for, i.e. 1 teaspoon for 4 people. Add salt and black pepper to taste. Cook for 2 minutes further and then take the mushroom mixture off the heat.</p>\n<p>Now rinse your aubergine slices and pat them dry with a clean dishcloth or paper towel. Dab/paint each side with a bit of oil and lay on the rinsed and oiled baking tray. Bake for 15 minutes, turning halfway.</p>\n<p>While the augergine is in the oven, prepare the spinach. Put it in a bowl and pour a kettle of boiling water over it to wilt it. Then rinse with cold water so that it is cool enough to handle. Squeeze the spinach in your hands as hard as you can to get excess water out.</p>\n<p>Beat the egg/s and add the cream cheese. Use a wooden spoon to beat together. Don\'t worry if there are a few lumps left. Add the spinach and stir together well. Season to taste with salt and black pepper.</p>\n<p>When your aubergine slices are baked, leave the oven on at 190 degrees C and grease an oven dish.</p>\n<p>Layer half the aubergine, half the mushroom mixture and half the creamed spinach. Repeat and finish off with the grated mozzarella.</p>\n<p>Bake for 30 minutes and then let the dish settle and cool for a while before serving.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-09-24 06:26:29','2023-02-18 17:23:53',NULL),(329,'vxkqgo','Mexican Lasagna (Vegetarian)','The best of two worlds - the layering and cheesiness of the original classic and the spicy yumminess of Mexican food - all in one dish!\nThe layers are tortillas, a spicy salsa of beans and corn, spinach creamed with cottage cheese and a topping of enchilada sauce and grated cheddar.','Gluten and Lactose',10,45,'<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heat oven to 180 degrees C and grease an oven dish.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heat some oil in a skillet over medium heat and fry the onion and the red pepper for 5 minutes. Add the marinara with jalapeno and the spice mix. Stir well. Then stir in the black beans and the corn. Simmer for 5 minutes.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Wilt the spinach under boiling water. Then run cold water over it so that you can handle it and squeeze it hard with your hands to get the water out. It will now look like a firm ball or sausage - chop it into pieces with a knife on a board.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Combine ⅔ of the cheddar, the cottage cheese, the beaten egg, the spinach and salt and pepper in a bowl. Mix well.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cut your tortillas into 8 pieces each with a pair of scissors. Place half the tortillas in the oven dish at the bottom. Follow this with half the bean mixture and then half the cheese and spinach mixture. Repeat this and then top with any remaining tortilla pieces, the enchilada sauce and the remaining cheddar cheese.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bake for 35 minutes or until the top is golden and bubbling.</span></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-09-30 09:42:22','2022-06-12 08:17:42','<p>Enchilada Sauce</p>\n<p>30 ml olive oil<br />30 ml flour<br />1 &nbsp;400g tin chopped tomatoes<br />3 tsp chilli powder<br />1 tsp oregano<br />&frac12; &nbsp;tsp ground cumin<br />&frac12; &nbsp;tsp garlic powder<br />&frac12; tsp onion powder<br />3 tsp sugar<br />Salt &amp; black pepper to taste</p>\n<p>Heat the oil in a saucepan over medium heat and then whisk in the flour until there are no lumps. Cook for 1 minute.<br />Stir in tomatoes, oregano, all the spices and the sugar. Stir in 400 ml water and season with salt and pepper to taste.<br />Bring to the boil and then reduce heat to simmer for 10 minutes. The sauce should thicken.</p>\n<p>Can be stored in the fridge for 2 weeks.</p>'),(330,'vhgyzy','Zucchini Fritters with Beetroot Salad and a Creamy Dressing','Zucchini fritters are a wonderful vegetarian staple. We pair them with an unusual but very tasty salad of red cabbage, beetroot, fresh parsley and sunflower seeds.  A sour cream, Dijon mustard and turmeric dressing pulls it all together.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,25,'<p>Grate the baby marrow into a colander, salt it generously, mix the salt in and let it stand for 10 minutes. The salt draws the water out. When the 10 minutes is up squeeze the baby marrow hard with your hands to try and get most of the water out.</p>\n<p>While the baby marrow is standing, chop the parsley and toss it with the cabbage, beetroot and sunflower seeds with a dash of oil and a squeeze of lime in a salad bowl. Taste and add salt and pepper accordingly.</p>\n<p>Place your Creamy Turmeric &amp; Dijon Dressing in a bowl and let it come to room temperature.</p>\n<p>For the fritters, mix the following in a big bowl: Cheese, half the flour, onion powder, dried mint, salt and pepper. When these are mixed together add the beaten egg and the baby marrow. Combine all the ingredients well.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a frying pan or skillet on a high heat. Use the other half of the flour to flour your hands to work with the baby marrow mixture. You can add some of this flour to the mixture if you think it is too runny.</p>\n<p>Shape into balls and place in the pan, pressing down to make a fritter shape. Flip after 3 minutes and judge the heat of the pan. If the fritters appear to be getting too dark then turn down your heat. Cook for 3 minutes the other side.</p>\n<p>Serve 2 or 3 fritters with some beetroot salad and Creamy Turmeric &amp; Dijon Dressing.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-10-07 09:59:19','2022-03-03 15:39:53',NULL),(331,'zxnepv','Pork Chops with Cauli-Leek Au Gratin','Pork neck chops are the most flavoursome cut of pork chop and to make them even yummier we marinade them for you. The Cauli-Leek Au Gratin is rich and creamy with cheddar cheese, cream cheese, crushed garlic and a bit of cream. A very satisfying dinner!','Traces of Lactose',5,30,'<p>Heat your oven to 200 degrees C and take your chops out of the fridge so they can reach room temperature before you cook them.</p>\n<p>Put a pot of salted water on to boil and when boiling put in the cauliflower and boil for 5 minutes. Drain and set aside for now.</p>\n<p>In a bowl, mix the cream, the cream cheese, 3/4 of the grated cheddar, the garlic and salt and pepper to taste.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Mix the leeks and the par-boiled cauliflower into the cheese mixture and transfer to an oven dish. Top it with the remaining grated cheddar.</p>\n<p>Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until nice and golden.</p>\n<p>While the cauliflower and leek dish is baking, heat some oil in a large skillet, using a medium high heat. Drain the chops from their marinade and fry them until they are done to your liking. Depending on the thickness this could be up to 10 minutes per side. Pork neck is normally still a bit pink inside even when it is cooked. Add salt and pepper to taste.</p>\n<p>Serve the Cauli-Leek Au Gratin along side a pork chop.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-10-12 11:03:18','2021-10-18 09:53:18',NULL),(332,'ixdhiz','Chicken Gnocchi Soup','If you\'re looking for comfort food that is also nutritious, look no further! This creamy chicken and vegetable soup goes a step further than your run of the mill noodle - it uses gnocchi! And with onion, garlic, red pepper, baby marrow, celery and carrot in the mix you are definitely getting your veg in.','Gluten',5,40,'<p>Make your stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Pour it into a pot. Add the chicken breast, salt and black pepper and 1/3 of the garlic. Bring to a simmer, put the lid on and poach the chicken for 15 minutes. Take off the heat, drain and keep the stock for the soup.</p>\n<p>Melt the butter with a bit of oil in a big soup pot. Add the onion, garlic, pepper, baby marrow, carrots and celery. Stir, put the lid on and allow the veggies to cook for 10 minutes. Stir them now and again.</p>\n<p>Add the flour, stir well into the veggies and cook for 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the chicken stock that you drained from the chicken and stir until the flour combines with the stock making the soup thick and smooth. This should take no more than 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Pour in the cream and simmer for 5 minutes more.</p>\n<p>Chop or shred your chicken and add it to the soup. Then add the gnocchi and the spinach. Add salt and pepper to taste as well as the dried thyme and nutmeg. Cook for 3 minutes. If your soup is too thick you can use a little boiling water to thin it out but don\'t overdo it as it will spoil the flavour.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-10-18 08:49:40','2021-10-19 17:05:57',NULL),(333,'qcbnns','Peppers Stuffed with Beef Mince and Cheese','This is much easier to make than it\'s impressive looks would lead you to believe. A mixture of tomato, onion, garlic and mince is spiced with chilli and cumin, mixed with grated cheddar and stuffed into the pepper halves. Bake until the cheese topping is golden and bubbling and serve with a dollop of mayo and some leafy greens.','Traces of Lactose',5,45,'<p>Preheat the oven to 200 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Rub the green pepper halves with some oil and place them in a greased oven dish.</p>\n<p>Heat some more oil in a pot or pan and fry the onion on a medium heat for 2 minutes. Then add the garlic and fry for a further 1 minute.</p>\n<p>Add the beef mince and fry for 8 minutes - it should no longer be pink.</p>\n<p>Add the cumin and chilli powder and fry with the meat for 1 minute. Then add the tomato and salt and pepper to taste. Add 1/4 teaspoon of sugar per person you are cooking for i.e 1 teaspoon for 4 people.</p>\n<p>Simmer this mixture for 10 minutes. Most of the moisture should be gone.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Remove from the heat and stir in half the cheddar cheese. Stuff the peppers with the mince mixture and top each with some of the remaining cheddar.</p>\n<p>Bake for 25 minutes.</p>\n<p>Place a dollop of mayo on each stuffed pepper and serve with some leafy greens.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-10-19 15:19:52','2023-03-13 16:02:16',NULL),(334,'mzizku','Veggie Loaded Flatbread','With chickpeas smashed with garlic and lemon juice, grilled red onion and cherry tomatoes bursting with goodness and then topped with feta and olives, these flatbreads have a distinctly Mediterranean feel. And the flatbreads are so easy to make, you\'ll find yourself wanting to make them to accompany soups and salads as well.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',10,20,'<p>Mix together the yoghurt and flour to make a dough. Rub some oil on your hands and onto your working surface to stop the dough sticking and knead it for a few minutes. Leave it to rest while you prepare the toppings.</p>\n<p>Heat your grill to its highest setting. Toss the onion in a little oil and place onto a baking tray. Put the tray under the grill and grill for 5 minutes, turning half way through. Then add the cherry tomatoes whole with salt and black pepper to taste and continue grilling until the tomaotes burst their skins and soften. The onion can be slightly blackened on the edges. When the tomato and onion is done take out from the grill. Set aside and keep warm.</p>\n<p>Heat the chick peas in a pan with some oil and the garlic. Heat them together for 5 minutes then smash the chickpeas and garlic with a potato masher. Add the lemon juice and an equal amount of water. Stir together with salt and pepper to taste. Set aside and keep warm.</p>\n<p>Make your flatbreads: Divide the dough into balls. Flatten the balls to slightly smaller than the size of your pan. If you have oiled your surface, flip the flattened ball over so it can get oil on both sides or else just paint some on.</p>\n<p>Heat a little oil on a high heat and then fry your flatbread, 1 minute on each side should be enough - they will have golden brown patches on each side. Keep the cooked ones warm until you are ready to assemble your meal. If your pan gets too dry add a teeny bit more oil.</p>\n<p>Take a flatbread and spread it with the chickpea mixture. Put some onion and tomato mix onto that and top with the olives and feta.</p>\n<p>Serve with a few leafy greens on the side.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-10-21 08:58:17','2021-10-21 09:34:56',NULL),(335,'kamckn','Moroccan Barley Traybake','Chick peas, ground coriander, cumin, and chilli roasted in a bit of oil plays very nicely with cooked barley, cherry tomatoes, chopped apricots and sliced green olives. Put them together on a single tray and bake them. Served with a dill yoghurt dressing this is a top notch vegetarian dish.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,30,'<p>Heat the oven to 200 degrees celsius.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>In an oven dish, toss the chick peas with the spice mix and enough oil to allow the spices to coat the chick peas.</p>\n<p>Roast for 15 minutes. The chick peas will start to crisp and turn golden brown.</p>\n<p>Add the barley, whole cherry tomatoes, apricots and olives and stir into the chick pea mixture.</p>\n<p>Put this back in the oven for another 15 minutes. The tomatoes should be softening and starting to burst.</p>\n<p>Allow to cool for 5 minutes and then top each serving with some dill yoghurt dressing.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-10-22 09:05:50','2023-02-19 14:15:58','<p>How to Cook Pearled Barley</p>\n<p>For 4 people, use 1 cup raw barley, 3 cups cold water and 3 tsp chicken stock powder or veg stock powder&nbsp; - we like Ina Paarman\'s stock powders.</p>\n<p>Place in pot with a lid and let it come to the simmer and simmer until the liquid is gone.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(336,'jpesjd','Baked Parmesan Chicken Breasts','Very easy to put together, this chicken bake boasts a fabulous flavour made up from Parmesan, white wine, a yoghurt and mayo mix, onion and garlic powder, nutmeg and oregano. Sweet potato and green beans are very necessary to mop up every drop of the delicious sauce.','Traces of Lactose',5,40,'<p>Heat the oven to 200 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Grease an oven dish big enough for your chicken and sauce.</p>\n<p>Season the chicken pieces with salt and black pepper to taste and place in the oven dish. You can overlap them if need be.</p>\n<p>Pour the Parmesan Sauce over the chicken and when the oven is heated bake the chicken for 40 minutes.</p>\n<p>Bring a pot of water to boil, add salt and the sweet potato and boil for 15 to 20 minutes. The potato pieces should be soft enough to mash. Drain and mash with the butter, a little milk and salt and pepper. Keep warm.</p>\n<p>Bring some more salted water to the boil and add the beans. Boil for 5 to 10 minutes, depending on how crunchy you like them. Drain and keep warm.</p>\n<p>When the chicken comes out of the oven and you are ready to serve, top the chicken with the parmesan cheese, the balsamic vinegar and some black pepper.</p>\n<p>Serve the chicken and sauce on the sweet potato with the beans on the side.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-10-26 08:41:22','2021-10-26 10:43:43',NULL),(337,'myjqnd','Loaded Mac \'n Cheese','We\'ve taken an old family favourite and upped its game. To the flavour and texture of the dish everyone loves, we have added grilled red onion, tomato wedges and red and green pepper slices. It gives the meal so much more in the way of nutrition, colour and flavour.','Gluten and Lactose',5,40,'<p>Heat the grill. Toss the onion, tomato wedges and pepper slices in some oil and salt and black pepper. Place them on a baking tray about 15 cm down fom the grill. Grill them for 15 minutes, turning once or twice.</p>\n<p>When the onion, tomato and peppers are grilled, switch the setting to bake and heat the oven to 180 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil and add a little oil. Boil the pasta for 8 minutes. It should be \"al dente\" - soft but not overcooked. Drain and place in an oven dish.</p>\n<p>Make the topping: Melt the butter marked for the topping (the smaller pack) and add the garlic and breadcrumbs. Mix well and set aside.</p>\n<p>Make the sauce: Melt the butter marked for the sauce in a pot on a medium heat. Then add the flour and stir well with a wooden spoon until you have a smooth paste. If the paste is too dry to be smooth add a drop or two of oil. Cook the paste, stirring for 1 minute.</p>\n<p>Add the milk to the paste in small amounts, stirring or whisking all the time to make a smooth sauce. Once the milk is all in, cook for a few minutes, still stirring until the sauce thickens.</p>\n<p>Add salt and pepper to taste. Mix the two cheeses and stir all except a handful into the sauce. Stir until the cheeses are melted and then take off the heat.</p>\n<p>Place the grilled onions, tomatoes and peppers in amongst the pasta in the oven dish and then pour the sauce over the top. Prod the mixture with a wooden spoon to let some of the sauce sink down and mix into the pasta and veg.</p>\n<p>Add the rest of the cheese to your crumb topping and put on top of the sauce. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.</p>\n<p>Serve with some leafy greens on the side.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-10-27 10:15:28','2021-10-28 09:15:31',NULL),(338,'osoygd','Ovenbaked Pork Chops with Basil Pesto & Parmesan Baby Potatoes','The pork chops are covered in our homemade basting sauce and oven baked along with baby potatoes smothered with basil pesto. The potato is finished off under the grill with a bit of parmesan, while those chops crisp up. Serve this delicious combo with a side of green beans.','Traces of Lactose',5,40,'<ol>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Heat your oven to 200 C.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Halve or quarter the baby potates, depending on the size. Place them in a baking dish. Spoon the basil pesto over them and stir to cover all the&nbsp; potatoes. Place the potatoes in the oven. Start timing 25 minutes.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Lay your baking paper on a baking tray and place your chops on the tray. Spoon the basting sauce over the chops on both sides. Once the potatoes have been in for 10 minutes, place the pork chops in the oven.&nbsp;</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> While the potatoes and pork chops are in the oven, bring a pot of salted water to the boil.&nbsp; Add the beans and boil for 5 to 10 minutes, depending on how crunchy/soft you like your&nbsp; beans. When they are done, drain and keep warm.&nbsp;</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Once the pork chops and potatoes have been in the oven together for 15 minutes, take the&nbsp; potatoes out and sprinkle the parmesan over them. Turn the oven onto grill. Leave the potatoes and chops under the grill for 10 minutes.&nbsp;</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Serve a pork chop or two with the potatoes and green beans. If you wish to cut carbs just take a smaller portion of potato.</span></li>\n</ol>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-10-27 11:51:38','2022-01-04 11:28:32',NULL),(339,'bswbic','Sirloin Strips with Broccoli Cheese','A delicious combination. The portions are fairly small but the meal is rich - both in nutrients and in taste! Learn how to make the yummiest sirloin strips as well as a simple but tasty cheese sauce for your broccoli.','Gluten and Lactose',5,25,'<p>Brin a pot of salted water to the boil and cook the broccoli for 4 minutes. Drain well and set aside. Do not overcook.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a pan on high heat. When its very hot sear each side of the steaks, adding salt and pepper to both. Once each side of the steaks are seared and sealed turn the heat down slightly and cook on each side for 5 or more minutes, depending on the thickness of the steak and your preference. Take out of the pan and place on a board. Keep the juices in the pan warm on the stove.</p>\n<p>Using a nice sharp knife slice your steaks into strips, putting the strips back into the pan. Stir them around with the juices and let them cook gently for a minute in those juices. Keep warm while you make the sauce.</p>\n<p>Melt the butter in a small saucepan or pot on a medium heat. Add the flour and stir well into a paste. Let the paste cook for 1 minute.</p>\n<p>Slowly add the milk, one dollop, whisk, one dollop, whisk until it is nicely incorporated into the flour paste. If you do not have a whisk use a wooden spoon and make sure you stir continuously and briskly.</p>\n<p>The sauce will come to a gentle boil and will thicken. It needs about 5 minutes. Add a pinch of salt and a pinch of nutmeg, taste it and add more salt if needed.</p>\n<p>Add half the cheese and let it melt into the sauce while you stir. When melted take the sauce off the heat.</p>\n<p>Place the broccoli into an oven dish and pour the sauce over it. Use the other half of the cheese to sprinkle over the sauce. Then sprinkle a pinch of paprika over that.</p>\n<p>Heat your grill and place the broccoli under it. It is ready when the cheese is golden and bubbling.</p>\n<p>Serve with a portion of the sirloin strips.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-10-29 17:14:15','2021-11-02 11:09:50',NULL),(340,'wkmwab','Italian Chicken Penne','A tomato based pasta dish with oregano, basil and Parmesan giving the Italian flavour. It also boasts onion, garlic and green pepper with a splash of dry white wine. Very easy to put together and very tasty.','Traces of Lactose',5,30,'<p>Make your stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Stir in the corn flour and set aside.</p>\n<p>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Put the pasta in and time for 10 minutes. Stir occasionally so the pasta does not stick. Drain and reserve half a cup of pasta water in case you need to thin your sauce. Set pasta aside.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a skillet over a medium heat and fry the chicken cubes for 5 minutes, adding salt and black pepper to taste.</p>\n<p>Add the onion, garlic and green pepper and cook for a further 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Stir in the tomatoes, the wine, the dried basil and oreganum and 1 teaspoon of sugar per person you are cooking for i.e. 4 teaspoons for 4 people. Simmer this mixture for 10 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the stock mixture and stir until the sauce is slightly thickened. Add the pasta. Cook for a few minutes so that everything is heated through, adding some of the reserved pasta water if you need to.</p>\n<p>Serve in bowls topped with the grated parmesan cheese.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-11-02 09:44:43','2021-11-02 10:24:08',NULL),(341,'mhkqon','Boerewors Pie','The British have their Shepherd\'s Pie so it occurred to us while fiddling around in our test kitchen that we South Africans should have a Boerewors Pie.  Without further ado we fried our wors, deglazed the pan with red wine, added some marinara sauce and green beans and left it to simmer for a while. We topped this with cheesy mashed potato and more cheese on top and baked it to a golden perfection. Try it - you won\'t be sorry!','Lactose',5,50,'<p>Heat the oven to 200 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Put a pot of salted water on to boil. Peel your potatoes and cut them into small chunks. When the water is boiling pop them into the pot and boil until soft enough to mash - 15 to 20 minutes, depending on the size of your chunks.</p>\n<p>While waiting for the potato pot to boil, heat a little oil in a pan over medium high heat and fry your boerewors. Prick it with a fork up and down so that it doesn\'t burst. Fry the wors for 15 minutes. Take it out of the pan and chop it into rounds.</p>\n<p>Do not wash the wors pan. Put it back on the heat and pour the red wine into it to deglaze it. Use a wooden spoon to scrape the yummy bits off the pan and into the wine. Let it bubble for 1 minute.</p>\n<p>Add the marinara sauce to the wine and stir together well. Add the green beans and the rounds of wors and simmer this mixture for 10 minutes. If it looks too dry add a splash of hot water.</p>\n<p>When the potatoes are ready place them in a bowl along with the butter and half the cheese. Add a little milk and mash all together, seasoning with salt and black pepper.</p>\n<p>When the wors mixture is ready, place it in a casserole or oven dish. Spoon the potato on top and spread it out over the wors. Sprinkle this with the remaining cheese.</p>\n<p>Place dish uncovered into the oven and bake for 20 minutes. The cheesy potato topping should be golden.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-11-08 12:17:42','2021-12-22 11:49:13',NULL),(342,'hqejyr','Minty Chicken & Peach Noodle Bowl','A fresh sweet chilli and lime dressing pulls together a healthy mixture of noodles, chicken, chopped peach, mint, spring onions, red pepper and sprouts. Top this with roughly chopped cashew nuts and you\'re good to go.','Gluten',5,20,'<p>Place the chicken in a pan of water with salt and pepper, bring the pan to a simmer and let the chicken simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. It should no longer be pink inside.</p>\n<p>Take the chicken out of the pan, lay on a board and season with salt and black pepper to taste. Cut it into cubes and leave to one side until you are ready for it.</p>\n<p>While the chicken is cooking, chop the mint leaves and add to the sprouts, spring onion, peach and red pepper in a bowl and leave to one side.</p>\n<p>Put a pot of salted water on to boil. When it is boiling add the egg noodles, breaking apart with a fork. Boil them for 3 minutes and then drain.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Place the noodles in a serving bowl. Add half the Sweet Chilli and Lime Dressing and toss together.</p>\n<p>Add the chicken pieces and the minted veg/fruit. Toss everything together with the rest of the dressing.</p>\n<p>Serve a portion with some chopped cashews and a spoon of sweet chilli on top.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-11-09 11:12:55','2021-11-09 11:47:08',NULL),(343,'jzuedr','Cosy Chicken Lasagne','Healthy comfort food for the whole family - poach your chicken in milk and stock and then use that tasty liquid for the sauce. The chicken is shredded and layered with spinach lasagne sheets, a mashed butternut and mushroom mix and a mozzarella sauce. Bake it all together and enjoy!','Gluten and Lactose',5,60,'<p>Put the oven on to heat to 200 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Place the chicken stock powder in a pot along with the amount of boiling water specified on the package, the milk, the bay leaves and thyme. Add salt and black pepper to taste.</p>\n<p>Put the pot on a medium heat with the lid on and when simmering add the chicken and leave the lid off. Simmer for 15 minutes. Then take the chicken out and reserve the liquid.</p>\n<p>Shred the chicken with a knife and fork. Do not worry if it is slightly pink as it will cook further in the oven. Put aside.</p>\n<p>While the chicken is cooking, bring some water to the boil on a high heat, add the vegetable stock powder and the butternut and boil for 15 minutes or until it is soft enough to mash. Drain it, place into a bowl and mash it.</p>\n<p>In the same pot, melt the butter marked for the mushrooms over a medium heat. Add the mushrooms, garlic and salt and black pepper. Fry for 5 minutes and then add to the butternut in the bowl.</p>\n<p>Melt the butter that is marked for the sauce in the leftover juices etc in the pot from the mushroom and garlic. Then add the flour and stir well until a nice paste is formed. Cook for 1 minute. Then slowly start adding the liquid from the poached chicken bit by bit whisking the mixture all the time.&nbsp;Add 3/4 of the mozzarella to the sauce, still stirring until it is melted.</p>\n<p>The sauce is ready when you can dip a spoon into the sauce and then draw a line in the sauce on the back of the spoon.</p>\n<p>Add the shredded chicken to the sauce and season well with salt and black pepper. Taste to check your seasoning, adding more if necessary.</p>\n<p>Layer your lasagne: In an oven dish put down a layer of sauce and chicken at the bottom, then a layer of lasagne sheets and then some butternut and mushroom. Repeat until everything is finished, ending with chicken and sauce on top. Sprinkle it with the rest of the mozzarella.</p>\n<p>Cover with foil and place in the oven for 25 minutes. Then remove the foil and cook for a further 10 minutes.</p>\n<p>While the lasagne is in the oven, chop the tomato into cubes and toss in the balsamic vinegar. Serve as a side to a portion of lasagne.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-11-09 12:05:25','2021-11-12 09:37:49',NULL),(344,'scrwkl','Hunter\'s Chicken','Hunters Chicken is thought to have originated in Central Italy during the Renaissance period as Chicken Cacciatore and over the years hundreds of different versions have been done. Our version is a delicious blend of bacon bits, roasted vegetable sauce, dry white wine and Italian herbs. And of course, chicken! We serve it on cauli-rice making it not only delicious but good for your waistline.','Gluten',5,55,'<p class=\"p1\">In a bowl, sprinkle the flour and Italian herbs over the chicken thighs. Use your hands to coat the chicken with the flour.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">Heat some oil in a skillet or pan over medium heat and brown the chicken thighs on each side for a few minutes. Place the chicken thighs in a large baking / casserole dish.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">Using the same pan (don\'t wash), cook the bacon bits for a few minutes and then put in the same dish with the chicken.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">Keeping the pan on the heat, add the wine and let it bubble while stirring and scraping the bits off the bottom of the pan to get all the flavour. Add the sauce and heat it through.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">Pour the sauce over the chicken and bacon. Place in the oven, covered, for 40 minutes and then remove the lid / cover and cook for a further ten minutes.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">While the chicken is in the oven, melt the butter in a pan and stir fry the cauli rice for 5 - 8 minutes. Season well with salt and pepper.</p>\n<p class=\"p1\">Serve the chicken on top of the cauli rice.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-11-25 11:33:38','2021-12-22 10:55:51',NULL),(345,'inmjfn','Creamy Haddock & Hake Chowder','A rich and creamy soup with a wonderful flavour. The chowder base is made up of butter, onion, celery, garlic, white wine, cream and chicken stock. Once this has simmered a short while to meld the flavours you add the fish and simmer until cooked. Served with bits of crispy bacon, this meal is rich enough to stand alone, but you can add a bit of bread or some crackers on the side (not included).','Traces of Lactose',5,30,'<p>Heat the oven to 200 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Make the chicken stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Set aside.</p>\n<p>Melt the butter in a suitable soup pot at a medium heat on the stove. Add the onion and the celery and fry in the butter for 3 minutes. Then add the garlic and keep frying for another minute.</p>\n<p>Add the white wine, the cream and the chicken stock to the soup pot. Stir together, turn the heat up to bring the pot to a simmer, then turn the heat back down to medium and simmer for 15 minutes with the lid off.</p>\n<p>Place a piece of baking paper on a baking tray. Put the bacon strips on it and roast the bacon in the oven for 10 to 15 minutes - it should be cooked and fairly crispy. When done take out and leave to cool. Baking paper saves on washing up but if you do not have it just lightly grease the baking pan.</p>\n<p>When the soup pot has been simmering for 15 minutes, turn the heat up, add the haddock and hake and put the lid on. Bring the pot back to a simmer and then turn the heat down again.&nbsp; Let the soup simmer for another 15 minutes.</p>\n<p>Every now and again open the lid and break up the fish with a wooden spoon and stir.</p>\n<p>When the 15 minutes is up, taste and, if necessary, add salt and black pepper.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Chop the parsley and stir it into the soup. Break up the cooked bacon strips into bits. Serve with bacon bits on top of each bowl.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-11-29 10:09:21','2022-06-23 08:47:39',NULL),(346,'tfbnza','Honey Ginger Pork Chops','This meal is quick and easy to put together. Pork neck chops are seared to seal and then cooked in a honey and ginger sauce which we send ready made. The sauce has a sticky consistency which coats the chops and leaves something for you to spoon over your veg. The chops are served with grilled red cabbage wedges and baby potatoes smashed with butter and salt.','None',5,30,'<p>Heat the grill. Rub the cabbage wedges with some oil and season lightly with salt and black pepper. Place them on a baking tray and put under the grill. Time for 15 minutes. They should be slightly charred but not overdone. When they are ready, keep warm.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Put a pot of salted water on to boil. Do not peel the baby potatoes but cut the larger ones into half and put them all into the pot once it is boiling. Cook for 20 minutes or until the potatoes are soft. Drain them and roughly smash them with the butter and salt and black pepper to taste. Keep warm.</p>\n<p>While the potatoes are cooking, heat some oil in a pan on a high heat. Sear the pork chops on each side to seal them and salt them lightly.</p>\n<p>Turn the heat down to medium high and cook the chops for 3 minutes per side. Pour the honey ginger sauce into the pan, coating the chops and continue to cook until the sauce looks nice and sticky. Pork neck chops will have a hint of pink even when they are cooked.</p>\n<p>Serve the chops with pieces of grilled red cabbage and the smashed baby potatoes. If you prefer to eat low-carb meals then reduce your potato portion or leave it out.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2021-12-14 10:15:30','2021-12-23 10:25:46',NULL),(347,'vorjds','Baked Feta Pasta','Feta is baked in rounds in the oven along with cherry tomatoes, red pepper, red onion, garlic, herbs, chilli flakes and lemon. Once baked we smoosh it all together with a spoon to make a delectable sauce which is added to the pasta along with fresh rocket or baby spinach. This is without doubt one of the nicest pasta dishes we have made.','Gluten, traces of Lactose',5,40,'<p>Heat the oven to 200 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Place the whole tomatoes, red onion, red pepper, garlic, Italian herbs and chilli flakes in an oven dish. Use a dish large enough that you can make space for the feta in the middle and the veg is not heaped up too much.</p>\n<p>Grate some skin off the lemon to make a little lemon zest. Add that to the dish. Cut the lemon into quarters and squeeze the juice over the veg. Discard the rest of the lemon. Add salt and black pepper to taste. Pour the olive oil over the top and mix all together .</p>\n<p>Make a space in the middle of the dish for the round(s) of feta, rubbing it gently into the oil on both sides so it is well coated with the herby, garlicky oil.</p>\n<p>Bake in the oven for 40 minutes. The tomatoes should be blistering and splitting when it is ready.</p>\n<p>While the feta and veg is baking, bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Boil the pasta for 12 minutes. When it is done, drain it and reserve a small cup of pasta water for when the pasta is mixed into the feta and veg sauce.</p>\n<p>When the feta and veg comes out of the oven use a wooden spoon to smoosh it all together making a chunky sauce.</p>\n<p>Put the pasta back into the drained pasta pot and pour your feta and veg sauce over the top along with the rocket. Mix into the pasta using a bit of the reserved pasta water to get the consisteny to your liking.</p>\n<p>Serve imediately.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-01-06 08:02:23','2022-02-03 08:29:46',NULL),(348,'gpdqbj','Chicken & Aubergine Curry','An easy to make chicken curry with plenty of extra veg and loads of flavour. We send you the spices ready-mixed  - just pop everything into the pot in the order we give you and voila! Your curry is done. Serve with rice (included) unless you are following a low carb diet in which case you should omit the rice.','Traces of Lactose',5,30,'<p>Place your rice in a pot of salted water. Bring to the boil and, once boiling, time it for 20 minutes. The rice should be done. Drain and keep warm.</p>\n<p>Place the chopped augergine into a colander or sieve and salt it well. Let it stand until you need it.</p>\n<p>Make your chicken stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of water specified on the package. Put aside until you need it.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a pot on a low heat. Add the spices and stir fry them for 1 minute. If they look a bit dry add a little more oil. Spices should not be fried on their own on a high heat or for too long.</p>\n<p>Add the chopped onion and the ginger and garlic mix. Turn the heat up to medium and stir fry for an additional 3 minutes.</p>\n<p>Then add the chicken. Turn the heat up some more - medium high so the chicken browns.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Rinse the augergine and add to the pot while the chicken is browning. Keep stirring with a wooden spoon so that the chicken changes colour all over. Do this for 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Then add the stock and the tomato paste and mix in well. Add the carrot and chopped tomato. Mix well.</p>\n<p>Once the curry is simmering turn the heat down to medium, put the pot lid on and simmer for 20 minutes. Stir every now and again.</p>\n<p>When the 20 minutes is up, take the pot off the heat and stir in the yoghurt. Taste and add salt accordingly.</p>\n<p>Chop the coriander.</p>\n<p>Serve the curry on the rice and garnish it with the coriander. For those on a low carb diet, omit the rice.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-01-10 09:08:44','2022-01-11 14:27:34',NULL),(349,'mcvitd','Pork & Apple Stew','Pork and apple  are good friends - think roast pork and apple sauce.\nHere we put them together in a stew along with red onion, garlic, herbs, baby potato, green beans and a splash of red wine. This is an easy one pot, one bowl meal with generous portions.','Gluten',10,40,'<p>Make the stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Set aside for now.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a Dutch oven or large pot with lid on a fairly high heat. Brown the pieces of pork, adding salt and black pepper to taste. Stir to make sure all sides are browned.&nbsp; This should take 3 to 5 minutes. Take the browned pork out of the pot and set aside.</p>\n<p>Using the same pot, turn the heat down to medium and melt the butter. Add the onion, garlic and rosemary and thyme. Fry for 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the parboiled baby potatoes along with salt and black pepper to taste and mix well so that they are coated with the garlic and herbs. Cook for 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the flour and mix well into the potatoes and onion. Cook for 1 minute.</p>\n<p>Add the stock and the red wine and keep stirring as it thickens. Add back the pork. Put the lid on and simmer for 20 minutes. Stir fairly often to make sure the stew is not catching on the bottom of the pot.</p>\n<p>Chop the apple into small bits.</p>\n<p>Put the apple and green beans in and cook for another 10 minutes with the lid on, stirring now and again.</p>\n<p>Let the stew cool a while and then serve in bowls.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-01-13 10:21:11','2022-04-13 18:58:33',NULL),(350,'esisjq','Bacon-wrapped Pork Fillet with Thai Green Beans','Green beans never had it so exciting!  They are sauteed with red onion and lemongrass, plenty of ginger, garlic, soy sauce, chilli flakes and peanuts to make a wonderful side dish. We pair them with roasted, bacon-wrapped pork fillet - a really good partnership!','Nuts',5,40,'<p>Heat the oven to 200 degrees C. Place the pork into a suitably sized oven pan, uncovered. Roast in the oven for 40 minutes.</p>\n<p>Start the beans by heating a good dollop of oil on a medium heat in a skillet with a lid. Leave the lid off for now.</p>\n<p>Add the red onion and the minced lemongrass and fry them for 3 minutes, stirring now and again.</p>\n<p>Add the green beans and lightly season with salt and black pepper. Stir-fry for 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Stir the garlic and ginger mix in well and fry for 1 minute more.</p>\n<p>Give the Thai-style sauce a shake or a stir and add it to the pan. Stir everything together well, put the lid on and simmer for 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Take the lid off and stir in the peanut butter. Let the mixture simmer until the sauce is coating the beans nicely. Add the peanuts and stir and simmer for 1 minute more.</p>\n<p>When the pork is done let is rest for a few minutes. Slice the pork and serve several slices with a side of the Thai green beans.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-01-19 09:43:50','2022-01-20 13:54:04',NULL),(351,'qgxrxf','Chicken Saag','This light chicken curry prepared with spinach and cream comes from the Punjab, Haryana and Uttar Pradesh regions to the north of India. It is one of the quickest and easiest curries to make and the flavour never disappoints. Served with rice. NOTE: YOU WILL NEED A BLENDER FOR THIS RECIPE','Traces of Lactose',10,25,'<p>Place the rice and some salt in a pot on the stove. Bring to the boil and time 20 minutes from when it is boiling. The rice should now be done. Drain and keep warm.</p>\n<p>Mix the tomato paste with a bit of water, 30 ml per person you are cooking for i.e. 120 ml for 4 people. Set aside for now.</p>\n<p>While the rice is cooking, start the curry: Heat some oil on a medium high heat in a skillet or pot with a lid. The skillet or pot should be big enough to fit the spinach in.</p>\n<p>Add the onion and fry for 3 minutes. Add the garlic and ginger mix and fry for a further 2 minutes, stirring together well.</p>\n<p>Turn the heat down to medium and add the spices and a good pinch of salt. Stir well for about 30 seconds and then add the tomato paste and water. Stir well and cook for 1 minute. This should create a thick spicy sauce.</p>\n<p>Add the spinach and gently stir to mix it in. Cover the skillet or pot and increase the heat to medium high to let the spinach wilt. This should take 3 to 5 minutes. Lift the lid and stir every now and again. You want your spinach to be wilted but still bright green.</p>\n<p>Pour the spinach mixture from the pot into a bowl for it to cool before you blend it.</p>\n<p>Wipe the pot out with a paper towel, add some more oil and heat on a medium high heat. Season the cubes of chicken with salt and cook them, turning frequently, for 7 minutes. Take off the heat for now but leave in the pot.</p>\n<p>Blend the spinach mixture in small batches on a low speed. Do not completely seal the top of the blender if possible. If you put too much hot mixture into a sealed blender it could explode. If the mixture is a little too dry to blend well add a splash of water to each batch.</p>\n<p>Once you have blended the spinach mixture check to see if it needs more salt and then pour it over the chicken and stir together. Put the pot back onto a medium high heat and cook for 3 minutes to let the flavours meld and the chicken finish cooking.</p>\n<p>Take the pot off the heat and stir in the cream.</p>\n<p>Serve the curry on a bed of rice. If you wish to make this meal low carb then either take a very small portion of rice or leave it out.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-01-21 14:37:06','2022-01-22 12:01:29',NULL),(352,'ytdmzk','Coriander & Ginger Pork with Easy Flatbreads','Pork strips are marinated in a delicious concoction of soy sauce, honey, dry sherry and ground cumin. They are then seared with slices of fresh ginger before adding the marinade to the pan to make a sauce. Fresh coriander, spring onion and sesame seeds are added before serving on flatbreads.','None',10,40,'<p>Place the pork in a bowl with the sherry marinade. Stir well so all the meat is coated and let it stand for 15 to 20 minutes while you make the flatbread.</p>\n<p>Mix the herbed flour with the yoghurt and use the extra flour for kneading it into a workable dough. This only takes a couple of minutes.</p>\n<p>Divide the dough into balls, a little smaller than a tennis ball. Heat some oil in a pan until the oil is very hot. The flatbreads work better if cooked quickly on a high heat.</p>\n<p>Flatten the first ball (if you have a rolling pin it\'s easier but not absolutely necessary). Pop the flattened dough into the pan and flip over so both sides have oil on.&nbsp; Cook for 1 to 2 minutes on each side. Take out of the pan and keep warm. Repeat this step for the other balls, adding a splash of oil each time.</p>\n<p>Wipe out your pan with a paper towel and add some more oil. Heat it on a fairly high heat. Using a slotted spoon or something similar take some of the meat out of the marinade and place in the hot oil along with some ginger. The meat and ginger should be in a single layer so unless you have a pan that fits all the meat and ginger like this, cook it in batches. Reserve the marinade to use for the sauce.</p>\n<p>Sear for 2 minutes without stirring and then stir-fry for a further 2 minutes. Take the batch out of the pan and repeat until all the meat and ginger has been seared.</p>\n<p>Chop your coriander.</p>\n<p>Put the meat and ginger back into the pan and add the reserved marinade. Stir while cooking for 2 minutes to make a nice sauce. Add the spring onion, coriander and sesame seeds and cook for 1 more minute.</p>\n<p>Serve some saucy coriander &amp; ginger pork strips on a flatbread.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-01-27 13:44:35','2023-02-19 14:14:27','<h3>How To Make Self-Raising Flour</h3>\n<p>1 cup all purpose or cake flour</p>\n<p>1,5 teaspoons baking powder</p>\n<p>0,25 teaspoons salt</p>\n<p>Mix together well.</p>'),(353,'lyljsh','Chicken Schnitzel with Butternut & Mushroom Risotto','Our chicken schnitzel is baked to cut down on the oil used - it also makes for an easier clean up! Your chicken is still coated in delicious crispiness and is the perfect partner for the  creamy Butternut & Mushroom Risotto.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',10,45,'<p>Preheat the oven to 220 degrees. Drizzle a little oil over a baking sheet and place in the oven to heat up.</p>\n<p>Prepare your chicken:&nbsp; Beat the eggs in a shallow bowl with salt and pepper. Grate the skin off the lemon to make lemon zest and mix this zest with the seasoned breadcrubs on a plate. Keep the rest of the lemon for squeezing on the chicken when serving. Put the seasoned flour on another plate.</p>\n<p>When the oven is ready, take the baking pan out, ready to place the chicken on. Dip each piece of chicken first in the flour, then in the egg and then in the breadcrumbs until nicely covered. Place on the baking tray. Sprinkle with salt and black pepper, and drizzle a little oil over the top.</p>\n<p>Place the baking tray in the oven. Bake for 6 minutes. Use tongs to flip the chicken pieces over, drizzle with oil and bake for another 6 minutes. Take out and keep warm. Turn the oven down to 180 degrees C for the risotto.</p>\n<p>Start the risotto while the chicken is cooking: Make the stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Set aside.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a pot, medium to high heat, and fry the onion for 3 minutes. Add the mushrooms. Fry for a further 3 minutes. Add the garlic and fry for a further 30 seconds. Add the butternut and rice and extra oil if need be and fry for 2 minutes, stirring. Add the wine and keep stirring for 2 minutes more. Add the stock and bring back to a simmer.&nbsp; Place the mixture in an oven dish with a lid and cook in the oven for 25 minutes. The rice and butternut should be cooked.</p>\n<p>Stir the parmesan through the risotto and taste for seasoning. Add salt if necessary. Serve with the chicken schnitzel. Squeeze a bit of lemon juice over each chicken piece.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-02-09 07:17:06','2022-02-21 15:16:49',NULL),(354,'rmlfat','Japanese Udon Noodles with Honey Soy Cashews','A mix of chicken strips, garlic & ginger, chilli flakes, green beans and carrots are stir-fried and then cooked further in a coconut milk, soy and Sriracha sauce to make a delicious topping for the udon noodles. Honey & soy roasted cashew nuts and fresh coriander finish the dish beautifully.','Nuts',5,25,'<p>Heat some oil in a large pan or wok using a medium to high heat. Add the chicken strips and stir fry for 2 minutes. Remove the chicken and set aside.</p>\n<p>In the same pan, add a little more oil. Add the the chilli flakes, the green beans and the carrots. Stir fry for 10 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the coconut milk, soy sauce, sriracha, ginger and garlic mix. Add the chicken and stir in well. Let the mixture simmer for 5 to 10 minutes while you cook the noodles.</p>\n<p>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil. When boiling add the noodles. Boil them for 3 minutes and then drain them.</p>\n<p>Chop the fresh coriander.</p>\n<p>Serve the noodles in a bowl, topped with the chicken. Sprinkle some honey soy roasted cashews and some fresh coriander over the top and serve immediately.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-02-15 10:14:31','2023-04-01 14:48:14','<h3>Honey Soy Roasted Cashew Nuts</h3>\n<p>Place 100 g raw cashews into an oven proof dish. Drizzle with 1 tsp of honey and 1 tsp soy sauce. Mix to coat nicely. Roast at 180 degrees C for 10 minutes but watch carefully.</p>'),(355,'stfiih','Zuppa Toscana','Zuppa Toscana translates to Tuscan soup and is traditionally made with Italian sausage, potatoes, onion, garlic and spinach or kale. We have substituted smoked Russian sausage and bacon bits as Italian sausage is hard to come by here and we think we may have improved on an old classic, the flavour is that good. Serve with buttered sourdough bread (in the kit).','Traces of Lactose (soup) & Gluten (bread)',5,40,'<p>Make your stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Set aside.</p>\n<p>Slice the potatoes fairly thin and also set aside. No need to peel them.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a suitable pot for soup over medium high heat and fry the sausage pieces and the chilli flakes for 5 minutes. Stir frequently. Take the sausage bits out of the pot and set aside.</p>\n<p>Using the same pot and the juices from the sausage cook the bacon bits, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes. Add a little more oil if the pan is too dry.</p>\n<p>Add the onion to the bacon bits and cook for another 5 minutes, stirring now and again. Add the garlic, stir in and cook for 1 minute more.</p>\n<p>Stir the stock into the onion, bacon and garlic mix in the pot and add the potato slices. Bring to the boil and then let the pot simmer vigourously for 20 minutes. Test the potatoes, they should be soft.</p>\n<p>With a potato masher or a wooden spoon, roughly break up the potato.</p>\n<p>Reduce the heat to medium. Stir in the cream, the sausage and the spinach and cook for a couple of minutes so that everything is heated through.</p>\n<p>Serve in bowls with some buttered sourdough bread. If you wish to adapt this meal to low carb then leave out the bread.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-02-16 09:06:31','2022-02-18 10:48:27',NULL),(356,'gapaai','Spicy Chicken with Basil Pesto and Bowtie Pasta','A very good looking dish if you are out to impress and extremely easy to put together! The chicken is sauted in chilli paste and to that we add the cooked pasta, basil pesto, fresh coriander and Parmesan cheese. Voila! Ready to serve.','Gluten & traces of Lactose',5,25,'<p>In a pot big enough for your pasta, bring salted water to the boil. Add the pasta, stir to separate. and boil for 12 minutes. Drain and set aside.</p>\n<p>Chop the fresh coriander and set aside.</p>\n<p>While the pasta is cooking, start the chicken. Heat some oil in a pot on a medium heat. Stir in the chilli paste and then the chicken pieces. Cook and stir for 10 minutes, by which time the chicken should be done.</p>\n<p>Put the pasta, the pesto, the Parmesan cheese and the coriander into the pot with the chicken. Toss it nicely together and carry on cooking for 2 minutes or so just to heat everyhting through.</p>\n<p>Serve immediately.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-02-17 08:08:36','2023-04-17 10:52:08','<p>We suggest Sambal Oelek, available at big supermarkets and Woolworths.</p>'),(357,'xrmkbu','Chicken Parmesan with Spicy Moroccan Carrots','Chicken Parmesan is a classic but we\'ve skipped the breading to take care of our waistlines! None of the exciting flavours are lost and to make the meal even more interesting we have Spicy Moroccan Carrots alongside.','Traces of Lactose',5,35,'<p>Take the Spicy Moroccan Carrots out of the fridge as they should be served at room temperature. Chop the fresh coriander and stir through the carrots.</p>\n<p>Preheat the oven to 225 degrees C.</p>\n<p>In a deep bowl whisk the eggs and add the seasoning marked for the egg dip. In another deep bowl or plate place your parmesan and parsley mix.</p>\n<p>Heat a generous amount of oil on a medium to high heat in a pan (non-stick if you have). Dip a piece of the chicken into the parmesan mix, then the egg mix and then the parmesan again. Place in the pan. Repeat until you have 2 to 4 pieces in the pan. If you are cooking for 4 (8 pieces of chicken) then you will have to do this in two batches.</p>\n<p>Fry the chicken pieces for 2 minutes each side. They should have a nice golden colour. Take out of the pan and set aside.</p>\n<p>Using the same pan and a little more oil, fry the garlic for 1 minute and then add the chopped tomatoes, the origanum and salt and black pepper to taste. Let this mixture simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.</p>\n<p>Pour this tomato sauce into an oven dish. Place the pieces of chicken on top and then top that with the pieces of mozarella. Bake for 15 minutes - the cheese should be completely melted.</p>\n<p>Serve with some Spicy Moroccan Carrots on the side.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-02-19 17:04:58','2023-05-25 07:48:48','<h3>Spicy Moroccan Carrots</h3>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>500 g carrots peeled and sliced into rounds</p>\n<p>2 cups water</p>\n<p>2 tsp crushed garlic</p>\n<p>2 Tbsp olive oil</p>\n<p>1/2 tsp paprika</p>\n<p>pinch of cayenne pepper</p>\n<p>salt and black pepper</p>\n<p>1 Tbsp wine vinegar (I used red, but I\'m sure white wine vinegar will work)</p>\n<p>1/2 tsp ground cumin</p>\n<p>Combine carrots, water, garlic, oil, paprika, cayenne pepper, salt and black pepper in a shallow pan. Bring to a boil over a medium to high heat and cook until carrots are tender and moisture has evaporated. A slight bit of moisture left is fine.</p>\n<p>Stir the vinegar and the ground cumin through the carrots and allow to cool before storing in the fridge.</p>'),(358,'shxcrw','Cheddar Chilli with Butternut & Cream Cheese','It is amazing what we can throw together with simple, healthy ingredients if we have the right sauce - a sauce that is WOW! Use chilli garlic sauce along with sauteed onion, bell peppers and beef mince to make a fabulous chilli. Layer it on some mashed butternut and top with grated cheddar and blobs of cream cheese. Deliciousness guaranteed.','Traces of Lactose',5,40,'<p>Heat oven to 180 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Put the butternut in a pot of salted water on the stove. When it comes to the boil, time it for 15 minutes. Check that it is soft enough to mash. Drain and mash the butternut with the butter and salt to taste. Place it in a layer at the bottom of an oven dish.</p>\n<p>While the butternut is cooking, start the chilli mince: Heat some oil in a pot on a medium heat and fry the onion. After 3 minutes. add the chopped peppers, stir well and put the pot lid on. Let the onion and pepper steam for 7 minutes.</p>\n<p>Take the lid off and add the mince, using a wooden spoon to break it down so that there are no clumps. Add salt and black pepper to taste. Fry the mince until it is no longer pink and then add the chilli garlic sauce. Cook together for a futher 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Take the mince off the heat and layer it on top of the butternut.</p>\n<p>Then sprinkle the grated cheddar on top of the mince. Using a spoon place blobs of cream cheese over the top.</p>\n<p>Place in oven and cook for 20 minutes, no lid. Take out of the oven and use a spoon to smoosh the cream cheese blobs over the top.</p>\n<p>Your chilli is ready to serve!</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-03-01 10:53:59','2023-04-17 10:45:23',NULL),(359,'aixggu','Chicken with Toasted Orzo','Orzo is one of the lesser know pastas so why not ring the changes and make a delicious orzo and chicken bowl, complete with mushrooms, red pepper and baby marrow. Sour cream and parmesan pulls it all together.','Gluten and Lactose',5,20,'<p>Make your stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Place the chicken breasts in a pot and pour the stock over them. Bring to the boil, turn the heat down and allow to simmer for 15 minutes. Take the chicken out of the pot and keep the stock as you will use it later.</p>\n<p>While the chicken is simmering, heat the butter in a pot or skillet that has a lid. Without using the lid for now, stir fry the orzo in the butter until it turns a dark toasted colour. Remove the orzo from the pot and set aside.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Using the same pot add a little oil and heat on a medium heat. Add the mushrooms, red pepper and baby marrow and cook them for 10 minutes, stirring fairly frequently.</p>\n<p>While the veg is cooking slice the chicken breasts into small pieces.</p>\n<p>Add the crushed garlic to the pot of veg and cook for 1 minute more.</p>\n<p>Now add the chicken pieces and the toasted orzo and pour the stock that you saved from the chicken over the top. Stir well, put the pot lid on and simmer on a low heat for 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the sour cream. Stir in well.</p>\n<p>Serve the meal in bowls with grated parmesan sprinkled on the top.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-03-09 09:47:41','2022-03-19 11:23:02',NULL),(360,'cjjait','Zucchini Pizza Bake','Pizza meets lasagne in a healthy low carb kind of way! The crust is a zucchini, egg and cheese mix. The next layer is  beef mince with a tomato pizza sauce and the topping is green pepper, mushrooms, black olives and some melty cheese. Nutritious and delicious!','Traces of Lactose',10,40,'<p>Preheat the oven to 200 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Grate the baby marrows into a colander and sprinkle with salt. Let them stand for 10 minutes and then squeeze out as much water as you can.</p>\n<p>Mix the drained baby marrow, the lightly beaten egg(s), all the parmesan, 1/2 the mozzarella and 1/2 the cheddar in a large bowl. Grease an oven dish and press the baby marrow mixture into it.</p>\n<p>Bake uncovered for 20 minutes. Leave the oven on when you take the crust out.</p>\n<p>While the crust is baking, heat a little oil in a pan on a medium high heat and stir fry the onion and beef mince until the mince is no longer pink. This should take 5 to 8 minutes.</p>\n<p>Drain any excess liquid off the mince and onions and stir in the tomato pizza sauce.</p>\n<p>When the crust is ready spoon the mince sauce over it. Top your pizza bake with the green pepper, the mushrooms and the black olives. Sprinkle all the remaining mozzarella and cheddar over the top and bake for 20 minutes. The cheese should be nicely melted.</p>\n<p>Let the dish rest for 5 minutes out of the oven before serving.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-03-11 08:21:14','2022-03-17 15:57:01',NULL),(361,'athnvu','Paneer Tikka Masala','A  delicious way to eat Paneer, the popular Indian \"cottage cheese\". The cheese is non-melting but very good at soaking up flavours and the flavour of the tikka masala sauce is really worth soaking up. Serve with rice (included in the kit) or adapt this to a low carb meal by leaving out the rice or using very little.','Traces of Lactose',5,20,'<p>Put your rice into a pot of salted water and bring to the boil. Time 20 minutes from when it boils and it should be done. Drain and keep warm.</p>\n<p>While the rice is cooking, heat some oil in a pot over a medium to high heat and gently stir fry the paneer for 3 to 4 minutes. Gently scoop out of the pot and set aside.</p>\n<p>In the same pot, adding some more oil if necessary, fry the cumin and mustard seeds along with the curry leaves for 30 seconds. Add the ground coriander and turmeric and fry for 1 minute before adding the blitzed tomato mixture. Bring to a simmer and then let it cook for 4 minutes on a medium heat.</p>\n<p>Stir in the paneer and cook gently for a further 4 minutes. Stir in the garma masala and cook for 1 minute more. Taste the sauce and add salt to taste if you require it.</p>\n<p>Serve on a bed of rice. To adapt this meal to low carb, leave out the rice or use only very little. You could use a slice or two of low carb bread or some fried cabbage to mop up the sauce but these are not included in the kit.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-03-17 07:18:05','2023-02-07 09:32:20','<h3><strong>Marinating the Paneer</strong></h3>\n<p>Mix together:</p>\n<p>3 ml salt, 3 ml chilli powder, 3 ml ground coriander, 2 tsp crushed garlic, 2 tsp minced ginger and 1 Tbsp plain yoghurt.</p>\n<p>Gently place the paneer cubes in this mixture and roll them around to coat them.</p>\n<p>Refrigerate for an hour or more.</p>\n<h3>Blitzed Tomato, Pepper &amp; Chilli</h3>\n<p>Place the ingredients specified into a Nutribullet or blender and blend well.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(362,'ugacaf','Brazilian Chicken in a Coconut Milk Sauce','The chicken is rubbed in an array of Brazilian spices, cooked until golden and then finished off in a delicious coconut milk sauce with onion, ginger, jalapeno peppers, garlic and fresh tomato. The dish is served on buttered spinach rice.','none',5,30,'<p>Place the chicken pieces in a bowl. Pour the Brazilian spices onto the chicken and rub in well. Heat some oil in a skillet or pot, no lid required. Place the spicy chicken into the skillet and add salt and black pepper to taste. Fry on a medium to high heat for 10 minutes, turning once. If you poke a sharp knife into the biggest piece the juices should run clear. Take out of the skillet and set aside, leaving the juices in the skillet for later.</p>\n<p>While the chicken is cooking, get the rice on. Place in a pot of salted water and bring to the boil. Time 20 minutes from boiling point and the rice should be done. 2 minutes from the end of the 20 minutes pop the spinach into the pot. When the 20 minutes is up, drain the rice and spinach and stir in the butter and salt to taste. Keep warm.</p>\n<p>In the skillet with the chicken juices, add a little more oil if necessary and heat it on a medium to high heat. Add the onion, garlic, ginger and jalapeno peppers and cook for 5 minutes, stirring now and again.</p>\n<p>Add the fresh tomato and cook for 3 minutes. Add the coconut milk and stir all together well and then add the chicken. Cook for a further 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>While the chicken dish is cooling a bit, chop the fresh parsley.</p>\n<p>Serve the chicken and sauce over the spinach rice and garnish with the parsley. If you want to eat a low carb meal use only a little rice and spinach - half a cup.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-04-05 10:06:40','2022-04-11 10:23:48',NULL),(363,'bxyhrb','Honey Garlic Chicken Thighs','This dish is so simple to prepare. We send you the sauce ready made. Just cook your chicken and add crushed garlic and our honey soy sauce. Served with buttery smashed sweet potato and green beans.','None',5,25,'<p>Place the chicken thighs in a bowl and add the garlic powder and some salt and pepper. Rub seasoning into the thighs well.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a skillet over medium to high heat and add the chicken. Cook, turning now and again, for 20 minutes. When you poke a sharp knife into the biggest piece, the juices should run clear.</p>\n<p>While the chicken is cooking, get the sweet potatoes on. Bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Add the sweet potatoes and boil for 10 minutes. When the 10 minutes is up, add the green beans, leaving the sweet potato in to boil for a further 10 minutes with the beans.</p>\n<p>When the sweet potato and beans are done, drain them and smash together with a potato masher or fork along with the butter and some salt to taste. Keep warm.</p>\n<p>When the chicken is done as above, if there is a lot of liquid in the pan, drain some of it out. Put the chicken back with the skin side down and place the crushed garlic in the remaining liquid in between the chicken pieces. Add the honey soy sauce and cook on medium high heat for 5 minutes. Stir gently once or twice.</p>\n<p>Serve the chicken and sauce on the smashed sweet potatoes and beans.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-04-07 06:34:26','2022-04-09 12:14:48',NULL),(364,'mhupoc','Creamy Carrot Soup with Chickpeas','A very tasty vegetarian soup with plenty of chickpeas for protein, a bit of cream, pureed carrot and onion with garlic and ground coriander and garnished with fresh thyme. Serve with a ciabatta loaf and butter which we send with the kit. Note: You will need a stick blender, blender or Nutribullet for this recipe.','Gluten (bread) and Lactose (soup)',5,40,'<p>Heat oven to 200 degrees C so that you can heat your ciabatta for 5 minutes before serving.</p>\n<p>Make your stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water stipulated on the package. Set aside for now.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a soup pot and fry the onion for 2 minutes. Add the carrot and stir to coat it in oil and fry for a further 3 minutes. Add the crushed garlic and ground coriander, stir well and cook for a further 1 minute.</p>\n<p>Add the stock to the pot, cover and simmer vigourously for 30 minutes. The carrots must be very soft.</p>\n<p>If you are using a normal blender or Nutribullet allow to cool for 5 minutes before you blend - boiling liquid in a blender can explode! If you are using a stick blender, blend the contents of the pot straight away.</p>\n<p>Pop the ciabatta into the oven straight onto the oven shelf without its wrapping for 5 minutes to heat.</p>\n<p>Put the carrot puree back into the soup pot, add the cream, milk and chickpeas and cook for 5 minutes. Add salt and black pepper to taste.</p>\n<p>Pull the leaves off the fresh thyme by running your forefinger and thumb up the stems and pinching off the top leaves.</p>\n<p>Put the soup into bowls and garnish with the thyme.</p>\n<p>Serve with warm ciabatta and butter.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-06-09 08:52:59','2022-07-09 08:41:17',NULL),(366,'okanby','Creamy Carrot, Chickpea & Bacon Soup','The humble carrot when combined with onion and garlic and made into a puree makes a wonderful base for a soup. Add stock, cream and milk, chickpeas and fried bacon pieces. Serve with a ciabatta loaf and butter which we send with the kit. Note: You will need a stick blender, blender or Nutribullet for this recipe.','Gluten (bread) and Lactose (soup)',5,40,'<p>Heat oven to 200 degrees C so that you can heat your ciabatta for 5 minutes before serving.</p>\n<p>Make your stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water stipulated on the package.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a soup pot and fry the bacon bits until crispy on a medium high heat Remove from pot and set aside</p>\n<p>Fry the onion in the bacon fat, adding a dash of oil, for 2 minutes. Add the carrot and stir to coat it in oil and fry for a further 3 minutes. Add the crushed garlic, stir well and cook for a further 1 minute.</p>\n<p>Add the stock to the pot, cover and simmer vigourously for 30 minutes. The carrots must be very soft.</p>\n<p>If you are using a normal blender or Nutribullet allow to cool for 5 minutes before you blend - boiling liquid in a blender can explode! If you are using a stick blender, blend the contents of the pot straight away.</p>\n<p>Pop the ciabatta into the oven straight onto the oven shelf without its wrapping for 5 minutes to heat.</p>\n<p>Put the carrot puree back into the soup pot, add the cream, milk, bacon bits and chickpeas and cook for 5 minutes. Taste the soup and add salt and black pepper if you wish.</p>\n<p>Pull the leaves off the fresh thyme by running your forefinger and thumb up the stems and pinching off the top leaves.</p>\n<p>Put the soup into bowls and garnish with the thyme.</p>\n<p>Serve with warm ciabatta and butter.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-06-11 07:26:17','2022-06-11 07:35:15',NULL),(367,'hwprgv','Savoury Rice & Mozzarella Quesadilla','These vegetarian quesadilla make a fun meal while getting in plenty of nutrients from the onion, garlic, coloured peppers, spring onion and fresh parsley in the savoury rice and the mozzarella. The savoury rice is easy to make and once you know how, you can use it as a base for many dishes.','Gluten (tortilla) and Traces of Lactose (cheese)',10,45,'<p>Bring tortilla to room temperature. They are not easy to work with when too cold.</p>\n<p>Place the rice and some salt in a pot with water and bring to the boil. Time 20 minutes from when the rice is boiling and it should be done. Drain and set aside.</p>\n<p>In another pot, heat some oil on a medium to high heat and fry the onion and peppers for 8 minutes.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Add the garlic, spring onions (keep a little for garnishing) and paprika and cook for another minute.</p>\n<p>Chop the parsley.</p>\n<p>Add the rice to the veg along with the lemon juice and chopped parsley. Toss well and cover. Allow to sit for a while for the flavours to blend. Taste and add salt and black pepper to your liking.</p>\n<p>Then add the grated mozzarella and mix everything together well.</p>\n<p>Take a tortilla and place some of the mixture down one half. Fold the tortilla into a half moon, flatten with your hand and use a sharp knife to cut into two. Repeat with the rest of the tortilla. You now have quesadilla.</p>\n<p>If you have a good non-stick pan you will not need oil but if not grease your pan with a dash of oil and make the pan very hot. Use a high heat throughout.</p>\n<p>Cook one or two quesadilla at a time depending on the size of your pan. Fry each side for a minute or two, flattening them with an egg lifter.</p>\n<p>Cook and eat as you go or do them all, keeping the first ones warm.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-06-12 09:41:05','2022-06-12 14:02:27',NULL),(368,'olzsoy','Mexican Beef and Rice','A yummy one-pan dish that is satisfyingly spicy but not hot as in curry hot. Apart from beef mince and rice, this recipe calls for black beans, corn, onion, spring onion, garlic, red pepper, Mexican spices and of course cheddar cheese. Lots of nutrition in an enjoyable package!','Traces of Lactose',5,35,'<p>In a large pot/skillet, heat some oil on medium high and fry the onion and garlic for 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the beef mince, break down the lumps with a wooden spoon, and fry for 3 minutes, or until there is no pink in the meat.</p>\n<p>Add the Mexican spices and cook for 30 seconds.</p>\n<p>Add the red pepper and tomato paste and cook for 2 minutes while stirring.</p>\n<p>Make the chicken stock by dissolving the powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</p>\n<p>Add the stock to the pot along with the black beans and the corn kernels. Stir to mix.</p>\n<p>Add the rice, stir it in and turn the heat down to low. Cover with a lid and cook for 20 minutes until the rice is done. Stir every now and then to ensure nothing is catching on the bottom of the pot.</p>\n<p>Add the chopped spring onion and half the cheese and mix it in.</p>\n<p>Sprinkle the rest of the cheese over the top and cover for a few minutes to melt it.</p>\n<p>Serve immediately in bowls.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-06-16 12:32:53','2022-06-16 12:53:42',NULL),(369,'ymbihw','Parmesan Chicken Breasts with Creamed Spinach','Chicken steaks are dipped in egg and then grated Parmesan and fried on a high heat to create a lovely crust. Serve this with a fabulous creamy spinach with grated cheddar.','Traces of Lactose',5,35,'<ol class=\"ol1\">\n<li class=\"li1\">Place the butter marked for the spinach in a pot and let it melt on a medium heat.</li>\n<li class=\"li1\">While the butter for the spinach is melting, heat the milk for 2 minutes in the microwave. It should be warm to hot, not boiling.</li>\n<li class=\"li1\">When the butter is melted add the flour to the melted butter and stir together well with a wooden spoon. Let this flour/butter mix cook for 1 minute.</li>\n<li class=\"li1\">Add the milk and use a whisk to mix it into the flour and butter mixture. It will soon blend and thicken.</li>\n<li class=\"li1\">Add some salt to taste and a sprinkling of nutmeg.</li>\n<li class=\"li1\">Stir in well and as you can see the sauce coming to a boil add the spinach.</li>\n<li class=\"li1\">Stir the spinach into the sauce and keep stirring and cooking for 2 minutes.</li>\n<li class=\"li1\">Add the cheese and stir until blended. Take off the heat and keep warm while you do the chicken.</li>\n<li class=\"li1\">Crack the eggs into a dish large enough for you to dredge each chicken breast through, and beat with a fork. Place the parmesan in a separate, similar size dish.</li>\n<li class=\"li1\">Its important to use a non-stick pan on a high heat for this dish. You don&rsquo;t want to overcook the chicken as it dries out.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>Cook as close to serving time as possible.</li>\n<li class=\"li1\">Get your pan on the heat and melt the butter marked for the chicken, plus a &frac14; of a tablespoon of oil per person you are cooking for (i.e. 1 tablespoon for 4 people).</li>\n<li class=\"li1\">Take a piece of chicken, dredge it through the beaten egg and then press it into the parmesan on both sides, so that some parmesan is sticking to the egg. Place the chicken on the hot pan. Don&rsquo;t move the chicken until it is a deep golden brown on the underside (you can just lift it to have a little peek). This may take about 3 minutes or maybe a little more. When deep golden brown, then flip it over and cook on the other side.</li>\n<li class=\"li1\">Serve the chicken with the creamed spinach.</li>\n</ol>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-06-17 07:44:42','2022-06-23 08:32:32',NULL),(370,'fthsaf','Cashew Beef with Rice','The garlic, ginger, peanut butter, sesame oil and soy sauce that coat the beef strips give this dish an Asian feel. Cashews and spring onions add to the oriental feel.  Serve the beef strips with rice. If you wish to eat a low carb meal, use only a very little rice or none at all.\nThe rice is included in the kit.','Nuts',5,20,'<p>Put the rice and some salt into a pot of water and bring to the boil. Time 20 minutes from when it boils and your rice should be done. Drain and keep warm.</p>\n<p>While the rice is cooking, heat some oil in a skillet/pot on a high heat and stir fry the beef for 5 minutes. Take the beef out and set aside, leaving the juices in the pot.</p>\n<p>Turn the heat down to medium high and add a bit more oil to the juices in the pot. Add the garlic, ginger, cashew nuts and spring onions and stir fry for 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the beef back into the pot along with the Oriental paste and mix everything together well. Cook on a medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring every now and then to check that nothing is catching on the pot.</p>\n<p>Serve on a bed of rice. For the low-carbers use only 2 tablespoons of rice or none at all.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-06-22 07:14:55','2022-06-27 10:46:07',NULL),(371,'psaxqr','Homemade Spaghetti with Tomato Sauce, Fresh Basil & Mozzarella','You cannot beat a dish with homemade pasta, you\'ll never want to go back to the mass produced stuff. The tomato sauce incorporates tomato (obvs), onion, carrot, celery, fresh rosemary and garlic with a  splash of balsamic vinegar and red wine. Top this off with fresh basil and grated mozzarella cheese.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,30,'<p>Heat some oil in a skillet/pot on a medium high heat and fry the onion, celery and carrots for 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the tomato puree, fresh rosemary, garlic and stock powder and stir in well.</p>\n<p>Add the balsamic vinegar and red wine and scrape all the yummy bits off the bottom of the pot (known as deglazing).</p>\n<p>Add the chopped tomatoes and let the pot simmer for 10 minutes.</p>\n<p>While that pot is simmering put some water and salt into another pot and bring it to the boil. When boiling, add the pasta, breaking it up gently with a fork. Cook the pasta for 6 minutes, stirring occasionally. Drain it and keep warm.</p>\n<p>Roughly chop the basil leaves.</p>\n<p>The tomato sauce should now be ready. Taste it and see if you wish to add a bit of salt and black pepper. Serve it on a portion of spaghetti and top with a generous amount of mozzarella and the basil leaves.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-06-22 07:16:45','2022-06-27 10:21:41',NULL),(372,'rbawgm','Scottish Kedgeree','Traditionally this is a breakfast dish but we cannot imagine why. It is tasty, nutritious and very satisfying. A creamy blend of smoked haddock, rice, butter, cream, hardboiled eggs, spices, peas and parsley. A winner for dinner!','Traces of Lactose',5,35,'<p>Place the haddock in a pan and add 500 ml of water. Add the bay leaves and bring to a simmer. Simmer the fish for 8 minutes.</p>\n<p>Drain the water from the fish into a pot and set the fish aside. Add the rice to this water, cover with a lid and bring to the boil. Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium, and simmer the rice for 10 minutes. Take it off the heat but leave the lid on and let it stand for at least 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>While the rice is cooking, bring some water to the boil, add the eggs very gently so that they don\'t crack and cook them for 8 minutes. When the 8 minutes is up pop the eggs into a bowl of cold water.</p>\n<p>When the eggs are cool to the touch take them out of the cold water and peel them. The easiest way to do this is to put an egg on a board, give it a sharp crack with a knife around its middle to halve the egg and then scoop out the two halves with a teaspoon. Roughly chop the eggs and put them aside.</p>\n<p>Melt the butter with a little oil in a skillet or pot and fry the onion for 5 minutes. Add the curry powder and cook for another 3 minutes, stirring constantly.</p>\n<p>Chop the parsley.</p>\n<p>Add the rice from the other pot, the peas, the parsley, the cream and some black pepper. Stir all together well.</p>\n<p>Break the fish into pieces and stir them into the pot along with the lemon juice and cook for 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Stir in the chopped egg, put the lid on the pot and leave it on the heat for 2 minutes for the egg to heat through.</p>\n<p>Serve immediately.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-06-24 07:23:49','2022-07-04 11:50:38',NULL),(373,'yvrspr','Creamy Steak & Mushroom with Fettucini','A delicious blend of cubed sirloin steak, plenty of mushrooms, garlic, fresh thyme and cream served on a bed of homemade fettucine.','Gluten and Lactose',5,25,'<p>Heat some oil in a pot on a high heat and fry the steak cubes. Add salt and black pepper to taste while stir frying for 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Turn the heat down to medium high. Add the mushrooms, the garlic and the fresh thyme and cook for a further 5 minutes, stirring occasionally so that nothing catches on the bottom of the pot.</p>\n<p>Stir the flour into the mixture combining well and let it cook for 1 minute. Then add the cream and milk, stirring continuously with a wooden spoon until it forms a nice sauce. If it is too thick add a dash of milk or water.</p>\n<p>Cook the steak and mushroom mix for 5 minutes on a medium low heat stirring frequently while you bring another pot with salted water to the boil.</p>\n<p>Boil the pasta for 6 minutes, breaking it up with a fork every now and then. Drain and keep warm.</p>\n<p>Serve the steak and mushroom on a bed of fettucine.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-06-26 09:28:47','2022-06-27 07:18:32',NULL),(374,'ugovfy','Creamy Tomato & Sausage Pasta','We use homemade penne pasta for this dish which somehow makes it more satisfying than the store bought variety.  The cooked penne and spinach is stirred into a creamy tomato sauce made with fried sausage meat and Parmesan giving us a really delicious combination.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',5,20,'<p>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Add the penne pasta and cook, stirring occasionally, for 6 minutes. Drain the pasta and set aside.</p>\n<p>Squueze the meat out of the sausage casings. Discard the casings.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a large pot over a high heat. Add the garlic and stir fry for 15 seconds. Add the sausage meat and use a wooden spoon to stir fry and break down clumps. Do this for 4 to 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the wine and use it to scrape the bits off the bottom of the pot. Cook for 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Divide the grated parmesan cheese in half. Set half aside for serving.</p>\n<p>Add the other half of the parmesan, the tomato puree, the cream and the Italian herb mix to the pot. Turn the heat down to medium low and cook for 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the spinach and the pasta to the pot, gently stirring everything together and cook for a further 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>If the mixture is too stiff add a splash of milk. If the mixture is too runny, cook for a further few minutes to reduce it.</p>\n<p>Serve in bowls garnished with the remaining grated parmesan.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-06-28 06:37:03','2022-07-04 12:27:33',NULL),(376,'mdmggs','Bacon & Barley Soup','This is a delicious and filling soup which does not need bread on the side. The portions are generous. Apart from the bacon and the barley, we have leek, carrot, celery, turnip and mushrooms all cooked up with a fabulous herb and spice mix to really pack in the nutrition.','Gluten',5,50,'<p>Heat some oil in a large pot over a medium high heat. Put all the vegetables and the garlic in the pot and saut&eacute; for 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the bacon bits and stir to break up any clumps.</p>\n<p>Add the spice mix and cook for another 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Mix the stock powder with the amount of water written on the label.</p>\n<p>Add the pearled barley and the stock to the pot.</p>\n<p>Bring to the boil and then turn down the heat and simmer on low for 35 &ndash; 40 minutes.</p>\n<p>Chop the parsley.</p>\n<p>Serve in bowls garnished with the chopped parsley.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-07-27 08:46:55','2022-08-15 14:48:20',NULL),(377,'ljszdw','Vegetable Barley Soup','This is a delicious and filling soup which does not need bread on the side. The portions are generous. Apart from the barley, we have leek, carrot, celery, turnip and mushrooms all cooked up with a fabulous herb and spice mix to really pack in the nutrition.','Gluten',5,50,'<p>Heat some oil in a large pot over a medium high heat. Put all the vegetables and the garlic in the pot and saut&eacute; for 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the spice mix and cook for another 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Mix the stock powder with the amount of water written on the label.</p>\n<p>Add the pearled barley and the stock to the pot.</p>\n<p>Bring to the boil and then turn down the heat and simmer on low for 35 &ndash; 40 minutes.</p>\n<p>Chop the parsley.</p>\n<p>Serve in bowls garnished with the chopped parsley.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-08-15 14:51:02','2022-08-15 14:54:50',NULL),(378,'tzockw','Tomato Chicken Skewers with Spinach Polenta','The chicken pieces are coated in a sticky tomato, Worcestershire and honey-based sauce with fresh rosemary, threaded onto skewers with whole baby tomatoes and then grilled. We serve these skewers with creamy spinach polenta which is a wonderful way to pack in that spinach with its powerhouse of anti-oxidants and other nutrients.','Lactose',10,20,'<ol>\n<li>Put the skewers to soak in a pan of water so that they don\'t burn when they are under the grill.</li>\n<li>Mix the tomato paste, honey, Worcestershire sauce and fresh rosemary in a bowl. Add the chicken and coat well. Add the whole tomatoes as well.</li>\n<li>Make the spinach polenta: Mix the stock powder with the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Bring the stock and milk to the boil in a pot and add a pinch of salt. Turn the heat down to medium and pour the polenta into the pot slowly while whisking the mixture. Cook, stirring constantly until the polenta has thickened nicely. Turn down to very low and stir in the cream, parmesan and the spinach. Season with more salt if necessary and take off the heat as soon as the spinach is wilted and the cheese is melted.</li>\n<li>Heat the oven grill, placing a shelf about 10 centimetres away from the hot element.</li>\n<li>Thread the chicken pieces and tomatoes onto the skewers and lay them on a grill rack or pan. Drizzle them with the leftover sauce.</li>\n<li>Grill the skewers for 5 minutes per side.</li>\n<li>Serve the spinach polenta with two skewers.<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-08-25 10:53:20','2022-08-25 11:16:26',NULL),(379,'axgixx','Spinach & Butternut Dhal','An Indian lentil dish featuring blanched spinach and roasted butternut, onion, tomato, garlic, ginger and our own mix of Tandoori spices. Delicious with locally made naan bread.','Gluten',5,40,'<p>Switch the oven on to 200 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Drizzle some oil onto the butternut pieces in an open oven pan and season with salt and black pepper.</p>\n<p>Do not wait for the oven to heat - place the butternut into the oven. Check the pieces after 30 minutes and then 40 minutes. They should be soft but not mushy.</p>\n<p>While the butternut is cooking get your lentils on. Place the amount of water specified on your stock powder package into a pot. Put in the stock powder and lentils and bring to the boil. Turn the heat down and slowly simmer the lentils with the lid on for 10 to 15 minutes. Do not cook fast. When they are soft, but not mushy, drain any remaining water off. Put aside.</p>\n<p>While the lentils and butternut are cooking, blanche the spinach. Bring a pot of salted water to the boil and, when boiling, pop the spinach in for 2 minutes. Drain and run cold water over it to stop it cooking. Put aside.</p>\n<p>In a big pot heat a bit of oil on a medium to high heat and fry the onions for 2 minutes. Add the garlic and ginger and cook for a further 1 minute. Add the Tandoori Spice and chilli flakes and cook for a further 30 seconds. If you do not want the heat leave out the chilli flakes.</p>\n<p>Add the tomato and cook for 2 minutes before adding the lentils, the spinach and the roasted butternut. Cook to heat through.</p>\n<p>Cut the lemon and squeeze the juice into the pot. Add the chutney and stir in well. Take the pot off the heat and stir in the plain yoghurt.</p>\n<p>Roughly chop the fresh coriander. Serve the dhal into bowls, sprinkling the corainder over the top. Break the naan into pieces and serve with the dhal.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-09-02 09:56:41','2022-09-05 09:45:14','<p>Tandoor Spice Mix</p>\n<p>1 teaspoon ground ginger<br />&frac12; teaspoon ground cumin<br />1 teaspoon ground coriander<br />1 teaspoon paprika<br />&frac12; teaspoon turmeric<br />&frac12; teaspoon salt<br />&frac14; teaspoon cayenne pepper<br />&frac14; teaspoon garlic powder<br />&frac14; teaspoon nutmeg<br />&frac14; teaspoon ground cloves</p>\n<p>Mix all together. Makes 1,5 tablespoons approx.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(380,'mhdxdz','Thai Chicken One Pot','This is a mild, family friendly Thai-inspired dish using yellow curry paste, coconut milk, chicken stock, red onion, butternut and peas. It all cooks in one pan and is served on rice with plenty of fresh basil leaves.','None',5,55,'<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Get the rice on first. Put it into some salted water in a pot and bring to the boil.&nbsp; Take the lid off and time 20 minutes from when it is boiling and it should be done. Drain and keep warm.</p>\n<p>While the rice is cooking, heat some oil in a large pan on a medium high heat and place the chicken pieces skin side down in the pan, season the top side with salt and pepper. Cook for 5 minutes. Then turn the pieces onto the other side, season, and cook for another 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>While the chicken is frying, make your stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the stock package. Set aside for now.</p>\n<p>When the chicken has done its 10 minutes, take it out of the pan and set aside for now - it will cook again later.</p>\n<p>Fry the red onion in the chicken juices, adding more oil if you need to. Fry, stirring now and again for 3 minutes and then add the curry paste. Stir it into the onion well and keep stirring while it cooks for 1 minute.</p>\n<p>Add the stock to the pan, along with the coconut milk. Stir in the butternut cubes and add the chicken pieces back, skin side up, nestling among the butternut.</p>\n<p>Simmer vigourously for 35 minutes. Give the pan a stir occasionally so that the sauce doesn\'t catch. Add the peas and simmer for another 5 minutes. Check a piece of chicken with a sharp knife - there should be no pink bits inside. Take off the heat.</p>\n<p>Pick the basil leaves off the stem and roughly chop them.</p>\n<p>Serve the chicken and plenty of sauce on rice, garnished with the fresh basil.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-09-08 12:57:37','2022-09-08 13:21:09',NULL),(382,'bjuvlm','Thai Tofu One Pot','This is our vegetarian take on the Thai Chicken One Pot. Tofu is fried to a golden colour, added to a very mild Thai inspired curry of onion, butternut and peas with coconut milk and served with fresh basil leaves and rice. The result is delicious!','None',5,50,'<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Get the rice on first. Put it into some salted water in a pot and bring to the boil.&nbsp; Take the lid off and time 20 minutes from when it is boiling and it should be done. Drain and keep warm.</p>\n<p>While the rice is cooking, heat some oil in a large pan on a medium high heat and fry the cubes of tofu. You will need a non-stick pan and/or a good amount of oil as tofu can stick. Fry for 10 minutes, turning the pieces now and again. Take off the heat and set aside.</p>\n<p>While the tofu is frying, make your stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the stock package. Set aside for now.</p>\n<p>Fry the red onion in the tofu pan, adding more oil if you need it. Fry, stirring now and again, for 3 minutes and then add the curry paste. Stir it into the onion well and keep stirring while it cooks for 1 minute.</p>\n<p>Add the stock to the pan, along with the coconut milk. Stir in the butternut cubes and simmer vigourously for 30 minutes. Give the pan a stir occasionally so that the sauce doesn\'t catch.</p>\n<p>Add the tofu back to the pan along with the peas and simmer for another 10 minutes, stirring gently now and again.</p>\n<p>Pick the basil leaves off the stem and roughly chop them.</p>\n<p>Serve the curry on rice, garnished with the fresh basil.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-09-13 07:26:47','2022-09-13 18:06:14',NULL),(383,'cqcxuu','Leek & Potato Soup with Nutty Wheat Bread','Leek, potatoes and cream are wonderful together in a soup. Throw in some corn kernels and peas for colour and top with grated cheddar cheese. Serve with nutty wheat bread hot from your oven - so easy with the ready made dough that comes in your kit.','Gluten, lactose',5,50,'<ol>\n<li>Heat the oven to 180 C. Unwrap the dough from the plastic wrap. Squish it into a greased bread tin. Once the oven is heated, bake the bread for 50 &ndash; 60 minutes. You will know the bread is cooked if you stick a skewer or bread knife into it and it comes out clean. Remove from the tin and leave to cool.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>While the bread is cooking, start the soup.</li>\n<li>Chop the potatoes into small cubes but leave the skins on.</li>\n<li>Heat a splash of oil and the butter in a big pot on a medium high heat. Put in the leeks and the potato cubes, stir well to coat with the butter and oil mix. Put the lid on the pot and \"sweat\" the potato and leek for 10 minutes. Stir every now and again.</li>\n<li>Make the stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package.</li>\n<li>Add the bay leaves, the thyme and the stock to the pot and stir everything together. Simmer with lid off for 25 minutes. Turn the heat down to medium or medium low.</li>\n<li>After 25 minutes, semi-blend the soup with a potato masher or blend with a stick blender. Do not use a closed blender for hot liquid - it can explode.</li>\n<li>Add the corn kernels, the peas and the cream and cook together for 5 minutes.</li>\n<li>Taste the soup and add salt and black pepper to taste. Take out the bay leaves and discard.</li>\n<li>Serve in bowls, topped with grated cheddar cheese, and slices of buttered homemade nutty wheat bread on the side.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\n</ol>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-09-21 11:18:41','2022-09-27 18:23:00',NULL),(384,'eytxv','Marinated Veg Quinoa Bowl','Red pepper, mixed marrows, onion and carrot are marinated in white wine vinegar, olive oil, honey and garlic mix and then grilled. Still crunchy and delicious from the marinade they are then mixed into quinoa cooked in veggie stock.','None',15,30,'<p>Add the zucchini, patty pans, onion, red pepper and carrots to the marinade in a bowl and toss together. Let it stand for 15 minutes while the quinoa cooks.</p>\n<p>Mix the vegetable stock powder with the amount of boiling water specified on the package and put into a pot. Bring to the boil, add the quinoa, stir and turn the heat to low. Put the lid on and simmer the quinoa for 15 minutes. Take off the heat and leave in the pot with the lid on for now.</p>\n<p>Turn your grill on. Drain the vegetables, reserving any marinade, and place them on a grill rack about 15 cm below the grill. Grill them for 5 minutes then turn them and grill for another 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>Cool the veg slightly and cut them into bite sized pieces.</p>\n<p>Fluff up the quinoa with a fork - the water should have been absorbed. Drain if necessary.</p>\n<p>Mix the quinoa, the grilled veg and any left over marinade together in a big bowl.</p>\n<p>Chop the basil and stir it in or use it as garnish when you serve the marinated veg quinoa in bowls.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-09-29 11:26:47','2022-10-10 10:11:43',NULL),(385,'kmxfel','Tuna Potato Bake','A family-style bake with lots of flavour, lots of nutrition. Tuna, spinach, potato, onion, cottage cheese, cheddar cheese and cream are all in the mix giving you a satisfying and easy to put together meal.','Lactose',5,40,'<p>Turn the oven on to 200 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Chop the potatoes into cubes but don\'t peel them. Place in a pot of salted water and bring to the boil. When boiling, time 20 minutes. Drain.</p>\n<p>While the potato is cooking, bring another pot of salted water to the boil. Put the spinach in for 2 minutes to blanche it. Drain it, run cold water over it and then squeeze all the moisture out of the spinach with your hands. You will now have a ball or roll of spinach which you can put on a board and roughly chop apart.</p>\n<p>In a large bowl mix the cottage cheese, the cream, half the cheddar cheese, the tuna and the onion. Stir in the spinach and when the potato is done stir that in as well. Add salt and pepper to taste.</p>\n<p>Place mixture into an oven dish and sprinkle the rest of the cheddar cheese over the top.</p>\n<p>Bake for 20 minutes. Take out of the oven and let the dish cool for a while before serving with the leafy greens on the side.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-10-10 09:15:05','2022-10-10 10:40:12',NULL),(386,'hkzgzh','Asian Meatballs with a Basil & Spring Onion Dressing','Ginger and fish sauce with ground pork give these meatballs their Asian flavour. We serve them on another Asian favourite, sauteed cabbage with a crunch, and then add a tangy basil and spring onion dressing to serve.','none',10,20,'<p>Mix together the meatball ingredients: the pork mince, onion powder, ginger, fish sauce and a good amount of black pepper. Use your hands to combine everything well and then form balls the size of golf balls. You should have 8 meat balls per person you are cooking for.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a pan on a medium high heat and fry the meat balls for 7 to 10 minutes, turning a couple of times. If you are cooking for 4 people you will have to do two batches. Once cooked, keep the meat balls warm.</p>\n<p>In the same pan, using the meat ball juices, add a bit more oil if necessary and saute the cabbage on a medium high heat for 5 minutes. The cabbage should be just changing colour and still crunchy. Add salt and pepper to taste.</p>\n<p>Serve the meatballs on the cabbage and top this with a generous amount of the Basil &amp; Spring Onion Dressing.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-10-11 07:34:43','2022-10-11 18:28:15',NULL),(387,'mpgxjj','Mediterranean Veg & Halloumi Rice Wraps','Lovely flavour and texture and fun to make! The veggies are roasted with our Mediterranean spice mix and placed in the wrap along with fried halloumi strips and a good dollop of a delicious basil pesto mayo.','None',5,40,'<p>Heat the oven to 180 C.</p>\n<p>Layer the aubergine, marrow, red onion and mushrooms on a greased baking tray. Sprinkle with some oil and make sure all the veg are nicely coated. Sprinkle the Mediterranean spice mix onto the veg and mix in. Place in the oven and cook for about 30 &ndash; 35 minutes. Check to see all the veg are nicely cooked.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>While the veg are cooking, pan fry the halloumi strips in some oil until nicely golden on each side.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;When the veg and halloumi are ready, lay out everything on the table. Have a large bowl or dish with cold water nearby (big enough to fit a rice wrap without breaking it).</p>\n<p>Submerge a rice wrap in for about 20 seconds, then put it on your plate. Let it sit for another 20 seconds, and then it will be soft and pliable. Put some of the veg, a strip or two of halloumi and a drizzle of basil pesto mayo. Fold it like you would a burrito &ndash; the bottom first and then the sides in. The trick is not to overfill your wrap otherwise the filling falls out! Don&rsquo;t be afraid to get a bit messy with this meal!&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-10-12 06:41:51','2022-12-09 09:12:21',NULL),(388,'uxkcst','Black Bean Lasagne','All the flavours of the traditional lasagne without the meat. You will make our marinara sauce, add a generous amount of black beans and then layer it with lasagne sheets and our cheese sauce which we send ready made. Top with grated cheddar and bake until bubbling and golden. Serve with fresh rocket. Easy and delicious.','Gluten & Lactose',5,50,'<p>Grease an oven dish. Heat the oven to 200 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a pot and fry the onion for 5 minutes on a medium high heat. Add the garlic and fry for another minute.&nbsp;<br />Add the tomatoes, tomato paste, balsamic vinegar, basil and oregano. Stir together well. Add salt and black pepper to taste.<br />Simmer without a lid for 20 minutes. Add the beans.&nbsp;<br />Make a paste with the cornflour and a little hot water. Stir into the pot and allow to simmer while stirring for a minute or two while the mixture thickens a bit. Taste to see whether you would like to add more salt and pepper.</p>\n<p>While the tomato and bean mixture is cooking, place the cheese sauce into a saucepan and gently heat it until it can be spread nicely. Do not boil.</p>\n<p>Place a spoon or two of the bean mixture to cover the bottom of the oven dish. Cover it with lasagne sheets. Break them if you need to. Then a layer of cheese sauce. Repeat these layers. Try and end with cheese sauce. Sprinkle the grated cheddar cheese over the top.</p>\n<p>Bake for 30 minutes.</p>\n<p>Serve with the leafy greens.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-10-24 09:47:14','2022-10-24 10:35:23','<p>CHEESE SAUCE</p>\n<p>You will need:</p>\n<p>60 grams butter<br />50 ml flour<br />2 cups full cream milk<br />100 grams of cheddar grated<br />1 tsp salt or to taste (start with half)<br />pinch of nutmeg</p>\n<p>Instructions:</p>\n<p>Melt the butter and stir in the flour with a wooden spoon until a smooth paste forms. Stir while this cooks for a minute.<br />Add the milk in four dollops, stirring out lumps in between each addition. Keep a whisk on hand for beating smooth if necessary. Let the sauce come to a simmer and simmer for about 4 minutes while it thickens. Make sure to stir constantly to avoid lumps. Add salt and nutmeg. When the sauce is the right consistency, take off the heat and stir in the cheese.</p>\n<p>This makes 500ml cheese sauce.</p>\n<p>TOP TIP: Heat the milk in the microwave and add it warm to the flour/butter paste - it\'s quicker and easier. Do not boil the milk, just warm it.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(389,'yrxdxo','Smoky Chickpea Stew with Couscous','This stew of chickpeas and tomato is flavoured with red onion, garlic, paprika, turmeric and cinnamon sticks, thickened with couscous and topped with roasted peppers and rocket. A swirl of plain yoghurt finishes it off. A delicious and satisfying vegetarian meal.','Gluten and Lactose',5,40,'<p>Preheat the oven to 220 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Place the red and yellow pepper pieces on a baking tray and drizzle with oil. When the oven is ready pop them in and time 15 minutes. When they are done, set aside.</p>\n<p>Make the stock by dissolving the stock powder into the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Set aside for now.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a pot on a medium to high heat and fry the red onion for 4 minutes. Add the garlic, the paprika, the turmeric and cinnamon stick and fry for a further 1 minute.</p>\n<p>Add HALF the stock, the chickpeas and the tomato. Bring to a boil and then turn the heat down so that the mixture can simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. After 15 minutes add the green beans and simmer for a further 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.</p>\n<p>Put the other half of the stock and a dash of oil into another pot and bring it to the boil. When it\'s boiling add the couscous and stir. Put the lid on and remove from heat. Let it stand for 5 minutes before fluffing up with a fork.</p>\n<p>When the chickpea mixture is done, add the couscous, stir all together well and let it cook together for a minute. Then add 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon of sugar per person you are cooking for, ie 1 teaspoon of each for 4 people. Stir in and taste again - you may need more salt.</p>\n<p>Serve the chickpea stew into bowls. Chop the roasted peppers into smaller pieces if necessary and place them on top of the stew. Then chop the rocket, discarding any tough stems, and sprinkle over the top of the bowls. Lastly swirl some yoghurt over each.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-10-27 09:49:27','2022-10-27 10:27:35',NULL),(390,'oayocx','Japanese Chicken Yaki Udon','This is a Japanese stir fry using yaki udon - thick Japanese noodles in a slightly sweet but savoury mix of soy and oyster sauces, dry white wine, vinegar and honey. It is quick to make and delicious to eat.','Gluten',5,25,'<p>Heat some oil in a large non-stick pan. Add the chicken mince and cook for about 8 minutes until its no longer pink. Season well with salt and pepper. Remove it into a bowl.</p>\n<p><br />Using the same pan, add some more oil and add the garlic and ginger. Cook for 2 minutes and then add the carrots and cabbage. Stir fry for about 8 &ndash; 10 minutes.</p>\n<p><br />While that is cooking, put your udon noodles in a bowl of hot water to loosen them.</p>\n<p><br />To the veg, add the chicken mince and sauce. Stir to combine. Then stir in the peas and udon noodles. Stir to mix everything together.<br />Serve immediately in bowls.&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-11-01 09:48:31','2022-11-01 10:29:34',NULL),(391,'qfeiup','Thai Fried Rice with Tofu & Pineapple','It\'s hard to describe this fabulous dish other than saying it tastes like more! Thai flavoured fried rice including the traditional egg is wonderful on its own but we go the extra mile by adding onion, tofu, carrots, peas, spring onion, coriander and pineapple. The cherry on the top is the addition of cashew nuts.','Nuts',10,35,'<p>Place the rice in salted water and bring to the boil. Time 20 minutes from boiling point and then drain. In a colander run cold water over the rice to cool, then spread it on a baking tray and pop into the freezer until you need it. Fried rice is better using cold rice, usually a day old, but the freezer does the trick.</p>\n<p>While the rice is boiling, heat some oil in a big pan on medium high heat. Place the tofu cubes in a bowl, add the cornflour and salt and pepper to taste, and gently mix so that the tofu is coated. Fry the tofu cubes, gently turning now and again. It should be light golden - 15 minutes should do it.</p>\n<p>When the tofu is done, take it out of the pan and set aside. Using the same pan, add a splash more oil and using a medium high heat, fry the onion and carrot for 5 minutes, stirring often.</p>\n<p>Separate the eggs and keep the yolks. Either use the whites in another recipe or discard. Beat the yolks. Make a well in the centre of the onion and carrot, pour the yolks into it and stir fry the egg for 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Take the rice from the freezer and add it to the pan. Stir all together well.</p>\n<p>Add the Thai Mix, stir in. Pick the leaves from the coriander and add them whole. Add the chilli flakes (leave them out if you dislike the heat). Cook together for 2 minutes, stirring frequently.</p>\n<p>Add the spring onion, the peas, the pineapple and the cashew nuts. Cook for 1 minute more, stirring.</p>\n<p>Stir the tofu into the pan very gently and cook until everything is heated through. Serve immediately.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-11-03 10:33:17','2022-11-03 11:03:12',NULL),(392,'njstib','Creamy Mushroom Noodle Bowl','Despite its simplicity, this meal is incredibly tasty and filling. Lots of mushrooms, some spinach, coconut milk and plenty of egg noodles with an optional touch of chilli make this dish a vegetarian\'s delight.','Gluten',5,15,'<p>Make your vegetable stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Set aside for now.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a pot and cook the mushrooms over a medium heat until they are soft and dark and the liquid in the pot has evaporated. This can take 10 minutes or more.</p>\n<p>While the mushrooms are cooking add the chilli flakes to them. You can omit them or use half if you prefer no heat or less heat. A few flakes should not be hot but does lift the flavour.</p>\n<p>Once the mushrooms are ready, add the stock to the pot, turn the heat to medium high and bring the pot to the boil. When boiling add the noodles and boil for 3 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the spinach and coconut milk and cook for 2 minutes more.</p>\n<p>Let the pot cool slightly and then serve in bowls.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-11-04 09:36:51','2022-11-04 11:03:29',NULL),(393,'vwqxon','Peruvian Quinoa Stew with Homemade Bread Rolls','Quinoa is a protein-rich seed that acts like a grain. It is indigenous to the Andean regions of South America and this mildly spicy Peruvian stew is a version of the hearty soups served in that part of the world. The veggies used are onion, garlic, celery, carrot, bell pepper, zucchini and tomato with a special mix of spices - fabulous flavour! Serve with your own homemade bread rolls warm from the oven.','Gluten & Lactose (Bread Rolls)',15,30,'<p>Start with the bread rolls: Preheat your oven to 200 degrees C. Grease a baking tray. Pour the flour mix into a bowl. Melt the butter and mix through the dry ingredients with a fork. Add the yoghurt and mix until well combined. Have a bowl of water at the ready to wet your hands - it stops the mixture from sticking to you. Shape roll-size balls of dough and place them on the baking tray. When your oven is hot enough bake the rolls for 30 minutes. The outside of the rolls should be crisp and when you stick a skewer into a roll it comes out clean. This means they are cooked through.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>While the rolls are baking:&nbsp;Put the quinoa into a pot with the amount of water specified on the package. Add a big pinch of salt and bring to the boil. Put the lid on. Turn the heat right down so that it just simmers for 15 minutes. Take the quinoa off the heat and leave it in the pot with the lid on until you need it.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>While the quinoa is cooking:&nbsp; Heat some oil in a soup pot on a medium high heat and fry the onion for 5 minutes. Add the garlic, the celery and the carrot and fry for a further 5 minutes. Add the pepper, baby marrow, tomato and the Peruvian spice mix. Stir together well. Turn the heat down a bit and simmer the mixture for 15 minutes. Add the quinoa, stir and taste for seasoning, adding salt if you think it needs it.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Chop the fresh coriander. Serve the stew in a bowl.&nbsp; Garnish with fresh coriander and serve with fresh buttered rolls.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-11-10 09:44:05','2022-11-10 17:14:37',NULL),(394,'jzhiqf','Roasted Butternut, Beet & Pecan Nut Salad','Roasted cubes of butternut and beetroot are tossed with pecan nuts and sunflower seeds in a sublime orange and cinnamon dressing. This beautiful salad is served with pan-fried halloumi and rocket to make a fully satisfying meal.','Nuts and traces of Lactose',5,40,'<p>Heat oven to 200 degrees C.</p>\n<p>Toss butternut cubes with a sprinkle of oil and salt and lay them on a baking tray, preferably in one layer. Take the tin foil and parcel up the beetroot pieces. Lay the parcel on the same baking tray. When the oven is hot, roast the butternut and beetroot for 30 minutes. If the butternut is not golden and slightly crispy leave it for a little longer.</p>\n<p>While the butternut and beetroot is in the oven, heat some oil in a pan on a medium high heat and fry the halloumi cubes. This should not take long, a couple of minutes on each side should make them crispy and golden brown. When they are done, take off the heat but keep warm.</p>\n<p>When the butternut and beetroot is done, place it in a heat-proof bowl and toss together with the pecan nuts, sunflower seeds and the Orange Cinnamon Dressing. Let the salad cool slightly.</p>\n<p>Arrange the rocket and fried halloumi on top and serve warm. This salad is nice warm or cold.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-11-16 08:19:33','2022-11-16 10:17:37',NULL),(395,'ceaazm','Mongolian Beef with Jasmine Rice','Mongolian Beef is a Chinese stir-fry dish which originated in Taiwan in the 1950\'s. Thin slices of beef along with some mushrooms and broccoli are stir-fried, coated in a sweet and spicy sauce and served with fragrant Jasmine rice, fresh coriander and lime wedges.','None',10,40,'<p>Place the beef strips in the marinade mix and leave to marinate for 30 minutes.</p>\n<p>Then cook the rice. Measure your rice in cups. Place the rice and some salt in a pot and add twice the amount of water ie if you are cooking 1 cup of rice you use 2 cups of water. Cover the pot and bring to the boil. Turn the heat off and leave the pot covered until you need to serve.</p>\n<p>Make a slurry with half the cornstarch and a bit of water. Set it aside.</p>\n<p>Dredge the marinated beef strips in the remaining cornstarch. It should all be lightly coated.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a wok or frying pan over a medium heat. When the oil is hot evenly spread the beef strips in the pan and sear on both sides. The pieces should be seared with a crusty coating. Remove them from the pan. If the pan is not big enough to have the strips in a single layer then sear them in batches. Pour off excess liquid each time. If you do not do this you will have too much liquid and&nbsp; a stew rather than a stir fry.</p>\n<p>Using the same wok/pan and after draining the liquid add a little more oil and return to medium heat.</p>\n<p>Add the ginger, chilli (optional), mushrooms and broccoli and stir fry for 20 seconds. Add the garlic and stir fry for another 20 seconds.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Add the Mongolian Sauce Mix, stir and simmer for 2 minutes. Then stir in the cornstarch slurry. Stir and cook until the sauce has thickened and can coat the back of the spoon. Use the spoon to scrape any bits off the bottom of the pan into the sauce.</p>\n<p>Add the beef and spring onions and mix well. The sauce should cling to the beef with almost no liquid left in the pan. If the sauce is still watery, increase the heat and stir until it is thickened.</p>\n<p>Chop the fresh coriander and slice the lime into wedges. Take the lid off the rice pot and fluff up the rice with a fork. It&nbsp; should have absorbed all the liquid.</p>\n<p>Serve the Mongolian Beef with the jasmine rice, chopped coriander and a wedge of lime.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-11-17 10:53:06','2022-11-18 11:02:47',NULL),(396,'rdxlgq','Black Bean & Corn Burrito','Yummy vegetarian burritos featuring a black bean and tomato sauce with Mexican spice, rice, sour cream, a fresh salsa and grated cheddar cheese. We even share our tips for rolling the perfect burrito!','Gluten and traces of Lactose',15,10,'<p>First measure the amount of rice you have in cups and put double that amount of water into a pot along with the rice and some salt, ie if you have one cup of rice use two cups of water. Put the lid on and bring to the boil. When boiling take the pot off the heat but leave the lid on until you need the rice.</p>\n<p>Heat the oven to 180 degrees C and grease a baking tray (if you have more than 1 burrito to prepare).</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a pan on medium heat and fry the white onion, garlic and oregano for about 5 minutes. Season with a pinch of salt and pepper. Add the Mexican spice and fry for a further 30 seconds.</p>\n<p>Add the chopped tomato and simmer for 5 minutes, reducing the heat if necessary. Check the seasoning and add some more salt and pepper if you wish. Add the black beans, stir in well and remove from the heat.</p>\n<p>Prepare the salsa: Chop the fresh tomato and the coriander and mix with the corn kernels and the red onion in a bowl. Season with some salt and pepper to taste.</p>\n<p>Next heat the burrito wraps in the microwave for 10 to 15 seconds so they are pliable and easy to fold.</p>\n<p>Assemble your burritos: Place the wrap on a flat surface and smear some of the sour cream down the centre. Put rice over the sour cream, then top that with black bean sauce, salsa and grated cheddar.</p>\n<p>When you stack the filling, try and keep the layers centred and even. Leave a space to the left and the right, top and bottom.</p>\n<p>Fold the sides in and the bottom flap and then roll the burrito away from you, keeping the sides tucked in until it is completely sealed.</p>\n<p>Heat a little oil in a clean pan over a medium heat and place the burrito folded side down to seal it. Let it brown. Using a spatula, flip it over and brown the other side. If you have more than one burrito to make, place the burrito on the greased baking tray and pop in the oven while you do the others.</p>\n<p>Cut your lime into quarters.</p>\n<p>Serve the burrito(s) with any remaining salsa and a squeeze of lime.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-11-17 11:06:39','2022-11-21 10:02:58','<p>Mexican Spice</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>1.5 tsp ground cumin</p>\n<p>1 tsp salt</p>\n<p>1 tsp ground black pepper</p>\n<p>0.5 tsp paprika</p>\n<p>1/4 tsp dried oregano</p>\n<p>1 Tbsp cayenne pepper</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Mix all together well.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>'),(397,'wixmfs','Baked Pumpkin & Mushroom Risotto with Pan-Fried Halloumi','Baking a risotto is definitely the way forward - it cuts out all that stirring and anxiety that risottos generally cause! This creamy risotto includes onion, pumpkin, mushrooms and parmesan with spring onions for a pop of green. It is served with crispy bits of fried halloumi.','Traces of Lactose',5,40,'<p>Heat the oven to 180 degrees C.</p>\n<p>For this dish an oven-proof skillet with a lid is ideal. You can also use a pot for the stove top and then transfer to an oven dish with a lid if you do not have an oven proof skillet.</p>\n<p>In your ovenproof skillet or your pot, heat some oil on a medium heat and fry the onion for 5 minutes. Add the mushrooms and fry until golden, about 3 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the garlic and fry for 30 seconds before adding the pumpkin and rice. Add a dash more oil if you feel it needs it. Fry the mixture, stirring now and again for 3 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the wine and allow to simmer for 2 minutes, still stirring frequently.</p>\n<p>Make the stock by dissolving the stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Add the stock to the skillet and stir all together.</p>\n<p>Put the lid on and place in oven. If you are cooking in a pot that is not oven-proof transfer the mixture to an oven dish that has a lid.</p>\n<p>Bake for 25 minutes and the the rice and pumpkin should be cooked and the liquid absorbed.</p>\n<p>While the risotto is in the oven, heat some oil in a pan over a medium hot heat and fry the pieces of halloumi. They brown up quickly so flip them over after a minute or two to brown the other side. Don\'t worry if they stick together. Once cooked place them on a board and use a knife to separate the bits. Keep warm.</p>\n<p>Stir the chopped spring onions and grated Parmesan through the risotto and serve with a handful of crispy halloumi pieces on top.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-11-24 10:11:32','2022-11-24 10:29:45',NULL),(398,'mndbeu','Thai-Style Chicken & Peanut Udon Noodles','We use chicken mince fried with garlic for this Asian-inspired udon noodle dish. The sauce is a spicy mix of red curry paste, soy sauce, coconut milk, apple cider vinegar and peanut butter in chicken stock - sounds unusual but works so well! We stir baby spinach and the noodles into the  chicken and sauce and each portion is topped with roughly chopped peanuts.','Nuts',5,15,'<p>In a large pan heat some oil on a medium high heat. Put in the garlic and fry for 20 seconds before adding the chicken mince. Use a wooden spoon to break up the clumps and fry until no longer pink, about 8 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the curry paste, curry powder and soy sauce. Cook for 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Make your stock by dissolving the chicken stock powder in the amount of boiling water specified on the package. Add the stock to the pan, turn down the heat and let it simmer for 1 minute, stirring.</p>\n<p>Add the coconut milk, apple cider vinegar and peanut butter and keep stirring until there are no more clumps of peanut butter.</p>\n<p>Add the udon noodles and the spinach. Stir in and let the mixture cook until the noodles are ready - 2 to 3 minutes.</p>\n<p>Serve immediately into bowls and sprinkle with chopped peanuts.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-12-01 09:56:17','2022-12-01 10:22:13',NULL),(399,'owskzl','Mushroom Bolognaise with Homemade Spaghetti & Parmesan','A delicious vegetarian bolognaise based on a generous portion of mushrooms simmered with our Red Wine and Tomato Mix and served on homemade spaghetti with chopped spring onions and grated Parmesan.','Gluten & Traces of Lactose',5,25,'<p>Heat some oil in a pot and fry the onion for 3 minutes. Add the garlic and fry for a further 1 minute.</p>\n<p>Add the mushrooms and cook for 5 minutes. Then add the Red Wine &amp; Tomato Mix. Stir everything together well and reduce heat to low so that the mushroom bolognasie simmers for 15 minutes.</p>\n<p>While the mushroom bolognasie is simmering cook your spahetti. Bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Add the spaghetti and stir gently to loosen the strands. Boil for 4 minutes and then drain immediately. Keep warm.</p>\n<p>When the bolgnaise is ready taste it for seasoning and add salt and pepper if you want to.&nbsp; Serve it on a portion of spaghetti, topped with chopped spring onion and grated parmesan.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-12-02 10:49:11','2023-01-16 12:02:56',NULL),(400,'qfxieb','Creamy Dill Chicken & Mushroom with Polenta','An easy to cook and creamy combination of chicken, mushrooms and dill in a sauce of stock, white wine, sherry, Dijon mustard and yoghurt. We serve the dish with tasty spinach polenta.','Gluten and Lactose',5,30,'<p>Season your chicken cubes with salt and black pepper.</p>\n<p>Make the chicken stock for the main dish using the amount of boiling&nbsp; water specified on that label. Set aside for now.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a large skillet on a medium high heat and fry the chicken for 8 minutes, turning and stirring regularly.</p>\n<p>Reduce heat to medium and add the onion. Fry for 3 minutes. Add the mushrooms and fry for a further 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in the garlic and fry for 20 seconds before adding the chicken stock, wine and sherry. Bring to the boil. Add the yoghurt, the dill and the dijon mustard.</p>\n<p>Melt the butter in the microwave and stir the flour into it to make a nice paste. Add that paste to the chicken dish and stir until the sauce thickens. Let it cook for a few minutes more, taste and add salt and pepper if you wish and then turn the heat off while you make the polenta.</p>\n<p>Make the stock labelled for the polenta with the amount of boiling water specified on that package. Place in a pot along with the milk. Bring this to the boil then turn the heat down slightly while you slowly trickle the polenta into the pot, whisking all the time. The polenta will thicken and pull away from the side of the pot fairly quickly. Add the spinach and once it is wilted into the polenta taste for seasoning and add salt if you wish. Take off the heat.</p>\n<p>Serve the spinach polenta topped with the creamy chicken.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2022-12-15 06:22:03','2022-12-15 14:24:18',NULL),(401,'zbyskj','Teriyaki Tofu','Japanese in origin, teriyaki sauce is sweet, tangy and sticky and works very well with crispy pan-fried tofu, as well as with the broccoli we serve with it. We also add rice to mop up the deliciousness but feel free to leave that out if you want a low carb meal.','None',5,20,'<p>Measure your rice in millilitres or cups. Place it in a pot with an equal volume of cold water and some salt. Place on a high heat with the lid on. When the pot is boiling vigourously, turn the heat off. Leave the lid on until you need the rice. By that time it will have absorbed the water and be cooked.</p>\n<p>Bring a little salted water to the boil in another pot. Then add the broccoli and boil for 4 minutes. Drain and keep warm. Do not overcook your broccoli.</p>\n<p>Place the tofu cubes in a bowl and gently mix in the soy sauce and seasoned cornstarch.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a pan over medium high heat. When the oil is hot add the tofu and toss to cook and crisp up all sides. This should take about 8 minutes. Remove from the pan and keep aside for now.</p>\n<p>Heat the Teriyaki sauce in a pan over medium low heat and let it simmer for 4 minutes, stirring frequently so it doesn\'t catch on the pan. The sauce will thicken. Taste it and add more water or a pinch of sugar if you need to.</p>\n<p>Turn the heat off and add the tofu to the sauce, stirring gently to coat it all. Let it lie in the hot sauce for 3 minutes before serving.</p>\n<p>Garnish the Tariyaki Tofu with chopped spring onions and serve on rice with broccoli on the side. If you would like a low carb meal, leave out the rice or use just 2 tablespoons.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2023-01-08 18:23:27','2023-01-09 08:46:31',NULL),(402,'ajhepp','Chicken Teriyaki',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2023-01-08 18:24:37','2023-01-08 18:24:37',NULL),(403,'cftynr','Baked Ziti with Cajun Chicken','The spiciness of the cajun chicken blends beautifully with the creaminess of the cheese sauce and the homemade pasta. The richness is nicely offset by a generous portion of chopped red and green pepper, onion and cherry tomatoes. The portions are generous and leafy greens are not included in the kit.','Gluten and Lactose',5,45,'<p>Heat the oven to 200 degrees C. Grease an oven proof casserole dish.</p>\n<p>For the pasta: Bring a pot of salted water to the boil. Place pasta in the pot. It should be done in 4 to 5 minutes. Test a piece and then, when ready, drain and set aside.</p>\n<p>For the chicken mix: Heat some oil in a skillet or pot on a medium-high heat and add the chicken, the Cajun spice and a pinch or two of salt, depending on your preference. Cook, stirring now and then, for 10 minutes. Add the red and green pepper, the onion and HALF the garlic. Halve the cherry tomatoes and add them to the pot. Stir together well and cook without a lid, stirring now and then, for another 10 minutes.</p>\n<p>For the sauce: Heat the milk in the microwave until hot but do not let it boil. Set aside. Melt the butter in a pot on a medium heat and then add the other half of the garlic. Cook for 1 minute. Add the flour and stir in well so that you make a paste. Cook for 1 minute more. Add the milk and whisk continuously while the sauce thickens. Add salt and pepper to taste. Add 2/3 of the cheese, leaving a third to sprinkle on top of your dish.</p>\n<p>To assemble: Add the drained pasta to the chicken mix, stir well and place in the oven dish. Pour your sauce evely over the top and then top that with the remaining grated cheese.</p>\n<p>Bake for 15 minutes - the dish should be golden and bubbling.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2023-01-25 11:11:28','2023-01-25 11:44:07',NULL),(404,'uzhllx','Siamese Chicken with Sticky Asian Sauce','We do love a taste of Thai and our Sticky Asian Sauce will not disappoint. This meal is very quick and easy to prepare. This chicken dish also boasts mushrooms and green beans, fresh coriander and mint, and is served on fragrant Jasmine rice.','None',5,25,'<p>Measure your rice. Add the same volume of cold water and some salt with the rice to a pot. With the lid on the pot, bring the rice and water to the boil. When it is boiling take it off the heat but leave the lid on the pot until you are ready to serve. When you are ready to serve, the rice will have absorbed all the water and be ready to serve as well.</p>\n<p>Place the sauce ingredients in a small pan and bring to the boil on a medium high heat. Let it cook until it is sticky and thick. Keep warm or reheat before serving</p>\n<p>Rub your chicken with some oil and season it with salt and black pepper. Then thinly brush some sauce on the top of each piece.</p>\n<p>Heat a little oil in a pan on medium heat and cook the prepared chicken for 1 minute. Then add the mushrooms. Once there is a little colour to the chicken cover the pan with a lid to create steam and continue cooking until the top side of the chicken is white. Then take the lid off and turn the chicken to cook the other side. If your pan is not big enough you may need to do the chicken in batches. If so, keep the cooked pieces warm.</p>\n<p>Add green beans to the chicken and cook for 30 seconds or until vibrant green. Set aside. Chop the fresh coriander and mint.</p>\n<p>Slice the chicken and place it on the heated sauce. Sprinkle with sesame seeds and the coriander and mint. Serve with Jasmine rice and the green beans.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2023-01-30 09:31:00','2023-02-06 14:32:34',NULL),(405,'lesifa','Cheese Burger & Sweet Potato Wedges with Aioli','A burger made in your own kitchen from fresh ingredients is always far healthier than a takeaway and this cheese burger with its fresh trimmings will not disappoint. Serve with roasted sweet potato wedges and the garlicky aioli.','Gluten and traces of Lactose',10,45,'<p>Heat your oven to 200 degrees C. If you have baking paper or foil, line a baking sheet to help with the clean up. If not just grease the baking sheet. Rub the sweet potato wedges with oil, salt and black pepper and place them on the baking tray in a single layer. Roast them for 45 minutes, tossing occasionally.</p>\n<p>Separate the eggs into yolk and white. Crack the egg open and carefully tip the white out into a bowl whilst keeping the yolk in the shell. Put separated yolk into another bowl. Put the yolks aside to use in the beef patties. You can use the egg whites to add extra protein to any other dish - e.g. scrambled eggs.</p>\n<p>In a bowl mix together the beef mince, crushed garlic, worcestershire sauce, oregano and the egg yolks. Add a generous amount of salt and pepper. Divide the mixture into 4 equal balls which you press out into 4 patties. Put aside for now.</p>\n<p>Put a little oil in a pan and fry the onion rings on a low to medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes - they need to caramelise but not burn. Keep warm or reheat just before using.</p>\n<p>In the same pan add a little oil if necessary and turn the heat up to medium high. Fry the burger patties for 4 to 5 minutes. Then flip them over (only flip once). Put a slice of cheese on top of each patty and cover with a pot lid to help the cheese melt into the patty. Cook for 5 minutes more, but remove the pot lid once the cheese has melted. Keep patties warm by turning off the heat and leaving them in the pan.</p>\n<p>Slice the burger buns in half and toast them in a pan or under a grill. Once toasted spread with Dijonnaise.</p>\n<p>Once the sweet potatoes are roasted slice your tomatoes and build your burgers.</p>\n<p>On the bottom half of the bun place some leafy greens and sliced tomato. Season with salt and pepper. Place the cheesy patty on top of that and the cooked onion rings on top of the patty. Place the other half of the bun on top.</p>\n<p>Tip the Aioli into a bowl and make sure it is well mixed. Serve the burgers with the sweet potato wedges and the Aioli.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2023-02-17 11:06:01','2023-02-17 12:22:29','<p>The Aioli ingredients should be mixed together vigourously.</p>'),(406,'qoaclp','Thai Yellow Curry Chicken','The Thai Yellow Curry is the mildest of the Thai curries but we think it\'s the the most flavourful. This dish is incredibly simple and quick to put together using chicken, curry paste, coconut milk, fish sauce and sugar snap peas. We serve it with rice.','None',5,25,'<p>Measure your rice and place double that volume of cold water into a pot. E.g. for 1 cup of rice you will use 2 cups of water.&nbsp; Salt it and add the rice. Bring to the boil with the lid on and, once boiling, remove the pot from the heat but DO NO LIFT THE LID until you are ready to serve.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Heat some oil in a pot. Add the chicken cubes and salt and pepper. Fry the chicken until it is no longer pink, about 8 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the curry paste and make sure it coats the chicken. Continue frying for 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Add the coconut milk, the sugar snap peas and the fish sauce and simmer for 2 minutes.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Scoop some of the coconut milk liquid from the pot with a cup or bowl and add the cornstarch to that, making a paste. Put the paste back into the pot and stir well - the sauce will thicken slightly. Cook for a further 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.</p>\n<p>When you are ready to serve open the rice pot and fluff the rice up with a fork - it should be perfectly cooked. Serve the rice topped with the curry.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2023-02-18 12:29:15','2023-02-18 16:45:45',NULL),(407,'nirisc','Coconut Chickpea Curry','A delicious chickpea curry made with coconut milk and served with Basmati rice, raita (minted cucumber and yoghurt) and a tomato coriander salsa.','Lactose (raita)',5,30,'<p>Cook Rice: Melt the butter in a small pot over a medium heat, add half the garlic and cook until fragrant (30 seconds), add rice, a big pinch of salt and double the quantity weightwise of cold water, i.e. if you have 200g of rice then use 200g of water. Cover with a lid and bring rice to the boil. Once the rice has come to the boil, switch off the heat and set aside.</p>\n<p><br />In a medium sized pot add a drizzle of oil and heat. Add the chopped onions &amp; red pepper. Cook until softened, 3-5 minutes. Season with salt &amp; pepper.<br />Add the remaining garlic, tomato paste, curry powder, paprika and garam masala. Cook until fragrant, about 1 minute. Stir occasionally.</p>\n<p><br />Stir in the coconut milk, stock concentrate, chickpeas &amp; 1 teaspoon per person of sugar, i.e 2 teaspoons if you are cooking for 2. Bring to a simmer then reduce heat to low and cook until thickened, stirring occasionally. This should take 10 to 15 minutes. If your curry seems too thick add a little water.</p>\n<p>Place the Raita in a small bowl and the tomato salsa in another bowl. Check them both for seasoning, adding salt and pepper if you wish.</p>\n<p>Check the seasoning of your curry - add salt and pepper if you wish.</p>\n<p>Chop the fresh coriander and fluff up the rice with a fork.</p>\n<p>Serve the curry on the rice, topped with some Raita and tomato salsa. Sprinkle with fresh coriander.</p>\n<p><br /><br />&nbsp;<br /><br /></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2023-03-03 10:29:38','2023-03-03 11:05:05',NULL),(408,'veyogw','Black Bean & Mushroom Burger','A vegetarian patty with black beans, mushrooms, green onions and herbed aioli makes a great burger. Served with potato wedges, extra leafy greens and more of the aioli, a creamy, garlicky sauce with a dash of lemon and some fresh herbs.','Gluten & Lactose',5,30,'<p>Preheat the oven to 200 degrees C. Cut your potatoes into fairly thin wedges, peeling them if you prefer. Toss them with some oil, salt and pepper in a bowl and put them on a baking tray to roast. Roast for 20-25 minutes, turning half way.</p>\n<p><br />Place the herbed aioli in a bowl. Add a few dashes of water to thin the mixture out if you need to. It should look like a creamy dressing.</p>\n<p><br />In a bowl mash the black beans with a potato masher or fork. The beans do not have to be completely smooth. Add the mushrooms, green spring onions and the flour. Mix together with some of the herbed aioli - about 1/2 tablespoon per person that you are cooking for. Check seasoning and add salt and pepper if necessary. Divide &amp; shape the mixture into patties, one for each bun.&nbsp; Brush both sides with oil. Set aside.<br />&nbsp;<br />Heat a few drizzles of oil in a pan over a medium-high heat. Using a spatula transfer the patties to the pan (if needed cook in batches &amp; re- oil the pan between each batch). Cook patties until golden brown on both sides. When flipping the patties they are likely to fall apart, so use a second spatula or utensil to assist &amp; reshape as needed. Set aside cooked patties.</p>\n<p><br />Halve the burger buns and lightly toast them in the pan. Put aside a few lettuce leaves for the buns and use the remaining lettuce for the salad. Separate the remaining herbed aioli into 2 bowls. Half goes onto the burgers &amp; the other half is for the salad dressing.</p>\n<p><br />Assemble burgers: On the bottom burger bun place 1-2 lettuce leaves, then place bean &amp; mushroom burger and top with herbed aioli. In a bowl place the chopped lettuce &amp; toss with the dressing. (Tip: if there is more dressing than is needed for the lettuce, keep aside extra dressing for dunking the potato wedges). Serve burger with potato wedges &amp; salad.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2023-03-03 11:58:32','2023-03-04 15:23:36',NULL),(409,'xcihjf','Lentil & Spinach Stuffed Mushroom with Barley Risotto','A creamy barley \"risotto\" and wilted spinach make a base for Portabello mushrooms stuffed with a cheesy and garlicky mixture of lentils, herbs and spinach. A delicious vegetarian meal.','Traces of Lactose',5,50,'<p>Make up the stock marked \"for lentils\" and place in a small pot. Bring to the boil, turn down and simmer until soft or the lentils &lsquo;pop&rsquo; easily between two fingers - about 20 minutes. Drain any excess liquid once cooked.</p>\n<p>Heat the oven to 180 degrees C. Lightly oil a baking tray or line with tin foil. Set aside. Heat a generous squeeze of oil in a pan over a medium heat and fry 1/2 the onion for 5 minutes. Add 3/4 of the spinach &amp; 1/2 the garlic with the thyme and cook until the spinach is wilted. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from heat.</p>\n<p>Chop the basil. Add the cooked lentils, basil, &amp; cheddar cheese to the spinach mixture and mix well. Check seasoning &amp; adjust accordingly. Remove thyme stalks if you have used fresh thyme.</p>\n<p>Drizzle a small amount of oil in the portobello mushrooms and season with salt and pepper. Stuff the mushrooms with the spinach &amp; lentil mix and bake for 15-20 minutes or until the mushroom is soft but still holds its structure &amp; the cheese is melted.</p>\n<p>In a small to medium sized pot over a medium/high heat, heat a splash of oil and fry the other half of the onion and all the barley until the onions are opaque. Add the remaining garlic.</p>\n<p>Add the wine and deglaze the pan (scrape all the yummy bits off the bottom) and reduce the liquid to about 1/2 to 1 Tablespoon. Season with salt and pepper.</p>\n<p>Make up the stock marked \"for the barley risotto\". Add the stock to the barley pot and reduce the heat to a simmer. Partly cover the pot &amp; stir frequently.</p>\n<p>Once the barley is soft but not mushy, and/or the liquid is mostly absorbed, remove from the heat. Add a splash of milk and stir in the grated parmesan. Check seasoning &amp; set aside to&lsquo;rest&rsquo;. If your risotto looks like it has too much liquid (it should not look saucey but rather just creamy) return to the heat and increase the heat to evaporate the liquid. Add the peas and the zest from your lemon ie grate some of the lemon skin into the pot.</p>\n<p>In the pan you used for the spinach, wilt the remaining spinach with a little oil, salt and pepper.</p>\n<p>Assemble: Place some wilted spinach on a plate and then top with risotto &amp; a stuffed mushroom (two if they are small). Drizzle with lemon juice &amp; serve.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2023-03-16 09:51:48','2023-03-20 07:19:24',NULL),(410,'fjrhno','Cannellini Bean & Barley Bowl','This vegetarian barley bowl is a wonderful mix of barley, hummus, cannellini beans fried with Za\'atar and a fresh minty salsa. A creamy feta dressing pulls it all together in an explosion of Middle Eastern flavour.','Gluten & Lactose',5,40,'<p>Measure your barley and place 3 times that amount of water in a pot with a generous pinch of salt. Bring to the boil and add the barley. Reduce the heat to a simmer and cook for 30 minutes. The barley should be tender. Drain any excess water and cool slightly.</p>\n<p>Shake the barley dressing well so that it is emulsified and add to the barley. Add salt &amp; pepper to taste and set aside.</p>\n<p>In a bowl mix the cannellini beans, the Za\'arta spice and some salt and pepper to taste. Heat some oil in a pan on a medium high heat and fry the seasoned beans unitl they are slightly crispy and have a bit of colour. Take off the heat and set aside.</p>\n<p>In a bowl mix the chopped tomato, cucumber and red onion. Chop the mint leaves and add them. Add salt and pepper to taste and a drizzle of oil and toss all together.</p>\n<p>In another bowl mash the crumbled feta with a fork and mix with the sour cream. Add a few grinds of pepper.</p>\n<p>To assemble: Spread some hummus as the base. Top with barley, salad and, lastly the beans. Drizzle with feta dressing.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2023-03-16 09:55:02','2023-03-29 16:42:22','<p>Hummus</p>\n<p>To make the hummus, drain the chick peas and keep a little of the liquid. Add the chick peas, tahini, garlic, lemon juice and oil to a blender or nutribullet. Blend until smooth, adding some of the reseved chick pea liquid if you need to. Add salt and black pepper to taste.</p>\n<p>If you cannot find Tahini you can use almond or cashew butter. Peanut butter will do in a pinch but preferably unsweetened peanut butter.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Za\'atar Substitute</p>\n<p>&frac14; cup sumac<br />3 tablespoon sesame seeds, toasted<br />2 tablespoons thyme<br />1 tablespoons oregano<br />1 tablespoon marjoram<br />1 teaspoon ground cumin, roasted<br />1 teaspoon ground coriander, roasted</p>\n<p>To enhance the flavour of your cumin, coriander and sesame seeds, place them in a small frypan and warm them through until aromatic. Allow to cool in a bowl.<br />Place everything in a small bowl and mix until well combined.<br />Transfer to a small glass jar and keep it in a dark part of your pantry.</p>'),(411,'eqnyqe','Pineapple Chicken',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2023-04-21 10:23:18','2023-04-21 10:23:18',NULL),(412,'tjwipw','One-Pan Chicken with Buttery Rice','This is a gem of a dish. Really easy to put together, super-satisfying to eat and also packed with some colourful veg. What more could we want?','None',5,40,'<p>Heat the oven to 180 C.</p>\n<p><br />You will need to use a large roasting pan, or oven dish.</p>\n<p>Tip the onion, red pepper, mushrooms, baby marrow and garlic cloves into the pan. Dot the butter around on top of the veg. Pop this in the oven (no need for it be completely heated) and let it cook for about 15 minutes, uncovered.</p>\n<p><br />While that is in the oven, put the chicken thighs into a bowl and pour the chicken spice mix over them. Use your hands to coat the chicken pieces in the spice. Mix the chicken stock powder with the amount of water on the label.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br />Remove pan from the oven and pour the rice over the veg and mix. Then pour the stock in and place the chicken pieces in the pan. Cover with a lid or foil.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br />Put it back in the oven with the foil or lid on for 20 minutes and then remove the foil or lid for the last 20 minutes.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br />Remove from the oven, fluff the rice up with a fork and serve immediately.&nbsp;</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2023-05-09 09:10:22','2023-05-16 10:25:15',NULL),(413,'jrykar','Easy Pineapple Chicken','An Asian-inspired, easy to make dish with  chicken, bell pepper, spring onions and pineapple, served on rice. This meal is quick to the table and can be adapted to a low carb diet by leaving out the rice and using sauteed cabbage as a base. (Note: the cabbage is not included in the kit whereas the rice is.)','None',5,25,'<p>Place the chicken strips in a bowl and pour the marinade over them. Let them marinate until you need them.</p>\n<p>Measue your rice and put double that amount of cold water with the rice and some salt in a pot with the lid on. Place on a high heat and when the pot is boiling vigourously, switch the heat off but let the pot stand without lifting the lid until you are ready to serve. Your rice will be done.</p>\n<p>Heat a bit of oil in a pan on a medium high heat and stir-fry your red pepper for 3 minutes. Add the spring onions (reserving a handful to garnish when serving) and stir-fry for 2 minutes more.</p>\n<p>Remove the chicken from the marinade and add the chicken to the pan, discarding excess marinade. Add the chilli flakes and stir together. Cook for 10 to 15 minutes, until the chicken is no longer pink in the middle.</p>\n<p>Add the pineapple chunks to the pan and cook for another 2 minutes.</p>\n<p>Mix the pineapple juice and the cornstarch in a bowl. Pour the mixture into the pan, stir well while bringing to the boil. Simmer until the sauce has thickened. This should take only a couple of minutes.</p>\n<p>Take the lid off your rice pot and fluff the rice up with a fork. Serve the chicken on a bed of rice, garnished with some spring onions. If you want a low carb meal, eat just the chicken or serve it on flash-fried shredded cabbage or perhaps some pumpkin mash. (Cabbage and pumpkin not included in the kit).</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2023-05-09 09:36:33','2023-05-09 10:23:54',NULL),(414,'wyaoam','Curtis Stone\'s Broccoli Pasta Bake','With its crispy topping of breadcrumbs, parmesan, butter and toasted walnuts this cheesy broccoli and pasta bake is superb - totally celebrity chef standard! The meal is rather decadent so please keep the dietician happy and accompany it with a salad as healthy eating is all about balance!','Lactose, gluten and nuts',10,15,'<p>Melt the butter. Use some of it to brush onto the inside of an oven proof dish big enought to take all the ingredients.</p>\n<p>In a small bowl, mix the breadcrumbs, walnuts, the rest of the melted butter and half the parmesan. Set aside.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<br />In a large saucepan of boiling salted water cook the pasta for 8 minutes. At 8 minutes add the broccoli and cook for 2 minutes more. Drain the pasta &amp; broccoli mixture, reserving 160 ml of the cooking liquid.<br /><br />Return the pasta mixture to the same pot, off the heat, with the cheddar and remaining parmesan, stirring until the cheese melts.</p>\n<p>In a bowl, whisk the cottage cheese with half of the reserved cooking liquid. Add cottage cheese mixture to the pasta mixture in the pot and stir until well combined and saucy. Stir in the remaining cooking liquid, a little at a time, to loosen the sauce.</p>\n<p>Heat your grill and have the oven rack about 12 cm away from the heat.</p>\n<p>Transfer the pasta mixture to the prepared baking dish and sprinkle with the breadcrumb mixture. Cook under the grill for 2-3 minutes. The topping should be golden brown and crispy. Serve immediately.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2023-05-10 09:49:16','2023-05-17 16:12:27',NULL),(415,'qryhbl','Kung Pao Tofu','This is a stir-fry of onion, garlic, ginger, red and green pepper, peanuts, a pinch of chilli flakes and cubed tofu, all pulled together with a sweet and spicy sauce. Serve in wraps. For those that are carb conscious, leave the wrap out and use flash-fried shredded cabbage as a base. Note: the cabbage is not included in the kit.','Nuts',5,20,'<p>Put the cornstarch and some salt and pepper to taste into a bowl and toss the tofu cubes gently in that mixture to coat it.</p>\n<p>Heat some oil on a medium high heat and fry the coated tofu cubes for 6 to 7 minutes, flipping them so that they are golden brown all over. When done remove from pan and set aside.</p>\n<p>In the same pan and on the same heat, add a little more oil and fry the chilli flakes, garlic and ginger for 1 minute. Add the onion and red and green pepper and fry for a further 3 minutes, stirring frequently.</p>\n<p>Shake the sauce in a jar or whisk in a bowl to blend and add it to the pan. It should thicken almost immediately. Add the tofu and stir gently until everything is well coated with the sauce. Stir in the peanuts and turn off the heat.</p>\n<p>Chop the fresh coriander. Heat the wraps in the microwave for 10 seconds to warm them. Place some Kung Pao Tofu on a wrap, garnish with coriander and wrap it, repeating for each serving.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2023-05-10 10:29:56','2023-05-10 10:55:59',NULL),(416,'knopop','Chickpea, Cranberry & Pecan Salad Wrap','Chickpeas, celery, green onion, cranberries and chopped pecan nuts are mixed into a lovely yoghurt, lemon and dill sauce with a dash of garlic. This salad is wonderful on its own or in a wrap (which we provide here) and makes a really great packed lunch with some leafy greens','Gluten, lactose and nuts',20,0,'<p>Add half the chickpeas to a bowl and mash them - they will still be chunky but not whole.</p>\n<p>Add the yoghurt, lemon juice, dried dill, garlic powder and spring onions. Stir until combined.</p>\n<p>Add the celery, cranberries, nuts and the whole chickpeas. Mix together, taste and season with salt and pepper to taste.</p>\n<p>If you think your mixture is too stiff, add a splash of milk.</p>\n<p>Warm the wraps for a few seconds in the microwave for easy wrapping (optional), place a bit of greenery on the wrap along with some chickpea salad. Roll up and enjoy!</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'2023-05-10 11:32:54','2023-05-18 08:12:39',NULL),(417,'arkpxc','Tomato Chickpea Stew with Ciabatta','A lovely cosy meal with the ciabatta hot from the oven, it has a hint of cumin and paprika along with ground and fresh coriander. A swirl of sour cream and chopped spinach is added at the end.','Gluten (ciabatta) and Lactose (cream)',5,20,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2023-05-18 08:19:34','2023-05-18 08:19:34',NULL),(418,'fnwdop','Cauliflower & Butterbean Curry',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2023-05-23 09:13:36','2023-05-23 09:13:36',NULL);
