INSERT INTO `notes` VALUES (1,'App\\Meals\\Meal',328,'Eggs','<p>Use 2 eggs for 4 people, 1 egg for 2 people and 1 egg for 1 person</p>','Lowly','2021-09-27 10:55:09','2021-09-27 10:55:09'),(2,'App\\Meals\\Meal',326,'Broccoli','<p>Separate the stems from the florets. Both should be chopped small and they should be packed separately</p>','Lowly','2021-09-27 11:56:08','2021-09-27 11:56:08'),(3,'App\\Meals\\Meal',327,'Flour','<p>I used stone ground bread flour instead of wholewheat flour and it worked perfectly. I wouldn\'t recommend cake flour though.</p>','Lowly','2021-09-28 09:39:32','2021-09-28 09:39:32'),(4,'App\\Meals\\Meal',319,'Chicken Marinade','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Chicken Marinade - enough for 2.5 kg chicken breasts</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">125 ml olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tsp salt&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&frac12; tsp black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&frac12; tsp paprika</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&frac12; tsp cumin</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&frac14; tsp cayenne pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp crushed garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">3 Tbsp onion flakes</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">3 Tbsp dried parsley</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">375 ml beer</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Place all ingredients except beer in a bowl and whisk well. Add the beer slowly.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you don\'t have beer use ginger ale.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Place chicken in a ziploc bag and pour the marinade in, keeping the air out as much as possible and letting the marinade cover the chicken.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Place in the fridge overnight or at least 1 hour.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The chicken can be frozen in the marinade. When you need it, thaw it out and pour off the marinade.</span></p>','Lowly','2021-09-28 15:29:55','2021-09-28 15:29:55'),(5,'App\\Meals\\Meal',38,'Pork Chops','<p>Pork loin chops are generally about 250 g each and then one per person is plenty. If the loin chops are small (need to ask FF), say about 150 g each, then you need 1.5 per person.</p>','Lowly','2021-09-29 11:02:25','2021-09-29 11:02:25'),(6,'App\\Meals\\Meal',329,'Enchilada Sauce','<p>30 ml olive oil<br />30 ml flour<br />1 &nbsp;400g tin chopped tomatoes<br />3 tsp chilli powder<br />1 tsp oregano<br />&frac12; &nbsp;tsp ground cumin<br />&frac12; &nbsp;tsp garlic powder<br />&frac12; tsp onion powder<br />3 tsp sugar<br />Salt &amp; black pepper to taste</p>\n<p>Heat the oil in a saucepan over medium heat and then whisk in the flour until there are no lumps. Cook for 1 minute.<br />Stir in tomatoes, oregano, all the spices and the sugar. Stir in 400 ml water and season with salt and pepper to taste.<br />Bring to the boil and then reduce heat to simmer for 10 minutes. The sauce should thicken.</p>\n<p>Can be stored in the fridge for 2 weeks.</p>','Lowly','2021-09-30 10:42:31','2021-09-30 10:42:31'),(7,'App\\Meals\\Meal',331,'Pork Chop Marinade','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">45 ml olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tsp black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">3 tsp crushed garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp cumin</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tsp dried rosemary</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tsp dried thyme</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">60 ml dry white wine</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mix all ingredients together well. This is enough to marinade 4 pork chops.</span></p>','Lowly','2021-10-13 10:13:24','2021-10-13 10:13:24'),(8,'App\\Meals\\Meal',319,'Chicken Marinade with Dry White Wine','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Chicken Marinade - enough for 2.5 kg chicken breasts</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">125 ml olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tsp salt&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&frac12; tsp black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&frac12; tsp paprika</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&frac12; tsp cumin</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&frac14; tsp cayenne pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp crushed garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">3 Tbsp onion flakes</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">3 Tbsp dried parsley</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">375 ml dry white wine</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Place all ingredients in a bowl and mix thoroughly</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Place chicken in a ziploc bag and pour the marinade in, keeping the air out as much as possible and letting the marinade cover the chicken.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Place in the fridge overnight or at least 1 hour.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The chicken can be frozen in the marinade. When you need it, thaw it out and pour off the marinade.</span></p>','Lowly','2021-10-13 10:21:57','2021-10-13 10:21:57'),(9,'App\\Meals\\Meal',316,'Chicken Marinade','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Chicken Marinade - enough for 2.5 kg chicken breasts</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">125 ml olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tsp salt&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&frac12; tsp black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&frac12; tsp paprika</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&frac12; tsp cumin</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&frac14; tsp cayenne pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp crushed garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">3 Tbsp onion flakes</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">3 Tbsp dried parsley</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">375 ml dry white wine</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Place all ingredients in a bowl and mix thoroughly</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Place chicken in a ziploc bag and pour the marinade in, keeping the air out as much as possible and letting the marinade cover the chicken.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Place in the fridge overnight or at least 1 hour.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The chicken can be frozen in the marinade. When you need it, thaw it out and pour off the marinade.</span></p>','Lowly','2021-10-13 10:22:57','2021-10-13 10:22:57'),(10,'App\\Meals\\Meal',331,'Packing Notes for the Pork','<p>Make the marinade as above. Let the pork chops lie in it for an hour in the fridge and then pack them, leaving as much marinade on them as possible. Then freeze.</p>','Lowly','2021-10-18 09:54:38','2021-10-18 09:54:38'),(11,'App\\Meals\\Meal',333,'Mayonnaise','<p>I used the Hellmans original mayo for this recipe because it has a consistency like sour cream and holds it\'s shape well for serving. I costed it with the Hellmans price.</p>','Lowly','2021-10-19 15:27:49','2021-10-19 15:27:49'),(12,'App\\Meals\\Meal',335,'Cooked Barley','<p>For 4 people, use 1 cup raw barley, 3 cups cold water and 3 tsp chicken stock powder.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>I suppose for a vegetarian dish you would use veg stock powder but I find chicken stock powder gives a nicer flavour and no one would be the wiser.</p>\n<p>Place in pot with a lid and let it come to the simmer and simmer until the liquid is gone.</p>','Lowly','2021-10-22 09:17:18','2021-10-22 09:17:18'),(13,'App\\Meals\\Meal',208,'Tangy Mayo Dressing','<p>The following mixed together makes 300 ml:</p>\n<p>125 ml cream or sour cream</p>\n<p>125 ml mayo</p>\n<p>60 ml white spriti vinegar</p>\n<p>15 ml sugar</p>','Lowly','2021-10-25 13:13:04','2021-10-25 13:13:04'),(14,'App\\Meals\\Meal',336,'Parmesan Sauce','<p>Add all the ingredients bundled under Parmesan Sauce, mix well and pack. Keep in fridge.</p>','Lowly','2021-10-26 08:52:59','2021-10-26 08:52:59'),(15,'App\\Meals\\Meal',147,'Tangy Mayo Dressing','<p>Mix the following to make approx 300 ml:</p>\n<p>125 ml mayo</p>\n<p>125 ml cream or sour cream</p>\n<p>60 ml white spirit vinegar</p>\n<p>15 ml sugar</p>','Lowly','2021-10-26 11:48:18','2021-10-26 11:48:18'),(16,'App\\Meals\\Meal',186,'Homemade Tomato Sauce','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">50 grams tomato paste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">240 g tub tomato puree&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">80 grams honey</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 Tablespoons apple cider vinegar</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 Tablespoons onion powder</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 teaspoon garlic powder</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 teaspoon salt</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 teaspoon cinnamon</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 teaspoon black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of nutmeg</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of chilli flakes</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Place all in a Nutribullet or blender and whizz until a smooth texture is reached.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This can be kept in the fridge for two weeks, probably longer because of the vinegar in it.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Makes about 400 ml</span></p>','Lowly','2021-10-26 12:17:49','2021-10-26 12:17:49'),(17,'App\\Meals\\Meal',243,'Lamb Chops','<p>It is nice to serve 2 chops per person so you need to ask for the smallest type of lamb chop. It may be the rib chops but you need to explain to FF why we need to know and which ones to get.</p>','Lowly','2021-10-26 12:36:32','2021-10-26 12:36:32'),(18,'App\\Meals\\Meal',325,'Homemade BBQ Sauce','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">10 ml olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tsp crushed garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">3 Tbsp onion flakes or 1 Tbsp onion powder</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">125 ml apple cider vinegar</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">125 ml tomato sauce</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">125 ml water</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">125 ml sugar</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 Tbsp mustard</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 Tbsp Worcestershire Sauce</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp chilli powder</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 Tbsp cornstarch mixed with 2 Tbsp water</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heat oil and fry the garlic for 1 minute before adding all the other ingredients. Let the sauce cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Should make approx 400 ml</span></p>','Lowly','2021-11-02 11:15:27','2021-11-02 11:15:27'),(19,'App\\Meals\\Meal',339,'Cheese Sauce Notes','<p>For the ingredients for the cheese sauce, halve the quantity for both two people and for one person. I\'m not sure if dividing by 4 for one person will work.</p>','Lowly','2021-11-02 11:19:29','2021-11-02 11:19:29'),(20,'App\\Meals\\Meal',206,'Notes for Mealie Bread','<p>For 4 people follow recipe.</p>\n<p>For 1 and for 2 people halve the recipe. I don\'t think it\'s worth trying to quarter it.</p>','Lowly','2021-11-12 10:59:48','2021-11-12 10:59:48'),(21,'App\\Meals\\Meal',255,'Egg portions','<p>Send one egg to everyone, whether they are cooking for 1, 2 or 4. I have adjusted the instructions.</p>','Lowly','2021-11-15 11:29:29','2021-11-15 11:29:29'),(22,'App\\Meals\\Meal',213,'Bobotie Custard Topping','<p>For 2 people send 2 eggs and 95 ml of milk.</p>\n<p>For 1 person send 1 egg and 50 ml of milk.</p>','Lowly','2021-11-29 11:55:04','2021-11-29 11:55:04'),(23,'App\\Meals\\Meal',225,'Seasoned Flour','<p>Send this in a brown bag big enough for them to add chicken pieces and shake to coat them.</p>','Lowly','2021-11-29 12:11:34','2021-11-29 12:11:34'),(24,'App\\Meals\\Meal',101,'Rocket','<p>If no rocket, baby spinach can be substituted.</p>','Lowly','2021-11-30 08:31:01','2021-11-30 08:31:01'),(25,'App\\Meals\\Meal',131,'Pulled Pork in BBQ Sauce','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">10 ml olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tsp crushed garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">3 Tbsp onion flakes or 1 Tbsp onion powder</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">125 ml apple cider vinegar</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">125 ml tomato sauce</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">125 ml water</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">125 ml sugar</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 Tbsp mustard</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 Tbsp Worcestershire Sauce</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp chilli powder</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 Tbsp cornstarch mixed with 2 Tbsp water</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heat oil and fry the garlic for 1 minute before adding all the other ingredients. Let the sauce cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Slow cook your pork in the above.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Remember if the bone is in then 2,5 raw pork shoulder equals 1.2 kg pulled pork.</span></p>','Lowly','2021-11-30 10:55:28','2021-11-30 10:55:28'),(26,'App\\Meals\\Meal',200,'Balsamic Vinegar Dressing','<p>For 75 ml (4 people):</p>\n<p>3 Tbsp olive oil</p>\n<p>1 Tbsp Balsamic Vinegar</p>\n<p>1 Tbsp honey</p>\n<p>Mix and shake vigourously.</p>','Lowly','2021-11-30 11:55:30','2021-11-30 11:55:30'),(27,'App\\Meals\\Meal',349,'Par Boiling Baby Potatoes','<p>Leave skins on.</p>\n<p>Place in pot with salt. Put the lid on. When pot is boiling time 10 minutes and then take off and drain.</p>\n<p>When cool pack and put in fridge.</p>\n<p>Make this meal the first one that people use.</p>','Lowly','2022-01-13 10:54:17','2022-01-13 10:54:17'),(28,'App\\Meals\\Meal',350,'Lemongrass','<p>Apack of lemongrass fromSpar usually has one long stalk or 2 shorter stalks. This is the amount for 4 people.</p>\n<p>Top and tail the stalk(s). Take the outer tough skin off the stalk(s).</p>\n<p>Bash the stalk(s) with something heavy to break it up.</p>\n<p>Then finely chop with a sharp knife. You now have minced lemongrass!</p>','Lowly','2022-01-20 14:33:15','2022-01-20 14:33:15'),(29,'App\\Meals\\Meal',203,'Tangy Mayo Dressing','<p>125 ml cream or sour cream</p>\n<p>125 ml mayonnaise</p>\n<p>60 ml white vinegar</p>\n<p>15 ml sugar</p>\n<p>1/2 tsp salt</p>\n<p>Mix well together - this batch makes 250 ml.</p>','Lowly','2022-01-20 14:36:20','2022-01-20 14:36:20'),(30,'App\\Meals\\Meal',203,'Parboiled Potatoes','<p>If we do not parboil the customer\'s cooking time is too long.</p>\n<p>Bring a pot of salted water to the boil, put the potatoes in and time 20 minutes from this point.</p>\n<p>When the potatoes are cold, wrap them in foil and keep in the fridge. This should be done on the Monday and this meal should be marked as the first meal.</p>','Lowly','2022-01-20 14:52:35','2022-01-20 14:52:35'),(31,'App\\Meals\\Meal',203,'Parboiling Additional Note','<p>Please rub the parboiled potatoes with olive oil before wrapping them in foil.</p>','Lowly','2022-01-20 14:56:48','2022-01-20 14:56:48'),(32,'App\\Meals\\Meal',228,'Homemade Tomato Sauce','<p>4 Tbsp tomato paste (2 sachets)</p>\n<p>1 x 410g tin tomato puree</p>\n<p>80 g sugar</p>\n<p>60 ml apple cider vinegar</p>\n<p>2 Tbsp onion powder</p>\n<p>1 tsp garlic powder</p>\n<p>1 tsp salt</p>\n<p>1 tsp cinnamon</p>\n<p>pinch of nutmeg</p>\n<p>pinch of chilli flakes</p>\n<p>Mix all in the nutrbullet and store in the fridge. This makes 400 ml.</p>','Lowly','2022-01-20 15:50:20','2022-01-20 15:50:20'),(33,'App\\Meals\\Meal',351,'Naan','<p>I\'ve worked on R15 for a plain naan at Tandoor, so R60 for Naan. If you need to get grom Woolworths or if Tandoor prices have increased, please adjust the number you send.</p>','Lowly','2022-01-21 15:56:11','2022-01-21 15:56:11'),(34,'App\\Meals\\Meal',353,'Eggs','<p>Send 2 eggs for 4 people, 1 egg for 2 people and 1 egg for 1 person.</p>','Lowly','2022-02-09 13:41:38','2022-02-09 13:41:38'),(35,'App\\Meals\\Meal',355,'Sourdough Loaf','<p>I costed this with the Woolworths Crushed Wheat Sourdough loaf at R43.00.</p>','Lowly','2022-02-18 10:32:29','2022-02-18 10:32:29'),(36,'App\\Meals\\Meal',356,'Hot Chilli Paste','<p>They suggest sambal oelek which I found online at Woolworths for R70 a jar - I used that for the costing.</p>\n<p>It is very easy to make in a nutribullet if you can find fresh red chillies.</p>','Lowly','2022-02-23 10:12:29','2022-02-23 10:12:29'),(37,'App\\Meals\\Meal',356,'Sambal Oelek Recipe','<p>They suggest sambal oelek which I found online at Woolworths for R70 a jar - I used that for the costing.</p>\n<p>It is very easy to make in a nutribullet if you can find fresh red chillies.</p>\n<header class=\"section__header \">\n<div class=\"loc section-header\">\n<div id=\"mntl-block_5-0\" class=\"comp section-header--ingredients mntl-block\">\n<h2 id=\"text-block_2-0\" class=\"comp section__title text-block\">Ingredients</h2>\n<button id=\"relish-save_2-0\" class=\"comp button--save-recipe relish-save mntl-relish-save-btn mntl-button\" data-tracking-container=\"true\">Save Recipe</button></div>\n</div>\n</header>\n<div class=\"loc section-content section__content \">\n<div id=\"structured-ingredients_1-0\" class=\"comp structured-ingredients\">\n<ul class=\"structured-ingredients__list text-passage\">\n<li class=\"structured-ingredients__list-item\">\n<p><span data-ingredient-quantity=\"true\">1</span>&nbsp;<span data-ingredient-unit=\"true\">pound</span>&nbsp;hot red chilies, such as red jalape&ntilde;os, fresnos, or&nbsp;<span data-ingredient-name=\"true\">red serranos</span></p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"structured-ingredients__list-item\">\n<p><span data-ingredient-quantity=\"true\">2</span>&nbsp;<span data-ingredient-unit=\"true\">tablespoons</span>&nbsp;<span data-ingredient-name=\"true\">rice vinegar</span></p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"structured-ingredients__list-item\">\n<p><span data-ingredient-quantity=\"true\">1</span>&nbsp;<span data-ingredient-unit=\"true\">tablespoon</span>&nbsp;<span data-ingredient-name=\"true\">salt.&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>','Lowly','2022-02-23 10:15:19','2022-02-23 10:15:19'),(38,'App\\Meals\\Meal',354,'Honey Soy Roasted Cashew Nuts','<p>100 g raw cashews into an oven proof dish. Drizzle with 1 tsp of honey and one tsp soy sauce. Mix to coat nicely. Roast at 180 degrees C for 10 minutes but watch carefully.</p>','Lowly','2022-03-02 11:58:39','2022-03-02 11:58:39'),(39,'App\\Meals\\Meal',357,'Spicy Moroccan Carrots','<p>500 g carrots peeled and sliced into rounds</p>\n<p>2 cups water</p>\n<p>2 tsp crushed garlic</p>\n<p>2 Tbsp olive oil</p>\n<p>1/2 tsp paprika</p>\n<p>pinch of cayenne pepper</p>\n<p>salt and black pepper</p>\n<p>1 Tbsp wine vinegar (I used red, but I\'m sure white wine vinegar will work)</p>\n<p>1/2 tsp ground cumin</p>\n<p>Combine carrots, water, garlic, oil, paprika, cayenne pepper, salt and black pepper in a shallow pan. Bring to a boil over a medium to high heat and cook until carrots are tender and moisture has evaporated. Aslight bit of moisture left is fine.</p>\n<p>Stir the vinegar and the ground cumin through the carrots and allow to cool before storing in the fridge.</p>','Lowly','2022-03-03 11:37:24','2022-03-03 11:37:24'),(40,'App\\Meals\\Meal',352,'How to Make Self Raising Flour','<p>1 cup all purpose or cake flour</p>\n<p>1,5 teaspoons baking powder</p>\n<p>0,25 teaspoons salt</p>\n<p>Mix together well.</p>','Lowly','2022-03-10 10:36:54','2022-03-10 10:36:54'),(41,'App\\Meals\\Meal',85,'How to Make Self Raising Flour','<p>1 cup of flour (in this case brown)</p>\n<p>1,5 teaspoons baking powder</p>\n<p>0,25 teaspoons salt</p>\n<p>Mix to gether well.</p>','Lowly','2022-03-10 10:54:09','2022-03-10 10:54:09'),(42,'App\\Meals\\Meal',361,'Marinating the Paneer','<p>This is for 500g paneer but I want it to stretch to 800g.</p>\n<p>Mix together:</p>\n<p>3 ml salt, 3 ml chilli powder, 3 ml ground coriander, 2 tsp crushed garlic, 2 tsp minced ginger and 1 Tbsp plain yoghurt.</p>\n<p>Gently place the paneer cubes in this mixture and roll them around to coat them.</p>\n<p>Pack and leave in fridge.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Lowly','2022-03-17 09:30:43','2022-03-17 09:30:43'),(43,'App\\Meals\\Meal',154,'Self Raising Whole wheat flour','<p>1 cup whole wheat flour</p>\n<p>1,5 tsp baking powder</p>\n<p>0,5 tsp salt</p>\n<p>Mix together</p>','Lowly','2022-03-30 16:15:42','2022-03-30 16:15:42'),(44,'App\\Meals\\Meal',282,'Brown Rice','<p>As we are cooking the brown rice on the Monday, this meal should be eaten 1st.</p>\n<p>The rice is fine in the fridge for four days.</p>','Lowly','2022-04-11 10:42:36','2022-04-11 10:42:36'),(45,'App\\Meals\\Meal',326,'Bread Rolls','<p>These are on a separate recipe card. Please add manually to orders to get the shopping list right.</p>','Lowly','2022-05-12 16:30:20','2022-05-12 16:30:20'),(46,'App\\Meals\\Meal',310,'Turkish Dressing','<p>125ml olive oil</p>\n<p>120 ml lemon juice</p>\n<p>10 g fresh mint leaves chopped</p>\n<p>1 tsp crushed garlic</p>\n<p>Salt and black pepper to taste</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Mix all together very well.</p>','Lowly','2022-05-12 18:09:53','2022-05-12 18:09:53'),(47,'App\\Meals\\Meal',158,'BBQ Sauce','<p>10 ml olive oil</p>\n<p>1 tsp crushed garlic</p>\n<p>1 Tbsp onion powder</p>\n<p>125 ml apple cider vinegar</p>\n<p>125 ml tomato sauce</p>\n<p>125 ml water</p>\n<p>125 ml sugar</p>\n<p>2 Tbsp mustard</p>\n<p>1 Tbsp Worcestershire Sauce</p>\n<p>2 tsp chilli powder</p>\n<p>2 Tbsp cornstarch mixed with 2 Tbsp water</p>\n<p>Heat oil and fry garlic for 1 minute. Then add all other ingredients and stir together well. Cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.</p>\n<p>This makes approx 400 ml</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Lowly','2022-05-13 14:52:11','2022-05-13 14:52:11'),(48,'App\\Meals\\Meal',364,'Ciabatta Loaf','<p>Recipe costed on the R30 loaf from Spar.</p>\n<p>Seems a waste to unwrap and rewrap - send in original wrapper?</p>\n<p>Check use by date.</p>','Lowly','2022-06-10 08:43:45','2022-06-10 08:43:45'),(49,'App\\Meals\\Meal',275,'Cooked Brown Rice','<p>Please make on the Monday because rice can go sour after a few days in the fridge. Maybe suggest it as first meal.</p>','Lowly','2022-06-12 08:06:43','2022-06-12 08:06:43'),(50,'App\\Meals\\Meal',218,'Passata','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Passata</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ingredients:</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 large onion</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp ground black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS tomato paste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Method:</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</span></p>','Lowly','2022-06-23 09:27:00','2022-06-23 09:27:00'),(51,'App\\Meals\\Meal',373,'Fresh thyme','<p>This is key to the flavour of this dish. It can be chopped beforehand as it is fairly woody with tough leaves.</p>','Lowly','2022-06-27 07:06:14','2022-06-27 07:06:14'),(52,'App\\Meals\\Meal',366,'Ciabatta Loaf','<p>Recipe costed on the R30 loaf from Spar.</p>\n<p>Seems a waste to unwrap and rewrap - send in original wrapper?</p>\n<p>Check use by date.</p>','Lowly','2022-07-09 09:17:08','2022-07-09 09:17:08'),(53,'App\\Meals\\Meal',15,'Marinara Recipe','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 onion, chopped</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp crushed garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tin chopped tomatoes</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 Tbsp tomato paste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tsp sugar</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tsp dried basil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tsp dried oregano</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">salt and pepper to taste</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fry the onion for 3 minutes. Add the garlic and fry for 1 minute more.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add the tomatoes and the tomato paste. the sugar, the basil, and the oregano.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bring to a simmer for 20 minutes or until the consistency and taste is good.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add salt and pepper if need be.</span></p>','Lowly','2022-07-09 09:38:25','2022-07-09 09:38:25'),(54,'App\\Meals\\Meal',58,'Passata Recipe','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Passata</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ingredients:</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 large onion</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp ground black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS tomato paste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Method:</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</span></p>','Lowly','2022-07-09 17:17:31','2022-07-09 17:17:31'),(55,'App\\Meals\\Meal',171,'Passata Recipe','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Passata</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ingredients:</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 large onion</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp ground black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS tomato paste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Method:</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</span></p>','Lowly','2022-07-09 18:09:18','2022-07-09 18:09:18'),(56,'App\\Meals\\Meal',113,'Passata Recipe','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Passata</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ingredients:</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 large onion</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp ground black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS tomato paste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Method:</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</span></p>','Lowly','2022-07-09 18:12:04','2022-07-09 18:12:04'),(57,'App\\Meals\\Meal',114,'Cheese Sauce Recipe','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">BASIC BECHAMEL SAUCE WITH CHEESE</span></p>\n<p><br /><br /><br /></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You will need:</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">60 grams butter</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">50 ml flour</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 cups full cream milk</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">100 grams of cheddar grated</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 tsp salt or to taste (start with half)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">pinch of nutmeg</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Instructions:</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Melt the butter and stir in the flour with a wooden spoon until a smooth paste forms. Stir while this cooks for a minute.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add the milk in four dollops, stirring out lumps in between each addition. Keep a whisk on hand for beating smooth if necessary. Let the sauce come to a simmer and simmer for about 4 minutes while it thickens. Make sure to stir constantly to avoid lumps. Add salt and nutmeg. When sauce is the right consistency, take off the heat and stir in the cheese.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This makes 500ml cheese sauce.</span></p>','Lowly','2022-07-09 18:23:00','2022-07-09 18:23:00'),(58,'App\\Meals\\Meal',91,'Weight of a Brinjal','<p>One medium brinjal is about 250 grams</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Lowly','2022-07-09 18:43:22','2022-07-09 18:43:22'),(59,'App\\Meals\\Meal',252,'Passata Recipe','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Passata</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ingredients:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 large onion</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp ground black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS tomato paste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Method:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</span></p>','Lowly','2022-07-16 09:46:22','2022-07-16 09:46:22'),(60,'App\\Meals\\Meal',30,'Italian Dressing','<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Ingredients</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Makes approx 250 ml</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>1/2 cup extra-virgin olive oil</p>\n<p>1/4 cup white wine vinegar OR red wine vinegar OR a combo of the two</p>\n<p>2 tablespoons water</p>\n<p>1 to 2 teaspoons honey</p>\n<p>1 teaspoon freshly squeezed lemon juice</p>\n<p>3 tablespoons freshly grated Parmesan</p>\n<p>3/4 teaspoon garlic salt</p>\n<p>3/4 teaspoon dried parsley</p>\n<p>3/4 teaspoon dried basil</p>\n<p>1/8 teaspoon dried oregano</p>\n<p>Pinch of red pepper flakes</p>\n<p>Freshly ground black pepper to taste</p>\n<p>Instructions</p>\n<p>1. Measure all ingredients into a jar with a tight-fitting lid. Shake vigorously until well-blended and emulsified. Taste and adjust seasonings, adding more salt and pepper if necessary. (Alternatively, you may whisk ingredients together in a bowl, process ingredients in a mini food processor, or blend them in a blender.) Store leftovers in a sealed container in the refrigerator; allow to come to room temperature and shake well before using.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>','Lowly','2022-07-16 11:21:54','2022-07-16 11:21:54'),(61,'App\\Meals\\Meal',226,'Tomato Sauce Recipe','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">5-Minute Tomato Sauce</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">50 grams tomato paste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">240 g tub tomato puree&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">80 grams honey</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 Tablespoons apple cider vinegar</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 Tablespoons onion powder</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 teaspoon garlic powder</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 teaspoon salt</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 teaspoon cinnamon</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 teaspoon black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of nutmeg</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of chilli flakes</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Place all in a Nutribullet or blender and whizz until a smooth texture is reached.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This can be kept in the fridge for two weeks, probably longer because of the vinegar in it.</span></p>','Lowly','2022-07-17 09:31:23','2022-07-17 09:31:23'),(62,'App\\Meals\\Meal',90,'Passata Recipe','<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ingredients:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 large onion</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp ground black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS tomato paste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Method:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</span></p>','Lowly','2022-07-17 16:42:11','2022-07-17 16:42:11'),(63,'App\\Meals\\Meal',236,'How to Caramelise Onions','<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Makes 500 ml</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Several (3 to 5 depending on sizd) medium or large onions, yellow, white, or red</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Extra virgin olive oil</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Butter, optional</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Kosher salt</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Sugar, optional</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Balsamic vinegar, optional</p>\n<p>Method</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Cut the onions root to tip:<br />Slice 1/2-inch off the stem ends of the onions and the roots off of the root end. Place the onions cut side down on</p>\n<p>the cutting board. Cut them in half through the root end. Peel back the peels from the onions.</p>\n<p>Lay the onions cut side down and make angled cuts into each onion, aimed at the center, cutting almost all the way, but not completely through the root end. Make the cuts to your desired level of thickness.</p>\n<p>The root end will help hold the onion together as you cut it, making it easier to cut. Then cut a V in the root end to cut out the tough root holding the slices together.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 2\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"section\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Heat the olive oil and add the onion:<br />Use a wide, thick-bottomed sauté pan for maximum pan contact with the onions. Coat the bottom of the pan with olive oil, or a mixture of olive oil and butter, (about 1 teaspoon per onion).</p>\n<p>Heat the pan on medium high heat until the oil is shimmering. Add the onion slices and stir to coat the onions with the oil. Spread the onions out evenly over the pan and let cook, stirring occasionally.</p>\n<p>Depending on how strong your stovetop burner is you may need to reduce the heat to medium or medium low to prevent the onions from burning or drying out.</p>\n<p>After 10 minutes, sprinkle some salt over the onions, and if you want, you can add some sugar to help with the caramelization process. (I add only about a teaspoon of sugar for 5 onions, you can add more.) One trick to keeping the onions from drying out as they cook is to add a little water to the pan.</p>\n<p>Stir the onions every few minutes:<br />Let the onions cook for 30 minutes to 1 hour more, stirring every few minutes. As soon as the onions start stickingto the pan, let them stick a little and brown, but then stir them before they burn.</p>\n<p>The trick is to leave them alone enough to brown (if you stir them too often, they won\'t brown), but not so long so that they burn. After the first 20 to 30 minutes you may want to lower the stove temperature a little, and add a little more oil, if you find the onions are verging on burning.</p>\n<p>A metal spatula will help you scrape up the browned bits from the bottom of the pan as the caramelization proceeds. As the onions cook down, you may find you need to scrape the pan every minute, instead of every few minutes.</p>\n<p>Continue to cook and scrape, cook and scrape, until the onions are a rich, browned color. At the end of the cooking process you might want to add a little balsamic vinegar or wine to help deglaze the pan and bring some additional flavor to the onions.</p>\n<p>Store refrigerated for several days in an air-tight container.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>','Lowly','2022-07-19 07:02:39','2022-07-19 07:02:39'),(64,'App\\Meals\\Meal',67,'Passata Recipe','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Passata</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ingredients:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 large onion</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp ground black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS tomato paste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Method:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</span></p>','Lowly','2022-08-05 10:09:58','2022-08-05 10:09:58'),(65,'App\\Meals\\Meal',26,'Passata Recipe','<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Passata</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ingredients:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 large onion</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS olive oil</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 tsp ground black pepper</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 TBS tomato paste</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Method:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</span></p>','Lowly','2022-08-05 10:13:08','2022-08-05 10:13:08'),(66,'App\\Meals\\Meal',136,'Italian Seasoning','<p>2 tablespoons dried basil<br />2 tablespoons dried oregano<br />1 tablespoons dried rosemary<br />2 tablespoons dried parsley<br />1 tablespoon dried thyme<br />1 tablespoon red chili flakes<br />1 teaspoon garlic powder</p>\n<p><br />1. Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.<br />2. Pour into an air tight container and store in a cool dark place for up to 6 months.</p>','Lowly','2022-08-15 15:52:07','2022-08-15 15:52:07'),(67,'App\\Meals\\Meal',298,'Marinara Sauce','<p>Marinara Sauce</p>\n<p>1 onion, chopped<br />2 tsp crushed garlic<br />1 tin chopped tomatoes<br />1 Tbsp tomato paste<br />1 tsp sugar<br />1 tsp dried basil<br />1 tsp dried oregano<br />salt and pepper to taste</p>\n<p>Fry the onion for 3 minutes. Add the garlic and fry for 1 minute more.<br />Add the tomatoes and the tomato paste, the sugar, the basil, and the oregano.<br />Bring to a simmer for 20 minutes or until the consistency and taste is good.<br />Add salt and pepper if need be.</p>','Lowly','2022-08-21 16:30:04','2022-08-21 16:30:04'),(68,'App\\Meals\\Meal',254,'Tex Mex Seasoning','<ul class=\"ckdc-recipe-ingredients-list\">\n<li><span class=\"ckdc-ingredient plural-us plural-metric\"><span class=\"ingredient-value ingredient-value-metric\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" data-servings=\"{&quot;1&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&lt;sup&gt;1&lt;\\/sup&gt;&frasl;&lt;sub&gt;8&lt;\\/sub&gt; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;2&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&frac14; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;3&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;\\/sup&gt;&frasl;&lt;sub&gt;5&lt;\\/sub&gt; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;4&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&frac12; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&quot;:&quot;plural-metric&quot;,&quot;remove&quot;:&quot;empty singular-metric&quot;},&quot;5&quot;:{&quot;value&quot;:&quot;&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;\\/sup&gt;&frasl;&lt;sub&gt;3&lt;\\/sub&gt; tbsp&quot;,&quot;set&q