l flour<br />2 cups full cream milk<br />1 tsp salt or to taste (start with half)<br />pinch of nutmeg</p>\n<p>Instructions:</p>\n<p>Melt the butter and stir in the flour with a wooden spoon until a smooth paste forms. Stir while this cooks for a minute.<br />Add the milk in four dollops, stirring out lumps in between each addition. Keep a whisk on hand for beating smooth if necessary. Let the sauce come to a simmer and simmer for about 4 minutes while it thickens. Make sure to stir constantly to avoid lumps. Add salt and nutmeg. When the sauce is the right consistency, take off the heat.</p>\n<p>This makes 500ml sauce.</p>','Lowly','2022-08-25 11:44:24','2022-08-25 11:44:24'),(70,'App\\Meals\\Meal',153,'Cheese Sauce','<p>CHEESE SAUCE</p>\n<p>You will need:</p>\n<p>60 grams butter<br />50 ml flour<br />2 cups full cream milk<br />100 grams of cheddar grated<br />1 tsp salt or to taste (start with half)<br />pinch of nutmeg</p>\n<p>Instructions:</p>\n<p>Melt the butter and stir in the flour with a wooden spoon until a smooth paste forms. Stir while this cooks for a minute.<br />Add the milk in four dollops, stirring out lumps in between each addition. Keep a whisk on hand for beating smooth if necessary. Let the sauce come to a simmer and simmer for about 4 minutes while it thickens. Make sure to stir constantly to avoid lumps. Add salt and nutmeg. When the sauce is the right consistency, take off the heat and stir in the cheese.</p>\n<p>This makes 500ml cheese sauce.</p>','Lowly','2022-08-26 11:50:12','2022-08-26 11:50:12'),(71,'App\\Meals\\Meal',6,'Marinara Recipe','<p>Marinara Sauce</p>\n<p>1 onion, chopped<br />2 tsp crushed garlic<br />1 tin chopped tomatoes<br />1 Tbsp tomato paste<br />1 tsp sugar<br />1 tsp dried basil<br />1 tsp dried oregano<br />salt and pepper to taste</p>\n<p>Fry the onion for 3 minutes. Add the garlic and fry for 1 minute more.<br />Add the tomatoes and the tomato paste, the sugar, the basil, and the oregano.<br />Bring to a simmer for 20 minutes or until the consistency and taste is good.<br />Add salt and pepper if need be.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Lowly','2022-08-26 11:58:08','2022-08-26 11:58:08'),(72,'App\\Meals\\Meal',6,'Tangy Mayo Dressing','<p>Tangy Mayo Dressing</p>\n<p><br />1/2 cup cream or sour cream<br />1/2 cup mayo<br />1/4 cup white spirit vinegar<br />1 TBS sugar<br />1/2 tsp salt</p>\n<p><br />Mix all together well.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Lowly','2022-08-26 12:01:11','2022-08-26 12:01:11'),(73,'App\\Meals\\Meal',379,'Tandoori Spice Mix','<p>Tandoor Spice Mix</p>\n<p>1 teaspoon ground ginger<br />&frac12; teaspoon ground cumin<br />1 teaspoon ground coriander<br />1 teaspoon paprika<br />&frac12; teaspoon turmeric<br />&frac12; teaspoon salt<br />&frac14; teaspoon cayenne pepper<br />&frac14; teaspoon garlic powder<br />&frac14; teaspoon nutmeg<br />&frac14; teaspoon ground cloves</p>\n<p>Mix all together. Makes 1,5 tablespoons approx.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Lowly','2022-09-02 10:11:52','2022-09-02 10:11:52'),(74,'App\\Meals\\Meal',5,'Lemon Mint Dressing','<p>1/2 cup extra-virgin olive oil&nbsp;<br />1/2 cup lemon juice (about 2 lemons)</p>\n<p>1/4 cup packed fresh mint leaves&nbsp;<br />3 tablespoons honey&nbsp;<br />1 tablespoon Dijon mustard&nbsp;<br />2 cloves garlic, roughly chopped&nbsp;<br />1/4 teaspoon fine sea salt&nbsp;<br />10 twists of freshly ground black pepper</p>\n<p>Mix well together. Keeps for at least a week in the fridge.</p>','Lowly','2022-09-26 15:20:17','2022-09-26 15:20:17'),(75,'App\\Meals\\Meal',217,'Lemon Mint Dressing','<p>1/2 cup extra-virgin olive oil&nbsp;<br />1/2 cup lemon juice&nbsp;</p>\n<p>1/4 cup packed fresh mint leaves&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />3 tablespoons honey&nbsp;<br />1 tablespoon Dijon mustard&nbsp;<br />2 cloves garlic, roughly chopped&nbsp;<br />1/4 teaspoon fine sea salt&nbsp;<br />10 twists of freshly ground black pepper</p>\n<p>Mix together well. This dressing keeps in the fridge for a week.</p>','Lowly','2022-09-26 17:27:09','2022-09-26 17:27:09'),(76,'App\\Meals\\Meal',89,'Tex Mex Seasoning','<p>1 tbsp chili powder<br />2 tsp paprika powder<br />2 tsp ground cumin<br />1 tsp garlic powder<br />1 tsp onion powder<br />1&frasl;2 tsp chili flakes<br />1&frasl;2 tsp dried oregano<br />1&frasl;2 tsp ground black pepper<br />1 pinch ground cinnamon 1 pinch ground cloves<br />1 tbsp sea salt (optional)</p>\n<p>Add all ingredients to a bowl and stir until thoroughly blended. Pour into a jar with a tight-fitting lid.<br />If you use whole seeds, grind in a grinder either in advance or when cooking.<br />Keep the spices in a dark, dry and cool/room temperature place. Small tin cans are great.<br />Make a big batch to last for 4&ndash;6 months; after this the spices will lose some flavor and color. They won\'t go bad, but will just be less powerful.</p>','Lowly','2022-10-18 10:35:38','2022-10-18 10:35:38'),(77,'App\\Meals\\Meal',388,'Cheese Sauce','<p>You will need:</p>\n<p>60 grams butter<br />50 ml flour<br />2 cups full cream milk<br />100 grams of cheddar grated<br />1 tsp salt or to taste (start with half)<br />pinch of nutmeg</p>\n<p>Instructions:</p>\n<p>Melt the butter and stir in the flour with a wooden spoon until a smooth paste forms. Stir while this cooks for a minute.<br />Add the milk in four dollops, stirring out lumps in between each addition. Keep a whisk on hand for beating smooth if necessary. Let the sauce come to a simmer and simmer for about 4 minutes while it thickens. Make sure to stir constantly to avoid lumps. Add salt and nutmeg. When the sauce is the right consistency, take off the heat and stir in the cheese.</p>\n<p>This makes 500ml cheese sauce.</p>\n<p>TOP TIP: Heat the milk in the microwave and add it warm to the butter/flour paste - it\'s quicker and easier. Do not boil the milk, just warm it.</p>','Lowly','2022-10-24 10:34:33','2022-10-24 10:34:33'),(78,'App\\Meals\\Meal',45,'Passata','<p>Passata</p>\n<p>Ingredients:</p>\n<p>4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped<br />1 large onion<br />2 TBS olive oil<br />4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic<br />8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)<br />1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste<br />2 tsp ground black pepper<br />2 TBS tomato paste<br />Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</p>\n<p>Method:</p>\n<p>Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.<br />Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.<br />Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.<br />Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.<br />Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</p>','Lowly','2022-10-24 10:39:48','2022-10-24 10:39:48'),(79,'App\\Meals\\Meal',155,'Barbecue Sauce','<p>Barbecue Sauce</p>\n<p>10 ml olive oil<br />1 tsp crushed garlic<br />3 Tbsp onion flakes or 1 Tbsp onion powder<br />125 ml apple cider vinegar<br />125 ml tomato sauce<br />125 ml water<br />125 ml sugar<br />2 Tbsp mustard<br />1 Tbsp Worcestershire Sauce<br />2 tsp chilli powder<br />2 Tbsp cornstarch mixed with 2 Tbsp water</p>\n<p>Heat oil and fry the garlic for 1 minute before adding all the other ingredients. Let the sauce cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.</p>\n<p>Should make approx 400 ml</p>','Lowly','2022-10-24 11:33:33','2022-10-24 11:33:33'),(80,'App\\Meals\\Meal',139,'Passata','<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong><br />4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped<br />1 large onion<br />2 TBSP olive oil<br />4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic<br />8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)<br />1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste<br />2 tsp ground black pepper<br />2 TBSP tomato paste<br />Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</p>\n<p><br /><strong>Method:</strong><br />Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.<br />Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.<br />Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.<br />Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.<br />Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</p>','Lowly','2022-11-02 10:47:51','2022-11-02 10:47:51'),(81,'App\\Meals\\Meal',138,'Marinara Sauce','<p>1 onion, finely chopped<br />1 tsp crushed garlic<br />a little oil<br />2 tbsp tomato paste (1 sachet)<br />2 tbsp balsamic vinegar&nbsp;<br />1 tin crushed tomato<br />1 tsp dried basil<br />1 tsp dried oregano&nbsp;<br />&frac12; tsp salt<br />Pepper, to taste</p>\n<p>Fry the onions in the oil until soft.<br />Add tomato paste, garlic, vinegar, crushed tomato and bring to a boil.<br />Add the herbs, salt and pepper.<br />Let it simmer on low for 20 minutes plus.</p>','Lowly','2022-11-02 10:55:05','2022-11-02 10:55:05'),(82,'App\\Meals\\Meal',19,'Marinara','<p>1 onion, finely chopped<br />1 tsp crushed garlic<br />a little oil<br />2 tbsp tomato paste (1 sachet)<br />2 tbsp balsamic vinegar&nbsp;<br />1 tin crushed tomato<br />1 tsp dried basil<br />1 tsp dried oregano&nbsp;<br />&frac12; tsp salt<br />Pepper, to taste</p>\n<p>Fry the onions in the oil until soft.<br />Add tomato paste, garlic, vinegar, crushed tomato and bring to a boil.<br />Add the herbs, salt and pepper.<br />Let it simmer on low for 20 minutes plus.</p>','Lowly','2022-11-02 11:20:07','2022-11-02 11:20:07'),(83,'App\\Meals\\Meal',214,'Tangy Mayo Dressing','<p>Tangy Mayo Dressing</p>\n<p><br />1/2 cup cream or sour cream<br />1/2 cup mayo<br />1/4 cup white spirit vinegar<br />1 TBS sugar<br />1/2 tsp salt</p>\n<p><br />Mix all together well.</p>','Lowly','2022-11-07 10:41:25','2022-11-07 10:41:25'),(84,'App\\Meals\\Meal',396,'Mexican Spice','<p>1.5 tsp ground cumin</p>\n<p>1 tsp salt</p>\n<p>1 tsp ground black pepper</p>\n<p>0.5 tsp paprika</p>\n<p>1/4 tsp dried oregano</p>\n<p>1 Tbsp cayenne pepper</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Mix all together well.</p>','Lowly','2022-11-21 09:27:36','2022-11-21 0