41'),(89,'App\\Meals\\Meal',410,'Hummus','<p>To make the hummus, drain the chick peas and keep a little of the liquid. Add the chick peas, tahini, garlic, lemon juice and oil to a blender or nutribullet. Blend until smooth, adding some of the reseved chick pea liquid if you need to. Add salt and black pepper to taste.</p>\n<p>If you cannot find Tahini you can use almond or cashew butter. Peanut butter will do in a pinch but preferably unsweetened peanut butter.</p>','Lowly','2023-03-29 16:10:20','2023-03-29 16:10:20'),(90,'App\\Meals\\Meal',410,'Za\'atar Substitute','<p>&frac14; cup sumac<br />3 tablespoon sesame seeds, toasted<br />2 tablespoons thyme<br />1 tablespoons oregano<br />1 tablespoon marjoram<br />1 teaspoon ground cumin, roasted<br />1 teaspoon ground coriander, roasted</p>\n<p>To enhance the flavour of your cumin, coriander and sesame seeds, place them in a small frypan and warm them through until aromatic. Allow to cool in a bowl.<br />Place everything in a small bowl and mix until well combined.<br />Transfer to a small glass jar and keep it in a dark part of your pantry.</p>','Lowly','2023-03-29 16:17:49','2023-03-29 16:17:49'),(91,'App\\Meals\\Meal',220,'Lemon Mint Dressing','<p>1/2 cup lemon juice</p>\n<p>1/2 cup olive oil</p>\n<p>1/4 cup fresh chopped mint leaves</p>\n<p>3 Tbsp honey</p>\n<p>1 Tbsp Dijon mustard</p>\n<p>2 tsp crushed garlic</p>\n<p>1/4 tsp salt</p>\n<p>10 twists black pepper</p>\n<p>Put all ingredients into a food processor and blend until smooth. This makes about 300 ml and keeps for a week or two in the fridge.</p>','Lowly','2023-04-13 09:20:00','2023-04-13 09:20:00'),(92,'App\\Meals\\Meal',305,'Marinara','<p>Marinara sauce<br />1 onion, finely chopped<br />1 tsp crushed garlic<br />a little oil<br />2 tbsp tomato paste (1 sachet)<br />2 tbsp balsamic vinegar&nbsp;<br />1 tin crushed tomato<br />1 tsp dried basil<br />1 tsp dried oregano&nbsp;<br />&frac12; tsp salt<br />Pepper, to taste</p>\n<p>Fry the onions in the oil until soft.<br />Add tomato paste, garlic, vinegar, crushed tomato and bring to a boil.<br />Add the herbs, salt and pepper.<br />Let it simmer on low for 20 minutes plus.</p>','Lowly','2023-05-22 06:41:04','2023-05-22 06:41:04'),(93,'App\\Meals\\Meal',35,'Passata','<p><br />Ingredients:</p>\n<p><br />4 &ndash; 6 tomatoes, must be ripe and red, roughly chopped<br />1 large onion<br />2 TBSP olive oil<br />4 &ndash; 6 cloves garlic<br />8 &ndash; 10 basil leaves (or 2 teaspoons dried basil)<br />1 &ndash; 2 tsp salt, adjust to taste<br />2 tsp ground black pepper<br />2 TBSP tomato paste<br />Pinch of sugar &ndash; important!</p>\n<p><br />Method:</p>\n<p><br />Heat 1 tsp oil in a pot and fry onion until golden.<br />Put fried onion, chopped tomatoes, basil and garlic into a grinder or blender and make a paste.<br />Put remaining oil into the same pot and add the paste and half a cup of water.<br />Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes &ndash; the colour will deepen.<br />Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and boil for a further 5 minutes.</p>','Lowly','2023-05-22 06:50:31','2023-05-22 06:50:31');
